window.NEO_DATA_W1_LEARN = {"title":"TOEFL Writing Task 1 — Build a Sentence · 개념 커리큘럼 v2","subtitle":"11개 문법 개념 · 확대 서브토픽 (개념1 상세, 2~11 개요)","header_right":"Writing Task 1 · 개념 학습","concepts":[{"n":1,"title":"기본 어순 (문장의 5형식)","status":"detailed","summary":"영어 문장은 **동사가 패턴을 정한다**. 목적어를 안 쓰는지(1형식), 보어를 쓰는지(2형식), 하나를 취하는지(3형식), 두 개를 주는지(4형식), 목적어까지 설명하는지(5형식) — 각 형식의 ==구조·대표 동사·혼동 포인트==를 훑고 TOEFL 문장에 바로 써먹는다.","subtopics":[{"key":"basic-order","title":"영어 기본 어순 (S+V+O)","points":["영어의 기본 뼈대는 **주어 → 동사 → 목적어(SVO)** 순서다.","한국어는 **주어 → 목적어 → 동사(SOV)**라 '나는 사과를 먹는다'처럼 동사가 맨 뒤에 온다.","한국어 순서대로 단어를 늘어놓으면 어순이 무너진다.","동사가 뒤에 목적어·보어를 몇 개 데려오는지에 따라 ==1~5형식==으로 갈린다.","먼저 **S+V**를 고정하고 그 뒤를 채운다는 감각을 잡는다."],"examples":[{"en":"I study English every day.","ko":"나는 매일 영어를 공부한다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"study","role":"V"},{"t":"English","role":"O"},{"t":"every day.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She reads a book.","ko":"그녀는 책을 읽는다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"reads","role":"V"},{"t":"a book.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The students finished the project.","ko":"학생들이 프로젝트를 끝냈다.","parts":[{"t":"The students","role":"S"},{"t":"finished","role":"V"},{"t":"the project.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"We watched a movie last night.","ko":"우리는 어젯밤에 영화를 봤다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"watched","role":"V"},{"t":"a movie","role":"O"},{"t":"last night.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He bought a new phone.","ko":"그는 새 휴대폰을 샀다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"bought","role":"V"},{"t":"a new phone.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Scientists study climate change.","ko":"과학자들은 기후 변화를 연구한다.","parts":[{"t":"Scientists","role":"S"},{"t":"study","role":"V"},{"t":"climate change.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The company launched a product.","ko":"그 회사는 제품을 출시했다.","parts":[{"t":"The company","role":"S"},{"t":"launched","role":"V"},{"t":"a product.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"They speak three languages.","ko":"그들은 세 개 언어를 구사한다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"speak","role":"V"},{"t":"three languages.","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["I every day English study.","I study English every day. (영어는 **동사가 주어 바로 뒤**에 온다 — 한국어 SOV 순서로 쓰면 안 된다)"],["She a book reads.","She reads a book. (목적어보다 동사가 먼저다 — **V+O 순서**다)"],["Finished the students the project.","The students finished the project. (문장은 **주어로 시작**한다 — 동사부터 쓰면 명령문처럼 읽힌다)"]]},{"key":"form1-intransitive","title":"1형식 S+V (완전자동사)","points":["1형식은 목적어도 보어도 없이 **주어+동사**만으로 뜻이 완성된다.","go·come·happen·exist·rise·occur처럼 스스로 완결되는 ==완전자동사==가 여기 속한다.","전치사구·부사(부사어)가 붙어도 형식은 그대로 **1형식**이다 — 'Plates move slowly.'도 1형식이다.","자동사는 목적어를 바로 못 받아 **through·into·from** 같은 전치사를 꼭 끼운다."],"examples":[{"en":"The sun rises in the east.","ko":"해는 동쪽에서 뜬다.","parts":[{"t":"The sun","role":"S"},{"t":"rises","role":"V"},{"t":"in the east.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Prices rose sharply last year.","ko":"작년에 가격이 급격히 올랐다.","parts":[{"t":"Prices","role":"S"},{"t":"rose","role":"V"},{"t":"sharply","role":"M"},{"t":"last year.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Many species exist in the desert.","ko":"많은 종이 사막에 존재한다.","parts":[{"t":"Many species","role":"S"},{"t":"exist","role":"V"},{"t":"in the desert.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"An earthquake occurred near the coast.","ko":"해안 근처에서 지진이 일어났다.","parts":[{"t":"An earthquake","role":"S"},{"t":"occurred","role":"V"},{"t":"near the coast.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Water flows into the river.","ko":"물이 강으로 흘러든다.","parts":[{"t":"Water","role":"S"},{"t":"flows","role":"V"},{"t":"into the river.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The disease spread rapidly.","ko":"그 병이 빠르게 퍼졌다.","parts":[{"t":"The disease","role":"S"},{"t":"spread","role":"V"},{"t":"rapidly.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"There are many factors.","ko":"많은 요인들이 있다.","parts":[{"t":"There","role":"M"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"many factors.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"Sound travels faster in water.","ko":"소리는 물에서 더 빨리 전달된다.","parts":[{"t":"Sound","role":"S"},{"t":"travels","role":"V"},{"t":"faster","role":"M"},{"t":"in water.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["The results go initial expectations.","The results go beyond initial expectations. (go는 **자동사**다 — 목적어를 바로 못 받고 beyond 같은 전치사가 필요하다)"],["An accident happened the road.","An accident happened on the road. (happen은 **자동사**다 — 장소 앞에 전치사를 꼭 쓴다)"],["The population rose 10%.","The population rose by 10%. (증감 폭 앞에는 **by**를 넣는다)"]]},{"key":"form2-linking","title":"2형식 S+V+SC (주격보어)","points":["2형식은 동사 뒤에 **주격보어(SC)**가 와서 주어의 상태·정체를 설명한다.","==SC = 주어== 관계가 성립하면 2형식이다 — He looks tired.에서 tired는 곧 He의 상태다.","대표 동사는 be, 감각동사(look·sound·smell·taste·feel), remain·stay·seem, become·get·turn·grow다.","보어 자리에는 **형용사나 명사**가 온다.","특히 감각동사는 부사가 아니라 반드시 **형용사**를 받는다."],"examples":[{"en":"The process is complex.","ko":"그 과정은 복잡하다.","parts":[{"t":"The process","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"complex.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The mechanism remains unclear.","ko":"그 메커니즘은 여전히 불분명하다.","parts":[{"t":"The mechanism","role":"S"},{"t":"remains","role":"V"},{"t":"unclear.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"This approach seems effective.","ko":"이 접근법은 효과적으로 보인다.","parts":[{"t":"This approach","role":"S"},{"t":"seems","role":"V"},{"t":"effective.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The theory sounds plausible.","ko":"그 이론은 그럴듯하게 들린다.","parts":[{"t":"The theory","role":"S"},{"t":"sounds","role":"V"},{"t":"plausible.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The leaves turn yellow in autumn.","ko":"나뭇잎은 가을에 노랗게 변한다.","parts":[{"t":"The leaves","role":"S"},{"t":"turn","role":"V"},{"t":"yellow","role":"SC"},{"t":"in autumn.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The climate became warmer.","ko":"기후가 더 따뜻해졌다.","parts":[{"t":"The climate","role":"S"},{"t":"became","role":"V"},{"t":"warmer.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The surface feels rough.","ko":"표면이 거칠게 느껴진다.","parts":[{"t":"The surface","role":"S"},{"t":"feels","role":"V"},{"t":"rough.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"She is a scientist.","ko":"그녀는 과학자다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"a scientist.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The population stayed stable.","ko":"인구는 안정적으로 유지됐다.","parts":[{"t":"The population","role":"S"},{"t":"stayed","role":"V"},{"t":"stable.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["It looks beautifully.","It looks beautiful. (감각동사 look은 부사가 아니라 **형용사 보어**를 받는다)"],["The soup smells deliciously.","The soup smells delicious. (smell 뒤에는 **형용사**가 온다 — 부사는 못 쓴다)"],["He became happily.","He became happy. (become은 상태를 나타내는 **형용사**를 보어로 받는다)"],["The idea sounds well.","The idea sounds good. (sound 뒤 보어는 형용사 good이다 — **well은 부사**다)"]]},{"key":"form3-transitive","title":"3형식 S+V+O (타동사)","points":["3형식은 동사가 목적어를 **전치사 없이** 바로 받는다.","discuss·mention·approach·enter·reach는 번역에 '~에/대해'가 들어가도 ==전치사를 안 쓴다==(False Intransitives).","반대로 rise·fall·lie·happen은 목적어를 못 받는 **자동사**라 헷갈리면 안 된다.","**rise(오르다)/raise(올리다), lie(놓여있다)/lay(놓다)**를 구분한다.","목적어 자리에는 명사·대명사·동명사·to부정사·명사절이 올 수 있다."],"examples":[{"en":"They discussed the problem.","ko":"그들은 그 문제를 논의했다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"discussed","role":"V"},{"t":"the problem.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The author mentions three factors.","ko":"저자는 세 가지 요인을 언급한다.","parts":[{"t":"The author","role":"S"},{"t":"mentions","role":"V"},{"t":"three factors.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"We attended the lecture.","ko":"우리는 강의에 참석했다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"attended","role":"V"},{"t":"the lecture.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Scientists approached the issue differently.","ko":"과학자들은 그 문제에 다르게 접근했다.","parts":[{"t":"Scientists","role":"S"},{"t":"approached","role":"V"},{"t":"the issue","role":"O"},{"t":"differently.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The team reached a consensus.","ko":"그 팀은 합의에 도달했다.","parts":[{"t":"The team","role":"S"},{"t":"reached","role":"V"},{"t":"a consensus.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"She entered the room quietly.","ko":"그녀는 조용히 방에 들어갔다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"entered","role":"V"},{"t":"the room","role":"O"},{"t":"quietly.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The paper addresses climate change.","ko":"그 논문은 기후 변화를 다룬다.","parts":[{"t":"The paper","role":"S"},{"t":"addresses","role":"V"},{"t":"climate change.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I enjoy reading academic articles.","ko":"나는 학술 논문 읽는 것을 즐긴다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"enjoy","role":"V"},{"t":"reading academic articles.","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["They discussed about the problem.","They discussed the problem. (discuss는 **타동사**다 — about 없이 목적어를 바로 받는다)"],["We attended to the lecture.","We attended the lecture. (attend는 참석의 뜻일 때 **전치사 없이** 쓴다 — attend to는 '돌보다'로 뜻이 다르다)"],["The company raised the issue quickly, and prices rise an issue.","...prices raised... (rise는 자동사, **raise가 타동사**다 — 목적어가 있으면 raise다)"],["He mentioned about the results.","He mentioned the results. (mention도 about 없이 **목적어를 직접** 취한다)"]]},{"key":"form4-ditransitive","title":"4형식 S+V+IO+DO (수여동사)","points":["4형식은 '누구에게(**간접목적어 IO**) 무엇을(**직접목적어 DO**)' 두 개를 주는 수여동사 패턴이다.","3형식으로 바꿀 때 전치사를 넣어 IO를 뒤로 보낸다 — give·send·show·teach는 **to**, buy·make·cook·get은 **for**다.","ask는 특이하게 ==of==를 쓴다(ask a favor of him).","explain·describe·suggest·introduce는 4형식처럼 보여도 IO를 바로 못 받고 **'to+사람'**을 꼭 쓴다(False Ditransitives)."],"examples":[{"en":"She gave the committee a report.","ko":"그녀는 위원회에 보고서를 줬다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"gave","role":"V"},{"t":"the committee","role":"IO"},{"t":"a report.","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"She gave a report to the committee.","ko":"그녀는 보고서를 위원회에 줬다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"gave","role":"V"},{"t":"a report","role":"DO"},{"t":"to the committee.","role":"IO"}]},{"en":"He sent me an email.","ko":"그는 나에게 이메일을 보냈다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"sent","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"an email.","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"The teacher taught us grammar.","ko":"선생님이 우리에게 문법을 가르쳤다.","parts":[{"t":"The teacher","role":"S"},{"t":"taught","role":"V"},{"t":"us","role":"IO"},{"t":"grammar.","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"My mom bought me a jacket.","ko":"엄마가 나에게 재킷을 사줬다.","parts":[{"t":"My mom","role":"S"},{"t":"bought","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"a jacket.","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"Can you make me a coffee?","ko":"나에게 커피 한 잔 만들어 줄 수 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"make","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"a coffee?","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"The guide showed the tourists the map.","ko":"가이드가 관광객들에게 지도를 보여줬다.","parts":[{"t":"The guide","role":"S"},{"t":"showed","role":"V"},{"t":"the tourists","role":"IO"},{"t":"the map.","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"I asked a question of the professor.","ko":"나는 교수님께 질문 하나를 했다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"asked","role":"V"},{"t":"a question","role":"DO"},{"t":"of the professor.","role":"IO"}]}],"mistakes":[["He explained me the theory.","He explained the theory to me. (explain은 **수여동사가 아니다** — 'to+사람'을 꼭 쓴다)"],["She suggested me a solution.","She suggested a solution to me. (suggest도 IO를 바로 못 받고 **to**를 쓴다)"],["My mom bought a jacket to me.","My mom bought a jacket for me. (buy는 **for 그룹**이다 — 이익을 주는 동사라 for다)"],["The teacher introduced us the topic.","The teacher introduced the topic to us. (introduce는 **to가 필수**다)"]]},{"key":"form5-adj-noun","title":"5형식 S+V+O+OC (형용사·명사 보어)","points":["5형식은 목적어(O) 뒤에 **목적격보어(OC)**가 와서 O의 상태·정체를 설명한다.","==O = OC== 관계가 성립한다 — They found the data reliable.에서 reliable은 곧 the data의 상태다.","make·keep·find·leave·render는 **형용사** 보어를, call·name·consider·elect·appoint은 **명사** 보어를 받는다.","consider·call은 as 없이 붙이지만, regard·describe·define은 **as**를 꼭 끼운다.","2형식과 헷갈리면 '보어가 목적어와 같은가'를 대입해 확인한다."],"examples":[{"en":"The news made everyone happy.","ko":"그 소식이 모두를 행복하게 만들었다.","parts":[{"t":"The news","role":"S"},{"t":"made","role":"V"},{"t":"everyone","role":"O"},{"t":"happy.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"Keep the door open, please.","ko":"문을 열어 둬라.","parts":[{"t":"Keep","role":"V"},{"t":"the door","role":"O"},{"t":"open,","role":"OC"},{"t":"please.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Researchers found the data reliable.","ko":"연구자들은 그 데이터가 믿을 만하다고 봤다.","parts":[{"t":"Researchers","role":"S"},{"t":"found","role":"V"},{"t":"the data","role":"O"},{"t":"reliable.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"Many historians consider it a turning point.","ko":"많은 역사학자들이 그것을 전환점으로 여긴다.","parts":[{"t":"Many historians","role":"S"},{"t":"consider","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"a turning point.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"They called the process natural selection.","ko":"그들은 그 과정을 자연선택이라고 불렀다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"called","role":"V"},{"t":"the process","role":"O"},{"t":"natural selection.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"The committee deemed the plan inadequate.","ko":"위원회는 그 계획이 부적절하다고 봤다.","parts":[{"t":"The committee","role":"S"},{"t":"deemed","role":"V"},{"t":"the plan","role":"O"},{"t":"inadequate.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"We elected her class president.","ko":"우리는 그녀를 반장으로 뽑았다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"elected","role":"V"},{"t":"her","role":"O"},{"t":"class president.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"The earthquake rendered the building unsafe.","ko":"지진이 그 건물을 위험한 상태로 만들었다.","parts":[{"t":"The earthquake","role":"S"},{"t":"rendered","role":"V"},{"t":"the building","role":"O"},{"t":"unsafe.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"Scholars regard him as a genius.","ko":"학자들은 그를 천재로 여긴다.","parts":[{"t":"Scholars","role":"S"},{"t":"regard","role":"V"},{"t":"him","role":"O"},{"t":"as a genius.","role":"OC"}]}],"mistakes":[["The news made everyone happily.","The news made everyone happy. (OC는 **형용사**다 — 부사 happily는 못 쓴다)"],["They consider as the plan risky.","They consider the plan risky. (consider는 **as 없이** 보어를 바로 붙인다)"],["Scholars regard him a genius.","Scholars regard him as a genius. (regard는 **as가 꼭 필요**하다)"],["Keep the door opened.","Keep the door open. (여기 보어는 상태를 나타내는 **형용사 open**이다)"]]},{"key":"form5-to-infinitive","title":"5형식 to부정사 보어","points":["5형식 중에는 목적격보어 자리에 **to부정사**가 오는 유형이 있다 — 'O에게 ~하기를/하도록' 시키거나 원할 때 쓴다.","want·ask·tell·expect·allow·enable·force·require·encourage·cause가 대표다.","구조는 ==S + V + O + to-V==로 고정된다 — I want you to stay.처럼.","부정형은 **to 앞에 not**을 넣는다(tell them not to go).","사역동사 make·let·have와 달리 이 동사들은 **to를 반드시 살린다**."],"examples":[{"en":"I want you to try again.","ko":"나는 당신이 다시 시도하기를 원한다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"want","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"O"},{"t":"to try","role":"OC"},{"t":"again.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The teacher told us to be quiet.","ko":"선생님이 우리에게 조용히 하라고 했다.","parts":[{"t":"The teacher","role":"S"},{"t":"told","role":"V"},{"t":"us","role":"O"},{"t":"to be quiet.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"She asked me to help her.","ko":"그녀는 나에게 도와달라고 부탁했다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"asked","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"to help her.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"The new rule allows students to use laptops.","ko":"새 규칙은 학생들이 노트북을 쓰도록 허용한다.","parts":[{"t":"The new rule","role":"S"},{"t":"allows","role":"V"},{"t":"students","role":"O"},{"t":"to use laptops.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"We expect prices to rise next month.","ko":"우리는 다음 달에 가격이 오를 것으로 예상한다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"expect","role":"V"},{"t":"prices","role":"O"},{"t":"to rise","role":"OC"},{"t":"next month.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The crisis forced the company to cut costs.","ko":"위기가 그 회사에 비용을 줄이도록 강요했다.","parts":[{"t":"The crisis","role":"S"},{"t":"forced","role":"V"},{"t":"the company","role":"O"},{"t":"to cut costs.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"Technology enables us to work remotely.","ko":"기술은 우리가 원격으로 일할 수 있게 해준다.","parts":[{"t":"Technology","role":"S"},{"t":"enables","role":"V"},{"t":"us","role":"O"},{"t":"to work remotely.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"The doctor advised him to rest.","ko":"의사는 그에게 쉬라고 권했다.","parts":[{"t":"The doctor","role":"S"},{"t":"advised","role":"V"},{"t":"him","role":"O"},{"t":"to rest.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"I warned them not to touch it.","ko":"나는 그들에게 그것을 만지지 말라고 경고했다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"warned","role":"V"},{"t":"them","role":"O"},{"t":"not to touch it.","role":"OC"}]}],"mistakes":[["I want you stay here.","I want you to stay here. (want는 목적격보어로 **to부정사**를 받는다 — to를 빼면 안 된다)"],["She asked me helping her.","She asked me to help her. (ask 뒤 보어는 동명사가 아니라 **to부정사**다)"],["The rule allows students using phones.","The rule allows students to use phones. (**allow + O + to-V** 구조다)"],["The teacher told us be quiet.","The teacher told us to be quiet. (tell도 **to를 살려야** 한다)"]]},{"key":"form5-bare-participle","title":"5형식 원형·분사 보어 (사역·지각동사)","points":["사역동사 **make·let·have**는 목적격보어로 to 없는 ==원형부정사==를 받는다 — make him go처럼.","지각동사 see·hear·watch·feel·observe는 **원형**(완결 강조)이나 **-ing**(진행 강조)를 보어로 쓴다.","help는 원형과 to부정사 둘 다 가능하다.","get은 예외로 **to부정사**를 쓴다(get him to go).","**have/get + O + 과거분사(p.p.)**는 O가 당하는 수동 사역이다(have the car repaired)."],"examples":[{"en":"The manager made him redo the report.","ko":"관리자가 그에게 보고서를 다시 하게 했다.","parts":[{"t":"The manager","role":"S"},{"t":"made","role":"V"},{"t":"him","role":"O"},{"t":"redo the report.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"Let me explain the reason.","ko":"내가 이유를 설명하게 해달라.","parts":[{"t":"Let","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"explain the reason.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"I had my brother wash the dishes.","ko":"나는 남동생에게 설거지를 하게 했다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"V"},{"t":"my brother","role":"O"},{"t":"wash the dishes.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"We saw the structure collapse.","ko":"우리는 그 구조물이 무너지는 것을 봤다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"saw","role":"V"},{"t":"the structure","role":"O"},{"t":"collapse.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"I heard someone calling my name.","ko":"나는 누군가 내 이름을 부르는 것을 들었다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"heard","role":"V"},{"t":"someone","role":"O"},{"t":"calling my name.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"She watched the children playing.","ko":"그녀는 아이들이 노는 것을 지켜봤다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"watched","role":"V"},{"t":"the children","role":"O"},{"t":"playing.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"This tool helps students (to) learn faster.","ko":"이 도구는 학생들이 더 빨리 배우도록 돕는다.","parts":[{"t":"This tool","role":"S"},{"t":"helps","role":"V"},{"t":"students","role":"O"},{"t":"(to) learn","role":"OC"},{"t":"faster.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I got him to fix my laptop.","ko":"나는 그에게 노트북을 고치게 했다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"got","role":"V"},{"t":"him","role":"O"},{"t":"to fix my laptop.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"I had my hair cut yesterday.","ko":"나는 어제 머리를 잘랐다(잘라 받았다).","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"V"},{"t":"my hair","role":"O"},{"t":"cut","role":"OC"},{"t":"yesterday.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["The manager made him to redo it.","The manager made him redo it. (사역동사 make는 **원형부정사**를 받는다 — to를 안 쓴다)"],["Let me to explain.","Let me explain. (let 뒤에도 **원형**이 온다)"],["I saw her to leave.","I saw her leave. (지각동사 see는 **원형이나 -ing**를 받는다)"],["I got him fix my laptop.","I got him to fix my laptop. (get은 사역이어도 **to부정사**를 쓴다)"]]},{"key":"adverb-placement","title":"부사·시간·장소의 위치","points":["부사는 위치 규칙이 따로 있다.","빈도부사(always·usually·often·sometimes·never)는 **일반동사 앞, be동사·조동사 뒤**에 놓는다.","장소와 시간을 같이 쓸 때는 ==장소 → 시간== 순서가 기본이다 — I studied at the library yesterday.","정도부사 very·too는 형용사·부사 앞에 붙는다.","very는 단순 강조(아주), too는 **'너무 ~해서 안 좋은'** 부정 뉘앙스라 뜻이 다르다."],"examples":[{"en":"She always arrives early.","ko":"그녀는 항상 일찍 온다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"always","role":"M"},{"t":"arrives","role":"V"},{"t":"early.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I have never been to Europe.","ko":"나는 유럽에 가본 적이 없다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"never","role":"M"},{"t":"been","role":"V"},{"t":"to Europe.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He is usually busy on Mondays.","ko":"그는 월요일에 보통 바쁘다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"usually","role":"M"},{"t":"busy","role":"SC"},{"t":"on Mondays.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We often go there in summer.","ko":"우리는 여름에 자주 거기 간다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"often","role":"M"},{"t":"go","role":"V"},{"t":"there","role":"M"},{"t":"in summer.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I met her at the cafe yesterday.","ko":"나는 어제 카페에서 그녀를 만났다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"met","role":"V"},{"t":"her","role":"O"},{"t":"at the cafe","role":"M"},{"t":"yesterday.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The book is very interesting.","ko":"그 책은 아주 흥미롭다.","parts":[{"t":"The book","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"very","role":"M"},{"t":"interesting.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"This coffee is too hot to drink.","ko":"이 커피는 너무 뜨거워서 못 마신다.","parts":[{"t":"This coffee","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"too hot","role":"SC"},{"t":"to drink.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"They sometimes work on weekends.","ko":"그들은 가끔 주말에 일한다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"sometimes","role":"M"},{"t":"work","role":"V"},{"t":"on weekends.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["She arrives always early.","She always arrives early. (빈도부사는 **일반동사 앞**에 놓는다)"],["I studied yesterday at the library.","I studied at the library yesterday. (**'장소 → 시간'** 순서가 기본이다)"],["This coffee is very hot to drink it.","This coffee is too hot to drink. ('너무 ~해서 못 한다'는 **too**를 쓴다 — very는 이 뜻이 안 된다)"],["He is often is late.","He is often late. (be동사 뒤에 빈도부사가 온다 — **동사를 두 번** 쓰면 안 된다)"]]}],"db":{"title":"형식별 대표 동사 DB","intro":"**동사가 문장의 형식을 결정한다.** 1~5형식별 대표 동사와 자주 붙는 전치사, 그리고 TOEFL 혼동 포인트를 한눈에 모았다. 특히 ==자·타동사 혼동 그룹==과 목적격보어 형태(형용사/명사/to부정사/원형/분사)를 꼼꼼히 봐두면 Writing Task 1에서 바로 써먹을 수 있다.","groups":[{"label":"1형식 완전자동사 (S + V)","note":"목적어·보어 없이 주어와 동사만으로 완결된다. 뒤에 오는 건 전부 부사어(전치사구·부사)라 형식은 그대로 **1형식**이다. 괄호 안은 자주 붙는 전치사다.","items":[{"w":"arrive","ko":"도착하다 (at/in)","ex":"The settlers arrived in the region by boat."},{"w":"come","ko":"오다 (from/into/about)","ex":"New evidence came from deep-sea expeditions."},{"w":"go","ko":"가다 (through/beyond/toward)","ex":"Species go through rapid evolutionary change."},{"w":"move","ko":"이동하다 (toward/across/along)","ex":"Tectonic plates move at different rates."},{"w":"travel","ko":"이동하다·전달되다 (through/at/across)","ex":"Sound travels faster in water than in air."},{"w":"flow","ko":"흐르다 (through/into/from)","ex":"Lava flows down the volcanic slope."},{"w":"run","ko":"흐르다·이어지다 (through/across/along)","ex":"A major fault line runs through the region."},{"w":"spread","ko":"퍼지다 (across/through/from)","ex":"The disease spread rapidly across continents."},{"w":"migrate","ko":"이주하다 (to/from/across)","ex":"Many birds migrate to warmer climates in winter."},{"w":"drift","ko":"표류하다 (toward/apart/away from)","ex":"Continents drift apart over geological time."},{"w":"rise","ko":"오르다·솟다 (from/to/above)","ex":"Sea levels rose significantly during this period."},{"w":"fall","ko":"떨어지다 (from/to/below)","ex":"Temperatures fall sharply in the upper atmosphere."},{"w":"sink","ko":"가라앉다 (to/into/beneath)","ex":"Cold, dense water sinks to the ocean floor."},{"w":"descend","ko":"내려가다·유래하다 (from/into/through)","ex":"Modern birds descend from theropod dinosaurs."},{"w":"pass","ko":"지나가다·통과하다 (through/across/over)","ex":"The light passes through the prism."},{"w":"proceed","ko":"나아가다·진행되다 (with/from/toward)","ex":"The reaction proceeds in the presence of heat."},{"w":"advance","ko":"전진하다·진보하다 (toward/into/along)","ex":"The glacier advanced steadily southward."},{"w":"radiate","ko":"방사되다·퍼지다 (from/outward/into)","ex":"Heat radiates outward from the Earth's core."},{"w":"diffuse","ko":"확산되다 (through/into/across)","ex":"Molecules diffuse from high to low concentration."},{"w":"disperse","ko":"분산되다·흩어지다 (into/across/from)","ex":"Seeds disperse by wind, water, or animals."},{"w":"circulate","ko":"순환하다 (through/among)","ex":"Ocean currents circulate heat around the globe."},{"w":"converge","ko":"수렴하다·모이다 (on/at/toward)","ex":"Research findings converge on a single conclusion."},{"w":"diverge","ko":"분기하다·갈라지다 (from/into)","ex":"The two species diverged millions of years ago."},{"w":"evaporate","ko":"증발하다 (from/into)","ex":"Surface water evaporates under solar radiation."},{"w":"condense","ko":"응결되다 (into/on)","ex":"Water vapor condenses into droplets at high altitudes."},{"w":"exist","ko":"존재하다 (in/within/alongside)","ex":"These microorganisms exist in extreme environments."},{"w":"occur","ko":"발생하다·일어나다 (in/at/during)","ex":"Photosynthesis occurs primarily in the chloroplasts."},{"w":"happen","ko":"일어나다 (in/during/as)","ex":"This transformation happens over millions of years."},{"w":"appear","ko":"나타나다 (in/during/as)","ex":"New species appeared following the mass extinction."},{"w":"disappear","ko":"사라지다 (from/into)","ex":"Many species disappeared from the fossil record."},{"w":"emerge","ko":"출현하다·부상하다 (from/as/during)","ex":"Complex social structures emerged over millennia."},{"w":"arise","ko":"생겨나다·발생하다 (from/in/as)","ex":"These challenges arose from rapid urbanization."},{"w":"originate","ko":"기원하다·시작되다 (from/in/as)","ex":"Agriculture likely originated in several regions."},{"w":"remain","ko":"남아있다·머무르다 (in/at/within)","ex":"Many ancient customs remained intact for centuries."},{"w":"persist","ko":"지속되다 (in/through/despite)","ex":"The drought persisted for over a decade."},{"w":"prevail","ko":"만연하다·우세하다 (in/over/throughout)","ex":"These conditions prevailed during the Mesozoic Era."},{"w":"lie","ko":"위치하다·놓여있다 (in/beneath/along/between)","ex":"The fault line lies beneath the continental shelf."},{"w":"stand","ko":"서다·위치하다 (as/for/at)","ex":"The ruins stand as evidence of early habitation."},{"w":"work","ko":"작동하다·일하다 (as/on/with)","ex":"The mechanism works without external power."},{"w":"function","ko":"기능하다·작동하다 (as/without)","ex":"Enzymes function as biological catalysts."},{"w":"operate","ko":"작동하다·운영되다 (on/under/within)","ex":"The device operates on solar power."},{"w":"live","ko":"살다·서식하다 (in/on/near)","ex":"These organisms live in deep-sea vents."},{"w":"sleep","ko":"잠자다 (for/during)","ex":"Some mammals sleep for months during hibernation."},{"w":"matter","ko":"중요하다 (to/for)","ex":"These small differences matter to the outcome."},{"w":"count","ko":"중요하다·유효하다 (toward/for)","ex":"Every observation counts in the analysis."},{"w":"differ","ko":"다르다 (from/in)","ex":"The two theories differ in key assumptions."},{"w":"vary","ko":"다양하다·변하다 (with/from/across)","ex":"Rainfall varies widely across the region."},{"w":"grow","ko":"자라다·성장하다 (from/into)","ex":"Urban populations grew rapidly in the 20th century."},{"w":"develop","ko":"발달하다 (from/into/over)","ex":"Complex behaviors developed through social learning."},{"w":"evolve","ko":"진화하다 (from/into/over)","ex":"Birds evolved from theropod dinosaurs."},{"w":"change","ko":"변화하다 (from/into/over)","ex":"Climate patterns changed dramatically in this epoch."},{"w":"shift","ko":"이동·변화하다 (from/to/toward)","ex":"Economic power shifted eastward in the medieval period."},{"w":"increase","ko":"증가하다 (by/from/to/in)","ex":"CO2 concentrations increased sharply after industrialization."},{"w":"decrease","ko":"감소하다 (by/from/in)","ex":"Biodiversity decreased as habitat was lost."},{"w":"decline","ko":"감소하다·쇠퇴하다 (from/by/in/toward)","ex":"Bird populations declined by 40% over two decades."},{"w":"expand","ko":"팽창하다·확장되다 (into/by/across)","ex":"The universe continues to expand at an accelerating rate."},{"w":"contract","ko":"수축하다 (by/under/upon)","ex":"Metals contract when cooled."},{"w":"shrink","ko":"축소되다 (from/to/by)","ex":"The ozone layer shrank significantly by the 1990s."},{"w":"fluctuate","ko":"변동하다 (between/around/with)","ex":"Sea surface temperatures fluctuate seasonally."},{"w":"accelerate","ko":"가속되다 (toward/due to/with)","ex":"Global warming accelerated in the late 20th century."},{"w":"stabilize","ko":"안정되다 (at/around/after)","ex":"Populations stabilize when resources become limited."},{"w":"collapse","ko":"붕괴하다 (under/during)","ex":"Several ancient civilizations collapsed within a century."},{"w":"erupt","ko":"분출하다·폭발하다 (from/into/during)","ex":"The volcano erupted catastrophically."},{"w":"erode","ko":"침식되다 (from/by/over)","ex":"Coastal cliffs erode under the force of ocean waves."},{"w":"melt","ko":"녹다 (at/under/into)","ex":"Permafrost melts when temperatures exceed freezing."},{"w":"freeze","ko":"얼다 (at/into/over)","ex":"Water freezes at 0°C under standard pressure."},{"w":"decay","ko":"붕괴·분해되다 (into/by/at)","ex":"Radioactive isotopes decay at predictable rates."},{"w":"decompose","ko":"분해되다 (into/through/under)","ex":"Organic matter decomposes rapidly in tropical climates."},{"w":"react","ko":"반응하다 (with/to/under)","ex":"Hydrogen reacts with oxygen to form water."},{"w":"interact","ko":"상호작용하다 (with/through/via)","ex":"These compounds interact at the molecular level."},{"w":"vibrate","ko":"진동하다 (at/with/in)","ex":"Molecules vibrate more rapidly at higher temperatures."},{"w":"survive","ko":"생존하다 (in/on/through/despite)","ex":"Only the most adaptable species survived."},{"w":"thrive","ko":"번성하다 (in/on/under)","ex":"Bacteria thrive in warm, moist environments."},{"w":"die","ko":"죽다·멸종하다 (from/out/off)","ex":"Dinosaurs died out 66 million years ago."},{"w":"breathe","ko":"호흡하다 (in/through)","ex":"Amphibians breathe through their skin."},{"w":"reproduce","ko":"번식하다 (by/through/in)","ex":"Bacteria reproduce by binary fission."},{"w":"result","ko":"결과가 나오다 (from/in)","ex":"Climate disruptions resulted from volcanic activity."},{"w":"depend","ko":"의존하다 (on/upon)","ex":"The outcome depends on several variables."},{"w":"rely","ko":"의존하다 (on/upon)","ex":"Many species rely on seasonal rainfall."},{"w":"consist","ko":"구성되다 (of/in)","ex":"The crust consists of several major plates."},{"w":"belong","ko":"속하다 (to)","ex":"This species belongs to a rare family."},{"w":"participate","ko":"참여하다 (in)","ex":"Many organisms participate in nutrient cycling."},{"w":"disagree","ko":"동의하지 않다 (with/on)","ex":"Scholars disagree on the exact date."}]},{"label":"2형식 연결동사 (S + V + SC, 보어=형용사/명사)","note":"**주격보어(SC)**가 주어의 상태·정체를 서술한다. SC ≈ 주어 관계가 성립하면 2형식이다. 감각동사(look·sound·smell·taste·feel)는 반드시 **형용사**를 받는다 — ==부사는 안 된다==!","items":[{"w":"be","ko":"~이다·~한 상태이다","ex":"The process is highly complex."},{"w":"become","ko":"~이 되다","ex":"The region became a major trade hub."},{"w":"get","ko":"~해지다 (구어적 변화)","ex":"The climate got colder over the centuries."},{"w":"turn","ko":"~으로 변하다 (색·상태 변화)","ex":"The leaves turn red in autumn."},{"w":"grow","ko":"점점 ~해지다","ex":"The evidence grew stronger over time."},{"w":"go","ko":"(나쁜 쪽으로) ~해지다","ex":"The food went bad in the heat."},{"w":"come","ko":"(바라던 대로) ~이 되다","ex":"His prediction came true."},{"w":"fall","ko":"(어떤 상태에) 빠지다","ex":"The patient fell ill during the expedition."},{"w":"run","ko":"(어떤 상태로) 되다","ex":"Supplies ran low during the winter."},{"w":"prove","ko":"~임이 판명되다","ex":"The hypothesis proved correct."},{"w":"remain","ko":"여전히 ~이다","ex":"The mechanism remains unclear."},{"w":"stay","ko":"~인 채로 있다","ex":"The temperature stayed constant for hours."},{"w":"keep","ko":"계속 ~인 상태이다","ex":"The samples kept fresh in cold storage."},{"w":"hold","ko":"(상태를) 유지하다","ex":"The theory holds true under most conditions."},{"w":"seem","ko":"~인 것 같다","ex":"The results seem inconsistent with the model."},{"w":"appear","ko":"~인 것처럼 보이다","ex":"The structure appears stable."},{"w":"look","ko":"~하게 보이다 (형용사만!)","ex":"The specimen looks fragile."},{"w":"sound","ko":"~하게 들리다 (형용사만!)","ex":"The theory sounds plausible."},{"w":"smell","ko":"~한 냄새가 나다 (형용사만!)","ex":"The compound smells acidic."},{"w":"taste","ko":"~한 맛이 나다 (형용사만!)","ex":"The water tastes salty near the coast."},{"w":"feel","ko":"~하게 느껴지다 (형용사만!)","ex":"The surface feels rough."},{"w":"lie","ko":"~인 채로 놓여있다","ex":"The valley lies dormant during winter."},{"w":"stand","ko":"~인 상태로 있다","ex":"The building stood empty for decades."},{"w":"rest","ko":"(상태로) 있다·달려있다","ex":"The conclusion rests uncertain without more data."},{"w":"emerge","ko":"~로 드러나다·부상하다","ex":"China emerged dominant in the region."},{"w":"rank","ko":"~로 순위 매겨지다","ex":"The river ranks second in length."},{"w":"count","ko":"~로 여겨지다","ex":"This finding counts significant."}]},{"label":"3형식 대표 타동사 (S + V + O, 전치사 없음)","note":"목적어를 **전치사 없이** 바로 취한다. 특히 discuss·marry·attend·mention·resemble·approach·answer·enter·reach는 한국어 번역에 '~에/대하여'가 있어 자동사로 착각하기 쉽지만 ==전치사를 안 쓴다==!","items":[{"w":"make","ko":"만들다","ex":"Volcanic activity makes new landforms."},{"w":"take","ko":"취하다·가져가다","ex":"The process takes several years."},{"w":"have","ko":"가지다","ex":"The cell has a rigid outer wall."},{"w":"get","ko":"얻다·받다","ex":"Plants get energy from sunlight."},{"w":"buy","ko":"사다","ex":"The museum bought the rare fossil."},{"w":"read","ko":"읽다","ex":"Researchers read the sediment layers like a record."},{"w":"write","ko":"쓰다","ex":"The scholar wrote a detailed account."},{"w":"finish","ko":"끝내다","ex":"The team finished the excavation in autumn."},{"w":"meet","ko":"만나다","ex":"The delegates met the visiting scholars."},{"w":"visit","ko":"방문하다","ex":"Naturalists visited the remote island."},{"w":"want","ko":"원하다","ex":"Organisms want a stable environment."},{"w":"need","ko":"필요로 하다","ex":"The reaction needs a catalyst."},{"w":"enjoy","ko":"즐기다·누리다","ex":"The region enjoys a mild climate."},{"w":"use","ko":"사용하다","ex":"Plants use sunlight for photosynthesis."},{"w":"produce","ko":"생산하다","ex":"The gland produces essential hormones."},{"w":"cause","ko":"일으키다·유발하다","ex":"The eruption caused widespread damage."},{"w":"affect","ko":"~에 영향을 주다","ex":"Temperature affects the reaction rate."},{"w":"influence","ko":"~에 영향을 미치다","ex":"Ocean currents influence regional climate."},{"w":"discuss","ko":"논의하다 (discuss about X)","ex":"The paper discusses the underlying causes."},{"w":"mention","ko":"언급하다 (mention about X)","ex":"The author mentions several exceptions."},{"w":"marry","ko":"~와 결혼하다 (marry with X)","ex":"He married a fellow scientist."},{"w":"resemble","ko":"~와 닮다 (resemble to X)","ex":"The fossil closely resembles a modern bird."},{"w":"attend","ko":"~에 참석하다 (attend to = 별개 뜻)","ex":"Hundreds attended the conference."},{"w":"approach","ko":"~에 다가가다·접근하다 (approach to X)","ex":"The comet approached the sun."},{"w":"answer","ko":"~에 답하다 (answer to X)","ex":"The study answers a long-standing question."},{"w":"enter","ko":"~에 들어가다 (enter into = 별개 뜻)","ex":"The species entered a new habitat."},{"w":"reach","ko":"~에 도달하다 (reach to X)","ex":"The signal reached the outer edge."},{"w":"join","ko":"~에 합류하다 (join to X)","ex":"The tributary joins the main river."},{"w":"contact","ko":"~에게 연락하다 (contact with X)","ex":"The team contacted local authorities."},{"w":"address","ko":"~을 다루다·~에게 연설하다 (address to X)","ex":"The report addresses the funding gap."},{"w":"emphasize","ko":"강조하다 (emphasize on X)","ex":"The author emphasizes the role of climate."},{"w":"lack","ko":"~이 부족하다 (lack of = 명사)","ex":"The soil lacks essential nutrients."},{"w":"survive","ko":"~에서 살아남다 (타동사 용법)","ex":"Few species survived the extinction event."},{"w":"leave","ko":"~을 떠나다","ex":"The migrants left their homeland."},{"w":"describe","ko":"묘사하다·기술하다","ex":"The passage describes the process in detail."},{"w":"explain","ko":"설명하다 (explain sb = X, explain to sb)","ex":"The model explains the observed pattern."},{"w":"consider","ko":"고려하다·여기다","ex":"Scientists consider several possibilities."},{"w":"examine","ko":"조사하다·검토하다","ex":"Researchers examined the fossil record."},{"w":"analyze","ko":"분석하다","ex":"The team analyzed the soil samples."},{"w":"require","ko":"요구하다·필요로 하다","ex":"The experiment requires precise measurements."},{"w":"provide","ko":"제공하다","ex":"The wetland provides critical habitat."},{"w":"support","ko":"뒷받침하다·지지하다","ex":"The data support the hypothesis."},{"w":"prevent","ko":"막다·예방하다","ex":"The barrier prevents coastal erosion."},{"w":"reduce","ko":"줄이다","ex":"The regulation reduced emissions sharply."}]},{"label":"4형식 수여동사 (S + V + IO + DO)","note":"간접목적어(받는 사람)와 직접목적어(전달물)를 함께 취한다. 3형식으로 바꿀 때 전치사가 다르다 — 방향/수신은 **to**, 이익/대신은 **for**, ask는 **of**를 쓴다. explain·describe·suggest·introduce는 4형식이 안 되고 ==반드시 to를 쓴다==.","items":[{"w":"give","ko":"주다 (→ give O to sb)","ex":"She gave him the data."},{"w":"tell","ko":"말해주다 (→ tell O to sb)","ex":"The guide told us the history."},{"w":"send","ko":"보내주다 (→ send O to sb)","ex":"They sent the lab a fresh sample."},{"w":"show","ko":"보여주다 (→ show O to sb)","ex":"The chart shows readers the trend."},{"w":"offer","ko":"제공하다 (→ offer O to sb)","ex":"The grant offered researchers new funding."},{"w":"teach","ko":"가르치다 (→ teach O to sb)","ex":"The mentor taught students the method."},{"w":"lend","ko":"빌려주다 (→ lend O to sb)","ex":"The library lent the scholar a manuscript."},{"w":"bring","ko":"가져다주다 (→ bring O to sb)","ex":"The current brings the coast warm water."},{"w":"pass","ko":"건네주다 (→ pass O to sb)","ex":"Cells pass daughter cells genetic material."},{"w":"hand","ko":"건네주다 (→ hand O to sb)","ex":"The assistant handed the professor the report."},{"w":"pay","ko":"지불하다 (→ pay O to sb)","ex":"The patron paid the artist a large sum."},{"w":"sell","ko":"팔다 (→ sell O to sb)","ex":"The merchants sold traders exotic spices."},{"w":"write","ko":"써 주다 (→ write O to sb)","ex":"She wrote her colleague a detailed letter."},{"w":"award","ko":"수여하다 (→ award O to sb)","ex":"The committee awarded her a prize."},{"w":"grant","ko":"부여하다 (→ grant O to sb)","ex":"The charter granted the city trading rights."},{"w":"buy","ko":"사 주다 (→ buy O for sb)","ex":"The foundation bought the museum a rare fossil."},{"w":"make","ko":"만들어 주다 (→ make O for sb)","ex":"The colony made settlers new tools."},{"w":"cook","ko":"요리해 주다 (→ cook O for sb)","ex":"She cooked the crew a warm meal."},{"w":"find","ko":"찾아 주다 (→ find O for sb)","ex":"The survey found the team a new site."},{"w":"get","ko":"구해 주다 (→ get O for sb)","ex":"The scout got the party fresh supplies."},{"w":"build","ko":"지어 주다 (→ build O for sb)","ex":"Engineers built the town a reservoir."},{"w":"order","ko":"주문해 주다 (→ order O for sb)","ex":"The lab ordered the team new equipment."},{"w":"choose","ko":"골라 주다 (→ choose O for sb)","ex":"The board chose the project a new leader."},{"w":"ask","ko":"묻다·요청하다 (→ ask O of sb)","ex":"The examiner asked the student a question."},{"w":"cost","ko":"(비용이) 들게 하다 (전환 불가)","ex":"The delay cost the project months."},{"w":"save","ko":"덜어 주다 (→ save O for sb)","ex":"Automation saved workers hours of labor."},{"w":"owe","ko":"빚지다 (→ owe O to sb)","ex":"Modern science owes much to early observers."}]},{"label":"5형식 — 형용사·명사 목적격보어 (S + V + O + OC)","note":"**목적격보어(OC)**가 목적어의 상태·정체를 보완한다. ==O = OC== 관계가 성립한다. make O 형용사 = '~하게 만들다', call/name O 명사 = '~라고 부르다'다.","items":[{"w":"make","ko":"~을 …하게 만들다 (O+형/명)","ex":"The mutation makes the cell resistant."},{"w":"keep","ko":"~을 …인 상태로 유지하다 (O+형)","ex":"Insulation keeps the interior warm."},{"w":"leave","ko":"~을 …인 채로 두다 (O+형)","ex":"The flood left the fields barren."},{"w":"find","ko":"~이 …하다고 여기다·알다 (O+형/명)","ex":"They found the data reliable."},{"w":"consider","ko":"~을 …라고 여기다 (O+형/명)","ex":"Scientists consider the method valid."},{"w":"think","ko":"~을 …라고 생각하다 (O+형/명)","ex":"Scholars thought the theory flawed."},{"w":"believe","ko":"~을 …라고 믿다 (O+형/명)","ex":"They believed the site sacred."},{"w":"deem","ko":"~을 …로 간주하다 (O+형/명)","ex":"The board deemed the evidence sufficient."},{"w":"call","ko":"~을 …라고 부르다 (O+명)","ex":"Geologists call this layer the boundary clay."},{"w":"name","ko":"~을 …라고 이름 짓다 (O+명)","ex":"They named the new species after its finder."},{"w":"elect","ko":"~을 …로 선출하다 (O+명)","ex":"The assembly elected him leader."},{"w":"appoint","ko":"~을 …로 임명하다 (O+명)","ex":"The council appointed her director."},{"w":"declare","ko":"~을 …라고 선언하다 (O+형/명)","ex":"The agency declared the area protected."},{"w":"label","ko":"~을 …로 분류·표시하다 (O+명)","ex":"Researchers labeled the sample contaminated."},{"w":"term","ko":"~을 …라고 칭하다 (O+명)","ex":"Biologists term this trait an adaptation."},{"w":"designate","ko":"~을 …로 지정하다 (O+명)","ex":"They designated the wetland a reserve."},{"w":"paint","ko":"~을 …색으로 칠하다 (O+형)","ex":"The pigment painted the walls red."},{"w":"drive","ko":"~을 …하게 몰아가다 (O+형)","ex":"Habitat loss drove the species extinct."},{"w":"render","ko":"~을 …한 상태로 만들다 (O+형)","ex":"The toxin renders the water undrinkable."},{"w":"prove","ko":"~을 …임을 증명하다 (O+형/명)","ex":"The test proved the sample authentic."},{"w":"turn","ko":"~을 …로 바꾸다 (O+명)","ex":"Erosion turned the plateau a canyon over time."},{"w":"set","ko":"~을 …인 상태로 두다 (O+형)","ex":"The reform set the economy free."}]},{"label":"5형식 — to부정사 목적격보어 (S + V + O + to-V)","note":"'O가 …하도록/하기를' 시키거나 바라는 동사다. want·ask·tell·allow·expect·advise·encourage 등이 **O + to부정사**를 받는다. (make/let/have는 원형을 받으니 ==다음 그룹에서 구분==!)","items":[{"w":"want","ko":"~이 …하기를 원하다","ex":"They wanted the samples to remain intact."},{"w":"ask","ko":"~에게 …하라고 요청하다","ex":"The committee asked the team to revise the plan."},{"w":"tell","ko":"~에게 …하라고 말하다","ex":"The guide told visitors to stay on the path."},{"w":"allow","ko":"~이 …하도록 허용하다","ex":"The permit allows researchers to collect samples."},{"w":"permit","ko":"~이 …하도록 허가하다","ex":"The law permits fishermen to operate seasonally."},{"w":"enable","ko":"~이 …할 수 있게 하다","ex":"The tool enables scientists to map the seafloor."},{"w":"expect","ko":"~이 …할 것으로 기대하다","ex":"Analysts expect the population to recover."},{"w":"advise","ko":"~에게 …하라고 조언하다","ex":"Experts advised the town to relocate."},{"w":"encourage","ko":"~이 …하도록 장려하다","ex":"The policy encouraged farmers to rotate crops."},{"w":"force","ko":"~이 …하도록 강요하다","ex":"Drought forced the herds to migrate."},{"w":"order","ko":"~에게 …하라고 명령하다","ex":"The court ordered the firm to halt operations."},{"w":"invite","ko":"~에게 …하도록 청하다","ex":"The journal invited scholars to submit papers."},{"w":"remind","ko":"~에게 …할 것을 상기시키다","ex":"The alert reminded residents to evacuate."},{"w":"warn","ko":"~에게 …하라고 경고하다","ex":"Officials warned people to avoid the coast."},{"w":"cause","ko":"~이 …하게 만들다","ex":"The heat caused the ice to melt."},{"w":"get","ko":"~이 …하게 하다 (설득·유도)","ex":"Researchers got the subjects to respond."},{"w":"require","ko":"~이 …할 것을 요구하다","ex":"The rule requires vessels to report catches."},{"w":"lead","ko":"~이 …하도록 이끌다","ex":"The findings led scientists to revise the model."},{"w":"persuade","ko":"~을 …하도록 설득하다","ex":"The data persuaded the board to fund the study."},{"w":"urge","ko":"~에게 …하라고 촉구하다","ex":"The report urged nations to cut emissions."},{"w":"permit","ko":"~이 …하게 허용하다","ex":"The climate permits crops to grow year-round."},{"w":"instruct","ko":"~에게 …하라고 지시하다","ex":"The manual instructs users to calibrate the device."},{"w":"prompt","ko":"~이 …하도록 촉발하다","ex":"The crisis prompted the government to act."},{"w":"teach","ko":"~에게 …하는 법을 가르치다","ex":"The program teaches students to code."},{"w":"help","ko":"~이 …하도록 돕다 (to 생략 가능)","ex":"The grant helped the lab (to) expand."}]},{"label":"5형식 — 원형/분사 (사역·지각동사)","note":"사역동사 make·let·have는 **O + 원형**, get은 O + to-V, have/get O + p.p.는 ==수동 사역(~되게 하다)==이다. 지각동사 see·watch·hear 등은 O + 원형(완결 행위)/O + -ing(진행 중)을 받는다.","items":[{"w":"make","ko":"~에게 …하게 하다 (강제 사역, +원형)","ex":"Gravity makes objects fall toward the center."},{"w":"let","ko":"~이 …하게 놔두다 (허용 사역, +원형)","ex":"The valve lets pressure escape gradually."},{"w":"have","ko":"~에게 …하게 시키다 (지시 사역, +원형)","ex":"The lab had assistants record the data."},{"w":"get","ko":"~이 …하게 하다 (설득 사역, +to-V)","ex":"They got the engine to restart."},{"w":"have (p.p.)","ko":"~이 …되게 하다 (수동 사역, +p.p.)","ex":"They had the samples analyzed overseas."},{"w":"get (p.p.)","ko":"~이 …되게 하다 (수동 사역, +p.p.)","ex":"She got the results verified independently."},{"w":"help","ko":"~이 …하도록 돕다 (+원형/to-V)","ex":"Enzymes help reactions proceed faster."},{"w":"see","ko":"~이 …하는 것을 보다 (+원형/-ing)","ex":"Observers saw the glacier retreat."},{"w":"watch","ko":"~이 …하는 것을 지켜보다 (+원형/-ing)","ex":"Scientists watched the cells divide."},{"w":"hear","ko":"~이 …하는 것을 듣다 (+원형/-ing)","ex":"Researchers heard the whales call across the bay."},{"w":"feel","ko":"~이 …하는 것을 느끼다 (+원형/-ing)","ex":"They felt the ground tremble during the quake."},{"w":"notice","ko":"~이 …하는 것을 알아채다 (+원형/-ing)","ex":"The team noticed the readings shift."},{"w":"observe","ko":"~이 …하는 것을 관찰하다 (+원형/-ing)","ex":"Biologists observed the birds migrate south."},{"w":"perceive","ko":"~이 …하는 것을 감지하다 (+원형/-ing)","ex":"Sensors perceived the temperature rise."},{"w":"listen to","ko":"~이 …하는 것을 귀 기울여 듣다 (+원형/-ing)","ex":"They listened to the signal fade."},{"w":"spot","ko":"~이 …하는 것을 포착하다 (+-ing)","ex":"The telescope spotted the comet approaching."},{"w":"catch","ko":"~이 …하는 것을 발견하다 (진행, +-ing)","ex":"They caught the reaction changing color."},{"w":"find","ko":"~이 …하고 있는 것을 발견하다 (+-ing)","ex":"Researchers found the population declining."},{"w":"keep","ko":"~이 계속 …하게 하다 (+-ing)","ex":"The current keeps nutrients circulating."},{"w":"leave","ko":"~이 …하는 채로 두다 (+-ing)","ex":"The leak left water dripping for hours."},{"w":"set","ko":"~이 …하기 시작하게 하다 (+-ing)","ex":"The spark set the reaction going."}]}]}},{"n":2,"title":"간접의문문 · 명사절","status":"detailed","summary":"질문이 더 큰 문장 안에 들어가면 물음표 어순을 풀고 ==평서문처럼== **의문사 + 주어 + 동사** 순서로 쓴다. 그래서 'where is he'가 아니라 'where he is'가 된다. know·wonder·tell·ask 같은 동사 뒤에 붙고, 예-아니오는 **if나 whether**로 잇는다. 여기에 **that 명사절**, **의문사 + to부정사**, 주절이 과거일 때의 **시제 일치**까지 함께 정리한다.","subtopics":[{"key":"in-statement","title":"평서문 속 간접의문문 (I know / I wonder / Could you tell me + 의문사 + S + V)","points":["평서문 안에 질문을 담을 때는 know, wonder, remember, be not sure 같은 동사 뒤에 **의문사 + 주어 + 동사**를 붙인다.","질문의 도치(be동사나 do 앞으로 빼기)를 반드시 ==푼다==.","즉 'where is he'가 아니라 **'where he is'** 순서로 쓴다.","**do/does/did**도 사라지고, 동사를 그 자리에 맞춰 변형해 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"I know where he lives now.","ko":"그가 지금 어디 사는지 안다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"where","role":"Wh"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"lives","role":"V"},{"t":"now.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I wonder why she left early.","ko":"그녀가 왜 일찍 갔는지 궁금하다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"wonder","role":"V"},{"t":"why","role":"Wh"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"left","role":"V"},{"t":"early.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Can you tell me what this word means?","ko":"이 단어가 무슨 뜻인지 말해줄 수 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"tell","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"what","role":"Wh"},{"t":"this word","role":"S"},{"t":"means?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"I don't remember when the meeting starts.","ko":"회의가 언제 시작하는지 기억이 안 난다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"remember","role":"V"},{"t":"when","role":"Wh"},{"t":"the meeting","role":"S"},{"t":"starts.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"She isn't sure how the machine works.","ko":"그녀는 그 기계가 어떻게 작동하는지 잘 모른다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"isn't","role":"V"},{"t":"sure","role":"SC"},{"t":"how","role":"Wh"},{"t":"the machine","role":"S"},{"t":"works.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Could you explain what the problem is?","ko":"문제가 무엇인지 설명해줄 수 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"explain","role":"V"},{"t":"what","role":"Wh"},{"t":"the problem","role":"S"},{"t":"is?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Nobody knows how she fixed it.","ko":"그녀가 그걸 어떻게 고쳤는지 아무도 모른다.","parts":[{"t":"Nobody","role":"S"},{"t":"knows","role":"V"},{"t":"how","role":"Wh"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"fixed","role":"V"},{"t":"it.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Please tell me why you are so tired.","ko":"왜 그렇게 피곤한지 말해달라.","parts":[{"t":"Please","role":"M"},{"t":"tell","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"why","role":"Wh"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"so tired.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["I know where does he work.","I know where he works. (내포절은 do를 빼고 **평서문 어순**으로 쓴다.)"],["I'm not sure what time is it.","I'm not sure what time it is. (be동사 도치를 풀어 **'it is'**로 쓴다.)"],["Can you tell me what means this word?","Can you tell me what this word means? (내포절도 **주어(this word) + 동사(means)** 순서를 지킨다.)"]]},{"key":"in-question","title":"직접의문문 속 간접의문문 (Do you know where he is?)","points":["바깥 문장이 질문이면 **바깥쪽만** 도치한다(Do you...?, Can you...?).","안에 들어간 간접의문문은 여전히 ==평서문 어순== **의문사 + 주어 + 동사**로 둔다.","겉과 속을 헷갈려 안쪽까지 도치하면 **안 된다**.","안쪽 절에서 **do/does/did**는 다시 쓰지 않는다."],"examples":[{"en":"Do you know where the station is?","ko":"역이 어디에 있는지 아는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"where","role":"Wh"},{"t":"the station","role":"S"},{"t":"is?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Can you tell me when the class starts?","ko":"수업이 언제 시작하는지 말해줄 수 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"tell","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"when","role":"Wh"},{"t":"the class","role":"S"},{"t":"starts?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Does she know why we are here?","ko":"우리가 왜 여기 있는지 그녀가 아는가?","parts":[{"t":"Does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"why","role":"Wh"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"here?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Do you remember what he said?","ko":"그가 뭐라고 했는지 기억하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"remember","role":"V"},{"t":"what","role":"Wh"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"said?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Could you show me how this app works?","ko":"이 앱이 어떻게 작동하는지 보여줄 수 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"show","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"how","role":"Wh"},{"t":"this app","role":"S"},{"t":"works?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Do you have any idea where they went?","ko":"그들이 어디로 갔는지 짐작이 가는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"V"},{"t":"any idea","role":"O"},{"t":"where","role":"Wh"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"went?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Did he mention when they will arrive?","ko":"그들이 언제 도착하는지 그가 말했는가?","parts":[{"t":"Did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"mention","role":"V"},{"t":"when","role":"Wh"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"arrive?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Can anyone explain what this chart shows?","ko":"이 도표가 무엇을 보여주는지 설명할 수 있는 사람이 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"anyone","role":"S"},{"t":"explain","role":"V"},{"t":"what","role":"Wh"},{"t":"this chart","role":"S"},{"t":"shows?","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["Do you know where is the station?","Do you know where the station is? (안쪽은 도치 없이 **'the station is'**로 쓴다.)"],["Can you tell me when does it start?","Can you tell me when it starts? (내포절에서 does를 **뺀다**.)"],["Do you know what did he say?","Do you know what he said? (바깥만 도치하고 안쪽은 **'he said'**로 쓴다.)"]]},{"key":"wh-fronting","title":"think/suppose류 (What do you think he wants?)","points":["think, suppose, imagine, guess, believe 같은 동사로 물으면 **의문사를 문장 맨 앞**으로 뺀다.","'Do you think what...'가 아니라 ==**What do you think...**== 순서로 쓴다.","바깥 질문은 도치하고, 안쪽 절은 그대로 **평서문 어순**으로 둔다.","안쪽 절에는 **do/does/did**를 다시 넣지 않는다."],"examples":[{"en":"What do you think he wants for lunch?","ko":"그가 점심으로 뭘 원한다고 생각하는가?","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"think","role":"V"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"wants","role":"V"},{"t":"for lunch?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Where do you suppose she went?","ko":"그녀가 어디 갔다고 생각하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Where","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"suppose","role":"V"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"went?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Who do you believe will win?","ko":"누가 이길 거라고 믿는가?","parts":[{"t":"Who","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"believe","role":"V"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"win?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"When do you guess they will arrive?","ko":"그들이 언제 도착할 거라고 짐작하는가?","parts":[{"t":"When","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"guess","role":"V"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"arrive?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"What do you imagine the test will be like?","ko":"시험이 어떨 거라고 상상하는가?","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"imagine","role":"V"},{"t":"the test","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"be","role":"V"},{"t":"like?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"How do you suppose he found out?","ko":"그가 어떻게 알아냈다고 생각하는가?","parts":[{"t":"How","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"suppose","role":"V"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"found","role":"V"},{"t":"out?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Why do you think she quit her job?","ko":"그녀가 왜 일을 그만뒀다고 생각하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Why","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"think","role":"V"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"quit","role":"V"},{"t":"her job?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"What time do you reckon the show ends?","ko":"쇼가 몇 시에 끝날 거라고 보는가?","parts":[{"t":"What time","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"reckon","role":"V"},{"t":"the show","role":"S"},{"t":"ends?","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["Do you think what he wants?","What do you think he wants? (think류는 의문사를 **문장 맨 앞**으로 뺀다.)"],["What do you think does he want?","What do you think he wants? (안쪽은 does 없이 **'he wants'**로 쓴다.)"],["Do you suppose where she went?","Where do you suppose she went? (suppose류도 의문사를 **맨 앞**으로 보낸다.)"]]},{"key":"if-whether","title":"예-아니오 내포절 (I'm not sure if/whether it will rain)","points":["의문사가 없는 예-아니오 질문을 담을 때는 **if나 whether**로 이어준다.","뒤에는 똑같이 ==평서문 어순== **주어 + 동사**가 온다.","ask, wonder, not sure 뒤에 자주 붙는다.","**whether**는 or not과 잘 어울리고, 주어절·전치사 뒤에서는 if 대신 whether를 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"I'm not sure if it will rain today.","ko":"오늘 비가 올지 잘 모르겠다.","parts":[{"t":"I'm","role":"S"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"sure","role":"SC"},{"t":"if","role":"Conj"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"rain","role":"V"},{"t":"today.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She asked whether I was free tonight.","ko":"그녀가 오늘 밤 시간이 되는지 물었다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"asked","role":"V"},{"t":"whether","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"free","role":"SC"},{"t":"tonight.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I wonder if the store is still open.","ko":"가게가 아직 열려 있는지 궁금하다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"wonder","role":"V"},{"t":"if","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the store","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"still open.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"Let me know whether you can come.","ko":"올 수 있는지 알려달라.","parts":[{"t":"Let","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"whether","role":"Conj"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"come.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"He can't decide if he should stay or go.","ko":"그는 머물지 갈지 결정하지 못한다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"can't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"decide","role":"V"},{"t":"if","role":"Conj"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"stay or go.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"I doubt whether she will agree.","ko":"그녀가 동의할지 의심스럽다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"doubt","role":"V"},{"t":"whether","role":"Conj"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"agree.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Do you know if the bank is open on Saturdays?","ko":"은행이 토요일에 여는지 아는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"if","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the bank","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"open","role":"SC"},{"t":"on Saturdays?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We need to find out whether the flight is delayed.","ko":"항공편이 지연되는지 알아봐야 한다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"need","role":"V"},{"t":"to find out","role":"O"},{"t":"whether","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the flight","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"delayed.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["I don't know will it rain tomorrow.","I don't know if it will rain tomorrow. (예-아니오 질문은 **if/whether**로 잇는다.)"],["I wonder does he like coffee.","I wonder whether he likes coffee. (whether 뒤엔 도치 없이 **'he likes'**로 쓴다.)"],["She asked if or not I was ready.","She asked whether or not I was ready. (**or not**은 whether와만 붙고 if와는 안 쓴다.)"]]},{"key":"wh-subject","title":"의문사가 내포절의 주어일 때 (I don't know who broke it)","points":["의문사(who/what/which)가 내포절의 **주어**면 그 뒤에 **바로 동사**가 온다.","이때는 do/does/did를 넣을 자리가 없어 ==do-support가 아예 없다==.","어순은 **의문사 + 동사**로, 직접의문문의 주어 의문사와 똑같이 생겼다.","주어 의문사는 보통 **3인칭 단수** 취급이라 동사에 -s가 붙는다."],"examples":[{"en":"I don't know who broke the window.","ko":"누가 창문을 깼는지 모르겠다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"who","role":"S"},{"t":"broke","role":"V"},{"t":"the window.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Nobody knows what caused the delay.","ko":"무엇이 지연을 일으켰는지 아무도 모른다.","parts":[{"t":"Nobody","role":"S"},{"t":"knows","role":"V"},{"t":"what","role":"S"},{"t":"caused","role":"V"},{"t":"the delay.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Can you tell me who left this note?","ko":"누가 이 쪽지를 남겼는지 말해줄 수 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"tell","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"who","role":"S"},{"t":"left","role":"V"},{"t":"this note?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"She wonders what happened last night.","ko":"그녀는 어젯밤 무슨 일이 있었는지 궁금해한다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"wonders","role":"V"},{"t":"what","role":"S"},{"t":"happened","role":"V"},{"t":"last night.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I forget which won the match.","ko":"어느 쪽이 경기를 이겼는지 잊었다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"forget","role":"V"},{"t":"which","role":"S"},{"t":"won","role":"V"},{"t":"the match.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Let me know who is coming to dinner.","ko":"누가 저녁 식사에 오는지 알려달라.","parts":[{"t":"Let","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"who","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"coming","role":"V"},{"t":"to dinner.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Do you remember what made her upset?","ko":"무엇이 그녀를 화나게 했는지 기억하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"remember","role":"V"},{"t":"what","role":"S"},{"t":"made","role":"V"},{"t":"her","role":"O"},{"t":"upset?","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"He asked who wanted more coffee.","ko":"그가 누가 커피를 더 원하는지 물었다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"asked","role":"V"},{"t":"who","role":"S"},{"t":"wanted","role":"V"},{"t":"more coffee.","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["I don't know who did break it.","I don't know who broke it. (주어 의문사 뒤엔 do를 **넣지 않는다**.)"],["Nobody knows what did cause the delay.","Nobody knows what caused the delay. (**주어가 what**이면 did 없이 바로 동사를 쓴다.)"],["Can you tell me who does live here?","Can you tell me who lives here? (주어 의문사는 **who lives**처럼 동사에 -s만 붙인다.)"]]},{"key":"wh-plus-noun","title":"what/which/whose + 명사 내포 (Tell me which bus goes downtown)","points":["**what/which/whose** 뒤에 명사를 붙여 ==한 덩어리 의문사구==로 내포절을 이끈다.","which는 **정해진 범위 안에서 선택**, what은 **범위가 열려 있을 때** 쓴다.","whose + 명사는 **소유**(누구의 ~)를 물을 때 쓴다.","뒤 어순은 그대로 **주어 + 동사**이고, 그 구가 주어면 바로 동사가 온다."],"examples":[{"en":"Tell me which bus goes downtown.","ko":"어느 버스가 시내로 가는지 말해달라.","parts":[{"t":"Tell","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"which bus","role":"S"},{"t":"goes","role":"V"},{"t":"downtown.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I don't know what size he wears.","ko":"그가 무슨 사이즈를 입는지 모른다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"what size","role":"O"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"wears.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"She asked whose car was blocking the driveway.","ko":"누구 차가 진입로를 막고 있는지 그녀가 물었다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"asked","role":"V"},{"t":"whose car","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"blocking","role":"V"},{"t":"the driveway.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Do you know which room the interview is in?","ko":"면접이 어느 방에서 열리는지 아는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"which room","role":"M"},{"t":"the interview","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"in?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I'm not sure what movie they picked.","ko":"그들이 무슨 영화를 골랐는지 잘 모르겠다.","parts":[{"t":"I'm","role":"S"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"sure","role":"SC"},{"t":"what movie","role":"O"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"picked.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Can you find out whose idea this was?","ko":"이게 누구 아이디어였는지 알아봐 줄 수 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"find","role":"V"},{"t":"out","role":"M"},{"t":"whose idea","role":"SC"},{"t":"this","role":"S"},{"t":"was?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Let me know which option works best.","ko":"어느 선택지가 가장 잘 맞는지 알려달라.","parts":[{"t":"Let","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"which option","role":"S"},{"t":"works","role":"V"},{"t":"best.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I wonder what color they will choose.","ko":"그들이 무슨 색을 고를지 궁금하다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"wonder","role":"V"},{"t":"what color","role":"O"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"choose.","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["Tell me which does bus go downtown.","Tell me which bus goes downtown. (의문사구 **which bus**가 주어면 do 없이 바로 동사를 쓴다.)"],["I don't know what size does he wear.","I don't know what size he wears. (내포절은 do를 빼고 **'he wears'**로 쓴다.)"],["She asked whose is car blocking the driveway.","She asked whose car was blocking the driveway. (**whose + 명사**를 한 덩어리로 붙여 쓴다.)"]]},{"key":"how-adj-adv","title":"how + 형용사/부사 내포 (I wonder how long it takes)","points":["**how + 형용사/부사**를 한 덩어리로 묶어 정도·수량을 묻는다.","how long(기간), how far(거리), how much(양·가격), how many(개수), how old(나이) 등이 있다.","뒤 어순은 역시 ==평서문== **주어 + 동사**로 둔다.","how much/how many는 뒤 명사와 붙어 **수량 의문사구**를 이룬다."],"examples":[{"en":"I wonder how long the trip takes.","ko":"그 여행이 얼마나 걸리는지 궁금하다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"wonder","role":"V"},{"t":"how long","role":"M"},{"t":"the trip","role":"S"},{"t":"takes.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Do you know how much this jacket costs?","ko":"이 재킷이 얼마인지 아는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"how much","role":"M"},{"t":"this jacket","role":"S"},{"t":"costs?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"She asked how far the beach was.","ko":"그녀가 해변이 얼마나 먼지 물었다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"asked","role":"V"},{"t":"how far","role":"SC"},{"t":"the beach","role":"S"},{"t":"was.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Tell me how many people are coming.","ko":"몇 명이 오는지 말해달라.","parts":[{"t":"Tell","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"how many people","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"coming.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"I'm not sure how old the building is.","ko":"그 건물이 얼마나 오래됐는지 잘 모르겠다.","parts":[{"t":"I'm","role":"S"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"sure","role":"SC"},{"t":"how old","role":"SC"},{"t":"the building","role":"S"},{"t":"is.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Let me know how soon you can finish.","ko":"얼마나 빨리 끝낼 수 있는지 알려달라.","parts":[{"t":"Let","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"how soon","role":"M"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"finish.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"I can't tell how well she speaks French.","ko":"그녀가 프랑스어를 얼마나 잘하는지 잘 모르겠다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"can't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"tell","role":"V"},{"t":"how well","role":"M"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"speaks","role":"V"},{"t":"French.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Do you remember how much we paid last time?","ko":"지난번에 우리가 얼마를 냈는지 기억하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"remember","role":"V"},{"t":"how much","role":"O"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"paid","role":"V"},{"t":"last time?","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I wonder how long does it take.","I wonder how long it takes. (내포절은 does 없이 **'it takes'**로 쓴다.)"],["Do you know how much costs this jacket?","Do you know how much this jacket costs? (**주어 + 동사** 순서로 'this jacket costs'라 쓴다.)"],["She asked how the beach was far.","She asked how far the beach was. (**how + 형용사**를 붙여 앞으로 함께 보낸다.)"]]},{"key":"that-clause","title":"that 명사절 (I think that... / The problem is that... / the fact that...)","points":["**that + 완전한 문장**이 명사절이 되어 주어·목적어·보어·동격으로 쓰인다.","동사의 **목적어**로 올 때 that은 자주 **생략**된다 (I think (that) he is right).","보어 자리 'The problem is that...'나 동격 'the fact that...'에서는 보통 that을 살린다.","that절 안은 질문이 아니라 ==평서문 그대로==라 어순 걱정이 없다."],"examples":[{"en":"I think that he is right.","ko":"그가 맞다고 생각한다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"think","role":"V"},{"t":"that","role":"Conj"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"right.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"She said she was tired.","ko":"그녀는 피곤하다고 말했다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"said","role":"V"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"tired.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The problem is that we are out of time.","ko":"문제는 우리에게 시간이 없다는 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"The problem","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"that","role":"Conj"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"out of time.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I hope that everything goes well.","ko":"모든 일이 잘되길 바란다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"hope","role":"V"},{"t":"that","role":"Conj"},{"t":"everything","role":"S"},{"t":"goes","role":"V"},{"t":"well.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The fact that she apologized surprised me.","ko":"그녀가 사과했다는 사실이 나를 놀라게 했다.","parts":[{"t":"The fact","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"Conj"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"apologized","role":"V"},{"t":"surprised","role":"V"},{"t":"me.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Everyone knows that practice matters.","ko":"연습이 중요하다는 것을 누구나 안다.","parts":[{"t":"Everyone","role":"S"},{"t":"knows","role":"V"},{"t":"that","role":"Conj"},{"t":"practice","role":"S"},{"t":"matters.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"I noticed that the door was open.","ko":"문이 열려 있는 것을 알아챘다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"noticed","role":"V"},{"t":"that","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the door","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"open.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"My worry is that we might be late.","ko":"내 걱정은 우리가 늦을지도 모른다는 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"My worry","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"that","role":"Conj"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"might","role":"Aux"},{"t":"be","role":"V"},{"t":"late.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["I think that is he right.","I think that he is right. (that절 안은 도치 없이 **'he is'** 평서문 어순이다.)"],["The problem is what we are late.","The problem is that we are late. (사실을 잇는 보어절은 what이 아니라 **that**을 쓴다.)"],["I hope will everything go well.","I hope that everything goes well. (that절 안은 **주어 + 동사** 평서문으로 쓴다.)"]]},{"key":"wh-to-infinitive","title":"의문사 + to부정사 (I don't know where to go / what to do)","points":["**의문사 + to부정사**는 '무엇을/어디에/어떻게 ~할지'를 짧게 나타낸다.","'의문사 + 주어 + should + 동사'를 ==압축한 형태==다 (where to go = where I should go).","what/where/when/how/who(m)/which와 잘 쓰고, ==why는 쓰지 않는다==.","뒤에 주어가 없어 **주어가 문맥상 정해질 때** 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"I don't know where to go.","ko":"어디로 가야 할지 모르겠다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"where","role":"Wh"},{"t":"to go.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"She taught me how to drive.","ko":"그녀가 나에게 운전하는 법을 가르쳐 줬다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"taught","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"how","role":"Wh"},{"t":"to drive.","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"Tell me what to do next.","ko":"다음에 뭘 해야 할지 말해달라.","parts":[{"t":"Tell","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"what","role":"Wh"},{"t":"to do","role":"DO"},{"t":"next.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He isn't sure when to leave.","ko":"그는 언제 떠나야 할지 잘 모른다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"isn't","role":"V"},{"t":"sure","role":"SC"},{"t":"when","role":"Wh"},{"t":"to leave.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We need to decide who to invite.","ko":"누구를 초대할지 정해야 한다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"need","role":"V"},{"t":"to decide","role":"V"},{"t":"who","role":"Wh"},{"t":"to invite.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I can't figure out how to fix this.","ko":"이걸 어떻게 고칠지 알아내지 못하겠다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"can't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"figure","role":"V"},{"t":"out","role":"M"},{"t":"how","role":"Wh"},{"t":"to fix this.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Let me show you which button to press.","ko":"어느 버튼을 눌러야 할지 보여주겠다.","parts":[{"t":"Let","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"show","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"IO"},{"t":"which button","role":"Wh"},{"t":"to press.","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"She was wondering what to wear tonight.","ko":"그녀는 오늘 밤 뭘 입을지 고민하고 있었다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"wondering","role":"V"},{"t":"what","role":"Wh"},{"t":"to wear","role":"O"},{"t":"tonight.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I don't know where should to go.","I don't know where to go. (의문사 + **to부정사**만으로 충분하다.)"],["Tell me what I to do.","Tell me what to do. (의문사 뒤에는 주어 없이 **to + 동사원형**을 붙인다.)"],["He isn't sure why to leave.","He isn't sure when to leave. (**why**는 to부정사와 함께 쓰지 않는다.)"]]},{"key":"verb-obj-to-inf","title":"ask/tell/want + 목적어 + to부정사 (She asked me to wait)","points":["**ask/tell/want/expect/advise** 등은 '**목적어 + to부정사**'로 간접 명령·요청을 나타낸다.","직접명령 'Wait!'을 She asked me to wait처럼 ==한 문장 안에 담는다==.","목적어가 to부정사 **행동의 주체**다 (me → 기다리는 사람).","부정은 **not to + 동사**로 만든다 (told me not to worry)."],"examples":[{"en":"She asked me to wait outside.","ko":"그녀가 나에게 밖에서 기다리라고 부탁했다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"asked","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"to wait","role":"OC"},{"t":"outside.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The teacher told us to be quiet.","ko":"선생님이 우리에게 조용히 하라고 하셨다.","parts":[{"t":"The teacher","role":"S"},{"t":"told","role":"V"},{"t":"us","role":"O"},{"t":"to be quiet.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"I want you to try again.","ko":"나는 네가 다시 시도하길 바란다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"want","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"O"},{"t":"to try again.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"He expects everyone to arrive on time.","ko":"그는 모두가 제시간에 오기를 기대한다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"expects","role":"V"},{"t":"everyone","role":"O"},{"t":"to arrive","role":"OC"},{"t":"on time.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"My boss advised me to take a break.","ko":"상사가 나에게 쉬라고 조언했다.","parts":[{"t":"My boss","role":"S"},{"t":"advised","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"to take a break.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"They told him not to worry.","ko":"그들은 그에게 걱정하지 말라고 했다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"told","role":"V"},{"t":"him","role":"O"},{"t":"not to worry.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"Could you remind her to call me?","ko":"그녀에게 나한테 전화하라고 상기시켜 줄 수 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"remind","role":"V"},{"t":"her","role":"O"},{"t":"to call me?","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"We need everyone to sign the form.","ko":"우리는 모두가 양식에 서명하기를 원한다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"need","role":"V"},{"t":"everyone","role":"O"},{"t":"to sign the form.","role":"OC"}]}],"mistakes":[["She asked me wait outside.","She asked me to wait outside. (**목적어 뒤**에는 to부정사를 쓴다.)"],["The teacher told to us be quiet.","The teacher told us to be quiet. (**tell + 목적어 + to부정사** 순서로 쓴다.)"],["They told him don't worry.","They told him not to worry. (부정은 **not to + 동사원형**으로 만든다.)"]]},{"key":"tense-agreement","title":"시제 일치 (He said he was tired)","points":["주절이 **과거**면 내포절 동사도 보통 ==한 시제 뒤로== 옮긴다 (is → was, will → would).","'He says he is tired'가 과거가 되면 **He said he was tired**가 된다.","can → could, will → would, 현재완료·과거 → 과거완료로 밀린다.","단, **변하지 않는 사실·습관**은 현재로 두기도 한다."],"examples":[{"en":"He said he was tired.","ko":"그는 피곤하다고 말했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"said","role":"V"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"tired.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"She told me she would be late.","ko":"그녀는 나에게 늦을 거라고 말했다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"told","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"would","role":"Aux"},{"t":"be","role":"V"},{"t":"late.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I thought you knew the answer.","ko":"나는 네가 답을 아는 줄 알았다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"thought","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"knew","role":"V"},{"t":"the answer.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"They said they had already eaten.","ko":"그들은 이미 먹었다고 말했다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"said","role":"V"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"already eaten.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"We knew the store would close soon.","ko":"우리는 가게가 곧 문을 닫을 것을 알았다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"knew","role":"V"},{"t":"the store","role":"S"},{"t":"would","role":"Aux"},{"t":"close","role":"V"},{"t":"soon.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He asked if I could help him.","ko":"그는 내가 그를 도울 수 있는지 물었다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"asked","role":"V"},{"t":"if","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"help","role":"V"},{"t":"him.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I wasn't sure what she wanted.","ko":"나는 그녀가 무엇을 원하는지 확실치 않았다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"wasn't","role":"V"},{"t":"sure","role":"SC"},{"t":"what","role":"Wh"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"wanted.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"She explained that the plan had changed.","ko":"그녀는 계획이 바뀌었다고 설명했다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"explained","role":"V"},{"t":"that","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the plan","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"changed.","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["He said he is tired.","He said he was tired. (주절이 과거면 내포절도 **was**로 맞춘다.)"],["She told me she will be late.","She told me she would be late. (will을 **would**로 한 시제 밀어 준다.)"],["I thought you know the answer.","I thought you knew the answer. (주절 과거에 맞춰 **knew**로 쓴다.)"]]}],"db":{"title":"간접의문문 · 명사절 DB · 이끄는 동사 & 패턴","intro":"간접의문문과 명사절은 <b>어떤 동사 뒤에 오느냐</b>가 절반이다. ==보고·인지 동사(know·wonder·ask·tell)는 의문사절·if/whether절을, think·believe류는 that절을 이끈다==. 아래 4개 그룹으로 이끄는 동사, if vs whether 구분, that절 동사, 의문사+to부정사 패턴을 한눈에 정리했다.","groups":[{"label":"간접의문문을 이끄는 보고·인지 동사","note":"뒤에 **의문사 + 주어 + 동사** 또는 **if/whether절**을 붙이는 동사다. ==안쪽 절은 도치 없이 평서문 어순==으로 쓴다는 점만 지키면 된다.","items":[{"w":"know","ko":"알다","ex":"I know where he lives."},{"w":"wonder","ko":"궁금하다","ex":"I wonder why she left."},{"w":"ask","ko":"묻다","ex":"She asked where I was."},{"w":"tell","ko":"말해 주다","ex":"Tell me what happened."},{"w":"remember","ko":"기억하다","ex":"I don't remember when it started."},{"w":"forget","ko":"잊다","ex":"I forget where I parked."},{"w":"decide","ko":"결정하다","ex":"We must decide who goes first."},{"w":"explain","ko":"설명하다","ex":"Explain how it works."},{"w":"understand","ko":"이해하다","ex":"I understand why you're upset."},{"w":"be sure","ko":"확신하다","ex":"I'm not sure what to do."},{"w":"find out","ko":"알아내다","ex":"Let's find out when it opens."},{"w":"guess","ko":"짐작하다","ex":"Guess what I found."},{"w":"imagine","ko":"상상하다","ex":"Imagine how hard it was."},{"w":"suppose","ko":"추측하다","ex":"Where do you suppose she went?"},{"w":"realize","ko":"깨닫다","ex":"I realized what he meant."},{"w":"doubt","ko":"의심하다","ex":"I doubt whether it's true."},{"w":"notice","ko":"알아채다","ex":"I noticed how tired he looked."},{"w":"check","ko":"확인하다","ex":"Let me check when it starts."},{"w":"recall","ko":"떠올리다","ex":"I can't recall what she said."},{"w":"discover","ko":"발견하다","ex":"They discovered how it happened."},{"w":"show","ko":"보여 주다","ex":"Show me how you did it."},{"w":"figure out","ko":"알아내다","ex":"Figure out what went wrong."},{"w":"point out","ko":"지적하다","ex":"She pointed out what was missing."}]},{"label":"if vs whether 구분","note":"둘 다 '~인지'를 뜻하지만 쓰임이 다르다. ==whether는 주어절·전치사 뒤·or not·to부정사와 함께 쓸 수 있고, if는 목적어 자리에서만== 편하게 쓴다.","items":[{"w":"if","ko":"~인지 (구어·목적어 자리)","ex":"I don't know if it's open."},{"w":"whether","ko":"~인지 (격식·모든 자리)","ex":"Whether it rains is unclear."},{"w":"whether ... or not","ko":"~인지 아닌지","ex":"I'll go whether or not it rains."},{"w":"whether + to부정사","ko":"~할지 말지","ex":"I can't decide whether to stay."},{"w":"if (주어 자리 불가)","ko":"주어절엔 못 씀","ex":"Whether he comes matters."},{"w":"whether (전치사 뒤)","ko":"전치사 뒤엔 whether","ex":"It depends on whether we have time."},{"w":"if (조건절 혼동 주의)","ko":"'만약' vs '~인지'","ex":"Ask if he is coming."},{"w":"whether (선택)","ko":"둘 중 하나를 물을 때","ex":"I asked whether he wanted tea or coffee."},{"w":"if (미래 will 가능)","ko":"if 명사절 안엔 will 가능","ex":"I don't know if I will pass."}]},{"label":"that절을 취하는 동사","note":"'**~라고/~라는 것을**'을 뜻하는 that 명사절을 목적어로 받는 동사다. ==구어에서 that은 자주 생략==되고, 안쪽은 평서문 그대로 쓴다.","items":[{"w":"think","ko":"생각하다","ex":"I think he's right."},{"w":"believe","ko":"믿다","ex":"I believe he'll come."},{"w":"say","ko":"말하다","ex":"She said she was busy."},{"w":"hope","ko":"바라다","ex":"I hope you feel better."},{"w":"know","ko":"알다","ex":"I know that it works."},{"w":"notice","ko":"알아채다","ex":"I noticed that it changed."},{"w":"mean","ko":"의미하다","ex":"It means that we're late."},{"w":"agree","ko":"동의하다","ex":"We agreed that it was fair."},{"w":"suppose","ko":"추측하다","ex":"I suppose you're tired."},{"w":"realize","ko":"깨닫다","ex":"I realize that I was wrong."},{"w":"admit","ko":"인정하다","ex":"He admitted that he lied."},{"w":"feel","ko":"느끼다","ex":"I feel that it's unfair."},{"w":"hear","ko":"듣다","ex":"I heard that they moved."},{"w":"promise","ko":"약속하다","ex":"She promised she would help."},{"w":"decide","ko":"결정하다","ex":"We decided that we'd wait."},{"w":"doubt","ko":"의심하다","ex":"I doubt that it's true."},{"w":"remember","ko":"기억하다","ex":"I remember that it rained."},{"w":"argue","ko":"주장하다","ex":"He argued that it was unfair."},{"w":"explain","ko":"설명하다","ex":"She explained that she was busy."},{"w":"assume","ko":"가정하다","ex":"I assume that you're ready."}]},{"label":"의문사 + to부정사 패턴","note":"'의문사 + 주어 + should + 동사'를 ==짧게 압축==한 형태다. **why만 이 패턴에 안 쓴다**는 점을 기억한다.","items":[{"w":"what to do","ko":"무엇을 할지","ex":"I don't know what to do."},{"w":"where to go","ko":"어디로 갈지","ex":"Tell me where to go."},{"w":"when to start","ko":"언제 시작할지","ex":"Decide when to start."},{"w":"how to use","ko":"어떻게 쓸지","ex":"Show me how to use it."},{"w":"who(m) to ask","ko":"누구에게 물을지","ex":"I'm not sure who to ask."},{"w":"which to choose","ko":"어느 것을 고를지","ex":"I can't decide which to choose."},{"w":"whether to stay","ko":"머무를지 말지","ex":"We debated whether to stay."},{"w":"how much to bring","ko":"얼마나 가져올지","ex":"Ask how much to bring."}]}]}},{"n":3,"title":"관계절","status":"detailed","summary":"명사(선행사)를 뒤에서 꾸미는 절을 관계절이라 한다. **관계사(who·which·that·whose·where·when 등)가 선행사에 붙어 뒤에서 수식**하며, ==관계사는 관계절 안에서 빠진 성분(주어·목적어·소유격·부사)을 대신==한다. 사람은 who, 사물은 which, 소유는 whose를 쓰고, 목적격 관계사와 「관계사+be」는 자주 생략·축약된다.","subtopics":[{"key":"subject-rel","title":"주격 관계대명사 (who/which/that + 동사 수일치)","points":["관계절 안에서 **주어가 빠졌을 때** 쓰는 관계사다. 사람은 **who**, 사물은 **which**, 둘 다 **that**을 쓴다.","「선행사 + 관계사 + **동사**」 순서로, ==관계사 바로 뒤에 동사가 온다==(관계사가 곧 그 절의 주어이기 때문이다).","관계절의 동사는 ==선행사의 인칭·수에 맞춰 수일치==한다. 선행사가 단수면 단수 동사, 복수면 복수 동사다.","**that**은 사람·사물 모두에 쓸 수 있어 who/which 자리를 대신할 수 있다."],"examples":[{"en":"The student who sits next to me is from Canada.","ko":"내 옆에 앉는 학생은 캐나다 출신이다.","parts":[{"t":"The student","role":"S"},{"t":"who","role":"RP"},{"t":"sits","role":"V"},{"t":"next to me","role":"M"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"from Canada.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I have a friend who speaks four languages.","ko":"나에게는 4개 언어를 하는 친구가 있다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"V"},{"t":"a friend","role":"O"},{"t":"who","role":"RP"},{"t":"speaks","role":"V"},{"t":"four languages.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The book which won the award is on the table.","ko":"그 상을 받은 책이 탁자 위에 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The book","role":"S"},{"t":"which","role":"RP"},{"t":"won","role":"V"},{"t":"the award","role":"O"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"on the table.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"A car that runs on electricity saves money.","ko":"전기로 달리는 차는 돈을 절약해 준다.","parts":[{"t":"A car","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"RP"},{"t":"runs","role":"V"},{"t":"on electricity","role":"M"},{"t":"saves","role":"V"},{"t":"money.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The people who work here are very kind.","ko":"여기서 일하는 사람들은 매우 친절하다.","parts":[{"t":"The people","role":"S"},{"t":"who","role":"RP"},{"t":"work","role":"V"},{"t":"here","role":"M"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"very kind.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"This is the app that helps students study.","ko":"이것은 학생들이 공부하도록 돕는 앱이다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the app","role":"SC"},{"t":"that","role":"RP"},{"t":"helps","role":"V"},{"t":"students","role":"O"},{"t":"study.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"The machine that makes coffee is broken.","ko":"커피를 만드는 기계가 고장 났다.","parts":[{"t":"The machine","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"RP"},{"t":"makes","role":"V"},{"t":"coffee","role":"O"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"broken.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"Scientists who study the ocean discovered a new species.","ko":"바다를 연구하는 과학자들이 새로운 종을 발견했다.","parts":[{"t":"Scientists","role":"S"},{"t":"who","role":"RP"},{"t":"study","role":"V"},{"t":"the ocean","role":"O"},{"t":"discovered","role":"V"},{"t":"a new species.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The train that leaves at noon is always crowded.","ko":"정오에 떠나는 기차는 늘 붐빈다.","parts":[{"t":"The train","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"RP"},{"t":"leaves","role":"V"},{"t":"at noon","role":"M"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"always crowded.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["The student who sit next to me","The student who sits next to me (선행사 **student**가 3인칭 단수라 관계절 동사도 **sits**로 수일치한다)"],["the man which called me","the man who called me (**사람 선행사**는 which가 아니라 who/that을 쓴다)"],["the book who won the award","the book which won the award (**사물 선행사**는 who가 아니라 which/that을 쓴다)"]]},{"key":"object-rel","title":"목적격 관계대명사 + 생략 (the book (that) I read)","points":["관계절 안에서 **목적어가 빠졌을 때** 쓰는 관계사다. 사람은 **whom/who/that**, 사물은 **which/that**이다.","「선행사 + 관계사 + **주어 + 동사**」 순서로, ==관계사 뒤에 새로운 주어가 온다==.","목적격 관계대명사는 ==대개 생략할 수 있다==(the book (that) I read). 이를 접촉절이라 한다.","관계사가 이미 목적어 역할을 하므로 **관계절 안에 목적어(it·her 등)를 또 쓰면 안 된다**."],"examples":[{"en":"The movie that I watched last night was boring.","ko":"내가 어젯밤에 본 영화는 지루했다.","parts":[{"t":"The movie","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"RP"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"watched","role":"V"},{"t":"last night","role":"M"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"boring.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The book I read last month was fascinating.","ko":"내가 지난달에 읽은 책은 매우 흥미로웠다.","parts":[{"t":"The book","role":"S"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"read","role":"V"},{"t":"last month","role":"M"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"fascinating.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The woman whom I met is a doctor.","ko":"내가 만난 여자는 의사다.","parts":[{"t":"The woman","role":"S"},{"t":"whom","role":"RP"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"met","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"a doctor.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The song that she sang moved everyone.","ko":"그녀가 부른 노래는 모두를 감동시켰다.","parts":[{"t":"The song","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"RP"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"sang","role":"V"},{"t":"moved","role":"V"},{"t":"everyone.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The people I invited didn't come.","ko":"내가 초대한 사람들은 오지 않았다.","parts":[{"t":"The people","role":"S"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"invited","role":"V"},{"t":"didn't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"come.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"This is the phone that I bought yesterday.","ko":"이것은 내가 어제 산 휴대폰이다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the phone","role":"SC"},{"t":"that","role":"RP"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"bought","role":"V"},{"t":"yesterday.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The restaurant we chose was fully booked.","ko":"우리가 고른 식당은 예약이 꽉 차 있었다.","parts":[{"t":"The restaurant","role":"S"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"chose","role":"V"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"fully booked.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The teacher whom we respect is retiring.","ko":"우리가 존경하는 선생님이 은퇴하신다.","parts":[{"t":"The teacher","role":"S"},{"t":"whom","role":"RP"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"respect","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"retiring.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The gift that he gave me was expensive.","ko":"그가 나에게 준 선물은 비쌌다.","parts":[{"t":"The gift","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"RP"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"gave","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"expensive.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["The book that I read it was good.","The book that I read was good. (**관계사가 이미 목적어**라 뒤에 it을 또 쓰면 안 된다)"],["The person which I called was busy.","The person whom I called was busy. (**사람 목적격**은 which가 아니라 whom/who/that이다)"],["The song what she sang moved everyone.","The song that she sang moved everyone. (**선행사가 있으면** what을 못 쓰고 that/which를 쓴다)"]]},{"key":"whose-possessive","title":"소유격 관계대명사 whose (the boy whose father …)","points":["선행사와 **뒤 명사의 소유 관계**('~의')를 연결할 때 **whose**를 쓴다. 사람·사물 모두 가능하다.","「선행사 + **whose + 명사** + 동사」 구조로, ==whose 뒤에는 반드시 명사가 붙는다==.","**whose**는 그 자체가 소유격이라, ==뒤에 his·her·its 같은 소유격을 또 쓰지 않는다==.","소유격 **whose**와 who is의 축약형 **who's**를 혼동하지 않는다."],"examples":[{"en":"I know a boy whose father is a pilot.","ko":"나는 아버지가 조종사인 소년을 안다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"a boy","role":"O"},{"t":"whose","role":"RP"},{"t":"father","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"a pilot.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The house whose roof is red belongs to us.","ko":"지붕이 빨간 그 집은 우리 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"The house","role":"S"},{"t":"whose","role":"RP"},{"t":"roof","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"red","role":"SC"},{"t":"belongs","role":"V"},{"t":"to us.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She is the author whose book became famous.","ko":"그녀는 책이 유명해진 작가다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the author","role":"SC"},{"t":"whose","role":"RP"},{"t":"book","role":"S"},{"t":"became","role":"V"},{"t":"famous.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I met a girl whose brother plays soccer.","ko":"나는 남동생이 축구를 하는 소녀를 만났다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"met","role":"V"},{"t":"a girl","role":"O"},{"t":"whose","role":"RP"},{"t":"brother","role":"S"},{"t":"plays","role":"V"},{"t":"soccer.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"We visited a town whose streets were very narrow.","ko":"우리는 거리가 매우 좁은 마을을 방문했다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"visited","role":"V"},{"t":"a town","role":"O"},{"t":"whose","role":"RP"},{"t":"streets","role":"S"},{"t":"were","role":"V"},{"t":"very narrow.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The company whose products I use is local.","ko":"내가 그 제품을 쓰는 회사는 지역 회사다.","parts":[{"t":"The company","role":"S"},{"t":"whose","role":"RP"},{"t":"products","role":"O"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"use","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"local.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"He is a writer whose stories inspire many.","ko":"그는 이야기가 많은 이들에게 영감을 주는 작가다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"a writer","role":"SC"},{"t":"whose","role":"RP"},{"t":"stories","role":"S"},{"t":"inspire","role":"V"},{"t":"many.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The student whose essay won is my friend.","ko":"에세이가 상을 받은 학생은 내 친구다.","parts":[{"t":"The student","role":"S"},{"t":"whose","role":"RP"},{"t":"essay","role":"S"},{"t":"won","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"my friend.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["the boy who's father is a pilot","the boy whose father is a pilot (**소유격 관계사**는 whose이고, who's는 who is의 축약이다)"],["the house which roof is red","the house whose roof is red (뒤 명사와의 **소유 관계**는 which가 아니라 whose로 잇는다)"],["a girl whose her brother plays soccer","a girl whose brother plays soccer (**whose가 이미 소유격**이라 her를 또 쓰지 않는다)"]]},{"key":"rel-adv-where","title":"관계부사 where (장소)","points":["**장소**를 나타내는 선행사(place·house·city·room 등) 뒤에서 '~하는 곳'을 이을 때 **where**를 쓴다.","관계부사 where는 ==「전치사 + which」(in/at which)와 같아== 뒤에 **완전한 절**(주어·동사·목적어가 다 있는 절)이 온다.","where 안에 이미 '~에서'의 뜻이 들어 있어 ==끝에 전치사(in·at)를 또 쓰지 않는다==.","뒤 절에 성분이 하나 빠져 있으면 where가 아니라 관계대명사(which/that)를 써야 한다."],"examples":[{"en":"This is the house where I grew up.","ko":"이곳은 내가 자란 집이다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the house","role":"SC"},{"t":"where","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"grew up.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The city where she lives is very cold.","ko":"그녀가 사는 도시는 매우 춥다.","parts":[{"t":"The city","role":"S"},{"t":"where","role":"Conj"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"lives","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"very cold.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The cafe where we first met has closed.","ko":"우리가 처음 만난 카페는 문을 닫았다.","parts":[{"t":"The cafe","role":"S"},{"t":"where","role":"Conj"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"first","role":"M"},{"t":"met","role":"V"},{"t":"has","role":"Aux"},{"t":"closed.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"This is the restaurant where they serve great pasta.","ko":"이곳은 훌륭한 파스타를 내는 식당이다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the restaurant","role":"SC"},{"t":"where","role":"Conj"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"serve","role":"V"},{"t":"great pasta.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The room where we study is quiet.","ko":"우리가 공부하는 방은 조용하다.","parts":[{"t":"The room","role":"S"},{"t":"where","role":"Conj"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"study","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"quiet.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"She works at a hospital where many babies are born.","ko":"그녀는 많은 아기가 태어나는 병원에서 일한다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"works","role":"V"},{"t":"at a hospital","role":"M"},{"t":"where","role":"Conj"},{"t":"many babies","role":"S"},{"t":"are born.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The park where children play is nearby.","ko":"아이들이 노는 공원은 근처에 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The park","role":"S"},{"t":"where","role":"Conj"},{"t":"children","role":"S"},{"t":"play","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"nearby.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I visited the town where my grandmother was born.","ko":"나는 할머니가 태어난 마을을 방문했다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"visited","role":"V"},{"t":"the town","role":"O"},{"t":"where","role":"Conj"},{"t":"my grandmother","role":"S"},{"t":"was born.","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["the city which she lives","the city where she lives (뒤 절이 **완전하고 '~에서'의 뜻**이면 관계부사 where를 쓴다)"],["the house where I grew up in","the house where I grew up (**where에 전치사 in의 의미가 포함**돼 in을 또 쓰지 않는다)"],["the restaurant where serves great pasta","the restaurant where they serve great pasta (**where 뒤에는 완전한 절**이 오므로 주어 they가 필요하다)"]]},{"key":"rel-adv-when","title":"관계부사 when (시간)","points":["**시간**을 나타내는 선행사(day·time·year·moment·season 등) 뒤에서 '~하는 때'를 이을 때 **when**을 쓴다.","관계부사 when은 ==「전치사 + which」(on/in/at which)와 같아== 뒤에 **완전한 절**이 온다.","when 안에 '~에'의 뜻이 들어 있어 ==끝에 전치사(on·in)를 또 쓰지 않는다==.","시간 선행사에는 where가 아니라 **when**을 쓴다(장소·시간 혼동 주의)."],"examples":[{"en":"I remember the day when we first met.","ko":"나는 우리가 처음 만난 날을 기억한다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"remember","role":"V"},{"t":"the day","role":"O"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"first","role":"M"},{"t":"met.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Summer is the season when I feel happiest.","ko":"여름은 내가 가장 행복한 계절이다.","parts":[{"t":"Summer","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the season","role":"SC"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"feel","role":"V"},{"t":"happiest.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"There was a time when phones didn't exist.","ko":"전화기가 없던 시절이 있었다.","parts":[{"t":"There","role":"M"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"a time","role":"S"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"phones","role":"S"},{"t":"didn't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"exist.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Monday is the day when the class begins.","ko":"월요일은 수업이 시작되는 날이다.","parts":[{"t":"Monday","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the day","role":"SC"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the class","role":"S"},{"t":"begins.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"I remember the moment when I passed the exam.","ko":"나는 시험에 합격한 순간을 기억한다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"remember","role":"V"},{"t":"the moment","role":"O"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"passed","role":"V"},{"t":"the exam.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"1990 was the year when my parents married.","ko":"1990년은 부모님이 결혼한 해였다.","parts":[{"t":"1990","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"the year","role":"SC"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"my parents","role":"S"},{"t":"married.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Winter is the time when bears sleep.","ko":"겨울은 곰이 잠을 자는 시기다.","parts":[{"t":"Winter","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the time","role":"SC"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"bears","role":"S"},{"t":"sleep.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Do you know the day when the store opens?","ko":"그 가게가 문을 여는 날을 아는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"the day","role":"O"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the store","role":"S"},{"t":"opens?","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["the day which we first met","the day when we first met (**시간 선행사 + 완전한 절**이면 관계부사 when을 쓴다)"],["the year where I was born","the year when I was born (**시간**에는 where가 아니라 when을 쓴다)"],["the day when the store opens on","the day when the store opens (**when이 전치사 on의 의미를 포함**해 on을 또 쓰지 않는다)"]]},{"key":"rel-adv-why-how","title":"관계부사 why · how (the reason why / the way)","points":["**이유**를 나타내는 선행사 the reason 뒤에는 **why**를 쓴다(= for which). '~한 이유'의 뜻이다.","**방법**은 **how**로 나타내되, ==the way와 how는 함께 쓰지 못한다==. the way, the way that, how 중 하나만 쓴다.","why·how 뒤에는 **완전한 절**이 오며, 뒤에 because·so 같은 접속사를 또 쓰지 않는다.","이유에는 why, 방법에는 how로 서로 구분해 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"That is the reason why I was late.","ko":"그것이 내가 늦은 이유다.","parts":[{"t":"That","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the reason","role":"SC"},{"t":"why","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"late.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"Nobody knows the reason why he left.","ko":"아무도 그가 떠난 이유를 모른다.","parts":[{"t":"Nobody","role":"S"},{"t":"knows","role":"V"},{"t":"the reason","role":"O"},{"t":"why","role":"Conj"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"left.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"This is how the machine works.","ko":"이것이 그 기계가 작동하는 방식이다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"how","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the machine","role":"S"},{"t":"works.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"I don't understand the way she solved it.","ko":"나는 그녀가 그것을 푼 방식을 이해하지 못한다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"understand","role":"V"},{"t":"the way","role":"O"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"solved","role":"V"},{"t":"it.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Tell me the reason why you are upset.","ko":"네가 화난 이유를 말해 달라.","parts":[{"t":"Tell","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"the reason","role":"DO"},{"t":"why","role":"Conj"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"upset.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"That is the way he talks to everyone.","ko":"그것이 그가 모두에게 말하는 방식이다.","parts":[{"t":"That","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the way","role":"SC"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"talks","role":"V"},{"t":"to everyone.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Do you know the reason why prices went up?","ko":"물가가 오른 이유를 아는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"the reason","role":"O"},{"t":"why","role":"Conj"},{"t":"prices","role":"S"},{"t":"went up?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"This is how I learned English.","ko":"이것이 내가 영어를 배운 방법이다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"how","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"learned","role":"V"},{"t":"English.","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["the reason because I was late","the reason why I was late (**이유 선행사 뒤 관계부사**는 why이고, because는 접속사다)"],["the way how she solved it","the way she solved it / how she solved it (**the way와 how는 함께** 쓰지 않는다)"],["the reason how he left","the reason why he left (**이유에는 why**, 방법에는 how로 구분한다)"]]},{"key":"non-restrictive","title":"계속적 용법 (콤마 , which / , who)","points":["선행사 뒤에 **콤마(,)**를 찍고 관계사를 이으면 **부가 설명**을 덧붙이는 계속적 용법이다.","계속적 용법에는 ==that을 쓸 수 없고== who·which만 쓴다. **생략도 불가**하다.","**, which**는 앞의 명사뿐 아니라 ==앞 문장 전체를 받을 수도 있다==(He was late, which annoyed us).","콤마가 없는 한정적 용법은 선행사의 범위를 좁히지만, 콤마가 있는 계속적 용법은 단지 정보를 더한다."],"examples":[{"en":"My brother, who lives in Seoul, called me today.","ko":"서울에 사는 내 형이 오늘 나에게 전화했다.","parts":[{"t":"My brother,","role":"S"},{"t":"who","role":"RP"},{"t":"lives","role":"V"},{"t":"in Seoul,","role":"M"},{"t":"called","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"today.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She passed the exam, which made her parents proud.","ko":"그녀는 시험에 합격했고, 그것이 부모님을 자랑스럽게 했다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"passed","role":"V"},{"t":"the exam,","role":"O"},{"t":"which","role":"RP"},{"t":"made","role":"V"},{"t":"her parents","role":"O"},{"t":"proud.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"This laptop, which I bought last year, still works well.","ko":"작년에 산 이 노트북은 아직도 잘 작동한다.","parts":[{"t":"This laptop,","role":"S"},{"t":"which","role":"RP"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"bought","role":"V"},{"t":"last year,","role":"M"},{"t":"still","role":"M"},{"t":"works","role":"V"},{"t":"well.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Mr. Kim, who teaches math, is very popular.","ko":"수학을 가르치는 김 선생님은 매우 인기가 많다.","parts":[{"t":"Mr. Kim,","role":"S"},{"t":"who","role":"RP"},{"t":"teaches","role":"V"},{"t":"math,","role":"O"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"very popular.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"We visited Paris, which is famous for its museums.","ko":"우리는 박물관으로 유명한 파리를 방문했다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"visited","role":"V"},{"t":"Paris,","role":"O"},{"t":"which","role":"RP"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"famous","role":"SC"},{"t":"for its museums.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He was late again, which annoyed his boss.","ko":"그는 또 늦었고, 그것이 상사를 짜증나게 했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"late","role":"SC"},{"t":"again,","role":"M"},{"t":"which","role":"RP"},{"t":"annoyed","role":"V"},{"t":"his boss.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"My sister, who is a nurse, works at night.","ko":"간호사인 내 여동생은 밤에 일한다.","parts":[{"t":"My sister,","role":"S"},{"t":"who","role":"RP"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"a nurse,","role":"SC"},{"t":"works","role":"V"},{"t":"at night.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The concert, which lasted three hours, was amazing.","ko":"세 시간 동안 이어진 그 콘서트는 놀라웠다.","parts":[{"t":"The concert,","role":"S"},{"t":"which","role":"RP"},{"t":"lasted","role":"V"},{"t":"three hours,","role":"O"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"amazing.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["My brother, that lives in Seoul, called me.","My brother, who lives in Seoul, called me. (**콤마 계속적 용법**에는 that을 쓸 수 없다)"],["She passed the exam, that made her proud.","She passed the exam, which made her proud. (**앞 문장 전체**를 받는 계속적 용법은 which이고 that은 안 된다)"],["He was late, what annoyed his boss.","He was late, which annoyed his boss. (문장 전체를 받을 때는 **what이 아니라 which**를 쓴다)"]]},{"key":"prep-relative","title":"전치사 + 관계대명사 (the house in which / the man to whom)","points":["관계절 안의 전치사를 **관계사 앞으로 보내** 「전치사 + which/whom」 형태로 쓸 수 있다(격식체).","전치사 바로 뒤에는 ==사물은 which, 사람은 whom==을 쓴다. **전치사 뒤에 that·who는 쓰지 못한다**.","전치사를 앞으로 보냈으면 ==관계절 끝에 그 전치사를 또 쓰지 않는다== (in which … 뒤에 in 반복 금지).","구어에서는 전치사를 원래 자리에 두고 관계사를 생략하기도 한다(the man I spoke to)."],"examples":[{"en":"The house in which they live is old.","ko":"그들이 사는 집은 오래됐다.","parts":[{"t":"The house","role":"S"},{"t":"in which","role":"Conj"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"live","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"old.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The man to whom I spoke was helpful.","ko":"내가 이야기를 나눈 남자는 도움이 되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The man","role":"S"},{"t":"to whom","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"spoke","role":"V"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"helpful.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"This is the tool with which I fixed the car.","ko":"이것이 내가 차를 고친 도구다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the tool","role":"SC"},{"t":"with which","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"fixed","role":"V"},{"t":"the car.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The company for which she works is huge.","ko":"그녀가 일하는 회사는 매우 크다.","parts":[{"t":"The company","role":"S"},{"t":"for which","role":"Conj"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"works","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"huge.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The chair on which I sat broke.","ko":"내가 앉았던 의자가 부서졌다.","parts":[{"t":"The chair","role":"S"},{"t":"on which","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"sat","role":"V"},{"t":"broke.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The friend with whom I traveled is fun.","ko":"나와 함께 여행한 친구는 재미있다.","parts":[{"t":"The friend","role":"S"},{"t":"with whom","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"traveled","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"fun.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The topic about which we argued is complex.","ko":"우리가 논쟁한 주제는 복잡하다.","parts":[{"t":"The topic","role":"S"},{"t":"about which","role":"Conj"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"argued","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"complex.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The box in which I kept the letters is gone.","ko":"내가 편지를 보관하던 상자가 사라졌다.","parts":[{"t":"The box","role":"S"},{"t":"in which","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"kept","role":"V"},{"t":"the letters","role":"O"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"gone.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["The man to who I spoke was helpful.","The man to whom I spoke was helpful. (**전치사 바로 뒤 사람 관계사**는 who가 아니라 whom이다)"],["The house in that they live is old.","The house in which they live is old. (**전치사 뒤에는 that을 쓸 수 없고** which를 쓴다)"],["The company for which she works for is huge.","The company for which she works is huge. (**전치사를 앞으로 보냈으면** 끝에 for를 또 쓰지 않는다)"]]},{"key":"reduced-present","title":"축약 관계절 - 현재분사 (the man standing there)","points":["「주격 관계사 + be동사」 뒤가 **진행(V-ing)이거나 능동**이면 ==관계사와 be를 지우고 현재분사(V-ing)만 남긴다==.","the man **who is** standing → the man **standing**처럼 who is/which is를 통째로 생략한다.","일반동사의 능동 관계절도 현재분사로 줄일 수 있다(people who live here → people **living** here).","축약형은 본동사가 아니라 **분사(형용사구)**이므로, live·wear 같은 원형·과거형을 그대로 쓰면 안 된다."],"examples":[{"en":"The man standing there is my uncle.","ko":"저기 서 있는 남자는 내 삼촌이다.","parts":[{"t":"The man","role":"S"},{"t":"standing there","role":"M"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"my uncle.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The girl wearing a red hat is my sister.","ko":"빨간 모자를 쓴 소녀는 내 여동생이다.","parts":[{"t":"The girl","role":"S"},{"t":"wearing a red hat","role":"M"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"my sister.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I know the people living next door.","ko":"나는 옆집에 사는 사람들을 안다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"the people","role":"O"},{"t":"living next door.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The students taking the exam looked nervous.","ko":"시험을 치르는 학생들은 긴장해 보였다.","parts":[{"t":"The students","role":"S"},{"t":"taking the exam","role":"M"},{"t":"looked","role":"V"},{"t":"nervous.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The dog barking loudly belongs to my neighbor.","ko":"시끄럽게 짖는 개는 내 이웃의 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"The dog","role":"S"},{"t":"barking loudly","role":"M"},{"t":"belongs","role":"V"},{"t":"to my neighbor.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The bus leaving now goes downtown.","ko":"지금 떠나는 버스는 시내로 간다.","parts":[{"t":"The bus","role":"S"},{"t":"leaving now","role":"M"},{"t":"goes","role":"V"},{"t":"downtown.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Look at the birds flying over the lake.","ko":"호수 위를 나는 새들을 봐라.","parts":[{"t":"Look at","role":"V"},{"t":"the birds","role":"O"},{"t":"flying over the lake.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The woman talking on the phone is my boss.","ko":"전화 통화 중인 여자는 내 상사다.","parts":[{"t":"The woman","role":"S"},{"t":"talking on the phone","role":"M"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"my boss.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["The man who standing there is my uncle.","The man standing there is my uncle. (관계사를 남기려면 **who is**를 함께 써야 하고, 축약하면 who is를 통째로 지운다)"],["The people live next door are nice.","The people living next door are nice. (**능동 축약은 현재분사 living**이고, 본동사 원형 live는 안 된다)"],["The girl wore a red hat is my sister.","The girl wearing a red hat is my sister. (수식은 **현재분사 wearing**으로, 과거형 wore는 본동사라 안 된다)"]]},{"key":"reduced-past","title":"축약 관계절 - 과거분사 (the report written yesterday)","points":["「주격 관계사 + be동사」 뒤가 **수동(p.p.)**이면 ==관계사와 be를 지우고 과거분사(p.p.)만 남긴다==.","the report **which was** written → the report **written**처럼 관계사와 be를 통째로 생략한다.","==능동이면 현재분사(V-ing), 수동이면 과거분사(p.p.)==로 갈린다(the man **making** vs the cake **made**).","과거분사는 수동의 뜻이므로, wrote·broke 같은 **과거형(능동)**을 그대로 쓰면 안 된다."],"examples":[{"en":"The report written yesterday is on your desk.","ko":"어제 작성된 보고서가 네 책상 위에 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The report","role":"S"},{"t":"written yesterday","role":"M"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"on your desk.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The car parked outside is mine.","ko":"밖에 주차된 차는 내 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"The car","role":"S"},{"t":"parked outside","role":"M"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"mine.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I found the keys hidden under the mat.","ko":"나는 매트 아래 숨겨진 열쇠를 찾았다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"found","role":"V"},{"t":"the keys","role":"O"},{"t":"hidden under the mat.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The book written by her sold millions.","ko":"그녀가 쓴 책은 수백만 권 팔렸다.","parts":[{"t":"The book","role":"S"},{"t":"written by her","role":"M"},{"t":"sold","role":"V"},{"t":"millions.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The bridge built in 1930 is still strong.","ko":"1930년에 지어진 다리는 아직도 튼튼하다.","parts":[{"t":"The bridge","role":"S"},{"t":"built in 1930","role":"M"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"still strong.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The email sent this morning was urgent.","ko":"오늘 아침에 보내진 이메일은 긴급했다.","parts":[{"t":"The email","role":"S"},{"t":"sent this morning","role":"M"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"urgent.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"We ate the food cooked by my grandmother.","ko":"우리는 할머니가 요리한 음식을 먹었다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"ate","role":"V"},{"t":"the food","role":"O"},{"t":"cooked by my grandmother.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The windows broken in the storm were replaced.","ko":"폭풍에 깨진 창문들은 교체되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The windows","role":"S"},{"t":"broken in the storm","role":"M"},{"t":"were","role":"V"},{"t":"replaced.","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["The report writing yesterday is on your desk.","The report written yesterday is on your desk. (**수동 축약은 과거분사 written**이고, 현재분사 writing은 능동이다)"],["The book wrote by her sold millions.","The book written by her sold millions. (수동 축약은 **과거분사 written**이며 과거형 wrote가 아니다)"],["The email was sent this morning was urgent.","The email sent this morning was urgent. (**축약하면 be동사 was를 지워야** 하고, 남기면 동사가 둘이 된다)"]]},{"key":"that-vs-which-quant","title":"that vs which 선택 + 수량표현 (some of which / both of whom)","points":["콤마 없는 **한정적 용법**은 that·which 둘 다 되지만, ==콤마가 있는 계속적 용법은 which만== 쓴다(that 불가).","**최상급·서수·the only·all·every·no** 뒤에서는 관습적으로 **that**을 선호한다.","「수량표현 + of + which/whom」으로 계속적 용법을 이을 수 있다: **some of which**, **both of whom**, **most of which** 등.","이때 사물은 **of which**, 사람은 **of whom**을 쓰며, ==them·some 같은 대명사로 두 절을 콤마만으로 잇지 않는다==."],"examples":[{"en":"This is the best movie that I have ever seen.","ko":"이것은 내가 본 최고의 영화다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the best movie","role":"SC"},{"t":"that","role":"RP"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"ever","role":"M"},{"t":"seen.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"She has two brothers, both of whom are doctors.","ko":"그녀에게는 형제가 둘 있는데, 둘 다 의사다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"has","role":"V"},{"t":"two brothers,","role":"O"},{"t":"both of whom","role":"Conj"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"doctors.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"He gave me some books, some of which were rare.","ko":"그는 나에게 책 몇 권을 줬는데, 그중 일부는 희귀했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"gave","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"some books,","role":"DO"},{"t":"some of which","role":"Conj"},{"t":"were","role":"V"},{"t":"rare.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"Everything that glitters is not gold.","ko":"반짝인다고 다 금은 아니다.","parts":[{"t":"Everything","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"RP"},{"t":"glitters","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"not gold.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The only thing that matters is your health.","ko":"중요한 유일한 것은 네 건강이다.","parts":[{"t":"The only thing","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"RP"},{"t":"matters","role":"V"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"your health.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I have many friends, most of whom live abroad.","ko":"나에게는 친구가 많은데, 대부분은 외국에 산다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"V"},{"t":"many friends,","role":"O"},{"t":"most of whom","role":"Conj"},{"t":"live","role":"V"},{"t":"abroad.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The house, which was built in 1920, is for sale.","ko":"1920년에 지어진 그 집은 매물로 나와 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The house,","role":"S"},{"t":"which","role":"RP"},{"t":"was built","role":"V"},{"t":"in 1920,","role":"M"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"for sale.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He read three books, one of which was in French.","ko":"그는 책 세 권을 읽었는데, 그중 한 권은 프랑스어였다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"read","role":"V"},{"t":"three books,","role":"O"},{"t":"one of which","role":"Conj"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"in French.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This is the first song that she wrote.","ko":"이것은 그녀가 쓴 첫 번째 곡이다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the first song","role":"SC"},{"t":"that","role":"RP"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"wrote.","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["She has two brothers, both of them are doctors.","She has two brothers, both of whom are doctors. (두 절을 관계절로 이으려면 them이 아니라 **of whom**을 쓴다)"],["He gave me some books, some of them were rare.","He gave me some books, some of which were rare. (사물을 관계절로 이을 때는 them이 아니라 **of which**를 쓴다)"],["The house that was built in 1920, is for sale.","The house, which was built in 1920, is for sale. (**콤마 계속적 용법**에는 that을 못 쓰고 which를 쓴다)"]]}],"db":{"title":"관계절 DB · 관계사 선택 & 축약","intro":"관계절의 핵심은 ==선행사가 사람인가 사물인가, 관계절 안에서 어떤 성분(주어·목적어·소유격·부사)이 빠졌는가==를 보고 **관계사를 고르는 것**이다. 목적격 관계사와 「관계사+be」는 자주 <b>생략·축약</b>된다. 아래 5개 그룹으로 관계대명사·관계부사·축약·계속적 용법·전치사 결합을 한눈에 정리했다.","groups":[{"label":"선행사별 관계사 선택표","note":"선행사가 **사람**이면 who 계열, **사물**이면 which를 쓰고, ==that은 사람·사물 모두== 가능하다. 관계절 안에서 빠진 자리가 주어면 주격, 목적어면 목적격, 소유면 whose다.","items":[{"w":"who (주격)","ko":"사람 주격 — 관계절의 주어가 빠짐","ex":"the man who called me"},{"w":"whom (목적격)","ko":"사람 목적격 (격식) — 목적어가 빠짐","ex":"the man whom I met"},{"w":"who (목적격)","ko":"사람 목적격 (구어) — whom 대신","ex":"the man who I met"},{"w":"which (주격)","ko":"사물 주격 — 주어가 빠짐","ex":"the book which sells well"},{"w":"which (목적격)","ko":"사물 목적격 — 목적어가 빠짐","ex":"the book which I read"},{"w":"that (사람)","ko":"사람 주격·목적격 — who/whom 대신","ex":"the man that called"},{"w":"that (사물)","ko":"사물 주격·목적격 — which 대신","ex":"the book that sells well"},{"w":"whose","ko":"소유격 (사람·사물) — 뒤에 명사","ex":"the boy whose father is a pilot"},{"w":"whose (사물)","ko":"사물의 소유 — of which 대신 자주 씀","ex":"the house whose roof is red"},{"w":"생략 (목적격)","ko":"목적격 관계사는 생략 가능 (접촉절)","ex":"the book (that) I read"},{"w":"who + 단수동사","ko":"선행사 단수 → 관계절 동사 단수","ex":"the student who sits here"},{"w":"who + 복수동사","ko":"선행사 복수 → 관계절 동사 복수","ex":"the students who sit here"},{"w":"that (사람+사물)","ko":"사람과 사물이 함께인 선행사","ex":"the boy and his dog that ran off"},{"w":"what","ko":"선행사를 포함(=the thing which) — 앞에 명사 없음","ex":"what I need is time"},{"w":"that (강한 선호)","ko":"최상급·서수·the only·all·every 뒤","ex":"the best that I know"},{"w":"who (보어)","ko":"사람 보어 자리 — 드물게 whom","ex":"the man who I thought he was"},{"w":"which (수량+of)","ko":"사물 + of which 결합","ex":"books, three of which are new"}]},{"label":"관계부사 & 전치사+관계대명사 대응표","note":"관계부사 뒤에는 ==빠진 성분이 없는 완전한 절==이 온다. 각 관계부사는 「전치사 + which」로 바꿔 쓸 수 있으며, ==관계부사 안에 이미 전치사 뜻이 들어 있어== 끝에 전치사를 또 쓰지 않는다.","items":[{"w":"where","ko":"장소 (= in/at which)","ex":"the place where I live"},{"w":"when","ko":"시간 (= on/in/at which)","ex":"the day when we met"},{"w":"why","ko":"이유 (= for which)","ex":"the reason why he left"},{"w":"how","ko":"방법 (= the way in which)","ex":"how it works"},{"w":"the way","ko":"방법 — how와 함께 못 씀","ex":"the way she smiles"},{"w":"the way that","ko":"방법 — how 대체 표현","ex":"the way that it happened"},{"w":"in which","ko":"장소 where 대체 (격식)","ex":"the house in which I live"},{"w":"at which","ko":"지점·장소 where 대체","ex":"the point at which it broke"},{"w":"on which","ko":"날짜·요일 when 대체","ex":"the day on which we met"},{"w":"in which (시간)","ko":"연도·월 when 대체","ex":"the year in which I was born"},{"w":"for which","ko":"이유 why 대체","ex":"the reason for which he left"},{"w":"to whom","ko":"사람 + 전치사 to","ex":"the man to whom I spoke"},{"w":"with which","ko":"사물 + 전치사 with (도구)","ex":"the pen with which I write"},{"w":"완전한 절","ko":"관계부사 뒤 — 성분이 다 있음","ex":"where + S + V + O"},{"w":"불완전한 절","ko":"관계대명사 뒤 — 성분 하나 빠짐","ex":"which + S + V (O 빠짐)"},{"w":"whereby","ko":"방법·수단 (격식) = by which","ex":"the system whereby it works"},{"w":"how = the way","ko":"how는 the way를 이미 포함","ex":"This is how it works"}]},{"label":"축약 규칙 (분사·형용사구)","note":"「주격 관계사 + be」는 통째로 지울 수 있다. ==능동·진행이면 현재분사(V-ing), 수동이면 과거분사(p.p.)==로 남는다. 목적격 관계사는 be 없이도 그냥 생략된다.","items":[{"w":"능동 → V-ing","ko":"who/which is + 진행/능동 → 현재분사","ex":"the man (who is) standing"},{"w":"수동 → p.p.","ko":"who/which is + 수동 → 과거분사","ex":"the report (which was) written"},{"w":"일반동사 능동 축약","ko":"who/which + 동사 → 현재분사","ex":"people (who live) → people living"},{"w":"be + 형용사구","ko":"관계사+be 삭제, 형용사구만 남김","ex":"the students (who are) present"},{"w":"be + 전치사구","ko":"관계사+be 삭제, 전치사구만 남김","ex":"the book (which is) on the desk"},{"w":"진행 축약","ko":"who is + V-ing → V-ing","ex":"the girl (who is) wearing a hat"},{"w":"who is 삭제","ko":"주격 관계사와 be를 함께 삭제","ex":"the man (who is) tall"},{"w":"목적격 생략","ko":"목적격 관계사만 삭제, S+V 남김","ex":"the book (that) I read"},{"w":"수동 by-구","ko":"과거분사 + by 행위자","ex":"the food cooked by her"},{"w":"현재분사 = 능동","ko":"'~하고 있는' — 스스로 함","ex":"the boy making noise"},{"w":"과거분사 = 수동","ko":"'~된' — 당함","ex":"the noise made by the boy"},{"w":"축약 불가 (완료)","ko":"who has done 등 완료형은 축약 안 함","ex":"the man who has left (그대로)"},{"w":"there being","ko":"be동사 → being 형태로 축약","ex":"the only one (there being) left"},{"w":"명사 수식 위치","ko":"분사구는 선행사 바로 뒤에 붙음","ex":"the car parked outside"}]},{"label":"that vs which & 계속적 용법","note":"콤마가 없으면 한정적 용법(that·which 모두 가능), ==콤마가 있으면 계속적 용법(which·who만, that 불가)==이다. 계속적 용법은 선행사에 정보를 덧붙일 뿐 범위를 좁히지 않으며, **생략도 불가**하다.","items":[{"w":"that (한정적)","ko":"콤마 없음 — 선행사 범위를 좁힘","ex":"the car that I bought"},{"w":"which (한정적)","ko":"콤마 없음 — that과 교체 가능","ex":"the car which I bought"},{"w":", which (계속적)","ko":"콤마 + 사물 — 부가 설명","ex":"my car, which is red"},{"w":", who (계속적)","ko":"콤마 + 사람 — 부가 설명","ex":"my dad, who is a doctor"},{"w":", which (문장 전체)","ko":"앞 문장 전체를 받음","ex":"He was late, which upset us"},{"w":"that 금지 (콤마)","ko":"계속적 용법에는 that 사용 불가","ex":"NOT: my car, that is red"},{"w":"생략 불가 (계속적)","ko":"콤마 관계사는 생략할 수 없음","ex":"my car, which I love (필수)"},{"w":"that 선호","ko":"the only·all·every·최상급 뒤","ex":"all that I have"},{"w":"that 선호 (서수)","ko":"first·last 등 서수 뒤","ex":"the first that arrived"},{"w":"한정적 = 필수정보","ko":"빼면 뜻이 불완전 (콤마 없음)","ex":"the man who called (누구?)"},{"w":"계속적 = 부가정보","ko":"빼도 문장 성립 (콤마 있음)","ex":"Tom, who called, is here"},{"w":"which (앞 명사)","ko":"계속적 — 바로 앞 명사를 받음","ex":"the book, which is new"},{"w":"고유명사 + 콤마","ko":"고유명사 선행사는 계속적 용법","ex":"Seoul, which is large"}]},{"label":"전치사+관계대명사 & 수량표현","note":"전치사를 관계사 앞으로 보낼 때 ==사물은 which, 사람은 whom==을 쓰고 that·who는 못 쓴다. 「수량표현 + of + which/whom」은 계속적 용법으로 선행사의 일부·전부를 가리킨다.","items":[{"w":"in which","ko":"장소·안 — 사물","ex":"the house in which I live"},{"w":"to whom","ko":"~에게 — 사람","ex":"the man to whom I spoke"},{"w":"with which","ko":"~로(도구) — 사물","ex":"the pen with which I write"},{"w":"for which","ko":"~을 위해 — 사물","ex":"the company for which I work"},{"w":"about which","ko":"~에 관해 — 사물","ex":"the topic about which we argued"},{"w":"of which","ko":"~의 (사물 소유)","ex":"the book the cover of which is torn"},{"w":"some of which","ko":"그중 일부 — 사물","ex":"books, some of which are old"},{"w":"all of whom","ko":"그들 모두 — 사람","ex":"friends, all of whom came"},{"w":"both of whom","ko":"둘 다 — 사람","ex":"brothers, both of whom left"},{"w":"most of which","ko":"대부분 — 사물","ex":"cars, most of which are new"},{"w":"one of which","ko":"그중 하나 — 사물","ex":"three books, one of which is rare"},{"w":"none of which","ko":"그중 아무것도 — 사물","ex":"options, none of which worked"},{"w":"many of whom","ko":"그중 다수 — 사람","ex":"students, many of whom passed"},{"w":"전치사 반복 금지","ko":"앞으로 보냈으면 끝에 또 쓰지 않음","ex":"NOT: for which I work for"}]}]}},{"n":4,"title":"부정 · 조동사","status":"detailed","summary":"문장의 시제·태도·부정·의문을 책임지는 **조동사**를 총정리한다. 서법조동사(can·could·will·would·may·might·must·should·shall)와 do/does/did, 완료의 have/has/had, be동사의 조동사 역할까지 다룬다. 공통 원칙은 세 가지다. 첫째, ==조동사 바로 뒤에는 to 없이 동사원형==이 온다. 둘째, **부정은 조동사 뒤에 not**을 붙인다(do not·is not·have not·cannot). 셋째, **의문은 조동사를 주어 앞으로 도치**한다(Do you…? / Is it…? / Have you…?). 조동사가 여러 개 겹칠 때는 ==서법 + have + been + p.p./-ing== 순서를 지킨다.","subtopics":[{"key":"can-could","title":"can / could (I can speak three languages.)","points":["**can**은 능력('~할 수 있다')·허가('~해도 된다')·가능성을 나타내고, 뒤에는 ==to 없이 동사원형==이 온다.","**could**는 can의 과거(과거의 능력)이자 ==더 정중한 요청==과 약한 가능성을 나타낸다.","조동사라서 **주어가 3인칭 단수여도 -s를 붙이지 않는다**(He can, not He cans).","부정은 뒤에 not을 붙여 **cannot / can't**, **could not / couldn't**로 쓴다.","의문은 ==can/could를 주어 앞으로 도치==한다(Can you…? / Could you…?)."],"examples":[{"en":"I can speak three languages.","ko":"나는 세 개 언어를 말할 수 있다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"speak","role":"V"},{"t":"three languages.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"She could read when she was four.","ko":"그녀는 네 살 때 글을 읽을 수 있었다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"read","role":"V"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"four.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"Can I borrow your pen for a second?","ko":"잠깐 펜 좀 빌려도 될까?","parts":[{"t":"Can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"borrow","role":"V"},{"t":"your pen","role":"O"},{"t":"for a second?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Could you help me with this box?","ko":"이 상자 옮기는 것 좀 도와줄 수 있어?","parts":[{"t":"Could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"help","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"with this box?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"You cannot park here after 6 p.m.","ko":"오후 6시 이후에는 여기 주차할 수 없다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"cannot","role":"Aux"},{"t":"park","role":"V"},{"t":"here","role":"M"},{"t":"after 6 p.m.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"It can get really cold here at night.","ko":"여기는 밤에 정말 추워질 수 있다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"get","role":"V"},{"t":"really cold","role":"SC"},{"t":"here","role":"M"},{"t":"at night.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We could go to the beach if it stops raining.","ko":"비가 그치면 우리는 해변에 갈 수도 있다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"go","role":"V"},{"t":"to the beach","role":"M"},{"t":"if","role":"Conj"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"stops","role":"V"},{"t":"raining.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Can you hear me okay?","ko":"내 말 잘 들려?","parts":[{"t":"Can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"hear","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"okay?","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I can to swim.","I can swim. (조동사 **can** 뒤에는 to 없이 **동사원형**)"],["She cans drive.","She can drive. (조동사는 **주어가 3인칭 단수여도 -s를 붙이지 않는다**)"],["Can you to help me?","Can you help me? (조동사 뒤 **동사원형**, to 불필요)"]]},{"key":"will-would","title":"will / would (I will call you when I arrive.)","points":["**will**은 미래('~할 것이다')·의지('~하겠다')를 나타내며 뒤에는 ==동사원형==이 온다.","**would**는 정중한 제안·요청(Would you…?)과 가정('~할 텐데'), ==과거의 습관('~하곤 했다')==을 나타낸다.","부정은 **will not / won't**, **would not / wouldn't**로 쓴다.","조동사끼리는 못 겹치므로 'will can'은 틀리고 ==will be able to==로 바꾼다.","의문은 will/would를 ==주어 앞으로 도치==한다."],"examples":[{"en":"I will call you when I arrive.","ko":"도착하면 전화할게.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"call","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"O"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"arrive.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"She will be twenty next week.","ko":"그녀는 다음 주면 스무 살이 된다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"be","role":"V"},{"t":"twenty","role":"SC"},{"t":"next week.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Would you like some coffee?","ko":"커피 좀 드릴까요?","parts":[{"t":"Would","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"like","role":"V"},{"t":"some coffee?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I would travel more if I had the money.","ko":"돈이 있다면 나는 여행을 더 다닐 텐데.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"would","role":"Aux"},{"t":"travel","role":"V"},{"t":"more","role":"M"},{"t":"if","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"V"},{"t":"the money.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"We will not give up so easily.","ko":"우리는 그렇게 쉽게 포기하지 않을 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"give up","role":"V"},{"t":"so easily.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"When we were kids, we would play outside all day.","ko":"어릴 때 우리는 하루 종일 밖에서 놀곤 했다.","parts":[{"t":"When","role":"Conj"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"were","role":"V"},{"t":"kids,","role":"SC"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"would","role":"Aux"},{"t":"play","role":"V"},{"t":"outside","role":"M"},{"t":"all day.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"That won't be a problem at all.","ko":"그건 전혀 문제가 되지 않을 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"That","role":"S"},{"t":"won't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"be","role":"V"},{"t":"a problem","role":"SC"},{"t":"at all.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Would you mind closing the window?","ko":"창문 좀 닫아 주시겠어요?","parts":[{"t":"Would","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"mind","role":"V"},{"t":"closing the window?","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["I will can help you.","I will be able to help you. (조동사 두 개를 연달아 못 쓴다 → **will be able to**)"],["She will goes tomorrow.","She will go tomorrow. (will 뒤에는 **동사원형**)"],["Would you to join us?","Would you join us? (조동사 뒤 to 없이 **동사원형**)"]]},{"key":"may-might","title":"may / might (It might rain later.)","points":["**may**는 허가('~해도 된다', 격식)와 ==약한 추측('~일지도 모른다')==을 나타낸다.","**might**은 may보다 ==더 약한 추측==을 나타내며 뒤에 동사원형이 온다.","부정은 **may not / might not**으로 쓰고, 보통 축약하지 않는다.","부사 **maybe**('아마')와 조동사 **may be**('~일지도 모른다')를 ==혼동하지 않는다==.","허가를 묻는 격식 표현은 **May I…?**이다."],"examples":[{"en":"You may leave when you finish.","ko":"다 끝나면 가도 좋다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"may","role":"Aux"},{"t":"leave","role":"V"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"finish.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"It might rain later this afternoon.","ko":"오늘 오후 늦게 비가 올지도 모른다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"might","role":"Aux"},{"t":"rain","role":"V"},{"t":"later this afternoon.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"May I ask you a quick question?","ko":"잠깐 질문 하나 해도 될까요?","parts":[{"t":"May","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"ask","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"IO"},{"t":"a quick question?","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"She may not know about the change yet.","ko":"그녀는 아직 그 변경을 모를 수도 있다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"may","role":"Aux"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"about the change","role":"O"},{"t":"yet.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We might go camping this weekend.","ko":"우리는 이번 주말에 캠핑을 갈지도 모른다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"might","role":"Aux"},{"t":"go","role":"V"},{"t":"camping","role":"M"},{"t":"this weekend.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He might have missed the bus.","ko":"그는 버스를 놓쳤을지도 모른다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"might","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"missed","role":"V"},{"t":"the bus.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"You may want to double-check the address.","ko":"주소를 다시 확인해 보는 게 좋겠다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"may","role":"Aux"},{"t":"want","role":"V"},{"t":"to double-check the address.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"It may be too late to register.","ko":"등록하기엔 너무 늦었을지도 모른다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"may","role":"Aux"},{"t":"be","role":"V"},{"t":"too late","role":"SC"},{"t":"to register.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["It may rains later.","It may rain later. (may 뒤에는 **동사원형**)"],["May I to sit here?","May I sit here? (조동사 뒤 to 없이 **동사원형**)"],["It maybe rain tomorrow.","It may rain tomorrow. (조동사 **may**와 부사 **maybe**를 혼동하지 않는다)"]]},{"key":"must-haveto","title":"must / have to (You must wear a seatbelt.)","points":["**must**는 강한 의무('반드시 ~해야 한다')와 ==강한 추측('~임이 틀림없다')==을 나타낸다.","**have to**도 의무를 뜻하지만 ==외부 규칙·상황==에서 비롯되며, 과거는 **had to**, 의문·부정은 do를 쓴다.","==must not(금지, '절대 하면 안 된다')==과 ==don't have to(불필요, '안 해도 된다')==는 뜻이 완전히 다르다.","must는 과거형이 없어 과거 의무는 ==had to==로 대신한다.","'must have + p.p.'는 과거에 대한 강한 추측('~했음이 틀림없다')이다."],"examples":[{"en":"You must wear a seatbelt in the car.","ko":"차 안에서는 안전벨트를 매야 한다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"must","role":"Aux"},{"t":"wear","role":"V"},{"t":"a seatbelt","role":"O"},{"t":"in the car.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I have to finish this report by Friday.","ko":"나는 금요일까지 이 보고서를 끝내야 한다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have to","role":"Aux"},{"t":"finish","role":"V"},{"t":"this report","role":"O"},{"t":"by Friday.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She must be tired after such a long trip.","ko":"그렇게 긴 여행 후라 그녀는 분명 피곤할 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"must","role":"Aux"},{"t":"be","role":"V"},{"t":"tired","role":"SC"},{"t":"after such a long trip.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We had to wait for over an hour.","ko":"우리는 한 시간 넘게 기다려야 했다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"had to","role":"Aux"},{"t":"wait","role":"V"},{"t":"for over an hour.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"You must not touch the wet paint.","ko":"젖은 페인트를 만지면 안 된다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"must","role":"Aux"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"touch","role":"V"},{"t":"the wet paint.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"You don't have to come if you are busy.","ko":"바쁘면 안 와도 된다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have to","role":"Aux"},{"t":"come","role":"V"},{"t":"if","role":"Conj"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"busy.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"Does he have to work on weekends?","ko":"그는 주말에도 일해야 하나?","parts":[{"t":"Does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"have to","role":"Aux"},{"t":"work","role":"V"},{"t":"on weekends?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"They must have left already.","ko":"그들은 이미 떠났음이 틀림없다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"must","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"left","role":"V"},{"t":"already.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["You must not to smoke here.","You must not smoke here. (must 뒤 to 없이 **동사원형**)"],["You mustn't come tomorrow. (안 와도 된다는 뜻으로)","You don't have to come tomorrow. (**must not**=금지, **don't have to**=불필요, 뜻이 다르다)"],["I must to go now.","I must go now. (must 뒤 to 없이 **동사원형**)"]]},{"key":"should-ought","title":"should / ought to (You should drink more water.)","points":["**should**는 충고('~하는 게 좋다')·약한 의무·합리적 기대를 나타내며 뒤에 ==동사원형==이 온다.","**ought to**는 should와 거의 같은 뜻이지만 ==항상 to와 함께== 쓴다.","부정은 **should not / shouldn't**로 쓴다.","과거의 후회·유감은 ==should have + p.p.==('~했어야 했는데')로 나타낸다.","의문은 **Should I…?**처럼 주어 앞으로 도치한다."],"examples":[{"en":"You should drink more water.","ko":"물을 더 마시는 게 좋다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"drink","role":"V"},{"t":"more water.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"We should leave now to avoid traffic.","ko":"차 막히는 걸 피하려면 지금 나가는 게 좋다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"leave","role":"V"},{"t":"now","role":"M"},{"t":"to avoid traffic.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"You ought to apologize to her.","ko":"너는 그녀에게 사과해야 마땅하다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"ought to","role":"Aux"},{"t":"apologize","role":"V"},{"t":"to her.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Should I bring anything to the dinner?","ko":"저녁 식사에 뭐 좀 가져가야 할까?","parts":[{"t":"Should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"bring","role":"V"},{"t":"anything","role":"O"},{"t":"to the dinner?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"You shouldn't skip breakfast.","ko":"아침을 거르면 안 좋다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"shouldn't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"skip","role":"V"},{"t":"breakfast.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"He should have studied harder.","ko":"그는 더 열심히 공부했어야 했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"studied","role":"V"},{"t":"harder.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"They should be here any minute.","ko":"그들은 곧 도착할 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"be","role":"V"},{"t":"here","role":"M"},{"t":"any minute.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"You should not worry so much.","ko":"너무 걱정하지 않는 게 좋다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"worry","role":"V"},{"t":"so much.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["You should to see a doctor.","You should see a doctor. (should 뒤 to 없이 **동사원형**)"],["You should went earlier.","You should have gone earlier. (과거의 후회는 **should have + p.p.**)"],["He ought study more.","He ought to study more. (**ought**은 항상 **to**와 함께 쓴다)"]]},{"key":"shall","title":"shall (Shall we get started?)","points":["**Shall we…? / Shall I…?**는 ==제안·권유==('~할까요?')를 나타내는 가장 흔한 쓰임이다.","격식·규정문에서 **shall**은 강한 미래나 의무('~하기로 한다')를 나타낸다.","뒤에는 항상 ==동사원형==이 오고, 부정은 **shall not**(영국식 축약 **shan't**)이다.","의문은 shall을 ==주어(I/we) 앞으로 도치==한다.","일상 회화에서는 제안 외의 shall이 드물고, 대신 will을 많이 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"Shall we get started?","ko":"이제 시작할까요?","parts":[{"t":"Shall","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"get started?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Shall I open the window?","ko":"창문을 열까요?","parts":[{"t":"Shall","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"open","role":"V"},{"t":"the window?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"We shall overcome this challenge together.","ko":"우리는 이 난관을 함께 극복할 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"shall","role":"Aux"},{"t":"overcome","role":"V"},{"t":"this challenge","role":"O"},{"t":"together.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Shall we meet at noon?","ko":"정오에 만날까요?","parts":[{"t":"Shall","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"meet","role":"V"},{"t":"at noon?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"You shall not pass without a ticket.","ko":"표 없이는 통과할 수 없다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"shall","role":"Aux"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"pass","role":"V"},{"t":"without a ticket.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Shall I call you a taxi?","ko":"택시를 불러 드릴까요?","parts":[{"t":"Shall","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"call","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"IO"},{"t":"a taxi?","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"Where shall we put the new sofa?","ko":"새 소파를 어디에 둘까요?","parts":[{"t":"Where","role":"Wh"},{"t":"shall","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"put","role":"V"},{"t":"the new sofa?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Shall we take a short break?","ko":"잠깐 쉴까요?","parts":[{"t":"Shall","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"take","role":"V"},{"t":"a short break?","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["Shall we to start?","Shall we start? (조동사 뒤 to 없이 **동사원형**)"],["Shall we starting now?","Shall we start now? (조동사 뒤 **동사원형**, -ing 아님)"],["We shall meets tomorrow.","We shall meet tomorrow. (shall 뒤에는 **동사원형**)"]]},{"key":"do-negation","title":"do/does/did — 부정문 (I do not agree.)","points":["일반동사의 부정은 스스로 못 하므로 ==do/does/did + not + 동사원형==으로 만든다.","현재 **3인칭 단수**는 does, 나머지 현재는 do, 과거는 인칭과 무관하게 **did**를 쓴다.","does·did에 이미 3인칭·과거 표시가 들어가 ==본동사는 원형==으로 둔다(does not like).","축약형은 **don't / doesn't / didn't**이다.","부정어 not은 반드시 ==조동사(do) 뒤==에 온다(He does not / not He does)."],"examples":[{"en":"I do not agree with that idea.","ko":"나는 그 생각에 동의하지 않는다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"agree","role":"V"},{"t":"with that idea.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She does not eat meat.","ko":"그녀는 고기를 먹지 않는다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"eat","role":"V"},{"t":"meat.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"We did not receive the email.","ko":"우리는 그 이메일을 받지 못했다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"receive","role":"V"},{"t":"the email.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"He doesn't like crowded places.","ko":"그는 붐비는 곳을 좋아하지 않는다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"doesn't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"like","role":"V"},{"t":"crowded places.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"They didn't finish the project on time.","ko":"그들은 프로젝트를 제때 끝내지 못했다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"didn't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"finish","role":"V"},{"t":"the project","role":"O"},{"t":"on time.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I don't have any cash on me.","ko":"나는 지금 현금이 하나도 없다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"V"},{"t":"any cash","role":"O"},{"t":"on me.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The store does not open on Sundays.","ko":"그 가게는 일요일에는 열지 않는다.","parts":[{"t":"The store","role":"S"},{"t":"does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"open","role":"V"},{"t":"on Sundays.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We didn't know the road was closed.","ko":"우리는 길이 막힌 줄 몰랐다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"didn't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"the road","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"closed.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["She does not likes coffee.","She does not like coffee. (do/does 뒤 본동사는 **동사원형**)"],["I did not went there.","I did not go there. (did 뒤 본동사는 **동사원형**)"],["He not does his homework.","He does not do his homework. (부정은 **do/does + not** 어순)"]]},{"key":"do-question","title":"do/does/did — 의문문 (Do you know the way?)","points":["일반동사 의문문은 ==Do/Does/Did + 주어 + 동사원형==으로 만든다.","현재 **3인칭 단수**는 Does, 나머지 현재는 Do, 과거는 **Did**를 쓴다.","Does·Did가 시제·인칭을 책임지므로 ==본동사는 원형==이다(Does she like…?).","의문사(Wh-)가 있으면 ==Wh- + do/does/did + 주어 + 동사원형== 순서다.","주어를 빠뜨리지 않도록 조동사 뒤에 반드시 주어를 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"Do you know the way to the station?","ko":"역까지 가는 길을 아나?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"the way to the station?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Does she work here?","ko":"그녀는 여기서 일하나?","parts":[{"t":"Does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"work","role":"V"},{"t":"here?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Did they enjoy the concert?","ko":"그들은 콘서트를 즐겼나?","parts":[{"t":"Did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"enjoy","role":"V"},{"t":"the concert?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Do we need a reservation?","ko":"예약이 필요한가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"need","role":"V"},{"t":"a reservation?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Where does he live now?","ko":"그는 지금 어디에 사나?","parts":[{"t":"Where","role":"Wh"},{"t":"does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"live","role":"V"},{"t":"now?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"What did you say?","ko":"뭐라고 했어?","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"Wh"},{"t":"did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"say?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Does this train stop at Central?","ko":"이 기차가 센트럴에 서나?","parts":[{"t":"Does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"this train","role":"S"},{"t":"stop","role":"V"},{"t":"at Central?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Did the package arrive yesterday?","ko":"소포가 어제 도착했나?","parts":[{"t":"Did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"the package","role":"S"},{"t":"arrive","role":"V"},{"t":"yesterday?","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["Does she works here?","Does she work here? (Does 뒤 본동사는 **동사원형**)"],["Did you went home?","Did you go home? (Did 뒤 본동사는 **동사원형**)"],["You do like it?","Do you like it? (의문문은 **조동사 do를 주어 앞으로** 도치)"]]},{"key":"be-aux","title":"be동사의 부정·의문 및 조동사 역할 (Is it raining?)","points":["be동사(am·are·is·was·were)는 ==do를 쓰지 않고== 바로 뒤에 not을 붙여 부정한다(is not, were not).","의문은 ==be동사를 주어 앞으로 도치==한다(Are you…? / Was it…?).","be는 진행형에서 ==be + -ing==, 수동태에서 ==be + p.p.==의 조동사 역할을 한다.","이때 부정·의문도 ==앞에 있는 be==를 기준으로 만든다(Is it raining? / It is not being used).","축약형은 isn't·aren't·wasn't·weren't이다."],"examples":[{"en":"She is not ready yet.","ko":"그녀는 아직 준비가 안 됐다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"ready","role":"SC"},{"t":"yet.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Are you a student here?","ko":"여기 학생인가?","parts":[{"t":"Are","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"a student","role":"SC"},{"t":"here?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"They were not at home last night.","ko":"그들은 어젯밤 집에 없었다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"were","role":"V"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"at home","role":"SC"},{"t":"last night.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Is it raining outside?","ko":"밖에 비가 오나?","parts":[{"t":"Is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"raining","role":"V"},{"t":"outside?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The report is being reviewed now.","ko":"그 보고서는 지금 검토되고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The report","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"being","role":"Aux"},{"t":"reviewed","role":"V"},{"t":"now.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We aren't sure about the schedule.","ko":"우리는 일정에 대해 확신이 없다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"aren't","role":"V"},{"t":"sure","role":"SC"},{"t":"about the schedule.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Was the museum open on Monday?","ko":"월요일에 박물관이 열었나?","parts":[{"t":"Was","role":"V"},{"t":"the museum","role":"S"},{"t":"open","role":"SC"},{"t":"on Monday?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The kids are playing in the yard.","ko":"아이들이 마당에서 놀고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The kids","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"playing","role":"V"},{"t":"in the yard.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["She don't is ready.","She is not ready. (be동사 부정은 **be + not**, do 불필요)"],["Do you are a student?","Are you a student? (be동사 의문은 **be동사를 앞으로**, do 불필요)"],["It is not rain now.","It is not raining now. (진행은 **be + -ing**)"]]},{"key":"have-perfect","title":"have/has/had — 완료 조동사 (I have finished it.)","points":["완료는 ==have/has/had + 과거분사(p.p.)==로 만든다(현재완료 have/has, 과거완료 had).","부정은 ==have/has/had + not + p.p.==('아직 ~하지 않았다')이다.","의문은 ==Have/Has/Had를 주어 앞으로 도치==한다(Have you…?).","이때 do를 쓰지 않고 have 자체가 조동사 역할을 한다.","과거분사(gone·seen·done)를 과거형(went·saw·did)과 ==혼동하지 않는다==."],"examples":[{"en":"I have finished my homework.","ko":"나는 숙제를 끝냈다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"finished","role":"V"},{"t":"my homework.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"She has lived here for ten years.","ko":"그녀는 여기서 10년째 살고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"has","role":"Aux"},{"t":"lived","role":"V"},{"t":"here","role":"M"},{"t":"for ten years.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"They had already left when I arrived.","ko":"내가 도착했을 때 그들은 이미 떠나 있었다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"already","role":"M"},{"t":"left","role":"V"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"arrived.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Have you ever been to Japan?","ko":"일본에 가 본 적 있나?","parts":[{"t":"Have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"ever","role":"M"},{"t":"been","role":"V"},{"t":"to Japan?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I have not seen that movie yet.","ko":"나는 아직 그 영화를 못 봤다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"seen","role":"V"},{"t":"that movie","role":"O"},{"t":"yet.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He hasn't replied to my message.","ko":"그는 내 메시지에 답장하지 않았다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"hasn't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"replied","role":"V"},{"t":"to my message.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Has the meeting started already?","ko":"회의가 벌써 시작됐나?","parts":[{"t":"Has","role":"Aux"},{"t":"the meeting","role":"S"},{"t":"started","role":"V"},{"t":"already?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We have known each other since childhood.","ko":"우리는 어릴 때부터 서로 알고 지냈다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"known","role":"V"},{"t":"each other","role":"O"},{"t":"since childhood.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I have went there.","I have gone there. (완료는 **have + 과거분사**, went 아님)"],["She has finish her work.","She has finished her work. (완료는 **have + 과거분사**)"],["Do you have seen it?","Have you seen it? (완료 의문은 **have를 앞으로** 도치, do 불필요)"]]},{"key":"stacking","title":"조동사 여러 개의 어순 (should have been finished)","points":["조동사가 겹칠 때의 순서는 ==서법조동사 + have + been + 과거분사/-ing==로 고정된다.","**서법 + have + p.p.**는 과거 추측·후회(should have gone, must have left)를 나타낸다.","**have been + p.p.**는 완료 수동('~되어 왔다'), **have been + -ing**는 완료 진행('~해 오고 있다')이다.","**be + being + p.p.**는 진행형 수동('~되고 있는 중이다')이다.","각 조동사 뒤 형태가 정해져 있다: 서법 뒤 ==원형(have)==, have 뒤 ==p.p.(been)==, been 뒤 ==p.p. 또는 -ing==."],"examples":[{"en":"The project should have been finished by now.","ko":"그 프로젝트는 지금쯤 끝났어야 했다.","parts":[{"t":"The project","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"finished","role":"V"},{"t":"by now.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She must have been sleeping when I called.","ko":"내가 전화했을 때 그녀는 자고 있었음이 틀림없다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"must","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"sleeping","role":"V"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"called.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"They will have arrived by the time we get there.","ko":"우리가 도착할 즈음이면 그들은 이미 와 있을 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"arrived","role":"V"},{"t":"by the time","role":"Conj"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"get","role":"V"},{"t":"there.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The house is being painted this week.","ko":"그 집은 이번 주에 페인트칠이 되고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The house","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"being","role":"Aux"},{"t":"painted","role":"V"},{"t":"this week.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The results will have been announced by Friday.","ko":"결과는 금요일까지 발표되어 있을 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"The results","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"announced","role":"V"},{"t":"by Friday.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He might have been waiting for hours.","ko":"그는 몇 시간째 기다리고 있었을지도 모른다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"might","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"waiting","role":"V"},{"t":"for hours.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"You should have been more careful.","ko":"너는 더 조심했어야 했다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"been","role":"V"},{"t":"more careful.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The documents have been sent to the client.","ko":"서류는 고객에게 발송되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The documents","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"sent","role":"V"},{"t":"to the client.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["It should be have finished.","It should have been finished. (어순은 **서법 + have + been + p.p.**)"],["She must had been sleeping.","She must have been sleeping. (must 뒤에는 **have**, had 아님)"],["The house is been painted.","The house is being painted. (진행형 수동은 **be + being + p.p.**)"]]},{"key":"negatives","title":"부정어 · used to · had better (I have never seen it.)","points":["**not**은 조동사 뒤에, **never**('결코 ~않다')는 보통 ==일반동사 앞·be/조동사 뒤==에 온다.","**no**는 명사 앞('~이 없는'), **none/nobody/nothing**은 그 자체로 부정 대명사다.","**hardly·scarcely·barely·rarely·seldom**은 ==그 자체가 부정 의미==라, not과 함께 쓰면 이중부정이 된다.","==이중부정('didn't see nothing')은 피하고==, 부정어 하나 + any 계열로 쓴다(didn't see anything).","**used to**(과거의 습관·상태), **had better**(강한 충고), **would rather**(선호) 뒤에는 ==동사원형==이 온다."],"examples":[{"en":"I have never seen anything like it.","ko":"나는 그런 건 한 번도 본 적 없다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"never","role":"M"},{"t":"seen","role":"V"},{"t":"anything like it.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"There is no milk left in the fridge.","ko":"냉장고에 우유가 하나도 안 남았다.","parts":[{"t":"There","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"no milk","role":"SC"},{"t":"left in the fridge.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"None of the answers were correct.","ko":"정답이 하나도 없었다.","parts":[{"t":"None of the answers","role":"S"},{"t":"were","role":"V"},{"t":"correct.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"He hardly ever eats out.","ko":"그는 외식을 거의 안 한다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"hardly ever","role":"M"},{"t":"eats","role":"V"},{"t":"out.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She rarely arrives late.","ko":"그녀는 좀처럼 늦게 오지 않는다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"rarely","role":"M"},{"t":"arrives","role":"V"},{"t":"late.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I used to play the piano as a child.","ko":"나는 어릴 때 피아노를 치곤 했다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"used to","role":"Aux"},{"t":"play","role":"V"},{"t":"the piano","role":"O"},{"t":"as a child.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"You had better see a doctor soon.","ko":"너는 곧 병원에 가 보는 게 좋겠다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"had better","role":"Aux"},{"t":"see","role":"V"},{"t":"a doctor","role":"O"},{"t":"soon.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I would rather stay home tonight.","ko":"나는 오늘 밤엔 차라리 집에 있고 싶다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"would rather","role":"Aux"},{"t":"stay","role":"V"},{"t":"home","role":"M"},{"t":"tonight.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I didn't see nothing.","I didn't see anything. (부정어 두 개가 겹치는 **이중부정**은 피한다)"],["I use to play soccer.","I used to play soccer. (과거의 습관은 **used to**, 항상 -d를 붙인다)"],["You had better to rest.","You had better rest. (**had better** 뒤에는 to 없이 동사원형)"]]}],"db":{"title":"조동사 · 부정 DB · 의미 & 형태","intro":"조동사는 문장의 **시제·태도·부정·의문**을 책임진다. 공통 원칙은 ==조동사 뒤 동사원형==, ==부정은 조동사 + not==, ==의문은 조동사 도치==이다. 아래 네 그룹으로 서법조동사의 의미, 부정어·빈도부정어, 축약형, 의무·추측의 강도 비교를 한눈에 정리했다. **must not**(금지)과 **don't have to**(불필요)처럼 뜻이 갈리는 짝에 특히 주의한다.","groups":[{"label":"서법조동사 의미·용법","note":"각 조동사는 여러 의미를 겹쳐 갖는다. 모두 ==뒤에 동사원형==을 취하고 **주어에 따라 형태가 변하지 않는다**. can·will 등의 시제 제약은 be able to·have to로 보완한다.","items":[{"w":"can","ko":"능력(~할 수 있다) · 허가 · 가능성","ex":"I can swim well."},{"w":"could","ko":"과거 능력 · 정중한 요청 · 약한 가능성","ex":"Could you help me?"},{"w":"will","ko":"미래(~할 것이다) · 의지 · 요청","ex":"I will call you later."},{"w":"would","ko":"정중한 제안·요청 · 가정 · 과거의 습관","ex":"Would you like tea?"},{"w":"shall","ko":"제안(Shall we~?) · 격식 미래·의무","ex":"Shall we go now?"},{"w":"should","ko":"충고(~하는 게 좋다) · 약한 의무 · 기대","ex":"You should rest."},{"w":"ought to","ko":"충고·의무(should와 유사, 항상 to)","ex":"You ought to apologize."},{"w":"may","ko":"허가(격식) · 약한 추측(~일지도)","ex":"May I come in?"},{"w":"might","ko":"약한 추측(may보다 더 약함)","ex":"It might rain."},{"w":"must","ko":"강한 의무(반드시) · 강한 추측(~임이 틀림없다)","ex":"You must stop here."},{"w":"have to","ko":"의무(외부 규칙·상황), 시제·의문 자유","ex":"I have to go now."},{"w":"had to","ko":"과거의 의무(must의 과거 대용)","ex":"We had to wait."},{"w":"had better","ko":"강한 충고·경고(~하는 게 좋겠다)","ex":"You had better hurry."},{"w":"would rather","ko":"선호(차라리 ~하겠다) + 동사원형","ex":"I would rather walk."},{"w":"used to","ko":"과거의 습관·상태(지금은 아님)","ex":"I used to smoke."},{"w":"would (과거습관)","ko":"과거에 반복하던 동작(~하곤 했다)","ex":"We would play outside."},{"w":"be able to","ko":"능력(can 대용, 모든 시제 가능)","ex":"I will be able to come."},{"w":"be going to","ko":"예정·계획된 미래(~할 예정이다)","ex":"I am going to leave."},{"w":"be supposed to","ko":"~하기로 되어 있다(예정·의무)","ex":"You are supposed to wait."},{"w":"need (조동사)","ko":"필요(주로 부정·의문 needn't)","ex":"You needn't worry."},{"w":"may as well","ko":"~하는 편이 낫다(딱히 대안 없음)","ex":"We may as well go."},{"w":"can't (추측)","ko":"~일 리 없다(강한 부정 추측)","ex":"It can't be true."}]},{"label":"부정어 · 빈도부정어","note":"**not**은 조동사 뒤에 붙지만, **never·hardly·rarely** 등은 ==자체가 부정 의미==라 not 없이 쓴다. hardly·scarcely·rarely·seldom을 not과 겹쳐 쓰면 ==이중부정==이 되니 주의한다.","items":[{"w":"not","ko":"~아니다/않다 (조동사 뒤에 붙음)","ex":"I do not agree."},{"w":"never","ko":"결코 ~않다 (강한 부정, 빈도 0)","ex":"I never lie."},{"w":"no","ko":"하나도 없는 (명사 앞)","ex":"There is no time."},{"w":"none","ko":"아무것도/아무도 ~않다 (대명사)","ex":"None of us knew."},{"w":"no one / nobody","ko":"아무도 ~않다 (사람)","ex":"Nobody came."},{"w":"nothing","ko":"아무것도 ~않다 (사물)","ex":"Nothing happened."},{"w":"nowhere","ko":"아무 데도 ~않다 (장소)","ex":"It led nowhere."},{"w":"hardly","ko":"거의 ~않다 (부정어, not 불필요)","ex":"I could hardly hear."},{"w":"scarcely","ko":"거의 ~않다 (hardly와 유사)","ex":"She scarcely spoke."},{"w":"barely","ko":"간신히 · 거의 ~않다","ex":"He barely ate."},{"w":"rarely","ko":"좀처럼 ~않다 (빈도 낮음)","ex":"We rarely meet."},{"w":"seldom","ko":"좀처럼 ~않다 (격식)","ex":"He seldom calls."},{"w":"neither","ko":"(둘 중) 어느 쪽도 ~아니다","ex":"Neither is correct."},{"w":"nor","ko":"~도 또한 아니다 (도치 동반)","ex":"Nor do I."},{"w":"not ... either","ko":"~도 (또한) 아니다","ex":"I don't either."},{"w":"no longer","ko":"더 이상 ~않다","ex":"She no longer works here."},{"w":"not at all","ko":"전혀 ~않다 (강조)","ex":"Not at all."},{"w":"by no means","ko":"결코 ~않다 (강한 부정)","ex":"It is by no means easy."},{"w":"few","ko":"(가산) 거의 없는","ex":"Few people came."},{"w":"little","ko":"(불가산) 거의 없는","ex":"There is little time."},{"w":"not ... any","ko":"하나도 ~않다 (이중부정 대신)","ex":"I don't have any."}]},{"label":"축약형","note":"회화에서는 ==조동사 + not==을 축약해 쓴다. **won't**(will not)·**can't**(cannot)처럼 형태가 크게 바뀌는 것에 주의한다. 아포스트로피(')로 생략을 표시한다.","items":[{"w":"don't","ko":"= do not","ex":"I don't know."},{"w":"doesn't","ko":"= does not","ex":"She doesn't care."},{"w":"didn't","ko":"= did not","ex":"We didn't go."},{"w":"won't","ko":"= will not (형태 크게 변함)","ex":"I won't tell."},{"w":"wouldn't","ko":"= would not","ex":"He wouldn't stop."},{"w":"can't","ko":"= cannot","ex":"I can't see it."},{"w":"couldn't","ko":"= could not","ex":"She couldn't come."},{"w":"shouldn't","ko":"= should not","ex":"You shouldn't skip it."},{"w":"mustn't","ko":"= must not (금지)","ex":"You mustn't enter."},{"w":"oughtn't","ko":"= ought not (드묾)","ex":"You oughtn't lie."},{"w":"shan't","ko":"= shall not (영국식)","ex":"I shan't be long."},{"w":"needn't","ko":"= need not (~할 필요 없다)","ex":"You needn't rush."},{"w":"isn't","ko":"= is not","ex":"It isn't fair."},{"w":"aren't","ko":"= are not","ex":"They aren't here."},{"w":"wasn't","ko":"= was not","ex":"It wasn't me."},{"w":"weren't","ko":"= were not","ex":"They weren't ready."},{"w":"haven't","ko":"= have not","ex":"I haven't eaten."},{"w":"hasn't","ko":"= has not","ex":"She hasn't left."},{"w":"hadn't","ko":"= had not","ex":"We hadn't met before."},{"w":"'ll","ko":"= will (I'll, he'll)","ex":"I'll go now."},{"w":"'d","ko":"= would 또는 had (문맥으로 구분)","ex":"I'd like some tea."},{"w":"'ve","ko":"= have (I've, we've)","ex":"I've done it."},{"w":"'s","ko":"= is 또는 has (문맥으로 구분)","ex":"She's finished."}]},{"label":"의무·추측 강도 비교","note":"같은 '의무'라도 **must**(강함) > **should**(약함), 같은 '추측'이라도 **must**(확신) > **may/might**(약함)로 세기가 다르다. 특히 ==must not(금지) ≠ don't have to(불필요)==를 반드시 구분한다.","items":[{"w":"must (의무)","ko":"반드시 해야 한다 (가장 강함·화자 권위)","ex":"You must stop now."},{"w":"have to (의무)","ko":"해야 한다 (외부 규칙·상황)","ex":"I have to work today."},{"w":"have got to (의무)","ko":"해야 한다 (구어, have to 유사)","ex":"I've got to go."},{"w":"be to (의무)","ko":"~하기로 되어 있다 (예정·지시)","ex":"You are to report at 9."},{"w":"should (의무)","ko":"~하는 게 좋다 (약함·권고)","ex":"You should rest."},{"w":"ought to (의무)","ko":"~해야 마땅하다 (should 유사)","ex":"You ought to go."},{"w":"had better (의무)","ko":"~하는 게 좋겠다 (경고 뉘앙스)","ex":"You had better hurry."},{"w":"need to (필요)","ko":"~할 필요가 있다","ex":"You need to rest."},{"w":"must not (금지)","ko":"절대 하면 안 된다 (강한 금지)","ex":"You must not enter."},{"w":"don't have to (불필요)","ko":"안 해도 된다 (금지 아님)","ex":"You don't have to pay."},{"w":"must (추측)","ko":"~임이 틀림없다 (강한 확신)","ex":"She must be tired."},{"w":"can't (추측)","ko":"~일 리 없다 (강한 부정 확신)","ex":"It can't be right."},{"w":"should (추측)","ko":"~일 것이다 (합리적 기대)","ex":"They should be home."},{"w":"may (추측)","ko":"~일지도 모른다 (약 50%)","ex":"It may snow tonight."},{"w":"might (추측)","ko":"~일지도 모른다 (may보다 약함)","ex":"He might know it."},{"w":"could (추측)","ko":"~일 수도 있다 (가능성)","ex":"That could work."},{"w":"will (추측)","ko":"~일 것이다 (확신 있는 예측)","ex":"That'll be him."}]}]}},{"n":5,"title":"to부정사","status":"detailed","summary":"to부정사(to + 동사원형)는 문장에서 ==명사·형용사·부사== 역할을 두루 맡는다. **명사적**(~하는 것), **형용사적**(~할), **부사적**(~하기 위해서) 세 갈래가 큰 줄기다. 여기에 **부정형**과 **동사 호응 패턴**까지 잡으면 회화·작문의 폭이 넓어진다.","subtopics":[{"key":"noun-subj-obj-comp","title":"명사적 용법 — 주어·목적어·보어","points":["to부정사가 ==명사==처럼 **주어·목적어·보어** 자리에 들어간다.","해석은 **\"~하는 것 / ~하기\"**다.","주어면 \"~하는 것은\", 목적어면 \"~하기를\", 보어면 \"~하는 것이다\"로 푼다.","**want·decide·promise** 등은 목적어로 to부정사를 자주 취한다."],"examples":[{"en":"To save money is my biggest goal this year.","ko":"돈을 모으는 것이 올해 가장 큰 목표다.","parts":[{"t":"To save money","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"my biggest goal","role":"SC"},{"t":"this year.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"To make new friends is always exciting.","ko":"새로운 친구를 사귀는 것은 언제나 신난다.","parts":[{"t":"To make new friends","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"always","role":"M"},{"t":"exciting.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I want to buy a new smartphone.","ko":"새 스마트폰을 사고 싶다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"want","role":"V"},{"t":"to buy a new smartphone.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"We decided to order pizza for dinner.","ko":"저녁으로 피자를 시키기로 했다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"decided","role":"V"},{"t":"to order pizza","role":"O"},{"t":"for dinner.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She promised to call me back later.","ko":"그녀는 나중에 다시 전화하겠다고 약속했다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"promised","role":"V"},{"t":"to call me back","role":"O"},{"t":"later.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He refused to share his Wi-Fi password.","ko":"그는 와이파이 비밀번호 공유를 거절했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"refused","role":"V"},{"t":"to share his Wi-Fi password.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"My dream is to travel around the world.","ko":"내 꿈은 세계 여행이다.","parts":[{"t":"My dream","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"to travel around the world.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The best way is to ask the teacher directly.","ko":"가장 좋은 방법은 선생님께 직접 물어보는 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"The best way","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"to ask the teacher directly.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"His plan was to surprise her on her birthday.","ko":"그의 계획은 그녀의 생일에 깜짝 놀라게 해주는 것이었다.","parts":[{"t":"His plan","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"to surprise her on her birthday.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["I want buy a new phone.","I want to buy a new phone. (want의 목적어는 **to부정사**, 동사원형만 바로 못 붙인다)"],["We decided ordering pizza.","We decided to order pizza. (decide는 **to부정사**를 목적어로 받는다, -ing 아님)"],["My dream is travel around the world.","My dream is to travel around the world. (보어 자리엔 **to**를 붙인다)"]]},{"key":"dummy-subject-it","title":"가주어 It ... to","points":["주어인 to부정사구가 길면 문장 앞이 무거워진다.","자리만 채우는 **가주어 It**을 앞에 세우고 ==진주어 to부정사구==는 뒤로 보낸다.","**\"It is + 형용사 + to부정사\"** 형태가 가장 흔하다.","해석은 뒤의 to부정사부터 \"~하는 건\"으로 하면 자연스럽다."],"examples":[{"en":"It is hard to wake up at 6 AM.","ko":"오전 6시에 일어나는 건 힘들다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"hard","role":"SC"},{"t":"to wake up at 6 AM.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It is fun to play video games with friends.","ko":"친구들이랑 게임하는 건 재미있다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"fun","role":"SC"},{"t":"to play video games with friends.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It is dangerous to walk alone at night.","ko":"밤에 혼자 걷는 건 위험하다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"dangerous","role":"SC"},{"t":"to walk alone at night.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It takes 30 minutes to get to the subway station.","ko":"지하철역까지 30분 걸린다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"takes","role":"V"},{"t":"30 minutes","role":"O"},{"t":"to get to the subway station.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It is important to drink enough water every day.","ko":"매일 물을 충분히 마시는 게 중요하다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"important","role":"SC"},{"t":"to drink enough water every day.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It is not easy to learn a new language.","ko":"새 언어를 배우는 건 쉽지 않다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"easy","role":"SC"},{"t":"to learn a new language.","role":"S"}]}],"mistakes":[["Is hard to wake up early.","It is hard to wake up early. (**가주어 It**을 빠뜨리면 안 된다)"],["It is fun playing games to say it this way here.","It is fun to play games. (가주어 It 뒤 진주어는 **to부정사**로 받는 게 기본이다)"],["To wake up at 6 AM is it hard.","It is hard to wake up at 6 AM. (긴 주어는 **It**으로 대신하고 뒤로 보낸다)"]]},{"key":"dummy-object-it","title":"가목적어 it (5형식)","points":["5형식 **동사 + 목적어 + 목적격 보어** 구조에서 쓴다.","목적어가 긴 to부정사구면 그 자리에 **가목적어 it**을 먼저 넣는다.","진짜 목적어인 ==to부정사구는 보어 뒤로== 보낸다.","어순은 **\"주어 + 동사 + it + 형용사/명사 + to부정사\"**다.","**make·find·think·believe·consider·keep·feel** 등에서 자주 나온다."],"examples":[{"en":"I found it hard to believe his crazy story.","ko":"그의 말도 안 되는 이야기를 믿기가 어렵다는 걸 알게 됐다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"found","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"hard","role":"OC"},{"t":"to believe his crazy story.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"She makes it a rule to jog every morning.","ko":"그녀는 매일 아침 조깅을 규칙으로 삼는다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"makes","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"a rule","role":"OC"},{"t":"to jog every morning.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I think it wrong to lie to your parents.","ko":"부모님께 거짓말하는 건 나쁘다고 생각한다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"think","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"wrong","role":"OC"},{"t":"to lie to your parents.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"He kept it secret to surprise everyone at the party.","ko":"파티에서 모두를 놀라게 하려고 비밀로 유지했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"kept","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"secret","role":"OC"},{"t":"to surprise everyone at the party.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We felt it necessary to change our travel plans.","ko":"여행 계획을 바꿀 필요가 있다고 느꼈다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"felt","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"necessary","role":"OC"},{"t":"to change our travel plans.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I find it easy to make friends here.","ko":"여기서 친구 사귀는 게 쉽게 느껴진다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"find","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"easy","role":"OC"},{"t":"to make friends here.","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["I found hard to believe his story.","I found it hard to believe his story. (**가목적어 it**을 빼면 안 된다)"],["She makes a rule it to jog every morning.","She makes it a rule to jog. (어순은 **it + 보어 + to부정사**)"],["I think wrong to lie.","I think it wrong to lie. (5형식 긴 목적어 앞엔 **가목적어 it**)"]]},{"key":"meaning-subject-for","title":"의미상 주어 — for + 목적격","points":["to부정사의 행위자가 문장 주어와 다르면 **의미상 주어**를 밝힌다.","일반 형용사(**hard·easy·difficult·impossible·necessary·natural·dangerous** 등) 뒤에서는 ==\"for + 목적격\"==을 쓴다.","**\"It is 형용사 for 사람 to부정사\"** 형태로 외운다.","for 뒤에는 **목적격**(me·him·us)이 온다."],"examples":[{"en":"It is difficult for me to eat spicy food.","ko":"내가 매운 음식을 먹는 건 어렵다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"difficult","role":"SC"},{"t":"for me","role":"M"},{"t":"to eat spicy food.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It is impossible for him to finish this by tomorrow.","ko":"그가 내일까지 이걸 끝내는 건 불가능하다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"impossible","role":"SC"},{"t":"for him","role":"M"},{"t":"to finish this by tomorrow.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It is necessary for us to leave right now.","ko":"우리가 지금 당장 떠나야 한다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"necessary","role":"SC"},{"t":"for us","role":"M"},{"t":"to leave right now.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It is natural for a baby to cry when hungry.","ko":"아기가 배고플 때 우는 건 자연스럽다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"natural","role":"SC"},{"t":"for a baby","role":"M"},{"t":"to cry when hungry.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It is dangerous for kids to play near the road.","ko":"아이들이 도로 근처에서 노는 건 위험하다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"dangerous","role":"SC"},{"t":"for kids","role":"M"},{"t":"to play near the road.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It is easy for her to solve this problem.","ko":"그녀가 이 문제를 푸는 건 쉽다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"easy","role":"SC"},{"t":"for her","role":"M"},{"t":"to solve this problem.","role":"S"}]}],"mistakes":[["It is difficult of me to eat spicy food.","It is difficult for me to eat spicy food. (일반 형용사엔 **for**, of 아님)"],["It is hard to me to wake up early.","It is hard for me to wake up early. (의미상 주어는 to me가 아니라 **for me**)"],["It is necessary for we to leave now.","It is necessary for us to leave now. (for 뒤엔 **목적격 us**)"]]},{"key":"meaning-subject-of","title":"의미상 주어 — of + 목적격 (성격 형용사)","points":["**성품·태도**를 평가하는 형용사 뒤에서는 for가 아니라 ==\"of + 목적격\"==을 쓴다.","**kind·nice·foolish·careless·stupid·brave·rude·polite** 등이 해당된다.","\"그렇게 행동하다니 그 사람이 ~하다\"라는 뉘앙스다.","**\"It is 성격형용사 of 사람 to부정사\"** 형태로 기억한다."],"examples":[{"en":"It was very kind of you to help me with my bags.","ko":"내 가방을 들어준 것은 무척 친절했다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"very kind","role":"SC"},{"t":"of you","role":"M"},{"t":"to help me with my bags.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It is foolish of him to spend all his money on games.","ko":"게임에 돈을 다 쓰다니 그는 어리석다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"foolish","role":"SC"},{"t":"of him","role":"M"},{"t":"to spend all his money on games.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It was careless of me to lose my keys again.","ko":"열쇠를 또 잃어버리다니 내가 부주의했다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"careless","role":"SC"},{"t":"of me","role":"M"},{"t":"to lose my keys again.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It is nice of them to invite us to dinner.","ko":"저녁에 초대해주다니 무척 고마운 사람들이다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"nice","role":"SC"},{"t":"of them","role":"M"},{"t":"to invite us to dinner.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It was stupid of her to trust a total stranger.","ko":"완전 낯선 사람을 믿다니 그녀는 바보 같았다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"stupid","role":"SC"},{"t":"of her","role":"M"},{"t":"to trust a total stranger.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"It is brave of you to speak up in class.","ko":"수업에서 목소리를 내다니 용감하다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"brave","role":"SC"},{"t":"of you","role":"M"},{"t":"to speak up in class.","role":"S"}]}],"mistakes":[["It was kind for you to help me.","It was kind of you to help me. (성격 형용사 kind엔 **of**)"],["It is foolish for him to waste money.","It is foolish of him to waste money. (성품 평가 형용사엔 **of**)"],["It was nice of they to invite us.","It was nice of them to invite us. (of 뒤엔 **목적격 them**)"]]},{"key":"adjective-modify-apposition","title":"형용사적 용법 — 명사 수식·동격","points":["to부정사가 **명사 바로 뒤**에 붙어 그 명사를 꾸민다.","해석은 ==\"~할, ~하는\"==이다.","**homework to do**(할 숙제), **time to think**(생각할 시간)처럼 뒤에서 수식한다.","**promise·plan·wish·decision** 뒤에서는 \"~하겠다는\" **동격**으로도 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"I have a lot of homework to do tonight.","ko":"오늘 밤 할 숙제가 많다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"V"},{"t":"a lot of homework","role":"O"},{"t":"to do","role":"M"},{"t":"tonight.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He is the first person to arrive at the office.","ko":"그는 사무실에 가장 먼저 도착한 사람이다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the first person","role":"SC"},{"t":"to arrive at the office.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Do you have anything to say?","ko":"할 말 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"V"},{"t":"anything","role":"O"},{"t":"to say?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I need some time to think about it.","ko":"그것에 대해 생각할 시간이 좀 필요하다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"need","role":"V"},{"t":"some time","role":"O"},{"t":"to think about it.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She made a promise to come back soon.","ko":"그녀는 곧 돌아오겠다는 약속을 했다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"made","role":"V"},{"t":"a promise","role":"O"},{"t":"to come back soon.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"It's time to go home now.","ko":"이제 집에 갈 시간이다.","parts":[{"t":"It's","role":"S"},{"t":"time","role":"SC"},{"t":"to go home now.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I have no reason to lie to you.","ko":"당신에게 거짓말할 이유가 없다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"V"},{"t":"no reason","role":"O"},{"t":"to lie to you.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I have a lot of homework doing tonight.","I have a lot of homework to do tonight. (명사 수식은 -ing가 아니라 **to부정사**)"],["He is the first person arrive at the office.","He is the first person to arrive at the office. (명사 뒤 수식엔 **to부정사**)"],["Do you have anything for say?","Do you have anything to say? (수식은 for say가 아니라 **to say**)"]]},{"key":"adjective-leave-preposition","title":"형용사적 용법 — 전치사 남기기","points":["수식받는 명사가 to부정사 안 동사의 **짝 전치사**와 연결될 때 쓴다.","그 ==전치사를 문장 끝에== 반드시 남긴다.","**sit on a chair → a chair to sit on**이 되는 원리다.","**전치사 누락**이 회화·시험에서 잦은 실수다."],"examples":[{"en":"I need a comfortable chair to sit on.","ko":"앉을 편안한 의자가 필요하다. (sit on a chair)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"need","role":"V"},{"t":"a comfortable chair","role":"O"},{"t":"to sit on.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He has no friends to talk to.","ko":"그는 같이 얘기할 친구가 없다. (talk to friends)","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"has","role":"V"},{"t":"no friends","role":"O"},{"t":"to talk to.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Give me a piece of paper to write on.","ko":"글 쓸 종이 한 장을 달라. (write on paper)","parts":[{"t":"Give","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"a piece of paper","role":"DO"},{"t":"to write on.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"They are looking for a house to live in.","ko":"그들은 살 집을 찾고 있다. (live in a house)","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"are looking for","role":"V"},{"t":"a house","role":"O"},{"t":"to live in.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I don't have a pen to write with.","ko":"쓸 만한 펜이 없다. (write with a pen)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"V"},{"t":"a pen","role":"O"},{"t":"to write with.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Is there anything to worry about?","ko":"걱정할 게 있는가? (worry about something)","parts":[{"t":"Is","role":"V"},{"t":"there","role":"S"},{"t":"anything","role":"SC"},{"t":"to worry about?","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I need a comfortable chair to sit.","I need a comfortable chair to sit on. (sit on이므로 **on**을 끝에 남긴다)"],["He has no friends to talk.","He has no friends to talk to. (talk to이므로 **to**를 남긴다)"],["Give me a paper to write.","Give me a paper to write on. (write on이므로 **on**을 빠뜨리면 안 된다)"]]},{"key":"adverb-purpose","title":"부사적 용법 — 목적 (~하기 위해서)","points":["부사적 용법 중 가장 흔한 쓰임이 ==목적==이다.","해석은 **\"~하기 위해서\"**다.","목적을 강조하려면 **in order to**나 **so as to**를 쓴다.","동사 뒤에 붙어 \"왜 그 행동을 하는지\"를 설명한다."],"examples":[{"en":"I went to the supermarket to buy some milk.","ko":"우유 좀 사러 슈퍼마켓에 갔다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"went","role":"V"},{"t":"to the supermarket","role":"M"},{"t":"to buy some milk.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She studies hard in order to pass the test.","ko":"그녀는 시험에 붙으려고 열심히 공부한다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"studies","role":"V"},{"t":"hard","role":"M"},{"t":"in order to pass the test.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I turned on the TV so as to watch the news.","ko":"뉴스를 보려고 TV를 켰다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"turned on","role":"V"},{"t":"the TV","role":"O"},{"t":"so as to watch the news.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He woke up early in order to catch the first train.","ko":"그는 첫차를 타려고 일찍 일어났다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"woke up","role":"V"},{"t":"early","role":"M"},{"t":"in order to catch the first train.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We saved money to buy a new car.","ko":"새 차를 사려고 돈을 모았다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"saved","role":"V"},{"t":"money","role":"O"},{"t":"to buy a new car.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I called her to say sorry.","ko":"사과하려고 그녀에게 전화했다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"called","role":"V"},{"t":"her","role":"O"},{"t":"to say sorry.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I went to the supermarket for buy some milk.","I went to the supermarket to buy some milk. (목적은 for buy가 아니라 **to buy**)"],["She studies hard in order pass the test.","She studies hard in order to pass the test. (in order 뒤에도 **to**가 필요하다)"],["I went there for buying milk.","I went there to buy milk. (\"~하려고\"는 **to부정사**가 자연스럽다)"]]},{"key":"adverb-adjective-emotion","title":"부사적 용법 — 형용사 수식·감정 원인","points":["형용사 뒤 to부정사는 **\"~하기에\"**(형용사 수식)로 해석된다.","**glad·surprised·sad·happy** 등 감정 형용사 뒤에서는 ==\"~해서\"==(원인)로 푼다.","**too...to**(너무 ~해서 못 …), **enough to**(…할 만큼 ~) 구조가 자주 나온다.","**enough**는 형용사 **뒤**에 놓인다(old enough)."],"examples":[{"en":"English grammar is sometimes hard to understand.","ko":"영어 문법은 가끔 이해하기 어렵다.","parts":[{"t":"English grammar","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"sometimes","role":"M"},{"t":"hard","role":"SC"},{"t":"to understand.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This coffee is too hot to drink.","ko":"이 커피는 너무 뜨거워서 못 마신다.","parts":[{"t":"This coffee","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"too hot","role":"SC"},{"t":"to drink.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The movie was easy to follow.","ko":"그 영화는 따라가기 쉬웠다.","parts":[{"t":"The movie","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"easy","role":"SC"},{"t":"to follow.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I'm so glad to meet you.","ko":"만나서 정말 반갑다.","parts":[{"t":"I'm","role":"S"},{"t":"so glad","role":"SC"},{"t":"to meet you.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I was surprised to see him there.","ko":"거기서 그를 봐서 놀랐다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"surprised","role":"SC"},{"t":"to see him there.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She was sad to hear the bad news.","ko":"그녀는 나쁜 소식을 들어서 슬펐다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"sad","role":"SC"},{"t":"to hear the bad news.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We are happy to help you.","ko":"기꺼이 도와주겠다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"happy","role":"SC"},{"t":"to help you.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He is old enough to drive.","ko":"그는 운전할 만큼 나이가 됐다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"old enough","role":"SC"},{"t":"to drive.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["This coffee is too hot for drink.","This coffee is too hot to drink. (**too ... to** 구조엔 to)"],["I'm so glad meeting you.","I'm so glad to meet you. (감정 원인은 **to부정사**로 표현한다)"],["He is enough old to drive.","He is old enough to drive. (**enough**는 형용사 뒤에 놓인다)"]]},{"key":"adverb-judgment-result","title":"부사적 용법 — 판단 근거·결과","points":["**판단 근거**는 \"~하다니\"로 해석하고 **must be** 같은 추측 뒤에서 이유를 댄다.","**결과**는 ==\"결국 ~하게 되다\"==로 행동 뒤의 결말을 나타낸다.","**grow up to be**(자라서 ~가 되다)가 대표적 결과 표현이다.","**only to**(결국 ~하고 말다), **never to**(다시는 ~않다)도 결과를 나타낸다."],"examples":[{"en":"He must be crazy to say such a thing.","ko":"그런 말을 하다니 그는 제정신이 아닌 게 틀림없다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"must","role":"Aux"},{"t":"be","role":"V"},{"t":"crazy","role":"SC"},{"t":"to say such a thing.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She must be smart to solve that puzzle so fast.","ko":"그 퍼즐을 그렇게 빨리 풀다니 그녀는 똑똑한 게 분명하다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"must","role":"Aux"},{"t":"be","role":"V"},{"t":"smart","role":"SC"},{"t":"to solve that puzzle so fast.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"You are foolish to believe his lies.","ko":"그의 거짓말을 믿다니 어리석다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"foolish","role":"SC"},{"t":"to believe his lies.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"My grandfather lived to be 90 years old.","ko":"할아버지는 90세까지 사셨다.","parts":[{"t":"My grandfather","role":"S"},{"t":"lived","role":"V"},{"t":"to be 90 years old.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He grew up to be a famous singer.","ko":"그는 자라서 유명한 가수가 됐다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"grew up","role":"V"},{"t":"to be a famous singer.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I woke up to find myself in a hospital room.","ko":"깨어 보니 병실이었다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"woke up","role":"V"},{"t":"to find myself in a hospital room.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He tried hard, only to fail again.","ko":"열심히 했지만 결국 또 실패했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"tried","role":"V"},{"t":"hard,","role":"M"},{"t":"only to fail again.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She left her hometown, never to return.","ko":"그녀는 고향을 떠나 다시는 돌아오지 않았다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"left","role":"V"},{"t":"her hometown,","role":"O"},{"t":"never to return.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["He must be crazy for say such a thing.","He must be crazy to say such a thing. (판단 근거는 **to부정사**)"],["He grew up being a famous singer.","He grew up to be a famous singer. (결과의 \"~가 되다\"는 **to be**)"],["He tried hard, only failing again.","He tried hard, only to fail again. (**only to + 동사원형**으로 결과를 나타낸다)"]]},{"key":"negative-form","title":"부정형 — not/never to, in order not to","points":["부정어 **not·never**를 반드시 ==to 바로 앞==에 놓는다.","어순은 **\"not to + 동사원형\"**이다.","**to not**은 틀린 어순이다.","부정 목적은 **in order not to**나 **so as not to**로 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"I promised not to tell anyone your secret.","ko":"네 비밀을 아무에게도 말하지 않기로 약속했다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"promised","role":"V"},{"t":"not to tell anyone your secret.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"He decided not to go to the party.","ko":"그는 파티에 안 가기로 결정했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"decided","role":"V"},{"t":"not to go to the party.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"It is hard not to laugh at his jokes.","ko":"그의 농담에 안 웃기가 힘들다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"hard","role":"SC"},{"t":"not to laugh at his jokes.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"The doctor advised me not to eat late at night.","ko":"의사 선생님이 밤늦게 먹지 말라고 했다.","parts":[{"t":"The doctor","role":"S"},{"t":"advised","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"not to eat late at night.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"I set an alarm in order not to oversleep.","ko":"늦잠 자지 않으려고 알람을 맞췄다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"set","role":"V"},{"t":"an alarm","role":"O"},{"t":"in order not to oversleep.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Walk quietly so as not to wake the baby.","ko":"아기를 깨우지 않게 조용히 걸어 달라.","parts":[{"t":"Walk","role":"V"},{"t":"quietly","role":"M"},{"t":"so as not to wake the baby.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We left early so as not to be late for the movie.","ko":"영화에 늦지 않으려고 일찍 나왔다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"left","role":"V"},{"t":"early","role":"M"},{"t":"so as not to be late for the movie.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I promised to not tell anyone.","I promised not to tell anyone. (**not**은 to 앞에 놓는다)"],["He decided don't to go to the party.","He decided not to go to the party. (부정은 don't가 아니라 **not to**)"],["I set an alarm in order to not oversleep.","I set an alarm in order not to oversleep. (부정 목적은 **in order not to**)"]]},{"key":"verb-to-only","title":"동사 호응 — to부정사만 받는 동사 (미래/계획)","points":["**want·hope·wish·expect·decide·plan·promise·agree·refuse** 등은 ==to부정사만== 목적어로 받는다.","대체로 **미래 지향**(계획·의지·바람)의 뜻이다.","**afford·manage·pretend·fail·tend·hesitate**도 여기에 속한다.","이 동사들 뒤에 **-ing**를 쓰면 어색하다."],"examples":[{"en":"I hope to see you again soon.","ko":"곧 또 만나길 바란다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"hope","role":"V"},{"t":"to see you again soon.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I expect to get a good grade.","ko":"좋은 성적을 받길 기대한다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"expect","role":"V"},{"t":"to get a good grade.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"They plan to travel to Europe this summer.","ko":"이번 여름에 유럽 여행을 갈 계획이다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"plan","role":"V"},{"t":"to travel to Europe","role":"O"},{"t":"this summer.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He agreed to help me with my homework.","ko":"그는 내 숙제를 도와주기로 했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"agreed","role":"V"},{"t":"to help me with my homework.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"She refused to eat her vegetables.","ko":"그녀는 채소 먹기를 거부했다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"refused","role":"V"},{"t":"to eat her vegetables.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I can't afford to buy that expensive bag.","ko":"그 비싼 가방을 살 여유가 없다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"can't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"afford","role":"V"},{"t":"to buy that expensive bag.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I managed to fix my computer.","ko":"간신히 컴퓨터를 고쳤다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"managed","role":"V"},{"t":"to fix my computer.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Don't hesitate to call me if you need anything.","ko":"필요한 게 있으면 주저 말고 전화하라.","parts":[{"t":"Don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"hesitate","role":"V"},{"t":"to call me","role":"O"},{"t":"if you need anything.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I hope seeing you again soon.","I hope to see you again soon. (hope는 **to부정사만** 받는다)"],["They plan traveling to Europe.","They plan to travel to Europe. (plan은 **to부정사만** 받는다)"],["He agreed helping me.","He agreed to help me. (agree는 **to부정사만** 받는다)"]]},{"key":"verb-ing-only","title":"동사 호응 — 동명사만 받는 동사 (과거/회피)","points":["**enjoy·mind·finish·avoid·give up·postpone·suggest·consider·deny·admit·practice** 등은 ==동명사(-ing)만== 받는다.","**이미 한 일·회피·중단**의 뜻이라 -ing와 어울린다.","이 동사들 뒤에 **to부정사**를 쓰면 틀린다.","**\"MEGA FADS\"**처럼 앞글자로 묶어 외우기도 한다."],"examples":[{"en":"I enjoy playing soccer on weekends.","ko":"주말에 축구 하는 걸 즐긴다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"enjoy","role":"V"},{"t":"playing soccer","role":"O"},{"t":"on weekends.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Do you mind closing the door?","ko":"문 좀 닫아주겠는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"mind","role":"V"},{"t":"closing the door?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"You should avoid eating too much sugar.","ko":"설탕을 너무 많이 먹는 건 피해야 한다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"avoid","role":"V"},{"t":"eating too much sugar.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Don't put off doing your chores.","ko":"집안일을 미루지 마라.","parts":[{"t":"Don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"put off","role":"V"},{"t":"doing your chores.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I suggest taking a taxi.","ko":"택시 타는 걸 제안한다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"suggest","role":"V"},{"t":"taking a taxi.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I am considering buying a new laptop.","ko":"새 노트북을 살까 고민 중이다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"am","role":"Aux"},{"t":"considering","role":"V"},{"t":"buying a new laptop.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"She admitted making a mistake.","ko":"그녀는 실수했다고 인정했다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"admitted","role":"V"},{"t":"making a mistake.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"You should practice speaking English.","ko":"영어 말하기를 연습해야 한다.","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"practice","role":"V"},{"t":"speaking English.","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["I enjoy to play soccer.","I enjoy playing soccer. (enjoy는 **동명사만** 받는다)"],["Do you mind to close the door?","Do you mind closing the door? (mind는 **동명사만** 받는다)"],["You should avoid to eat too much sugar.","You should avoid eating too much sugar. (avoid는 **동명사만** 받는다)"]]},{"key":"verb-both-and-diff","title":"동사 호응 — 둘 다 가능 & 의미가 달라지는 동사","points":["**like·love·hate·start·begin·continue·prefer**는 둘 다 받고 뜻 차이가 거의 없다.","**remember·forget·regret·try**는 형태에 따라 뜻이 ==완전히 달라진다==.","**to부정사=앞으로 할 일**, **동명사=이미 한 일**을 가리킨다.","**stop + -ing**는 \"~하던 걸 멈추다\", **stop + to부정사**는 \"~하려고 멈추다\"다."],"examples":[{"en":"I like to read. / I like reading.","ko":"나는 독서를 좋아한다. (뜻 차이 거의 없다)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"like","role":"V"},{"t":"to read. /","role":"O"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"like","role":"V"},{"t":"reading.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"It started to rain. / It started raining.","ko":"비가 오기 시작했다. (둘 다 자연스럽다)","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"started","role":"V"},{"t":"to rain. /","role":"O"},{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"started","role":"V"},{"t":"raining.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Please remember to buy some milk on your way home.","ko":"집에 올 때 우유 살 것을 기억하라. (미래: 할 일을 기억)","parts":[{"t":"Please","role":"M"},{"t":"remember","role":"V"},{"t":"to buy some milk","role":"O"},{"t":"on your way home.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I remember meeting him at the party last year.","ko":"작년 파티에서 그를 만난 게 기억난다. (과거: 한 일을 기억)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"remember","role":"V"},{"t":"meeting him","role":"O"},{"t":"at the party last year.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Don't forget to lock the door.","ko":"문 잠그는 거 잊지 마라. (미래: 할 일을 잊다)","parts":[{"t":"Don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"forget","role":"V"},{"t":"to lock the door.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I regret to say that I can't come to your party.","ko":"파티에 못 간다고 말하게 되어 유감이다. (현재: ~하게 되어 유감)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"regret","role":"V"},{"t":"to say that I can't come to your party.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I regret buying this expensive jacket.","ko":"이 비싼 재킷을 산 게 후회된다. (과거: 한 일을 후회)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"regret","role":"V"},{"t":"buying this expensive jacket.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"He stopped smoking for his health.","ko":"그는 건강을 위해 담배를 끊었다. (하던 걸 멈춤)","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"stopped","role":"V"},{"t":"smoking","role":"O"},{"t":"for his health.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He stopped to smoke.","ko":"그는 담배를 피우려고 걸음을 멈췄다. (피우기 위해 멈춤)","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"stopped","role":"V"},{"t":"to smoke.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["Please remember buying some milk on your way home.","Please remember to buy some milk. (앞으로 할 일은 **remember to**)"],["Don't forget locking the door.","Don't forget to lock the door. (앞으로 할 일은 **forget to**)"],["He stopped to smoke for his health.","He stopped smoking for his health. (하던 걸 끊는 건 **stop + -ing**)"],["I tried to add salt and the soup tasted better.","I tried adding salt and the soup tasted better. (시험 삼아 해본 건 **try + -ing**)"]]}],"db":{"title":"동사 + 목적어 DB · to부정사 vs 동명사","intro":"타동사마다 목적어로 받는 짝(to-V / V-ing)이 정해져 있다. 이걸 틀리면 회화든 라이팅이든 바로 어색해지니, ==유형별==로 묶어 익혀 둔다.","groups":[{"label":"to부정사(to-V)만 목적어로 · 미래/계획/의도","note":"앞으로 할 일·바람·결심을 나타내는 동사들이다. **\"~하기를 / ~하려고\"** 미래 지향이라 ==to-V==와 짝을 이룬다.","items":[{"w":"want","ko":"원하다","ex":"I want to eat pizza tonight."},{"w":"would like","ko":"~하고 싶다 (정중)","ex":"I would like to book a table."},{"w":"hope","ko":"바라다","ex":"I hope to see you again soon."},{"w":"wish","ko":"소망하다","ex":"I wish to talk to the manager."},{"w":"expect","ko":"기대·예상하다","ex":"I expect to get a good grade."},{"w":"decide","ko":"결정하다","ex":"We decided to stay home."},{"w":"determine","ko":"결심하다","ex":"She determined to finish the race."},{"w":"plan","ko":"계획하다","ex":"They plan to travel to Europe."},{"w":"intend","ko":"의도하다","ex":"I intend to apply next year."},{"w":"aim","ko":"목표로 하다","ex":"We aim to cut costs by half."},{"w":"promise","ko":"약속하다","ex":"I promise to pay you back tomorrow."},{"w":"agree","ko":"동의하다","ex":"He agreed to help me."},{"w":"consent","ko":"승낙하다","ex":"She consented to join the panel."},{"w":"offer","ko":"제안·제의하다","ex":"He offered to drive me home."},{"w":"volunteer","ko":"자원하다","ex":"She volunteered to lead the team."},{"w":"refuse","ko":"거절하다","ex":"She refused to eat her vegetables."},{"w":"decline","ko":"정중히 거절하다","ex":"He declined to comment."},{"w":"hesitate","ko":"주저하다","ex":"Don't hesitate to call me."},{"w":"afford","ko":"~할 여유가 있다","ex":"I can't afford to buy that bag."},{"w":"manage","ko":"간신히 해내다","ex":"I managed to fix my computer."},{"w":"fail","ko":"실패하다·못하다","ex":"I failed to pass the test."},{"w":"pretend","ko":"~인 척하다","ex":"He pretended to be asleep."},{"w":"claim","ko":"주장하다","ex":"She claims to know the truth."},{"w":"seem","ko":"~인 것 같다","ex":"He seems to be tired."},{"w":"appear","ko":"~해 보이다","ex":"They appear to be lost."},{"w":"tend","ko":"경향이 있다","ex":"I tend to eat a lot when stressed."},{"w":"learn","ko":"배우다·알게 되다","ex":"She learned to swim last summer."},{"w":"choose","ko":"선택하다","ex":"He chose to stay quiet."},{"w":"prepare","ko":"준비하다","ex":"We prepared to leave early."},{"w":"arrange","ko":"~하도록 준비·조정하다","ex":"I arranged to meet her at noon."},{"w":"prove","ko":"~임이 드러나다","ex":"The plan proved to be wrong."},{"w":"threaten","ko":"~하겠다고 위협하다","ex":"He threatened to quit."},{"w":"swear","ko":"맹세하다","ex":"She swore to never lie again."},{"w":"vow","ko":"굳게 다짐하다","ex":"He vowed to return."},{"w":"struggle","ko":"애쓰다","ex":"I struggled to stay awake."},{"w":"strive","ko":"분투하다","ex":"We strive to do better."},{"w":"long","ko":"간절히 바라다","ex":"She longs to go home."},{"w":"care","ko":"~하고 싶어하다 (부정·의문)","ex":"Would you care to join us?"},{"w":"deserve","ko":"~할 자격이 있다","ex":"You deserve to win."},{"w":"happen","ko":"우연히 ~하다","ex":"I happened to see him there."}]},{"label":"동명사(-ing)만 목적어로 · 과거/회피/진행","note":"이미 한 일·피하거나 그만두는 일을 나타낸다. **실제 경험·현재 상태** 느낌이라 ==V-ing==와 짝을 이룬다.","items":[{"w":"enjoy","ko":"즐기다","ex":"I enjoy playing soccer."},{"w":"finish","ko":"끝내다","ex":"Have you finished doing your homework?"},{"w":"mind","ko":"꺼리다","ex":"Do you mind closing the door?"},{"w":"avoid","ko":"피하다","ex":"You should avoid eating too much sugar."},{"w":"escape","ko":"모면하다","ex":"He narrowly escaped being caught."},{"w":"suggest","ko":"제안하다","ex":"I suggest taking a taxi."},{"w":"recommend","ko":"추천하다","ex":"I recommend visiting the museum."},{"w":"consider","ko":"고려하다","ex":"I am considering buying a laptop."},{"w":"imagine","ko":"상상하다","ex":"Imagine living on the moon."},{"w":"admit","ko":"인정하다","ex":"She admitted making a mistake."},{"w":"deny","ko":"부인하다","ex":"He denied breaking the window."},{"w":"practice","ko":"연습하다","ex":"You should practice speaking English."},{"w":"keep","ko":"계속하다","ex":"She kept talking for an hour."},{"w":"give up","ko":"포기하다","ex":"He gave up playing the guitar."},{"w":"quit","ko":"그만두다","ex":"He quit working there last month."},{"w":"stop","ko":"멈추다·그만두다","ex":"He stopped smoking for his health."},{"w":"put off","ko":"미루다","ex":"Don't put off doing your chores."},{"w":"postpone","ko":"연기하다","ex":"We postponed having the meeting."},{"w":"delay","ko":"지연시키다","ex":"The rain delayed starting the game."},{"w":"risk","ko":"위험을 무릅쓰다","ex":"I don't want to risk losing my job."},{"w":"miss","ko":"놓치다·~할 뻔하다","ex":"I miss seeing my old friends."},{"w":"involve","ko":"수반하다·포함하다","ex":"The job involves traveling a lot."},{"w":"finish","ko":"끝마치다","ex":"She finished writing the report."},{"w":"dislike","ko":"싫어하다","ex":"I dislike waiting in long lines."},{"w":"appreciate","ko":"고맙게 여기다","ex":"I appreciate your helping me."},{"w":"resist","ko":"참다·저항하다","ex":"I couldn't resist buying it."},{"w":"tolerate","ko":"참아내다","ex":"She won't tolerate being ignored."},{"w":"understand","ko":"이해하다","ex":"I can't understand him behaving that way."},{"w":"report","ko":"보고하다","ex":"He reported seeing the accident."},{"w":"mention","ko":"언급하다","ex":"She mentioned meeting you before."},{"w":"discuss","ko":"논의하다","ex":"We discussed moving the office."},{"w":"complete","ko":"완료하다","ex":"He completed filling out the form."},{"w":"anticipate","ko":"예상하다","ex":"We anticipate selling out fast."},{"w":"recall","ko":"기억해내다","ex":"I don't recall saying that."},{"w":"suggest","ko":"제안하다","ex":"He suggested going by train."},{"w":"can't help","ko":"~하지 않을 수 없다","ex":"I can't help laughing at that."},{"w":"feel like","ko":"~하고 싶다","ex":"I feel like taking a nap."},{"w":"give up","ko":"단념하다","ex":"Don't give up trying."},{"w":"picture","ko":"머릿속에 그리다","ex":"I can't picture him lying."},{"w":"fancy","ko":"~하고 싶다 (영국)","ex":"Do you fancy going out tonight?"}]},{"label":"둘 다 OK · 의미 차이 거의 없음","note":"**to-V**든 **V-ing**든 뜻이 사실상 같다. 골라 써도 자연스럽다.","items":[{"w":"like","ko":"좋아하다","ex":"I like to read / I like reading."},{"w":"love","ko":"사랑하다·아주 좋아하다","ex":"She loves to travel / loves traveling."},{"w":"hate","ko":"싫어하다","ex":"He hates to wait / hates waiting."},{"w":"prefer","ko":"선호하다","ex":"I prefer to stay / prefer staying home."},{"w":"begin","ko":"시작하다","ex":"She began to cry / began crying."},{"w":"start","ko":"시작하다","ex":"It started to rain / started raining."},{"w":"continue","ko":"계속하다","ex":"They continued to play / continued playing."},{"w":"bother","ko":"수고롭게 ~하다","ex":"Don't bother to call / bother calling."},{"w":"intend","ko":"의도하다","ex":"I intend to go / intend going."},{"w":"cease","ko":"그치다·중단하다","ex":"It ceased to exist / ceased existing."},{"w":"attempt","ko":"시도하다","ex":"He attempted to climb / attempted climbing."},{"w":"neglect","ko":"소홀히 하다","ex":"She neglected to reply / neglected replying."},{"w":"can't bear","ko":"참을 수 없다","ex":"I can't bear to watch / bear watching."},{"w":"propose","ko":"제안·작정하다","ex":"He proposed to wait / proposed waiting."}]},{"label":"⚠ 둘 다 OK · 의미가 완전히 달라짐","note":"형태에 따라 문장 뜻이 확 바뀐다. **to-V는 미래/목적**, **V-ing는 과거/실제 경험**을 가리킨다. 대화·라이팅에서 특히 조심한다.","items":[{"w":"remember","ko":"기억하다","ex":"remember to lock (~할 것을) / remember locking (~한 것을)"},{"w":"forget","ko":"잊다","ex":"forget to call (~할 것을) / forget calling (~한 것을)"},{"w":"regret","ko":"후회·유감","ex":"regret to say (~하게 되어 유감) / regret saying (~한 것을 후회)"},{"w":"try","ko":"시도하다·시험 삼아 해보다","ex":"try to open (힘들게 시도) / try adding (시험 삼아 해봄)"},{"w":"stop","ko":"멈추다","ex":"stop to smoke (피우려고 멈추다·목적) / stop smoking (피우던 걸 끊다·목적어)"},{"w":"go on","ko":"계속하다·넘어가다","ex":"go on to explain (다음으로 넘어가 ~하다) / go on talking (하던 걸 계속하다)"},{"w":"mean","ko":"의도하다·의미하다","ex":"mean to hurt (~하려고 의도) / mean losing (~을 의미·초래)"},{"w":"need","ko":"필요하다","ex":"I need to fix it (내가 고쳐야) / It needs fixing (고쳐질 필요=수동)"},{"w":"want","ko":"원하다·필요하다","ex":"I want to wash it (원하다) / It wants washing (씻겨야 한다=수동, 영국식)"},{"w":"come","ko":"~하게 되다","ex":"come to like (점점 ~하게 되다) / come running (달려오다·동작)"}]},{"label":"성격 형용사 + of + 목적격 (사람 성품 평가)","note":"사람의 **성품·태도**를 평가하는 형용사는 뒤에 ==\"of + 사람\"==을 쓴다. \"~하다니 (그 사람이) …하네\" 느낌이다. It was kind OF you to help. 나머지 일반 형용사(hard·easy·important·necessary…)는 **\"for + 목적격\"**이다.","items":[{"w":"kind","ko":"친절한","ex":"It was kind of you to help me."},{"w":"nice","ko":"착한·다정한","ex":"It's nice of them to invite us."},{"w":"sweet","ko":"상냥한","ex":"It was sweet of her to remember."},{"w":"thoughtful","ko":"사려 깊은","ex":"It's thoughtful of you to ask."},{"w":"considerate","ko":"배려하는","ex":"It was considerate of him to wait."},{"w":"generous","ko":"관대한·후한","ex":"It's generous of you to donate."},{"w":"polite","ko":"예의 바른","ex":"It was polite of her to say thanks."},{"w":"rude","ko":"무례한","ex":"It was rude of him to interrupt."},{"w":"brave","ko":"용감한","ex":"It's brave of you to speak up."},{"w":"wise","ko":"현명한","ex":"It was wise of them to leave early."},{"w":"clever","ko":"영리한","ex":"It's clever of her to solve it."},{"w":"smart","ko":"똑똑한","ex":"It was smart of you to save money."},{"w":"foolish","ko":"어리석은","ex":"It's foolish of him to spend it all."},{"w":"silly","ko":"바보 같은","ex":"It was silly of me to forget."},{"w":"stupid","ko":"멍청한","ex":"It was stupid of her to trust him."},{"w":"careless","ko":"부주의한","ex":"It was careless of me to lose my keys."},{"w":"cruel","ko":"잔인한","ex":"It was cruel of them to laugh."},{"w":"mean","ko":"못되게 구는","ex":"It's mean of you to tease him."},{"w":"selfish","ko":"이기적인","ex":"It was selfish of him to leave."},{"w":"wrong","ko":"잘못된","ex":"It was wrong of her to lie."},{"w":"good","ko":"착한·좋은","ex":"It's good of you to come."},{"w":"honest","ko":"정직한","ex":"It was honest of him to admit it."},{"w":"modest","ko":"겸손한","ex":"It's modest of her to say that."},{"w":"patient","ko":"인내심 있는","ex":"It was patient of you to wait so long."},{"w":"arrogant","ko":"거만한","ex":"It was arrogant of him to assume that."}]}]}},{"n":6,"title":"시제","status":"detailed","summary":"시제는 '언제'와 '어떤 상태'를 동사 형태로 표시한다. 한국어는 습관과 진행, 완료와 진행을 구분하지 않지만 영어는 **반드시 구분한다**. ==단순현재·현재진행·단순과거·과거진행·미래·완료시제==까지 신호 단어와 함께 잡아 본다.","subtopics":[{"key":"simple-present","title":"단순현재 — 습관·사실·영구 상태","points":["**단순현재**는 반복되는 습관, 변하지 않는 진리, 영구적 상태를 ==나타낸다==.","주어가 **3인칭 단수**(he/she/it)면 동사에 **-s/-es**를 붙인다.","부정은 **don't/doesn't + 동사원형**으로 만든다 — doesn't 뒤 동사엔 -s를 다시 붙이지 않는다.","always, usually, often, never 같은 **빈도부사**와 자주 함께 쓴다.","TOEFL에서 **학술 인용**(Smith argues that~)이나 일반적 사실에 핵심이다."],"examples":[{"en":"Water boils at 100 degrees Celsius.","ko":"물은 100도에서 끓는다. (변하지 않는 사실)","parts":[{"t":"Water","role":"S"},{"t":"boils","role":"V"},{"t":"at 100 degrees Celsius.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She lives in Seoul.","ko":"그녀는 서울에 산다. (영구적 상태)","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"lives","role":"V"},{"t":"in Seoul.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I study English every morning.","ko":"나는 매일 아침 영어를 공부한다. (습관)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"study","role":"V"},{"t":"English","role":"O"},{"t":"every morning.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He always drinks coffee before work.","ko":"그는 출근 전에 항상 커피를 마신다. (빈도부사)","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"always","role":"M"},{"t":"drinks","role":"V"},{"t":"coffee","role":"O"},{"t":"before work.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The Earth revolves around the Sun.","ko":"지구는 태양 주위를 공전한다. (진리)","parts":[{"t":"The Earth","role":"S"},{"t":"revolves","role":"V"},{"t":"around the Sun.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Smith argues that globalization increases inequality.","ko":"Smith는 세계화가 불평등을 키운다고 주장한다. (학술 인용)","parts":[{"t":"Smith","role":"S"},{"t":"argues","role":"V"},{"t":"that","role":"Conj"},{"t":"globalization","role":"S"},{"t":"increases","role":"V"},{"t":"inequality.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"He rarely misses a class.","ko":"그는 수업을 거의 빠지지 않는다. (빈도부사)","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"rarely","role":"M"},{"t":"misses","role":"V"},{"t":"a class.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The train doesn't arrive on time.","ko":"그 기차는 제시간에 도착하지 않는다. (부정)","parts":[{"t":"The train","role":"S"},{"t":"doesn't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"arrive","role":"V"},{"t":"on time.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"If you heat water to 100 degrees, it boils.","ko":"물을 100도로 가열하면 끓는다. (조건절, 둘 다 현재형)","parts":[{"t":"If","role":"Conj"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"heat","role":"V"},{"t":"water","role":"O"},{"t":"to 100 degrees,","role":"M"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"boils.","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["She live in Seoul.","She lives in Seoul. (3인칭 단수 주어라 **동사에 -s 필수**)"],["He doesn't likes coffee.","He doesn't like coffee. (**doesn't 뒤에는 동사원형**, -s 빼기)"],["The professor assign two essays.","The professor assigns two essays. (professor는 3인칭 단수라 **-s**)"]]},{"key":"present-progressive","title":"현재진행 — 지금·일시적·변화 추세","points":["**현재진행**은 be동사(am/is/are) + **동사-ing**로 ==만든다==.","말하는 바로 지금 진행 중, 일시적 상황, 변화 추세를 나타낸다.","now, right now, currently, these days 같은 **신호 단어**와 잘 어울린다.","**상태동사**(know, believe, want)는 진행형으로 못 쓴다.","**always + 진행형**은 짜증·불만의 감정적 뉘앙스가 된다."],"examples":[{"en":"I am writing an essay right now.","ko":"나는 지금 에세이를 쓰고 있다. (지금 진행)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"am","role":"Aux"},{"t":"writing","role":"V"},{"t":"an essay","role":"O"},{"t":"right now.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The climate is getting warmer.","ko":"기후가 점점 더 따뜻해지고 있다. (변화 추세)","parts":[{"t":"The climate","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"getting","role":"V"},{"t":"warmer.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"She is staying with friends this week.","ko":"그녀는 이번 주에 친구 집에 머물고 있다. (일시적)","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"staying","role":"V"},{"t":"with friends","role":"M"},{"t":"this week.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"More people are working from home these days.","ko":"요즘 더 많은 사람들이 재택으로 일하고 있다. (추세)","parts":[{"t":"More people","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"working","role":"V"},{"t":"from home","role":"M"},{"t":"these days.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The researchers are conducting an experiment.","ko":"연구원들이 실험을 수행하고 있다. (지금 진행)","parts":[{"t":"The researchers","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"conducting","role":"V"},{"t":"an experiment.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Online education is becoming increasingly popular.","ko":"온라인 교육이 점점 더 인기를 얻고 있다. (추세)","parts":[{"t":"Online education","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"becoming","role":"V"},{"t":"increasingly popular.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"She is always interrupting me.","ko":"그녀는 맨날 나에게 끼어들고 있다. (always + 진행형, 짜증)","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"always","role":"M"},{"t":"interrupting","role":"V"},{"t":"me.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I'm meeting my advisor tomorrow.","ko":"나는 내일 지도교수를 만난다. (확정된 개인 약속의 미래 용법)","parts":[{"t":"I'm","role":"S"},{"t":"meeting","role":"V"},{"t":"my advisor","role":"O"},{"t":"tomorrow.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I write an essay right now.","I am writing an essay right now. (**right now = 지금 진행**이라 진행형 필수)"],["I am knowing the answer.","I know the answer. (**know는 상태동사**라 진행형 불가)"],["I am believing that education is important.","I believe that education is important. (**believe는 상태동사**)"]]},{"key":"stative-verbs","title":"상태동사 — 진행형 불가 & 이중의미","points":["**상태동사**는 비자발적 인지·감정·지각·소유를 나타내 진행형과 ==충돌한다==.","know, believe, understand, love, want, need, see, have(소유), seem, cost 등이 속한다.","한국어 '알고 있다', '믿고 있다'가 자연스러워도 영어는 **단순현재**로 쓴다.","단, **think, have, see, taste, feel**은 의미가 '동작'으로 바뀌면 진행형이 가능한 **이중의미 동사**다."],"examples":[{"en":"I understand the concept.","ko":"나는 그 개념을 이해한다. (인지, 진행형 불가)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"understand","role":"V"},{"t":"the concept.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"She has two cats.","ko":"그녀는 고양이 두 마리를 키운다. (소유, 진행형 불가)","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"has","role":"V"},{"t":"two cats.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"This soup tastes delicious.","ko":"이 수프는 맛있다. (지각 상태)","parts":[{"t":"This soup","role":"S"},{"t":"tastes","role":"V"},{"t":"delicious.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The chef is tasting the soup.","ko":"요리사가 수프를 맛보고 있다. (동작, 진행형 가능)","parts":[{"t":"The chef","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"tasting","role":"V"},{"t":"the soup.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I think you're right.","ko":"나는 당신이 맞다고 생각한다. (의견, 상태)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"think","role":"V"},{"t":"you're","role":"S"},{"t":"right.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I'm thinking about the problem.","ko":"나는 그 문제를 숙고하고 있다. (동작, 진행형 가능)","parts":[{"t":"I'm","role":"S"},{"t":"thinking","role":"V"},{"t":"about the problem.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We're having dinner with the professor.","ko":"우리는 교수님과 저녁을 먹고 있다. (동작 have, 진행형 가능)","parts":[{"t":"We're","role":"S"},{"t":"having","role":"V"},{"t":"dinner","role":"O"},{"t":"with the professor.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"It costs fifty dollars.","ko":"그것은 50달러다. (비용 상태, 진행형 불가)","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"costs","role":"V"},{"t":"fifty dollars.","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["I am wanting to go home.","I want to go home. (**want는 상태동사**)"],["She is having two cats.","She has two cats. (**소유의 have는 진행형 불가**)"],["I am seeing the mountain from here.","I see the mountain from here. (**지각의 see는 진행형 불가**)"]]},{"key":"simple-past","title":"단순과거 — 완료된 사건·순서·과거 습관","points":["**단순과거**는 과거에 완료된 사건, 연속 동작, 반복 습관을 ==나타낸다==.","규칙동사는 **-ed**를 붙이고(work-worked), **불규칙동사**는 통째로 외운다(go-went, eat-ate).","부정·의문은 **did**를 쓰고, did 뒤에는 **동사원형**을 쓴다.","yesterday, last week, ago, in 2020 같은 명확한 **과거 시점**과 함께 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"I submitted my essay yesterday.","ko":"나는 어제 에세이를 제출했다. (완료된 사건)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"submitted","role":"V"},{"t":"my essay","role":"O"},{"t":"yesterday.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She graduated in 2022.","ko":"그녀는 2022년에 졸업했다. (완료된 사건)","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"graduated","role":"V"},{"t":"in 2022.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I woke up, ate breakfast, and went to school.","ko":"나는 일어나서 아침을 먹고 학교에 갔다. (순차적 사건)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"woke up,","role":"V"},{"t":"ate","role":"V"},{"t":"breakfast,","role":"O"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"went","role":"V"},{"t":"to school.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The researchers published their findings last month.","ko":"연구원들은 지난달에 연구 결과를 발표했다.","parts":[{"t":"The researchers","role":"S"},{"t":"published","role":"V"},{"t":"their findings","role":"O"},{"t":"last month.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"When I was young, I played soccer every day.","ko":"어렸을 때 나는 매일 축구를 했다. (과거 습관)","parts":[{"t":"When","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"young,","role":"SC"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"played","role":"V"},{"t":"soccer","role":"O"},{"t":"every day.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The scientist collected the samples and analyzed them.","ko":"과학자는 시료를 채취하고 분석했다. (순서)","parts":[{"t":"The scientist","role":"S"},{"t":"collected","role":"V"},{"t":"the samples","role":"O"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"analyzed","role":"V"},{"t":"them.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I didn't finish the report on time.","ko":"나는 보고서를 제때 끝내지 못했다. (부정)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"didn't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"finish","role":"V"},{"t":"the report","role":"O"},{"t":"on time.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Did you attend the lecture yesterday?","ko":"어제 강의에 참석했는가? (의문)","parts":[{"t":"Did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"attend","role":"V"},{"t":"the lecture","role":"O"},{"t":"yesterday?","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I go to school yesterday.","I went to school yesterday. (**yesterday가 있으니 과거형 went**)"],["She didn't graduated in 2022.","She didn't graduate in 2022. (**did 뒤에는 동사원형**)"],["I eated breakfast.","I ate breakfast. (**eat는 불규칙동사**, ate)"]]},{"key":"past-progressive","title":"과거진행 — 배경·중단·동시 진행","points":["**과거진행**은 was/were + **동사-ing**로 만들어 과거 시점의 배경 동작을 ==나타낸다==.","긴 배경(과거진행) 도중 짧은 사건(단순과거)이 끼어드는 **중단 패턴**이 핵심이다.","**when** 뒤엔 순간 사건(단순과거), **while** 뒤엔 지속 동작(과거진행)이 온다.","한국어 '-었-'은 완료·진행을 구분하지 않으니, 배경 묘사엔 반드시 진행형을 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"I was studying when the phone rang.","ko":"공부하고 있었는데 전화가 울렸다. (중단 패턴)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"studying","role":"V"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the phone","role":"S"},{"t":"rang.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"It was raining and people were hurrying home.","ko":"비가 오고 있었고 사람들이 집으로 서두르고 있었다. (배경 묘사)","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"raining","role":"V"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"people","role":"S"},{"t":"were","role":"Aux"},{"t":"hurrying","role":"V"},{"t":"home.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I was reading while my roommate was watching TV.","ko":"내가 책을 읽는 동안 룸메이트는 TV를 보고 있었다. (동시 진행)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"reading","role":"V"},{"t":"while","role":"Conj"},{"t":"my roommate","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"watching","role":"V"},{"t":"TV.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"While she was cooking, he was setting the table.","ko":"그녀가 요리하는 동안 그는 식탁을 차리고 있었다. (동시)","parts":[{"t":"While","role":"Conj"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"cooking,","role":"V"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"setting","role":"V"},{"t":"the table.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The professor was explaining the theory when a student raised a question.","ko":"교수가 이론을 설명하고 있었는데 한 학생이 질문했다. (중단)","parts":[{"t":"The professor","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"explaining","role":"V"},{"t":"the theory","role":"O"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"a student","role":"S"},{"t":"raised","role":"V"},{"t":"a question.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The sun was setting and the birds were singing.","ko":"해가 지고 있었고 새들이 노래하고 있었다. (장면 묘사)","parts":[{"t":"The sun","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"setting","role":"V"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the birds","role":"S"},{"t":"were","role":"Aux"},{"t":"singing.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"I was wondering if you could help me.","ko":"도움을 주실 수 있는지 궁금했다. (공손 표현)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"wondering","role":"V"},{"t":"if","role":"Conj"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"help","role":"V"},{"t":"me.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"When I arrived, she was leaving.","ko":"내가 도착했을 때 그녀는 나가고 있었다. (도착 시점에 출발이 진행 중)","parts":[{"t":"When","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"arrived,","role":"V"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"leaving.","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["I studied when the phone rang.","I was studying when the phone rang. (**배경 동작은 진행형으로**)"],["While I read, my roommate watched TV.","While I was reading, my roommate was watching TV. (**동시 진행은 진행형**)"],["When I arrived, she was leaving vs left","의미 차이 주의: 'she left'는 도착 후 떠남(순차), 'she was leaving'은 도착 시 이미 나가는 중 (**시제로 의미가 달라진다**)"]]},{"key":"future","title":"미래 — will / be going to / 현재형의 미래 용법","points":["미래는 여러 형태로 ==표현한다==.","**will**은 즉흥적 결정, 순수 예측·의견, 약속에 쓴다.","**be going to**는 이미 세운 계획이나 눈에 보이는 근거가 있는 예측에 쓴다.","확정된 개인 약속은 **현재진행**, 기관이 정한 공식 시간표는 **단순현재**로 미래를 나타낸다.","**will be + 동사-ing**(미래진행)는 미래 특정 시점의 진행·공손한 질문에 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"I'll help you with that.","ko":"내가 그거 도와주겠다. (즉흥 결정)","parts":[{"t":"I'll","role":"S"},{"t":"help","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"O"},{"t":"with that.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I think AI will transform education.","ko":"나는 AI가 교육을 바꿀 거라고 생각한다. (의견 예측)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"think","role":"V"},{"t":"AI","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"transform","role":"V"},{"t":"education.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I'm going to study abroad next year.","ko":"나는 내년에 유학을 갈 것이다. (이미 결정한 계획)","parts":[{"t":"I'm","role":"S"},{"t":"going to","role":"Aux"},{"t":"study","role":"V"},{"t":"abroad","role":"M"},{"t":"next year.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Look at those clouds — it's going to rain.","ko":"저 구름을 보라 — 비가 올 것이다. (눈앞의 근거)","parts":[{"t":"Look","role":"V"},{"t":"at those clouds —","role":"M"},{"t":"it's","role":"S"},{"t":"going to","role":"Aux"},{"t":"rain.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The exam starts at 9 AM.","ko":"시험은 오전 9시에 시작한다. (기관 시간표, 단순현재)","parts":[{"t":"The exam","role":"S"},{"t":"starts","role":"V"},{"t":"at 9 AM.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I'm flying to New York next week.","ko":"나는 다음 주에 뉴욕으로 간다. (비행기표 구매 완료, 현재진행)","parts":[{"t":"I'm","role":"S"},{"t":"flying","role":"V"},{"t":"to New York","role":"M"},{"t":"next week.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"At this time tomorrow, I'll be taking the TOEFL.","ko":"내일 이 시간에 나는 TOEFL을 보고 있을 것이다. (미래진행)","parts":[{"t":"At this time tomorrow,","role":"M"},{"t":"I'll","role":"S"},{"t":"be","role":"Aux"},{"t":"taking","role":"V"},{"t":"the TOEFL.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Will you be attending the conference?","ko":"컨퍼런스에 참석할 것인가? (공손한 질문)","parts":[{"t":"Will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"be","role":"Aux"},{"t":"attending","role":"V"},{"t":"the conference?","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["It's raining, I think I take an umbrella.","It's raining, I think I'll take an umbrella. (**즉흥 결정은 will**)"],["Look, it will rain — the sky is dark.","Look, it's going to rain — the sky is dark. (**눈에 보이는 근거는 be going to**)"],["The exam is starting at 9 tomorrow.","The exam starts at 9 tomorrow. (**공식 시간표는 단순현재**가 자연스럽다)"]]},{"key":"time-clause-trap","title":"시간·조건절의 현재시제 — will 금지","points":["when, before, after, until, as soon as, if, unless 뒤에서는 미래 의미여도 ==현재형==을 쓴다.","주절의 **will**이 이미 미래 시간을 정해주기 때문이다.","한국어는 종속절에서도 미래 표현이 자유로워 실수하기 쉽다.","단, **명사절**(know/wonder의 목적어)의 when에는 will을 쓸 수 있다.","이 오류 하나만 고쳐도 **점수가 크게 오른다**."],"examples":[{"en":"When I graduate, I will look for a job.","ko":"졸업하면 일자리를 찾을 것이다. (when절은 현재형)","parts":[{"t":"When","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"graduate,","role":"V"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"look","role":"V"},{"t":"for a job.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Before the deadline arrives, I will finish.","ko":"마감이 오기 전에 끝낼 것이다. (before절은 현재형)","parts":[{"t":"Before","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the deadline","role":"S"},{"t":"arrives,","role":"V"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"finish.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"I'll wait until you finish.","ko":"당신이 끝낼 때까지 기다릴 것이다. (until절은 현재형)","parts":[{"t":"I'll","role":"S"},{"t":"wait","role":"V"},{"t":"until","role":"Conj"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"finish.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"If it rains tomorrow, I will stay home.","ko":"내일 비가 오면 집에 있을 것이다. (if절은 현재형)","parts":[{"t":"If","role":"Conj"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"rains","role":"V"},{"t":"tomorrow,","role":"M"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"stay","role":"V"},{"t":"home.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"As soon as everyone arrives, the meeting will begin.","ko":"모두 도착하는 대로 회의가 시작될 것이다. (as soon as절은 현재형)","parts":[{"t":"As soon as","role":"Conj"},{"t":"everyone","role":"S"},{"t":"arrives,","role":"V"},{"t":"the meeting","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"begin.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Unless you study, you won't pass.","ko":"공부하지 않으면 통과하지 못한다. (unless절은 현재형)","parts":[{"t":"Unless","role":"Conj"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"study,","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"won't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"pass.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"I don't know when she will arrive.","ko":"그녀가 언제 도착할지 모르겠다. (명사절이라 will 가능)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"when","role":"Conj"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"arrive.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Once the results come out, we will discuss them.","ko":"결과가 나오면 우리는 논의할 것이다. (once절은 현재형)","parts":[{"t":"Once","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the results","role":"S"},{"t":"come out,","role":"V"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"discuss","role":"V"},{"t":"them.","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["When I will graduate, I will look for a job.","When I graduate, I will look for a job. (**시간절에는 will 금지**, 현재형)"],["If it will rain tomorrow, I will stay home.","If it rains tomorrow, I will stay home. (**조건절에는 will 금지**)"],["I'll wait until you will finish.","I'll wait until you finish. (**until절은 현재형**)"]]},{"key":"present-perfect","title":"현재완료 — 과거와 현재의 연결","points":["**현재완료**는 have/has + **과거분사**(p.p.)로 만들어 과거와 현재를 ==연결한다==.","네 가지 용법이 있다: **경험·계속·완료·결과**.","**already, yet, just, ever, never**는 완료·경험과 어울린다.","**since**(시점)와 **for**(기간)는 계속과 어울린다.","yesterday, in 2020처럼 명확한 과거 시점이 있으면 **단순과거**를 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"I have visited Paris three times.","ko":"나는 파리에 세 번 가 봤다. (경험)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"visited","role":"V"},{"t":"Paris","role":"O"},{"t":"three times.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She has lived here for ten years.","ko":"그녀는 여기 10년째 살고 있다. (계속, for + 기간)","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"has","role":"Aux"},{"t":"lived","role":"V"},{"t":"here","role":"M"},{"t":"for ten years.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I have known him since 2015.","ko":"나는 2015년부터 그를 알아 왔다. (계속, since + 시점)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"known","role":"V"},{"t":"him","role":"O"},{"t":"since 2015.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I have just finished my essay.","ko":"나는 방금 에세이를 끝냈다. (완료, just)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"just","role":"M"},{"t":"finished","role":"V"},{"t":"my essay.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Have you eaten lunch yet?","ko":"점심 벌써 먹었는가? (완료, yet)","parts":[{"t":"Have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"eaten","role":"V"},{"t":"lunch","role":"O"},{"t":"yet?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He has already submitted the report.","ko":"그는 이미 보고서를 제출했다. (완료, already)","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"has","role":"Aux"},{"t":"already","role":"M"},{"t":"submitted","role":"V"},{"t":"the report.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I have never been to Japan.","ko":"나는 일본에 가 본 적이 없다. (경험, never)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"never","role":"M"},{"t":"been","role":"V"},{"t":"to Japan.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She has lost her keys, so she can't get in.","ko":"그녀는 열쇠를 잃어버려서 못 들어간다. (결과)","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"has","role":"Aux"},{"t":"lost","role":"V"},{"t":"her keys,","role":"O"},{"t":"so","role":"Conj"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"can't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"get in.","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["I have submitted my essay yesterday.","I submitted my essay yesterday. (**명확한 과거 시점 yesterday면 단순과거**)"],["She has lived here since ten years.","She has lived here for ten years. (**기간에는 for, 시점에는 since**)"],["I have saw that movie.","I have seen that movie. (**완료는 과거분사 seen**, saw 아님)"]]},{"key":"past-perfect","title":"과거완료 — 대과거(과거보다 더 과거)","points":["**과거완료**는 had + **과거분사**(p.p.)로 만들어 과거의 한 시점보다 ==더 이전==의 일을 나타낸다.","이를 **대과거**라고 한다.","먼저 일어난 일에 **과거완료**, 나중 일에 **단순과거**를 써서 순서를 분명히 한다.","**before, after, by the time, already**와 자주 함께 쓴다.","**when**으로 두 과거 사건의 앞뒤 관계를 표시할 때 유용하다."],"examples":[{"en":"When I arrived, the train had already left.","ko":"내가 도착했을 때 기차는 이미 떠난 뒤였다. (도착보다 출발이 먼저)","parts":[{"t":"When","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"arrived,","role":"V"},{"t":"the train","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"already","role":"M"},{"t":"left.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"She had finished her homework before dinner.","ko":"그녀는 저녁 전에 숙제를 끝냈다. (저녁보다 숙제가 먼저)","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"finished","role":"V"},{"t":"her homework","role":"O"},{"t":"before dinner.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"By the time the professor came, we had prepared everything.","ko":"교수님이 오셨을 때쯤 우리는 모든 걸 준비해 둔 상태였다.","parts":[{"t":"By the time","role":"Conj"},{"t":"the professor","role":"S"},{"t":"came,","role":"V"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"prepared","role":"V"},{"t":"everything.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I realized I had left my phone at home.","ko":"나는 집에 휴대폰을 두고 온 걸 깨달았다. (깨달음보다 두고 온 게 먼저)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"realized","role":"V"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"left","role":"V"},{"t":"my phone","role":"O"},{"t":"at home.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He had studied English for years before he moved abroad.","ko":"그는 해외로 가기 전에 몇 년간 영어를 공부했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"studied","role":"V"},{"t":"English","role":"O"},{"t":"for years","role":"M"},{"t":"before","role":"Conj"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"moved","role":"V"},{"t":"abroad.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"They had never seen snow until they visited Korea.","ko":"그들은 한국에 오기 전까지 눈을 본 적이 없었다. (경험, 대과거)","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"never","role":"M"},{"t":"seen","role":"V"},{"t":"snow","role":"O"},{"t":"until","role":"Conj"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"visited","role":"V"},{"t":"Korea.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"After she had submitted the essay, she felt relieved.","ko":"에세이를 제출한 뒤 그녀는 안도했다. (제출이 먼저)","parts":[{"t":"After","role":"Conj"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"submitted","role":"V"},{"t":"the essay,","role":"O"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"felt","role":"V"},{"t":"relieved.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The room was empty; everyone had gone home.","ko":"방은 비어 있었다; 모두 집에 가 버린 뒤였다. (결과)","parts":[{"t":"The room","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"empty;","role":"SC"},{"t":"everyone","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"gone","role":"V"},{"t":"home.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["When I arrived, the train already left.","When I arrived, the train had already left. (**먼저 일어난 일은 과거완료**)"],["She had finish her homework before dinner.","She had finished her homework before dinner. (**had 뒤에는 과거분사**)"],["I realized I have left my phone at home.","I realized I had left my phone at home. (**과거 기준 더 이전은 과거완료 had left**)"]]},{"key":"modal-perfect","title":"조동사완료 — should/could/must have p.p.","points":["**조동사 + have + 과거분사**(p.p.)는 과거의 일에 대한 추측·후회·비판을 ==나타낸다==.","**should have p.p.**: ~했어야 했는데(안 해서 후회).","**could have p.p.**: ~할 수도 있었는데(안 함).","**must have p.p.**: ~했음이 틀림없다(강한 확신).","**might/may have p.p.**: ~했을지도 모른다(약한 추측).","발음은 'shoulda/coulda/musta'처럼 약해져도 글로는 반드시 **have**를 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"I should have studied harder for the exam.","ko":"시험 공부를 더 열심히 했어야 했다. (후회)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"studied","role":"V"},{"t":"harder","role":"M"},{"t":"for the exam.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"You should have told me earlier.","ko":"나에게 더 일찍 말해줬어야 했다. (아쉬움)","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"told","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"earlier.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She could have passed if she had tried.","ko":"그녀가 노력했다면 통과할 수 있었을 것이다. (가능성)","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"passed","role":"V"},{"t":"if","role":"Conj"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"tried.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"He must have forgotten the meeting.","ko":"그는 회의를 잊어버린 게 틀림없다. (강한 확신)","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"must","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"forgotten","role":"V"},{"t":"the meeting.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"They must have left already; the lights are off.","ko":"그들은 이미 떠난 게 틀림없다; 불이 꺼져 있다. (추측)","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"must","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"left","role":"V"},{"t":"already;","role":"M"},{"t":"the lights","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"off.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I might have left my umbrella on the bus.","ko":"나는 버스에 우산을 두고 왔을지도 모른다. (약한 추측)","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"might","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"left","role":"V"},{"t":"my umbrella","role":"O"},{"t":"on the bus.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"You could have called me — I was worried.","ko":"나에게 전화할 수도 있었다 — 걱정했다. (비판)","parts":[{"t":"You","role":"S"},{"t":"could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"called","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"—","role":"M"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"worried.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"She may have misunderstood the instructions.","ko":"그녀는 지시를 오해했을지도 모른다. (약한 추측)","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"may","role":"Aux"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"misunderstood","role":"V"},{"t":"the instructions.","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["I should studied harder.","I should have studied harder. (**조동사완료는 should + have + p.p.**)"],["He must have forgot the meeting.","He must have forgotten the meeting. (**have 뒤에는 과거분사 forgotten**)"],["You should of told me.","You should have told me. (**'should of'는 잘못된 표기**, have가 맞음)"]]}],"db":{"title":"시제 DB · 불규칙동사 & 시제 표현","intro":"시제의 핵심은 '언제(과거·현재·미래)'와 '어떤 상태(단순·진행·완료)'다. 특히 **불규칙동사**는 과거·과거분사 형태를 통째로 외워야 실수가 없다. 완료시제 부사어와 미래 표현까지 함께 정리했으니, ==표를 여러 번 훑으면서== 감을 잡아 본다.","groups":[{"label":"불규칙동사 · AAA형 (원형=과거=과거분사)","note":"세 형태가 모두 같다. 과거인지 현재인지는 **문맥으로 판단한다**. read는 철자는 같지만 과거·과거분사는 '레드'로 발음한다.","items":[{"w":"cut","ko":"자르다","ex":"cut / cut"},{"w":"put","ko":"놓다, 두다","ex":"put / put"},{"w":"let","ko":"허락하다","ex":"let / let"},{"w":"set","ko":"놓다, 설정하다","ex":"set / set"},{"w":"hit","ko":"치다","ex":"hit / hit"},{"w":"hurt","ko":"다치게 하다, 아프다","ex":"hurt / hurt"},{"w":"cost","ko":"비용이 들다","ex":"cost / cost"},{"w":"read","ko":"읽다 (과거는 '레드' 발음)","ex":"read / read"},{"w":"shut","ko":"닫다","ex":"shut / shut"},{"w":"quit","ko":"그만두다","ex":"quit / quit"},{"w":"spread","ko":"펼치다, 퍼지다","ex":"spread / spread"},{"w":"split","ko":"쪼개다","ex":"split / split"},{"w":"burst","ko":"터지다","ex":"burst / burst"},{"w":"cast","ko":"던지다, 배역을 맡기다","ex":"cast / cast"},{"w":"bet","ko":"내기하다","ex":"bet / bet"},{"w":"beat","ko":"때리다, 이기다 (과거분사는 beaten도 가능)","ex":"beat / beaten"}]},{"label":"불규칙동사 · ABA형 (원형=과거분사)","note":"과거형만 다르고, **원형과 과거분사가 같다**.","items":[{"w":"come","ko":"오다","ex":"came / come"},{"w":"become","ko":"~이 되다","ex":"became / become"},{"w":"run","ko":"달리다","ex":"ran / run"},{"w":"overcome","ko":"극복하다","ex":"overcame / overcome"}]},{"label":"불규칙동사 · ABB형 (과거=과거분사)","note":"과거와 과거분사가 같아서 외우기 상대적으로 쉽다. **시험에 정말 자주 나온다**.","items":[{"w":"bring","ko":"가져오다","ex":"brought / brought"},{"w":"buy","ko":"사다","ex":"bought / bought"},{"w":"catch","ko":"잡다","ex":"caught / caught"},{"w":"teach","ko":"가르치다","ex":"taught / taught"},{"w":"think","ko":"생각하다","ex":"thought / thought"},{"w":"fight","ko":"싸우다","ex":"fought / fought"},{"w":"seek","ko":"찾다, 구하다","ex":"sought / sought"},{"w":"find","ko":"찾다, 발견하다","ex":"found / found"},{"w":"feel","ko":"느끼다","ex":"felt / felt"},{"w":"keep","ko":"유지하다","ex":"kept / kept"},{"w":"sleep","ko":"자다","ex":"slept / slept"},{"w":"sweep","ko":"쓸다","ex":"swept / swept"},{"w":"leave","ko":"떠나다, 남기다","ex":"left / left"},{"w":"lose","ko":"잃다, 지다","ex":"lost / lost"},{"w":"make","ko":"만들다","ex":"made / made"},{"w":"mean","ko":"의미하다","ex":"meant / meant"},{"w":"meet","ko":"만나다","ex":"met / met"},{"w":"pay","ko":"지불하다","ex":"paid / paid"},{"w":"say","ko":"말하다","ex":"said / said"},{"w":"lay","ko":"놓다, 눕히다","ex":"laid / laid"},{"w":"sell","ko":"팔다","ex":"sold / sold"},{"w":"tell","ko":"말하다, 알려주다","ex":"told / told"},{"w":"send","ko":"보내다","ex":"sent / sent"},{"w":"spend","ko":"쓰다, 소비하다","ex":"spent / spent"},{"w":"lend","ko":"빌려주다","ex":"lent / lent"},{"w":"bend","ko":"구부리다","ex":"bent / bent"},{"w":"build","ko":"짓다","ex":"built / built"},{"w":"sit","ko":"앉다","ex":"sat / sat"},{"w":"stand","ko":"서다","ex":"stood / stood"},{"w":"understand","ko":"이해하다","ex":"understood / understood"},{"w":"win","ko":"이기다","ex":"won / won"},{"w":"hold","ko":"잡다, 개최하다","ex":"held / held"},{"w":"hear","ko":"듣다","ex":"heard / heard"},{"w":"lead","ko":"이끌다","ex":"led / led"},{"w":"feed","ko":"먹이다","ex":"fed / fed"},{"w":"read","ko":"읽다","ex":"read / read"},{"w":"light","ko":"불을 켜다","ex":"lit / lit"},{"w":"lose","ko":"잃다","ex":"lost / lost"},{"w":"shoot","ko":"쏘다","ex":"shot / shot"},{"w":"get","ko":"얻다 (미국식 과거분사는 gotten)","ex":"got / gotten"},{"w":"sting","ko":"쏘다, 찌르다","ex":"stung / stung"},{"w":"swing","ko":"흔들리다","ex":"swung / swung"},{"w":"hang","ko":"걸다","ex":"hung / hung"},{"w":"dig","ko":"파다","ex":"dug / dug"},{"w":"stick","ko":"붙이다, 찌르다","ex":"stuck / stuck"},{"w":"strike","ko":"치다, 파업하다","ex":"struck / struck"}]},{"label":"불규칙동사 · ABC형 (셋 다 다름)","note":"세 형태가 모두 달라서 가장 헷갈린다. 과거분사에 **-en**이 붙는 경우가 많다. 완료시제·수동태에서 과거분사가 필수라 반드시 외워 둔다.","items":[{"w":"go","ko":"가다","ex":"went / gone"},{"w":"do","ko":"하다","ex":"did / done"},{"w":"eat","ko":"먹다","ex":"ate / eaten"},{"w":"give","ko":"주다","ex":"gave / given"},{"w":"take","ko":"가지다, 데려가다","ex":"took / taken"},{"w":"see","ko":"보다","ex":"saw / seen"},{"w":"write","ko":"쓰다","ex":"wrote / written"},{"w":"speak","ko":"말하다","ex":"spoke / spoken"},{"w":"break","ko":"깨다, 부수다","ex":"broke / broken"},{"w":"choose","ko":"선택하다","ex":"chose / chosen"},{"w":"drive","ko":"운전하다","ex":"drove / driven"},{"w":"know","ko":"알다","ex":"knew / known"},{"w":"grow","ko":"자라다, 기르다","ex":"grew / grown"},{"w":"fly","ko":"날다","ex":"flew / flown"},{"w":"draw","ko":"그리다, 끌다","ex":"drew / drawn"},{"w":"throw","ko":"던지다","ex":"threw / thrown"},{"w":"blow","ko":"불다","ex":"blew / blown"},{"w":"show","ko":"보여주다","ex":"showed / shown"},{"w":"begin","ko":"시작하다","ex":"began / begun"},{"w":"drink","ko":"마시다","ex":"drank / drunk"},{"w":"sing","ko":"노래하다","ex":"sang / sung"},{"w":"swim","ko":"수영하다","ex":"swam / swum"},{"w":"ring","ko":"울리다","ex":"rang / rung"},{"w":"sink","ko":"가라앉다","ex":"sank / sunk"},{"w":"ride","ko":"타다","ex":"rode / ridden"},{"w":"rise","ko":"오르다","ex":"rose / risen"},{"w":"wear","ko":"입다","ex":"wore / worn"},{"w":"tear","ko":"찢다","ex":"tore / torn"},{"w":"swear","ko":"맹세하다","ex":"swore / sworn"},{"w":"bear","ko":"견디다, 낳다","ex":"bore / borne"},{"w":"fall","ko":"떨어지다","ex":"fell / fallen"},{"w":"forget","ko":"잊다","ex":"forgot / forgotten"},{"w":"forgive","ko":"용서하다","ex":"forgave / forgiven"},{"w":"hide","ko":"숨다, 숨기다","ex":"hid / hidden"},{"w":"bite","ko":"물다","ex":"bit / bitten"},{"w":"steal","ko":"훔치다","ex":"stole / stolen"},{"w":"wake","ko":"깨다, 깨우다","ex":"woke / woken"},{"w":"freeze","ko":"얼다, 얼리다","ex":"froze / frozen"},{"w":"speak","ko":"말하다","ex":"spoke / spoken"},{"w":"shake","ko":"흔들다","ex":"shook / shaken"},{"w":"take","ko":"가져가다","ex":"took / taken"},{"w":"mistake","ko":"오해하다, 착각하다","ex":"mistook / mistaken"},{"w":"is/am/are (be)","ko":"~이다, 있다","ex":"was·were / been"},{"w":"lie","ko":"눕다, 놓여 있다","ex":"lay / lain"}]},{"label":"완료시제 부사어 (현재완료와 함께)","note":"현재완료(have/has + 과거분사)는 '과거~지금'을 잇는 시제라, 아래 부사어들과 짝을 이룬다. 참고로 **yesterday, ~ago, last week** 같은 '끝난 과거 시점'은 현재완료와 못 쓴다.","items":[{"w":"already","ko":"이미, 벌써 (긍정문). 보통 have와 과거분사 사이","ex":"I have already finished. (벌써 끝냈어요)"},{"w":"yet","ko":"아직(부정문)·벌써(의문문). 문장 끝에","ex":"I haven't finished yet. (아직 안 끝났어요)"},{"w":"just","ko":"방금, 막. have와 과거분사 사이","ex":"She has just left. (방금 떠났어요)"},{"w":"ever","ko":"지금까지(주로 의문문). 과거분사 앞","ex":"Have you ever been to Paris? (가본 적 있어요?)"},{"w":"never","ko":"한 번도 ~않은. 과거분사 앞","ex":"I have never seen it. (한 번도 못 봤어요)"},{"w":"so far","ko":"지금까지, 여태껏. 주로 문장 끝","ex":"So far, we have finished three tasks. (지금까지 세 개 끝냈어요)"},{"w":"recently","ko":"최근에. 문장 앞·끝, 또는 과거분사 앞","ex":"He has recently moved. (최근에 이사했어요)"},{"w":"lately","ko":"요즘, 최근에. 주로 문장 끝","ex":"I haven't slept well lately. (요즘 잠을 못 잤어요)"},{"w":"since + 시점","ko":"~ 이후로 (시작점). since 2020, since last year","ex":"I have lived here since 2020. (2020년부터 살았어요)"},{"w":"for + 기간","ko":"~ 동안 (지속 기간). for three years, for a week","ex":"She has worked here for five years. (5년 동안 일했어요)"},{"w":"before","ko":"전에 (막연한 과거 경험). 문장 끝","ex":"I have seen this movie before. (전에 본 적 있어요)"},{"w":"how long","ko":"얼마나 오래 (기간 질문). 문장 앞","ex":"How long have you studied English? (얼마나 공부했어요?)"},{"w":"up to now","ko":"지금까지, 현재까지. 문장 앞·끝","ex":"Up to now, everything has gone well. (지금까지 잘 됐어요)"},{"w":"once / twice / ~ times","ko":"한 번·두 번·~번 (경험 횟수). 과거분사 뒤","ex":"I have been there twice. (두 번 가봤어요)"}]},{"label":"미래 표현 · 뉘앙스 구분","note":"영어 미래는 형태마다 뉘앙스가 다르다. '지금 결정했나 vs 이미 계획했나', '근거가 있나 vs 순수 추측인가'로 구분하면 **감이 잡힌다**.","items":[{"w":"will + 동사원형","ko":"즉흥적 결정·의견 예측·약속/의지. 말하는 순간 정한 느낌","ex":"I'll help you. / AI will change the world."},{"w":"be going to + 동사원형","ko":"이미 세운 계획·눈에 보이는 근거가 있는 예측. 미리 결정된 느낌","ex":"I'm going to study abroad. / Look at the clouds—it's going to rain."},{"w":"be about to + 동사원형","ko":"막 ~하려는 참이다. 아주 가까운 미래(직전)","ex":"The movie is about to start. (막 시작하려 해요)"},{"w":"be to + 동사원형","ko":"공식 예정·의무·운명. 격식체·뉴스/공지에 많이 쓰여요","ex":"The president is to visit Korea. (방문할 예정이다)"},{"w":"현재진행형 (be + V-ing)","ko":"이미 확정된 개인 약속·일정. 티켓 구매·예약처럼 준비된 미래","ex":"I'm meeting my advisor tomorrow. (내일 만나기로 약속됨)"},{"w":"단순현재 (V-s/es)","ko":"시간표·공식 일정처럼 정해진 스케줄. 기관이 정한 미래","ex":"The train leaves at 6 PM. (기차는 6시에 출발해요)"},{"w":"will be + V-ing (미래진행)","ko":"미래 특정 시점에 진행 중·당연한 흐름·공손한 질문","ex":"At this time tomorrow, I'll be taking the test."},{"w":"시간·조건절 주의","ko":"when·before·after·until·if·as soon as 뒤에는 미래여도 현재형! (will 금지)","ex":"When I graduate, I will look for a job."}]}]}},{"n":7,"title":"직접의문문","status":"detailed","summary":"질문을 그대로 던지는 **직접의문문**을 유형별로 정리한다. Yes/No 의문문(be동사·do/does/did·조동사·완료 have 도치), 부정 의문문, Wh- 의문문, 의문사가 주어인 경우, 긴 의문사구, 전치사+의문사, 선택의문문까지 ==도치 규칙과 어순==을 예문으로 익힌다.","subtopics":[{"key":"yn-be","title":"Yes/No 의문문 ① Be동사 도치","points":["본동사가 **be동사**(am·are·is·was·were)이면 조동사 없이 ==주어와 be동사의 자리만 바꾼다==.","\"You are ready\" → \"Are you ready?\"처럼 be동사를 문장 맨 앞으로 보낸다.","**현재진행**(be+ing)·**수동태**(be+p.p.)도 앞에 있는 be만 도치한다.","주어의 인칭·수에 맞춰 **is/are**, **was/were**를 골라 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"Are you ready to order?","ko":"주문할 준비가 됐는가?","parts":[{"t":"Are","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"ready","role":"SC"},{"t":"to order?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Is the Wi-Fi working in this room?","ko":"이 방 와이파이가 되는가?","parts":[{"t":"Is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"the Wi-Fi","role":"S"},{"t":"working","role":"V"},{"t":"in this room?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Am I in the right line for the tickets?","ko":"내가 티켓 줄을 제대로 선 것인가?","parts":[{"t":"Am","role":"V"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"in the right line","role":"M"},{"t":"for the tickets?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Are they still open at this hour?","ko":"그곳이 이 시간에도 열려 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Are","role":"V"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"still","role":"M"},{"t":"open","role":"SC"},{"t":"at this hour?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Is it raining outside?","ko":"밖에 비가 오는가?","parts":[{"t":"Is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"raining","role":"V"},{"t":"outside?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Were you at home yesterday afternoon?","ko":"어제 오후에 집에 있었는가?","parts":[{"t":"Were","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"at home","role":"M"},{"t":"yesterday afternoon?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Was she wearing a red dress?","ko":"그녀가 빨간 드레스를 입고 있었는가?","parts":[{"t":"Was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"wearing","role":"V"},{"t":"a red dress?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Are these shoes on sale?","ko":"이 신발이 세일 중인가?","parts":[{"t":"Are","role":"V"},{"t":"these shoes","role":"S"},{"t":"on sale?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Is your brother coming with us?","ko":"네 형도 우리와 같이 가는가?","parts":[{"t":"Is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"your brother","role":"S"},{"t":"coming","role":"V"},{"t":"with us?","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["Do you ready?","Are you ready? (**be동사 문장**은 do를 쓰지 않고 be동사를 앞으로 보낸다)"],["Is raining outside?","Is it raining outside? (**주어 it**을 빠뜨리면 안 된다)"],["Are she your roommate?","Is she your roommate? (**3인칭 단수 주어**엔 is를 쓴다)"]]},{"key":"yn-do","title":"Yes/No 의문문 ② 일반동사 Do/Does/Did","points":["일반동사는 스스로 못 나가서 ==조동사 Do/Does/Did==를 주어 앞에 세운다.","현재 **3인칭 단수**는 Does, 나머지 현재는 Do, 과거는 인칭과 무관하게 Did를 쓴다.","Does·Did에 이미 3인칭·과거 표시가 들어가 **본동사는 원형**으로 둔다.","\"She likes coffee\" → \"Does she like coffee?\"로 바뀐다."],"examples":[{"en":"Do you want to grab lunch together?","ko":"같이 점심을 먹겠는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"want","role":"V"},{"t":"to grab lunch","role":"O"},{"t":"together?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Does this bus go to the airport?","ko":"이 버스가 공항에 가는가?","parts":[{"t":"Does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"this bus","role":"S"},{"t":"go","role":"V"},{"t":"to the airport?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Do they accept credit cards here?","ko":"여기서 신용카드를 받는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"accept","role":"V"},{"t":"credit cards","role":"O"},{"t":"here?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Does the store close at 9 PM?","ko":"그 가게가 밤 9시에 닫는가?","parts":[{"t":"Does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"the store","role":"S"},{"t":"close","role":"V"},{"t":"at 9 PM?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Did you lock the front door?","ko":"현관문을 잠갔는가?","parts":[{"t":"Did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"lock","role":"V"},{"t":"the front door?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Did she call you last night?","ko":"어젯밤에 그녀가 전화했는가?","parts":[{"t":"Did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"call","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"O"},{"t":"last night?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Do your parents live nearby?","ko":"부모님이 근처에 사시는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"your parents","role":"S"},{"t":"live","role":"V"},{"t":"nearby?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Did the package arrive yesterday?","ko":"어제 택배가 도착했는가?","parts":[{"t":"Did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"the package","role":"S"},{"t":"arrive","role":"V"},{"t":"yesterday?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Does it hurt when you press here?","ko":"여기를 누르면 아픈가?","parts":[{"t":"Does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"hurt","role":"V"},{"t":"when you press here?","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["Does she likes coffee?","Does she like coffee? (**Does 뒤 본동사**는 원형이다)"],["Did you locked the door?","Did you lock the door? (**Did 뒤 본동사**는 원형이다)"],["Do he play the guitar?","Does he play the guitar? (**3인칭 단수 현재**는 Does이다)"],["You want some coffee?","Do you want some coffee? (**일반동사 의문문**엔 Do를 넣는다)"]]},{"key":"yn-modal","title":"Yes/No 의문문 ③ 서법·준조동사","points":["**Can·Will·Should·May·Must** 같은 서법조동사는 바로 주어 앞으로 나가고 뒤에 ==원형==이 온다.","have to·need to·used to 같은 **준조동사**는 일반동사 취급이라 Do/Does/Did의 도움을 받는다.","예: \"Do we have to go?\"처럼 do로 묻는다.","**ought to**만 예외로 \"Ought we to go?\"처럼 스스로 도치할 수 있다."],"examples":[{"en":"Can you help me move this sofa?","ko":"이 소파를 옮기는 것을 도와줄 수 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"help","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"move this sofa?","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"Should I wear a suit to the interview?","ko":"면접에 정장을 입고 가야 하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"wear","role":"V"},{"t":"a suit","role":"O"},{"t":"to the interview?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Will you be home for dinner?","ko":"저녁을 먹으러 집에 올 것인가?","parts":[{"t":"Will","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"be","role":"V"},{"t":"home","role":"SC"},{"t":"for dinner?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"May I use your restroom?","ko":"화장실을 써도 되는가?","parts":[{"t":"May","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"use","role":"V"},{"t":"your restroom?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Could you pass me the salt?","ko":"소금을 좀 건네줄 수 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"pass","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"IO"},{"t":"the salt?","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"Must we attend the orientation?","ko":"오리엔테이션에 꼭 참석해야 하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Must","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"attend","role":"V"},{"t":"the orientation?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Do we have to submit it today?","ko":"오늘 그것을 제출해야 하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"have to submit","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"today?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Do you need to verify the account?","ko":"계정을 인증해야 하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"need to verify","role":"V"},{"t":"the account?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Did you use to live in Seattle?","ko":"예전에 시애틀에 살았는가?","parts":[{"t":"Did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"use to live","role":"V"},{"t":"in Seattle?","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["Can you to help me?","Can you help me? (**조동사 뒤 본동사**는 to 없이 원형이다)"],["Have we to submit it today?","Do we have to submit it today? (**have to는 준조동사**라 Do로 묻는다)"],["Should we to order pizza?","Should we order pizza? (**조동사 뒤**엔 원형만 온다)"]]},{"key":"yn-perfect","title":"Yes/No 의문문 ④ 완료시제 Have/Has/Had","points":["완료시제(have/has/had+p.p.)의 have는 ==조동사==라 바로 주어 앞으로 나간다.","\"You have seen him\" → \"Have you seen him?\"이 되고 **과거분사**는 그대로 둔다.","'가지다' 뜻의 **일반동사 have**는 Do의 도움을 받으니 둘을 구별한다.","과거완료 **had**도 똑같이 바로 도치한다."],"examples":[{"en":"Have you seen my glasses anywhere?","ko":"내 안경을 어디서 본 적이 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"seen","role":"V"},{"t":"my glasses","role":"O"},{"t":"anywhere?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Have you ever been to Paris?","ko":"파리에 가 본 적이 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"ever","role":"M"},{"t":"been","role":"V"},{"t":"to Paris?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Has the mail arrived?","ko":"우편물이 왔는가?","parts":[{"t":"Has","role":"Aux"},{"t":"the mail","role":"S"},{"t":"arrived?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Has she told you the news?","ko":"그녀가 그 소식을 말했는가?","parts":[{"t":"Has","role":"Aux"},{"t":"she","role":"S"},{"t":"told","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"IO"},{"t":"the news?","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"Have they finished the project yet?","ko":"그들이 프로젝트를 아직 끝내지 않았는가?","parts":[{"t":"Have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"finished","role":"V"},{"t":"the project","role":"O"},{"t":"yet?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Had you met him before the party?","ko":"파티 전에 그를 만난 적이 있었는가?","parts":[{"t":"Had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"met","role":"V"},{"t":"him","role":"O"},{"t":"before the party?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Have we met before?","ko":"우리가 전에 만난 적이 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"Have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"met","role":"V"},{"t":"before?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Has it stopped raining?","ko":"비가 그쳤는가?","parts":[{"t":"Has","role":"Aux"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"stopped","role":"V"},{"t":"raining?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Had they already left when you arrived?","ko":"네가 도착했을 때 그들은 이미 떠났었는가?","parts":[{"t":"Had","role":"Aux"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"already","role":"M"},{"t":"left","role":"V"},{"t":"when you arrived?","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["Do you have seen him?","Have you seen him? (**완료시제 have**는 조동사라 직접 앞으로 나간다)"],["Have you saw my glasses?","Have you seen my glasses? (**완료시제**엔 과거분사 seen을 쓴다)"],["Has arrived the mail?","Has the mail arrived? (**주어**는 has와 p.p. 사이에 온다)"]]},{"key":"negative","title":"부정 의문문 (Don't/Isn't/Aren't...)","points":["맨 앞 조동사·be동사에 **not을 축약**해 붙인다(Aren't·Isn't·Don't·Haven't·Won't 등).","**놀람·확인·동의**를 구할 때 자주 쓴다.","대답은 질문의 긍정·부정과 무관하게 ==사실이 긍정이면 Yes, 부정이면 No==로 한다.","\"Don't you remember me?\"에 기억나면 \"Yes, I do\"로 답한다."],"examples":[{"en":"Don't you remember me?","ko":"나를 기억하지 못하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"remember","role":"V"},{"t":"me?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Isn't it a beautiful day today?","ko":"오늘 날씨가 정말 좋지 않은가?","parts":[{"t":"Isn't","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"a beautiful day","role":"SC"},{"t":"today?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Aren't you going to eat your dessert?","ko":"디저트를 먹지 않을 것인가?","parts":[{"t":"Aren't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"going to eat","role":"V"},{"t":"your dessert?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Doesn't he work at the bank?","ko":"그 사람은 은행에서 일하지 않는가?","parts":[{"t":"Doesn't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"he","role":"S"},{"t":"work","role":"V"},{"t":"at the bank?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Didn't I tell you to be careful?","ko":"내가 조심하라고 하지 않았는가?","parts":[{"t":"Didn't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"tell","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"IO"},{"t":"to be careful?","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"Haven't you finished your homework yet?","ko":"숙제를 아직 끝내지 않았는가?","parts":[{"t":"Haven't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"finished","role":"V"},{"t":"your homework","role":"O"},{"t":"yet?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Won't it be too cold to go swimming?","ko":"수영하러 가기엔 너무 춥지 않겠는가?","parts":[{"t":"Won't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"be","role":"V"},{"t":"too cold","role":"SC"},{"t":"to go swimming?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Shouldn't we call and reserve a table?","ko":"전화해서 테이블을 예약해야 하지 않는가?","parts":[{"t":"Shouldn't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"call and reserve","role":"V"},{"t":"a table?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Can't you just stay a little longer?","ko":"조금만 더 있다 갈 수는 없는가?","parts":[{"t":"Can't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"just","role":"M"},{"t":"stay","role":"V"},{"t":"a little longer?","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["Do not you remember me?","Don't you remember me? (**부정 의문문**은 축약형 Don't로 시작한다)"],["Amn't I right?","Aren't I right? (**I am의 부정 의문문**은 특수하게 aren't I를 쓴다)"],["No, I remember you. (기억나는데 No)","Yes, I remember you. (**사실이 긍정**이면 Yes로 답한다)"]]},{"key":"wh-basic","title":"Wh- 의문문 (who/what/when/where/why/how)","points":["**Wh- 의문사**(who·what·when·where·why·how)로 구체적 정보를 묻는다.","어순은 ==의문사 + 조동사 + 주어 + 본동사==이다.","Yes/No 의문문을 만든 뒤 앞에 의문사를 붙인다고 생각하면 쉽다(Did you buy? → What did you buy?).","who·what은 사람·사물, when·where·why는 시간·장소·이유, how는 방법·상태·정도를 묻는다."],"examples":[{"en":"What are you doing this weekend?","ko":"이번 주말에 무엇을 하는가?","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"Wh"},{"t":"are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"doing","role":"V"},{"t":"this weekend?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"What did you buy at the mall?","ko":"쇼핑몰에서 무엇을 샀는가?","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"Wh"},{"t":"did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"buy","role":"V"},{"t":"at the mall?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Where is the nearest subway station?","ko":"가장 가까운 지하철역이 어디인가?","parts":[{"t":"Where","role":"Wh"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the nearest subway station?","role":"S"}]},{"en":"Where did you put my keys?","ko":"내 열쇠를 어디에 뒀는가?","parts":[{"t":"Where","role":"Wh"},{"t":"did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"put","role":"V"},{"t":"my keys?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"When does the movie start?","ko":"영화가 언제 시작하는가?","parts":[{"t":"When","role":"Wh"},{"t":"does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"the movie","role":"S"},{"t":"start?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Why did you quit your job?","ko":"일을 왜 그만뒀는가?","parts":[{"t":"Why","role":"Wh"},{"t":"did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"quit","role":"V"},{"t":"your job?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"How do you turn this machine on?","ko":"이 기계를 어떻게 켜는가?","parts":[{"t":"How","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"turn","role":"V"},{"t":"this machine","role":"O"},{"t":"on?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"How are you feeling today?","ko":"오늘 기분이 어떤가?","parts":[{"t":"How","role":"Wh"},{"t":"are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"feeling","role":"V"},{"t":"today?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Who did you invite to the party?","ko":"파티에 누구를 초대했는가?","parts":[{"t":"Who","role":"Wh"},{"t":"did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"invite","role":"V"},{"t":"to the party?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Who should we ask for help?","ko":"누구에게 도움을 요청해야 하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Who","role":"Wh"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"ask","role":"V"},{"t":"for help?","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["What you did buy?","What did you buy? (**의문사 뒤에도 조동사**가 주어보다 앞에 온다)"],["Where you put my keys?","Where did you put my keys? (**일반동사 과거**엔 did가 필요하다)"],["Why did you quitted your job?","Why did you quit your job? (**did 뒤 본동사**는 원형이다)"]]},{"key":"wh-subject","title":"의문사가 주어일 때 (Who broke it?)","points":["의문사가 **주어 자리**에 오면 ==도치도 do/does/did도 없다==.","이미 의문사가 주어라 어순을 바꿀 필요가 없다.","\"Who broke this vase?\"처럼 **의문사+동사** 순서로 바로 쓴다.","동사는 **3인칭 단수** 취급해 -s를 붙인다(Who wants...?)."],"examples":[{"en":"Who left the door open?","ko":"누가 문을 열어놨는가?","parts":[{"t":"Who","role":"S"},{"t":"left","role":"V"},{"t":"the door","role":"O"},{"t":"open?","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"Who broke this vase?","ko":"이 꽃병을 누가 깼는가?","parts":[{"t":"Who","role":"S"},{"t":"broke","role":"V"},{"t":"this vase?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Who wants to grab a coffee?","ko":"누가 커피를 마시러 가겠는가?","parts":[{"t":"Who","role":"S"},{"t":"wants","role":"V"},{"t":"to grab a coffee?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"What happened here yesterday?","ko":"어제 여기서 무슨 일이 있었는가?","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"S"},{"t":"happened","role":"V"},{"t":"here","role":"M"},{"t":"yesterday?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"What makes you say that?","ko":"무엇 때문에 그렇게 말하는가?","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"S"},{"t":"makes","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"O"},{"t":"say that?","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"What caused the accident?","ko":"무엇이 사고를 일으켰는가?","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"S"},{"t":"caused","role":"V"},{"t":"the accident?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Which team won the match?","ko":"어느 팀이 경기를 이겼는가?","parts":[{"t":"Which team","role":"S"},{"t":"won","role":"V"},{"t":"the match?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Who told you that?","ko":"누가 그렇게 말했는가?","parts":[{"t":"Who","role":"S"},{"t":"told","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"IO"},{"t":"that?","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"What smells so good in the kitchen?","ko":"부엌에서 나는 좋은 냄새는 무엇인가?","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"S"},{"t":"smells","role":"V"},{"t":"so good","role":"SC"},{"t":"in the kitchen?","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["Who did break this vase?","Who broke this vase? (**의문사가 주어**면 did 없이 바로 동사를 쓴다)"],["What did happen here?","What happened here? (**주어 what 뒤**엔 도치·조동사가 없다)"],["Who want to go?","Who wants to go? (**주어 who**는 3인칭 단수 취급이라 -s를 붙인다)"]]},{"key":"wh-phrase","title":"긴 의문사구 (What kind of / How+형·부 / Whose+명사)","points":["의문사가 명사·형용사·부사와 결합해 ==긴 의문사구==를 이룬다.","What/Which/Whose/How many·much는 **명사 앞**에 붙어 의문 명사구를 만든다.","How는 **형용사·부사 앞**에 붙어 정도를 묻는다(How long·How often·How far).","이 구가 **주어**면 도치가 없고, **목적어**면 뒤에 조동사+주어+동사가 온다."],"examples":[{"en":"What kind of music do you like?","ko":"어떤 종류의 음악을 좋아하는가?","parts":[{"t":"What kind of music","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"like?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"What time is it right now?","ko":"지금 몇 시인가?","parts":[{"t":"What time","role":"Wh"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"right now?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"How much is this sweater?","ko":"이 스웨터는 얼마인가?","parts":[{"t":"How much","role":"Wh"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"this sweater?","role":"S"}]},{"en":"How long does it take?","ko":"얼마나 걸리는가?","parts":[{"t":"How long","role":"Wh"},{"t":"does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"take?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"How often do you go to the gym?","ko":"얼마나 자주 헬스장에 가는가?","parts":[{"t":"How often","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"go","role":"V"},{"t":"to the gym?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"How far is the beach from here?","ko":"여기서 해변까지 얼마나 먼가?","parts":[{"t":"How far","role":"Wh"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the beach","role":"S"},{"t":"from here?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Which movie should we watch tonight?","ko":"오늘 밤 어느 영화를 볼 것인가?","parts":[{"t":"Which movie","role":"Wh"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"watch","role":"V"},{"t":"tonight?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Whose car is parked outside?","ko":"밖에 주차된 차는 누구의 것인가?","parts":[{"t":"Whose car","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"parked","role":"V"},{"t":"outside?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"How many bags are you checking in?","ko":"가방을 몇 개 부치는가?","parts":[{"t":"How many bags","role":"Wh"},{"t":"are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"checking in?","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["How long it takes?","How long does it take? (**의문사구 뒤에도 조동사** does가 필요하다)"],["What kind music do you like?","What kind of music do you like? (**kind of의 of**를 빼면 안 된다)"],["Whose is car parked outside?","Whose car is parked outside? (**Whose는 명사 car**와 붙여 쓴다)"]]},{"key":"prep-wh","title":"전치사 + 의문사 (To whom / In which / who vs whom)","points":["전치사의 목적어인 의문사가 문두로 갈 때 ==전치사를 데리고 함께== 나갈 수 있다(To whom·In which).","전치사를 앞에 붙이는 건 **격식체**이고, 회화에서는 전치사를 문장 끝에 남긴다(Who are you waiting for?).","전치사 바로 뒤에는 **whom·which·what·where**만 오고 who·why·how는 못 온다.","격식체에서는 전치사 뒤에 who 대신 목적격 **whom**을 쓴다(To whom·With whom)."],"examples":[{"en":"To whom should I send this email?","ko":"이 이메일을 누구에게 보내야 하는가?","parts":[{"t":"To whom","role":"Wh"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"send","role":"V"},{"t":"this email?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"With whom are you going?","ko":"누구와 함께 가는가?","parts":[{"t":"With whom","role":"Wh"},{"t":"are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"going?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"In which century did it happen?","ko":"몇 세기에 그 일이 일어났는가?","parts":[{"t":"In which century","role":"Wh"},{"t":"did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"happen?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"On what grounds was it rejected?","ko":"무슨 근거로 그것이 기각됐는가?","parts":[{"t":"On what grounds","role":"Wh"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"rejected?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"From which platform does the train leave?","ko":"기차가 몇 번 플랫폼에서 출발하는가?","parts":[{"t":"From which platform","role":"Wh"},{"t":"does","role":"Aux"},{"t":"the train","role":"S"},{"t":"leave?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"At what time should we meet tomorrow?","ko":"내일 몇 시에 만날 것인가?","parts":[{"t":"At what time","role":"Wh"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"meet","role":"V"},{"t":"tomorrow?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Who are you waiting for?","ko":"누구를 기다리는가?","parts":[{"t":"Who","role":"Wh"},{"t":"are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"waiting","role":"V"},{"t":"for?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"What are you talking about?","ko":"무슨 얘기를 하고 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"Wh"},{"t":"are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"talking","role":"V"},{"t":"about?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"To what extent is this true?","ko":"이것이 어느 정도까지 사실인가?","parts":[{"t":"To what extent","role":"Wh"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"this","role":"S"},{"t":"true?","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["To who should I send this?","To whom should I send this? (**전치사 뒤**엔 목적격 whom을 쓴다)"],["With who are you going?","With whom are you going? / Who are you going with? (**전치사 뒤 who**는 안 된다)"],["For why did he cancel?","Why did he cancel? / For what reason did he cancel? (**why 앞**엔 전치사를 못 붙인다)"]]},{"key":"choice","title":"선택의문문 (A or B)","points":["둘 이상의 선택지를 ==or로 연결==해 '어느 쪽?'을 묻는다.","형태는 Yes/No·Wh- 의문문과 같고 끝에 **'A or B'**를 붙인다.","Yes/No 형태여도 예/아니오가 아니라 **둘 중 하나를 골라** 답한다.","억양은 앞 선택지에서 올리고 마지막 선택지에서 내린다.","**which**와 함께 쓰면 선택 범위가 분명해진다."],"examples":[{"en":"Which do you prefer, coffee or tea?","ko":"커피와 차 중에 무엇이 더 좋은가?","parts":[{"t":"Which","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"prefer,","role":"V"},{"t":"coffee or tea?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Do you want to eat in or take out?","ko":"여기서 먹을 것인가, 포장할 것인가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"want","role":"V"},{"t":"to eat in or take out?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Should we take the bus or the subway?","ko":"버스를 탈 것인가, 지하철을 탈 것인가?","parts":[{"t":"Should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"take","role":"V"},{"t":"the bus or the subway?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Is it a boy or a girl?","ko":"아들인가, 딸인가?","parts":[{"t":"Is","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"a boy or a girl?","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"Would you like it hot or iced?","ko":"따뜻하게 줄 것인가, 차갑게 줄 것인가?","parts":[{"t":"Would","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"like","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"hot or iced?","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"Do you want to go now or later?","ko":"지금 갈 것인가, 나중에 갈 것인가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"want","role":"V"},{"t":"to go now or later?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Which is better, this one or that one?","ko":"이것과 저것 중 어느 것이 더 나은가?","parts":[{"t":"Which","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"better,","role":"SC"},{"t":"this one or that one?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Are we meeting on Friday or Saturday?","ko":"우리가 금요일에 만나는가, 토요일에 만나는가?","parts":[{"t":"Are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"meeting","role":"V"},{"t":"on Friday or Saturday?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Do you prefer the window or the aisle?","ko":"창가 자리가 좋은가, 통로 자리가 좋은가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"prefer","role":"V"},{"t":"the window or the aisle?","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["Do you want coffee, tea?","Do you want coffee or tea? (**선택지는 or**로 연결한다)"],["Which you prefer, coffee or tea?","Which do you prefer, coffee or tea? (**조동사 do**를 빠뜨리면 안 된다)"],["Yes. (선택의문문에 Yes/No로 답)","Coffee, please. (**선택의문문**엔 둘 중 하나를 골라 답한다)"]]}],"db":{"title":"의문문 DB · 의문사 & 도치","intro":"직접의문문은 문장 맨 앞에 조동사·be동사를 끌어와 <b>주어와 자리를 바꾸는(도치)</b> 것이 핵심이다. ==의문사(Wh-)로 시작하면 뒤에 도치가 따라오고, 의문사 자체가 주어면 도치가 없다==. 아래 4개 그룹으로 의문사·의문사구·도치표·전치사 결합을 한눈에 정리했다.","groups":[{"label":"의문사 Wh-words","note":"단일 의문사 9개다. 사람·사물·장소·시간·이유·방법을 묻는 **기본 도구**라, ==who/what은 주어로 쓰면 도치가 없다==는 점만 기억한다.","items":[{"w":"who","ko":"누가 / 누구를 (사람 주어·목적어·보어)","ex":"Who broke this vase?"},{"w":"who (주어)","ko":"누가 (주어 자리 · 도치 없음)","ex":"Who left the door open?"},{"w":"who (목적어)","ko":"누구를 (구어에서 whom 대신)","ex":"Who did you invite to the party?"},{"w":"whom","ko":"누구를 / 누구에게 (사람 목적어 전용, 격식·전치사 뒤)","ex":"Whom did the committee select?"},{"w":"what","ko":"무엇 / 무슨 (사물을 물음)","ex":"What are you doing this weekend?"},{"w":"what (주어)","ko":"무엇이 (주어 자리 · 도치 없음)","ex":"What happened here yesterday?"},{"w":"which","ko":"어느 것 / 어느 (정해진 선택지 중에서)","ex":"Which do you prefer, coffee or tea?"},{"w":"whose","ko":"누구의 (소유를 물음, 뒤에 명사)","ex":"Whose car is parked outside?"},{"w":"when","ko":"언제 (시간·시점)","ex":"When does the movie start?"},{"w":"where","ko":"어디 / 어디에서 (장소·위치)","ex":"Where is the nearest subway station?"},{"w":"why","ko":"왜 (이유·원인)","ex":"Why did you quit your job?"},{"w":"how","ko":"어떻게 / 얼마나 (방법·수단·상태·정도)","ex":"How do you turn this machine on?"}]},{"label":"의문사구 Wh-phrases","note":"의문사에 명사나 형용사·부사가 붙어 하나의 **큰 덩어리**로 움직인다. What/Which/Whose는 명사 앞에 붙어 형용사처럼 쓰고, How는 형용사·부사 앞에 붙어 ==정도==를 묻는다.","items":[{"w":"what kind of","ko":"어떤 종류의 ~","ex":"What kind of music do you like?"},{"w":"what time","ko":"몇 시에","ex":"What time is it right now?"},{"w":"what day","ko":"무슨 요일 / 며칠","ex":"What day is it today?"},{"w":"what color","ko":"무슨 색","ex":"What color should I paint my room?"},{"w":"what size","ko":"어떤 사이즈","ex":"What size do you wear?"},{"w":"what kind","ko":"어떤 종류","ex":"What kind of food do you want?"},{"w":"how long","ko":"얼마나 오래 / 기간·길이","ex":"How long does it take?"},{"w":"how far","ko":"얼마나 멀리 / 거리","ex":"How far is the beach from here?"},{"w":"how often","ko":"얼마나 자주 / 빈도","ex":"How often do you go to the gym?"},{"w":"how many","ko":"몇 개 / 몇 명 (셀 수 있는 명사)","ex":"How many bags are you checking in?"},{"w":"how much","ko":"얼마 / 얼마나 (값·양·셀 수 없는 명사)","ex":"How much is this sweater?"},{"w":"how old","ko":"몇 살 / 얼마나 오래된","ex":"How old is your younger sister?"},{"w":"how tall","ko":"키가 얼마 / 얼마나 높은","ex":"How tall is that building?"},{"w":"how fast","ko":"얼마나 빠르게 / 속도","ex":"How fast can this car go?"},{"w":"how late","ko":"얼마나 늦게까지","ex":"How late are they open on Sundays?"},{"w":"how quickly","ko":"얼마나 빨리","ex":"How quickly can you finish this?"},{"w":"how accurately","ko":"얼마나 정확하게","ex":"How accurately can carbon dating determine the age?"},{"w":"how prevalent","ko":"얼마나 널리 퍼진","ex":"How prevalent is this disorder?"},{"w":"which one","ko":"어느 것","ex":"Which one is yours?"},{"w":"which way","ko":"어느 길로","ex":"Which way should we go?"},{"w":"which movie","ko":"어느 영화","ex":"Which movie should we watch tonight?"},{"w":"whose book","ko":"누구의 책","ex":"Whose book is this on the desk?"},{"w":"whose idea","ko":"누구의 아이디어","ex":"Whose idea was it to come here?"},{"w":"what percentage","ko":"몇 퍼센트","ex":"What percentage goes toward maintenance?"},{"w":"to what extent","ko":"어느 정도까지","ex":"To what extent is human behavior determined by genetics?"}]},{"label":"조동사·be동사 도치표","note":"직접의문문의 **뼈대**다. 문장의 조동사·be동사를 주어 앞으로 보내는 것이 규칙이고, ==일반동사는 스스로 못 나가서 do/does/did를 빌려온다==.","items":[{"w":"am / is / are (be 현재)","ko":"be동사가 본동사면 주어와 자리만 바꿔요","ex":"Are you ready? (← You are ready)"},{"w":"was / were (be 과거)","ko":"과거 be동사도 그대로 주어 앞으로","ex":"Was the movie good? (← The movie was good)"},{"w":"do (일반동사 현재·복수/you/I)","ko":"본동사는 원형으로 두고 do가 앞으로","ex":"Do they accept credit cards here?"},{"w":"does (일반동사 현재·3인칭 단수)","ko":"does가 나가면 본동사는 원형 (-s 없앰)","ex":"Does this bus go to the airport?"},{"w":"did (일반동사 과거)","ko":"did가 나가면 본동사는 원형 (과거형 안 씀)","ex":"Did you lock the front door?"},{"w":"will / would","ko":"서법 조동사는 바로 주어 앞으로","ex":"Will you be home for dinner?"},{"w":"can / could","ko":"능력·허가·요청, 바로 도치","ex":"Can you help me move this sofa?"},{"w":"shall / should","ko":"제안·의무, 바로 도치","ex":"Should we order pizza tonight?"},{"w":"may / might","ko":"허가·추측, 바로 도치","ex":"May I use your restroom?"},{"w":"must","ko":"의무·강한 추측, 바로 도치","ex":"Must we attend the orientation?"},{"w":"have / has (완료시제)","ko":"완료의 have는 조동사라 바로 앞으로 (일반동사 have '가지다'와 구별!)","ex":"Have you seen my glasses?"},{"w":"had (과거완료)","ko":"과거완료의 had도 조동사라 바로 도치","ex":"Had you met him before the party?"},{"w":"have to / need to (준조동사)","ko":"준조동사는 일반동사 취급 → do/does/did 사용","ex":"Do we have to go?"},{"w":"used to / ought to (준조동사)","ko":"used to도 did로 처리, ought는 자체 도치도 가능","ex":"Did you use to live in Seattle?"},{"w":"부정 의문문 (Aren't/Don't/Didn't 등)","ko":"조동사·be동사에 not 축약형을 붙여 맨 앞에 (놀람·확인·동의)","ex":"Don't you remember me?"}]},{"label":"전치사 + 의문사 (who vs whom)","note":"전치사의 목적어였던 의문사가 앞으로 나갈 때 전치사를 데리고 갈 수 있다. 이때 who가 아니라 <b>whom</b>을 쓴다. 결합 가능한 의문사는 **whom·which·what·where**로 제한된다. (who·why·how는 전치사 바로 뒤 불가)","items":[{"w":"To whom","ko":"누구에게 (send/give의 대상)","ex":"To whom should I send this email?"},{"w":"For whom","ko":"누구를 위해","ex":"For whom are these flowers?"},{"w":"With whom","ko":"누구와 함께","ex":"With whom are you going?"},{"w":"About whom","ko":"누구에 대해","ex":"About whom is this story?"},{"w":"From whom","ko":"누구로부터","ex":"From whom did you hear that?"},{"w":"In which","ko":"어느 것 안에 / 어느 (범위·시기)","ex":"In which century did it happen?"},{"w":"On which","ko":"어느 것 위에 / 어느 (요일·표면)","ex":"On which day are you free?"},{"w":"From which","ko":"어느 것으로부터","ex":"From which platform does the train leave?"},{"w":"At what time","ko":"몇 시에","ex":"At what time should we meet tomorrow?"},{"w":"On what floor","ko":"몇 층에","ex":"On what floor is your office?"},{"w":"For what reason","ko":"무슨 이유로 (why의 격식체)","ex":"For what reason did he cancel the trip?"},{"w":"On what grounds","ko":"무슨 근거로","ex":"On what grounds was the hypothesis rejected?"},{"w":"Under what name","ko":"어느 이름으로","ex":"Under what name is the reservation?"},{"w":"In what ways","ko":"어떤 방식으로","ex":"In what ways do these theories intersect?"},{"w":"By what mechanism","ko":"어떤 메커니즘으로","ex":"By what mechanism do these plants survive?"},{"w":"From where","ko":"어디로부터 (where는 원래 전치사 불필요, 격식체에서만)","ex":"From where did he arrive?"},{"w":"who vs whom 규칙","ko":"who=주어 자리(누가), whom=목적어·전치사 뒤(누구를). 구어는 who로 통일, 격식·전치사 직후는 반드시 whom","ex":"Who called you? / To whom did you speak?"}]}]}},{"n":8,"title":"수동태","status":"detailed","summary":"동작을 '받는' 대상을 주어로 세우는 **수동태**를 종합적으로 정리한다. 핵심 골격은 언제나 **be + 과거분사**이고, ==현재·과거·미래·진행·완료 같은 시제와 인칭·수는 앞의 be(또는 조동사)가 담당==한다. 동작을 한 사람을 밝히고 싶으면 **by + 행위자**를 붙이되, 모르거나 뻔하거나 굳이 밝힐 필요가 없으면 생략한다. 4형식(was given)·5형식(was elected)·관계절 속 수동(the desk that was ordered)·구어체 **get-수동**(got fired)까지 다루고, ==interested in처럼 by 이외의 전치사를 쓰는 관용 수동==과 happen·resemble처럼 **아예 수동으로 못 쓰는 자동사**도 구분한다.","subtopics":[{"key":"basic","title":"수동태 기본 (The report was written)","points":["수동태의 골격은 항상 **be + 과거분사**다. be가 없으면 수동태가 아니다.","능동문의 ==목적어를 주어 자리로 끌어올리면== 수동문이 된다. \"They wrote the report → The report was written.\"","동작을 '하는' 쪽이 아니라 **동작을 '받는' 대상**에 초점을 맞출 때 쓴다.","과거분사는 **-ed** 규칙형이 많지만 written·built·sent처럼 **불규칙형**도 많으니 따로 외운다.","행위자를 밝히려면 **by + 사람/사물**을 뒤에 붙인다."],"examples":[{"en":"The report was written last night.","ko":"그 보고서는 어젯밤에 작성되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The report","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"written","role":"V"},{"t":"last night.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This bridge was built in 1990.","ko":"이 다리는 1990년에 지어졌다.","parts":[{"t":"This bridge","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"built","role":"V"},{"t":"in 1990.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The windows are cleaned every week.","ko":"그 창문들은 매주 청소된다.","parts":[{"t":"The windows","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"cleaned","role":"V"},{"t":"every week.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The cake was eaten by the kids.","ko":"그 케이크는 아이들이 먹었다.","parts":[{"t":"The cake","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"eaten","role":"V"},{"t":"by the kids.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"English is spoken here.","ko":"여기서는 영어가 쓰인다.","parts":[{"t":"English","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"spoken","role":"V"},{"t":"here.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The room was cleaned this morning.","ko":"그 방은 오늘 아침에 청소되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The room","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"cleaned","role":"V"},{"t":"this morning.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The package was delivered on time.","ko":"그 소포는 제때 배달되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The package","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"delivered","role":"V"},{"t":"on time.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Dinner is served at seven.","ko":"저녁 식사는 7시에 제공된다.","parts":[{"t":"Dinner","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"served","role":"V"},{"t":"at seven.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["The house built last year.","The house was built last year. (be동사 없이는 수동이 안 돼요; **be + 과거분사**가 기본이에요)"],["The report was write.","The report was written. (be 뒤에는 원형이 아니라 **과거분사** written)"],["The letters are send every day.","The letters are sent every day. (send의 과거분사는 **sent**)"]]},{"key":"present-past","title":"현재·과거 수동 (is/are made · was/were taken)","points":["현재 수동은 **am/is/are + 과거분사**, 과거 수동은 **was/were + 과거분사**다.","==be동사가 주어의 인칭·수와 시제를 모두 책임진다==. 과거분사는 형태가 변하지 않는다.","단수 주어엔 **is/was**, 복수 주어엔 **are/were**를 맞춰 쓴다.","'지금 늘 그렇게 된다'는 현재, '이미 그렇게 됐다'는 과거로 골라 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"These cars are made in Germany.","ko":"이 차들은 독일에서 만들어진다.","parts":[{"t":"These cars","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"made","role":"V"},{"t":"in Germany.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The tickets are sold online.","ko":"그 표들은 온라인으로 판매된다.","parts":[{"t":"The tickets","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"Aux"},{"t":"sold","role":"V"},{"t":"online.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The bill was paid yesterday.","ko":"그 청구서는 어제 지불되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The bill","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"paid","role":"V"},{"t":"yesterday.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The photos were taken last summer.","ko":"그 사진들은 지난여름에 찍혔다.","parts":[{"t":"The photos","role":"S"},{"t":"were","role":"Aux"},{"t":"taken","role":"V"},{"t":"last summer.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The store is closed on Sundays.","ko":"그 가게는 일요일마다 닫혀 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The store","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"closed","role":"V"},{"t":"on Sundays.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The keys were found under the sofa.","ko":"그 열쇠들은 소파 밑에서 발견되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The keys","role":"S"},{"t":"were","role":"Aux"},{"t":"found","role":"V"},{"t":"under the sofa.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The homework is checked by the teacher.","ko":"그 숙제는 선생님이 검사한다.","parts":[{"t":"The homework","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"checked","role":"V"},{"t":"by the teacher.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The trees were planted ten years ago.","ko":"그 나무들은 10년 전에 심어졌다.","parts":[{"t":"The trees","role":"S"},{"t":"were","role":"Aux"},{"t":"planted","role":"V"},{"t":"ten years ago.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["These cars is made in Germany.","These cars are made in Germany. (복수 주어엔 **are**를 써요)"],["The bill were paid yesterday.","The bill was paid yesterday. (단수 주어엔 **was**를 써요)"],["The photos were took last summer.","The photos were taken last summer. (take의 과거분사는 took이 아니라 **taken**)"]]},{"key":"modal-future","title":"미래·조동사 수동 (will be done · must be done)","points":["미래 수동은 **will be + 과거분사**, 조동사 수동은 **조동사 + be + 과거분사**다.","==조동사·will 뒤에는 반드시 원형 be==가 오고, 그다음 과거분사를 붙인다.","조동사가 이미 시제·의미를 담으므로 be는 **원형 그대로** 둔다(is/was로 바꾸지 않는다).","can be(가능)·must be(의무)·should be(당위)처럼 조동사 뜻이 그대로 살아 있다."],"examples":[{"en":"The results will be announced tomorrow.","ko":"그 결과는 내일 발표될 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"The results","role":"S"},{"t":"will be","role":"Aux"},{"t":"announced","role":"V"},{"t":"tomorrow.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The work must be finished by Friday.","ko":"그 일은 금요일까지 끝내져야 한다.","parts":[{"t":"The work","role":"S"},{"t":"must be","role":"Aux"},{"t":"finished","role":"V"},{"t":"by Friday.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This form can be downloaded online.","ko":"이 양식은 온라인으로 내려받을 수 있다.","parts":[{"t":"This form","role":"S"},{"t":"can be","role":"Aux"},{"t":"downloaded","role":"V"},{"t":"online.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The rules should be followed carefully.","ko":"그 규칙들은 신중히 지켜져야 한다.","parts":[{"t":"The rules","role":"S"},{"t":"should be","role":"Aux"},{"t":"followed","role":"V"},{"t":"carefully.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The building will be painted next week.","ko":"그 건물은 다음 주에 페인트칠될 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"The building","role":"S"},{"t":"will be","role":"Aux"},{"t":"painted","role":"V"},{"t":"next week.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The problem can be solved easily.","ko":"그 문제는 쉽게 해결될 수 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The problem","role":"S"},{"t":"can be","role":"Aux"},{"t":"solved","role":"V"},{"t":"easily.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The documents must be signed today.","ko":"그 서류들은 오늘 서명되어야 한다.","parts":[{"t":"The documents","role":"S"},{"t":"must be","role":"Aux"},{"t":"signed","role":"V"},{"t":"today.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Your order will be shipped soon.","ko":"당신의 주문은 곧 배송될 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"Your order","role":"S"},{"t":"will be","role":"Aux"},{"t":"shipped","role":"V"},{"t":"soon.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["The results will announced tomorrow.","The results will be announced tomorrow. (will 뒤에 **be**를 빠뜨리면 안 돼요; will **be** + 과거분사)"],["The work must be finish by Friday.","The work must be finished by Friday. (be 뒤에는 원형이 아니라 **과거분사** finished)"],["This form can be download online.","This form can be downloaded online. (조동사 수동도 **be + 과거분사**; downloaded)"]]},{"key":"progressive","title":"진행 수동 (is/are being + p.p.)","points":["진행 수동은 **be동사 + being + 과거분사**다. '지금 ~되고 있는 중'을 나타낸다.","현재진행 수동은 **is/are being + p.p.**, 과거진행 수동은 **was/were being + p.p.**다.","==being 뒤에는 반드시 과거분사==가 온다. -ing를 쓰면 능동 진행이 되어 뜻이 완전히 달라진다.","\"They are repairing the road → The road is being repaired.\"처럼 목적어를 주어로 올린다."],"examples":[{"en":"The road is being repaired now.","ko":"그 도로는 지금 보수되고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The road","role":"S"},{"t":"is being","role":"Aux"},{"t":"repaired","role":"V"},{"t":"now.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The house is being painted this week.","ko":"그 집은 이번 주에 페인트칠되고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The house","role":"S"},{"t":"is being","role":"Aux"},{"t":"painted","role":"V"},{"t":"this week.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"New rules are being made.","ko":"새 규칙들이 만들어지고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"New rules","role":"S"},{"t":"are being","role":"Aux"},{"t":"made.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Dinner is being prepared right now.","ko":"저녁 식사가 지금 준비되고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"Dinner","role":"S"},{"t":"is being","role":"Aux"},{"t":"prepared","role":"V"},{"t":"right now.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The bridge is being built this year.","ko":"그 다리는 올해 지어지고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The bridge","role":"S"},{"t":"is being","role":"Aux"},{"t":"built","role":"V"},{"t":"this year.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"My computer is being fixed today.","ko":"내 컴퓨터는 오늘 수리되고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"My computer","role":"S"},{"t":"is being","role":"Aux"},{"t":"fixed","role":"V"},{"t":"today.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The rooms are being cleaned at the moment.","ko":"그 방들은 지금 청소되고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The rooms","role":"S"},{"t":"are being","role":"Aux"},{"t":"cleaned","role":"V"},{"t":"at the moment.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The report is being reviewed by the manager.","ko":"그 보고서는 관리자에 의해 검토되고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The report","role":"S"},{"t":"is being","role":"Aux"},{"t":"reviewed","role":"V"},{"t":"by the manager.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["The road is repairing now.","The road is being repaired now. (진행 수동은 **is being + 과거분사**; repairing은 능동이라 도로가 '고치는' 뜻이 돼요)"],["The house is being paint this week.","The house is being painted this week. (being 뒤에는 **과거분사** painted)"],["The rooms are cleaning at the moment.","The rooms are being cleaned at the moment. (지금 청소'되는' 중이면 **being + 과거분사**)"]]},{"key":"perfect","title":"완료 수동 (has/have/had been + p.p.)","points":["완료 수동은 **have동사 + been + 과거분사**다. 현재완료 수동은 **has/have been + p.p.**다.","과거완료 수동은 **had been + p.p.**, 미래완료 수동은 **will have been + p.p.**다.","==been을 빠뜨리지 않는 것이 핵심==이다. \"has sent\"는 능동, \"has been sent\"가 수동이다.","'이미 ~되어 버렸다/그 시점까지 ~되어 있었다'처럼 **완료의 의미**가 그대로 살아 있다."],"examples":[{"en":"The email has been sent already.","ko":"그 이메일은 이미 발송되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The email","role":"S"},{"t":"has been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"sent","role":"V"},{"t":"already.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The project has been finished.","ko":"그 프로젝트는 완료되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The project","role":"S"},{"t":"has been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"finished.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The books have been returned.","ko":"그 책들은 반납되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The books","role":"S"},{"t":"have been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"returned.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The window had been broken before we came.","ko":"그 창문은 우리가 오기 전에 깨져 있었다.","parts":[{"t":"The window","role":"S"},{"t":"had been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"broken","role":"V"},{"t":"before we came.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"My car has been stolen.","ko":"내 차는 도난당했다.","parts":[{"t":"My car","role":"S"},{"t":"has been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"stolen.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The tickets have been sold out.","ko":"그 표들은 매진되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The tickets","role":"S"},{"t":"have been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"sold out.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The decision had been made already.","ko":"그 결정은 이미 내려져 있었다.","parts":[{"t":"The decision","role":"S"},{"t":"had been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"made","role":"V"},{"t":"already.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The house has been sold to a young couple.","ko":"그 집은 젊은 부부에게 팔렸다.","parts":[{"t":"The house","role":"S"},{"t":"has been","role":"Aux"},{"t":"sold","role":"V"},{"t":"to a young couple.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["The email has sent already.","The email has been sent already. (완료 수동은 **has been + 과거분사**; been을 빠뜨리면 능동이 돼요)"],["The books have been return.","The books have been returned. (been 뒤에는 **과거분사** returned)"],["My car has been stole.","My car has been stolen. (steal의 과거분사는 **stolen**)"]]},{"key":"by-agent","title":"by + 행위자 · by 생략 (was written by / was canceled)","points":["동작을 한 사람·사물을 밝히려면 **by + 행위자**를 붙인다. 이 by구는 문장 성분상 **수식어(M)**다.","==행위자가 누구인지 모르거나(불명), 일반 사람이거나(일반), 뻔할 때(자명)는 by 이하를 통째로 생략==한다.","\"My wallet was stolen.\"처럼 행위자를 모르면 by를 아예 쓰지 않는다.","학술·뉴스체에서는 **행위자보다 사건 자체**가 중요할 때가 많아 by 생략이 오히려 자연스럽다.","행위자는 **by**로 표시한다. from·with·of 같은 다른 전치사로 바꾸면 안 된다."],"examples":[{"en":"The novel was written by a famous author.","ko":"그 소설은 유명한 작가가 썼다.","parts":[{"t":"The novel","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"written","role":"V"},{"t":"by a famous author.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This song was composed by Mozart.","ko":"이 곡은 모차르트가 작곡했다.","parts":[{"t":"This song","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"composed","role":"V"},{"t":"by Mozart.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"My wallet was stolen.","ko":"내 지갑은 도난당했다.","parts":[{"t":"My wallet","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"stolen.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"French is spoken in Canada.","ko":"캐나다에서는 프랑스어가 쓰인다.","parts":[{"t":"French","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"spoken","role":"V"},{"t":"in Canada.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The thief was arrested last night.","ko":"그 도둑은 어젯밤에 체포되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The thief","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"arrested","role":"V"},{"t":"last night.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The bridge was designed by a Korean engineer.","ko":"그 다리는 한국인 기술자가 설계했다.","parts":[{"t":"The bridge","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"designed","role":"V"},{"t":"by a Korean engineer.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Rice is grown in many countries.","ko":"쌀은 많은 나라에서 재배된다.","parts":[{"t":"Rice","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"grown","role":"V"},{"t":"in many countries.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The meeting was canceled.","ko":"그 회의는 취소되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The meeting","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"canceled.","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["This song was composed of Mozart.","This song was composed by Mozart. (동작을 한 **행위자**는 by; of가 아니에요)"],["The window was broken by.","The window was broken. (행위자가 불명하면 by만 남기지 말고 **by 이하를 통째로 생략**해요)"],["French speaks in Canada.","French is spoken in Canada. (언어는 말해'지는' 대상이라 **is spoken** 수동으로 써요)"]]},{"key":"type4","title":"4형식 수동 (was given / was sent)","points":["4형식(주어+동사+간접목적어+직접목적어)은 목적어가 둘이라 ==수동문 주어가 될 후보도 둘==이다.","**간접목적어(사람)를 주어**로 올리면 \"She was given a present.\"처럼 뒤에 직접목적어가 남는다.","**직접목적어(사물)를 주어**로 올리면 \"A present was given to her.\"처럼 사람 앞에 **to/for**를 붙인다.","give·send·offer·tell·teach·show 같은 **수여동사**에서 자주 나온다.","간접목적어를 주어로 삼을 때 남는 직접목적어 앞에 by를 붙이면 안 된다."],"examples":[{"en":"She was given a present.","ko":"그녀는 선물을 받았다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"given","role":"V"},{"t":"a present.","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"I was sent an email.","ko":"나는 이메일을 받았다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"sent","role":"V"},{"t":"an email.","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"A present was given to her.","ko":"선물 하나가 그녀에게 주어졌다.","parts":[{"t":"A present","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"given","role":"V"},{"t":"to her.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"We were offered a discount.","ko":"우리는 할인을 제안받았다.","parts":[{"t":"We","role":"S"},{"t":"were","role":"Aux"},{"t":"offered","role":"V"},{"t":"a discount.","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"He was told the truth.","ko":"그는 진실을 들었다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"told","role":"V"},{"t":"the truth.","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"The students were taught grammar.","ko":"그 학생들은 문법을 배웠다.","parts":[{"t":"The students","role":"S"},{"t":"were","role":"Aux"},{"t":"taught","role":"V"},{"t":"grammar.","role":"DO"}]},{"en":"A medal was awarded to the winner.","ko":"메달 하나가 우승자에게 수여되었다.","parts":[{"t":"A medal","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"awarded","role":"V"},{"t":"to the winner.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She was shown the new office.","ko":"그녀는 새 사무실을 안내받았다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"shown","role":"V"},{"t":"the new office.","role":"DO"}]}],"mistakes":[["A present was given her.","A present was given to her. (직접목적어를 주어로 올리면 사람 앞에 **to**를 붙여요)"],["She was given by a present.","She was given a present. (간접목적어가 주어면 직접목적어를 바로 붙여요; **by는 필요 없어요**)"],["I was send an email.","I was sent an email. (send의 과거분사는 **sent**)"]]},{"key":"type5","title":"5형식 수동 (was elected president / was made to wait)","points":["5형식(주어+동사+목적어+목적격보어)을 수동으로 바꾸면 ==목적격보어(OC)는 그대로 남는다==.","\"They elected him president → He was elected president.\"처럼 보어 president가 뒤에 붙어 있다.","**사역동사 make**의 수동은 목적격보어의 원형부정사가 **to부정사로 바뀐다**: be made **to** do.","call·name·elect·keep·leave 등은 명사·형용사 보어가, ask·tell·want 등은 to부정사 보어가 남는다."],"examples":[{"en":"He was elected president.","ko":"그는 대통령으로 선출되었다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"elected","role":"V"},{"t":"president.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"The baby was named Emma.","ko":"그 아기는 엠마라고 이름 지어졌다.","parts":[{"t":"The baby","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"named","role":"V"},{"t":"Emma.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"She was made to wait outside.","ko":"그녀는 밖에서 기다리게 되었다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"made","role":"V"},{"t":"to wait","role":"OC"},{"t":"outside.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The dog was called Max.","ko":"그 개는 맥스라고 불렸다.","parts":[{"t":"The dog","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"called","role":"V"},{"t":"Max.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"He was asked to leave.","ko":"그는 떠나라는 요청을 받았다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"asked","role":"V"},{"t":"to leave.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"The window was left open.","ko":"그 창문은 열린 채로 놔두어졌다.","parts":[{"t":"The window","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"left","role":"V"},{"t":"open.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"The soup was kept warm.","ko":"그 수프는 따뜻하게 유지되었다.","parts":[{"t":"The soup","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"kept","role":"V"},{"t":"warm.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"The children were told to be quiet.","ko":"그 아이들은 조용히 하라는 말을 들었다.","parts":[{"t":"The children","role":"S"},{"t":"were","role":"Aux"},{"t":"told","role":"V"},{"t":"to be quiet.","role":"OC"}]}],"mistakes":[["He was made wait outside.","He was made to wait outside. (사역 make의 수동은 보어가 **to부정사**로 바뀌어요; be made **to** wait)"],["The baby was named as Emma.","The baby was named Emma. (name 뒤 이름 보어엔 **as를 붙이지 않아요**)"],["She was asked leave.","She was asked to leave. (ask의 목적격보어는 **to부정사** to leave)"]]},{"key":"relative","title":"관계절 속 수동 (the desk that was ordered / provided by)","points":["관계절 안에서도 **be + 과거분사**로 수동이 자주 쓰인다: the desk **that was ordered**.","==관계대명사 + be동사는 함께 생략==되어 과거분사만 남기도 한다: the report **written by** the team.","이렇게 줄인 형태를 **과거분사 수식(줄인 관계절)**이라 하고, 명사 뒤에서 앞 명사를 꾸민다.","명사가 동작을 '받는' 대상이면 과거분사를, '하는' 주체면 현재분사를 쓴다(the man **standing** vs the desk **ordered**).","관계절 속 be도 시제·수를 담당하므로 **주절의 동사와 헷갈리지 않게** 구분한다."],"examples":[{"en":"The guide provided by the hotel was helpful.","ko":"호텔이 제공한 안내서는 유용했다.","parts":[{"t":"The guide","role":"S"},{"t":"provided","role":"V"},{"t":"by the hotel","role":"M"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"helpful.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The desk that was ordered arrived on Friday.","ko":"주문된 그 책상은 금요일에 도착했다.","parts":[{"t":"The desk","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"Wh"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"ordered","role":"V"},{"t":"arrived","role":"V"},{"t":"on Friday.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The letter that was sent never arrived.","ko":"발송된 그 편지는 끝내 도착하지 않았다.","parts":[{"t":"The letter","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"Wh"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"sent","role":"V"},{"t":"never","role":"M"},{"t":"arrived.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The house built in 1900 is still standing.","ko":"1900년에 지어진 그 집은 아직 서 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The house","role":"S"},{"t":"built","role":"V"},{"t":"in 1900","role":"M"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"still","role":"M"},{"t":"standing.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The report written by the team was excellent.","ko":"그 팀이 작성한 보고서는 훌륭했다.","parts":[{"t":"The report","role":"S"},{"t":"written","role":"V"},{"t":"by the team","role":"M"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"excellent.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The song that was played at the party was great.","ko":"파티에서 틀어진 그 노래는 아주 좋았다.","parts":[{"t":"The song","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"Wh"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"played","role":"V"},{"t":"at the party","role":"M"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"great.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"The products made in Korea sell well.","ko":"한국에서 만들어진 그 제품들은 잘 팔린다.","parts":[{"t":"The products","role":"S"},{"t":"made","role":"V"},{"t":"in Korea","role":"M"},{"t":"sell","role":"V"},{"t":"well.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The bridge that was damaged is being repaired.","ko":"손상된 그 다리는 보수되고 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The bridge","role":"S"},{"t":"that","role":"Wh"},{"t":"was","role":"Aux"},{"t":"damaged","role":"V"},{"t":"is being","role":"Aux"},{"t":"repaired.","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["The desk that ordered arrived today.","The desk that was ordered arrived today. (책상은 주문'되는' 대상이라 관계절도 **was ordered** 수동으로 써요)"],["The guide provide by the hotel was helpful.","The guide provided by the hotel was helpful. (줄인 관계절엔 **과거분사** provided)"],["The report writing by the team was excellent.","The report written by the team was excellent. ('~에 의해 쓰여진'이면 현재분사가 아니라 **과거분사** written)"]]},{"key":"get-passive","title":"get-수동 (got fired / got broken)","points":["구어에서는 be 대신 **get + 과거분사**로 수동을 만든다: got fired, got broken.","==get-수동은 '갑작스러운 변화'나 '부정적인 일'== 을 강조하는 느낌이라 회화에서 많이 쓴다.","형태는 **get + 과거분사**이고, 시제는 get에서 담당한다(got·gets·will get).","get married·get lost·get dressed처럼 **관용 표현**으로도 굳어져 있다.","격식 있는 글(학술·시험 라이팅)에서는 **be동사 수동**이 더 안전하다."],"examples":[{"en":"He got fired last week.","ko":"그는 지난주에 해고당했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"got","role":"Aux"},{"t":"fired","role":"V"},{"t":"last week.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"My phone got broken.","ko":"내 휴대폰이 고장 났다.","parts":[{"t":"My phone","role":"S"},{"t":"got","role":"Aux"},{"t":"broken.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"She got hired at a big company.","ko":"그녀는 큰 회사에 채용되었다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"got","role":"Aux"},{"t":"hired","role":"V"},{"t":"at a big company.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"They got married in June.","ko":"그들은 6월에 결혼했다.","parts":[{"t":"They","role":"S"},{"t":"got","role":"Aux"},{"t":"married","role":"V"},{"t":"in June.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I got hurt during the game.","ko":"나는 경기 중에 다쳤다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"got","role":"Aux"},{"t":"hurt","role":"V"},{"t":"during the game.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The window got smashed in the storm.","ko":"그 창문은 폭풍에 산산조각 났다.","parts":[{"t":"The window","role":"S"},{"t":"got","role":"Aux"},{"t":"smashed","role":"V"},{"t":"in the storm.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He got promoted to manager.","ko":"그는 관리자로 승진했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"got","role":"Aux"},{"t":"promoted","role":"V"},{"t":"to manager.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Our flight got canceled.","ko":"우리 항공편이 취소되었다.","parts":[{"t":"Our flight","role":"S"},{"t":"got","role":"Aux"},{"t":"canceled.","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["He got fire last week.","He got fired last week. (get 수동도 **과거분사**를 써요; get + fired)"],["My phone got break.","My phone got broken. (break의 과거분사는 **broken**)"],["She got hire at a big company.","She got hired at a big company. (get + **과거분사** hired)"]]},{"key":"prep-nopassive","title":"by 이외 전치사 & 수동 불가 (interested in / happen)","points":["감정·상태를 나타내는 수동 표현은 by가 아니라 ==정해진 전치사==와 짝을 이룬다: interested **in**, known **for**.","made **of**(형태 유지)·made **from**(성질 변화)·covered **with**·filled **with**처럼 전치사가 뜻을 가른다.","worried **about**·surprised **at**·satisfied **with**처럼 형용사처럼 굳은 관용 수동은 통째로 외운다.","==happen·occur·appear·arrive·exist·seem 같은 자동사==와 resemble·have·lack·fit·suit 같은 **상태동사는 수동이 불가능**하다.","\"The accident happened.\"를 was happened로 쓰면 안 된다. 자동사는 목적어가 없어 수동 주어를 만들 수 없다."],"examples":[{"en":"I am interested in art.","ko":"나는 미술에 관심이 있다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"am","role":"Aux"},{"t":"interested","role":"V"},{"t":"in art.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She is known for her kindness.","ko":"그녀는 친절함으로 유명하다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"known","role":"V"},{"t":"for her kindness.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The table is made of wood.","ko":"그 탁자는 나무로 만들어졌다.","parts":[{"t":"The table","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"made","role":"V"},{"t":"of wood.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The mountain is covered with snow.","ko":"그 산은 눈으로 덮여 있다.","parts":[{"t":"The mountain","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"covered","role":"V"},{"t":"with snow.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I am worried about the exam.","ko":"나는 그 시험이 걱정된다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"am","role":"Aux"},{"t":"worried","role":"V"},{"t":"about the exam.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She is satisfied with the result.","ko":"그녀는 그 결과에 만족한다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"satisfied","role":"V"},{"t":"with the result.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Something strange happened yesterday.","ko":"어제 이상한 일이 일어났다.","parts":[{"t":"Something strange","role":"S"},{"t":"happened","role":"V"},{"t":"yesterday.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The twins resemble their mother.","ko":"그 쌍둥이는 엄마를 닮았다.","parts":[{"t":"The twins","role":"S"},{"t":"resemble","role":"V"},{"t":"their mother.","role":"O"}]}],"mistakes":[["I am interested by art.","I am interested in art. (interested는 관용적으로 **in**과 짝을 이뤄요)"],["The table is made from wood.","The table is made of wood. (재료의 형태가 그대로 보이면 **made of**; 성질이 변하면 made from)"],["The accident was happened at night.","The accident happened at night. (happen은 **자동사**라 수동이 안 돼요; was happened는 틀려요)"]]}],"db":{"title":"수동태 DB · 과거분사 · 전치사 · 수동 불가 · 시제표","intro":"수동태의 성패는 **be + 과거분사**에서 ==과거분사를 정확히 아는 것==에 달려 있다. 아래 4개 그룹으로 (1) 자주 틀리는 **불규칙 과거분사**, (2) by가 아닌 **관용 전치사 수동**, (3) 아예 **수동으로 못 쓰는 동사**, (4) **시제별 수동 형태 골격**을 한눈에 정리했다. 그룹 3의 예문은 수동이 아니라 **올바른 능동형**임에 유의한다.","groups":[{"label":"불규칙 과거분사 (base–past–pp)","note":"수동태에서 be 뒤에 오는 **과거분사(세 번째 칸)**가 핵심이다. write–wrote–**written**처럼 ==과거형과 과거분사가 다른 것==을 특히 조심한다.","items":[{"w":"write / wrote / written","ko":"쓰다","ex":"The essay was written overnight."},{"w":"speak / spoke / spoken","ko":"말하다","ex":"English is spoken worldwide."},{"w":"take / took / taken","ko":"가져가다·찍다","ex":"The photo was taken at dawn."},{"w":"give / gave / given","ko":"주다","ex":"A gift was given to her."},{"w":"break / broke / broken","ko":"깨다","ex":"The vase was broken."},{"w":"steal / stole / stolen","ko":"훔치다","ex":"My bike was stolen."},{"w":"drive / drove / driven","ko":"운전하다","ex":"The car was driven carefully."},{"w":"ride / rode / ridden","ko":"타다","ex":"The horse was ridden by a child."},{"w":"eat / ate / eaten","ko":"먹다","ex":"The cake was eaten quickly."},{"w":"see / saw / seen","ko":"보다","ex":"The movie was seen by millions."},{"w":"do / did / done","ko":"하다","ex":"The work was done well."},{"w":"make / made / made","ko":"만들다","ex":"It was made by hand."},{"w":"build / built / built","ko":"짓다","ex":"The tower was built in 1889."},{"w":"send / sent / sent","ko":"보내다","ex":"The parcel was sent yesterday."},{"w":"buy / bought / bought","ko":"사다","ex":"The house was bought last year."},{"w":"teach / taught / taught","ko":"가르치다","ex":"The class was taught in English."},{"w":"catch / caught / caught","ko":"잡다","ex":"The thief was caught fast."},{"w":"bring / brought / brought","ko":"가져오다","ex":"The dish was brought to the table."},{"w":"think / thought / thought","ko":"생각하다","ex":"It was thought to be true."},{"w":"find / found / found","ko":"찾다","ex":"The keys were found at last."},{"w":"pay / paid / paid","ko":"지불하다","ex":"The fee was paid in full."},{"w":"sell / sold / sold","ko":"팔다","ex":"The tickets were sold out."},{"w":"tell / told / told","ko":"말하다","ex":"He was told the truth."},{"w":"hold / held / held","ko":"열다·잡다","ex":"The meeting was held online."},{"w":"keep / kept / kept","ko":"유지하다","ex":"The food was kept fresh."},{"w":"leave / left / left","ko":"떠나다·놔두다","ex":"The door was left open."},{"w":"lose / lost / lost","ko":"잃다","ex":"The game was lost by one point."},{"w":"choose / chose / chosen","ko":"선택하다","ex":"She was chosen as leader."},{"w":"wear / wore / worn","ko":"입다","ex":"The uniform was worn daily."},{"w":"know / knew / known","ko":"알다","ex":"The city is known for food."},{"w":"grow / grew / grown","ko":"재배하다","ex":"Rice is grown in Asia."},{"w":"throw / threw / thrown","ko":"던지다","ex":"The trash was thrown away."},{"w":"show / showed / shown","ko":"보여주다","ex":"She was shown the office."},{"w":"hide / hid / hidden","ko":"숨기다","ex":"The gift was hidden away."},{"w":"forget / forgot / forgotten","ko":"잊다","ex":"His name was forgotten."},{"w":"freeze / froze / frozen","ko":"얼리다","ex":"The lake was frozen solid."},{"w":"begin / began / begun","ko":"시작하다","ex":"The project was begun in May."},{"w":"win / won / won","ko":"이기다","ex":"The prize was won by our team."},{"w":"draw / drew / drawn","ko":"그리다","ex":"The map was drawn by hand."},{"w":"cut / cut / cut","ko":"자르다","ex":"The grass was cut this morning."},{"w":"read / read / read","ko":"읽다","ex":"The book was read in a day."},{"w":"forbid / forbade / forbidden","ko":"금지하다","ex":"Smoking is forbidden here."}]},{"label":"by 이외 전치사 관용 수동","note":"감정·상태 수동은 by가 아니라 **정해진 전치사**를 쓴다. ==interested in·known for처럼 짝을 통째로 외우는 것==이 안전하다.","items":[{"w":"interested in","ko":"~에 관심이 있는","ex":"I am interested in science."},{"w":"known for","ko":"~로 유명한","ex":"The city is known for its food."},{"w":"known as","ko":"~로 알려진","ex":"He is known as a leader."},{"w":"made of","ko":"~로 만든 (형태 유지)","ex":"The ring is made of gold."},{"w":"made from","ko":"~로 만든 (성질 변화)","ex":"Wine is made from grapes."},{"w":"covered with","ko":"~로 덮인","ex":"The floor is covered with dust."},{"w":"filled with","ko":"~로 가득 찬","ex":"The jar is filled with candy."},{"w":"crowded with","ko":"~로 붐비는","ex":"The mall is crowded with people."},{"w":"worried about","ko":"~을 걱정하는","ex":"She is worried about money."},{"w":"surprised at / by","ko":"~에 놀란","ex":"We were surprised at the price."},{"w":"satisfied with","ko":"~에 만족하는","ex":"He is satisfied with the deal."},{"w":"pleased with","ko":"~에 기뻐하는","ex":"I am pleased with the result."},{"w":"tired of","ko":"~에 싫증 난","ex":"I am tired of waiting."},{"w":"disappointed with / in","ko":"~에 실망한","ex":"They were disappointed with the show."},{"w":"composed of","ko":"~로 구성된","ex":"Water is composed of two elements."},{"w":"based on","ko":"~에 근거한","ex":"The film is based on a novel."},{"w":"married to","ko":"~와 결혼한","ex":"She is married to a doctor."},{"w":"related to","ko":"~와 관련된","ex":"This issue is related to health."}]},{"label":"수동 불가 동사 (능동만 가능)","note":"목적어가 없는 **자동사**와 상태를 나타내는 동사는 수동으로 못 쓴다. ==was happened·is resembled 같은 형태는 전부 틀림==이다. 아래 예문은 모두 **올바른 능동형**이다.","items":[{"w":"happen","ko":"일어나다 (자동사)","ex":"The accident happened."},{"w":"occur","ko":"발생하다 (자동사)","ex":"A problem occurred."},{"w":"appear","ko":"나타나다","ex":"A rainbow appeared."},{"w":"disappear","ko":"사라지다","ex":"The stain disappeared."},{"w":"arrive","ko":"도착하다","ex":"The train arrived late."},{"w":"exist","ko":"존재하다","ex":"Such rules no longer exist."},{"w":"seem","ko":"~처럼 보이다","ex":"She seems tired."},{"w":"remain","ko":"남아 있다","ex":"Few seats remain."},{"w":"resemble","ko":"닮다 (상태동사)","ex":"He resembles his dad."},{"w":"have","ko":"가지고 있다 (소유)","ex":"I have a car."},{"w":"lack","ko":"부족하다","ex":"The plan lacks detail."},{"w":"fit","ko":"(치수가) 맞다","ex":"The shirt fits me."},{"w":"suit","ko":"어울리다","ex":"That color suits you."},{"w":"cost","ko":"비용이 들다","ex":"It costs ten dollars."}]},{"label":"시제별 수동 형태표 (be + p.p. 골격)","note":"수동의 뼈대는 **be + 과거분사**로 같고, ==앞의 be(또는 조동사·have)만 시제에 맞춰 변신==한다. 과거분사(아래 locked)는 그대로 고정이다.","items":[{"w":"현재 수동","ko":"am / is / are + 과거분사","ex":"The door is locked."},{"w":"과거 수동","ko":"was / were + 과거분사","ex":"The door was locked."},{"w":"미래 수동","ko":"will be + 과거분사","ex":"The door will be locked."},{"w":"현재진행 수동","ko":"am / is / are being + 과거분사","ex":"The door is being locked."},{"w":"과거진행 수동","ko":"was / were being + 과거분사","ex":"The door was being locked."},{"w":"현재완료 수동","ko":"has / have been + 과거분사","ex":"The door has been locked."},{"w":"과거완료 수동","ko":"had been + 과거분사","ex":"The door had been locked."},{"w":"미래완료 수동","ko":"will have been + 과거분사","ex":"The door will have been locked."},{"w":"조동사 수동","ko":"조동사 + be + 과거분사","ex":"The door must be locked."},{"w":"부정 수동","ko":"be + not + 과거분사","ex":"The door is not locked."}]}]}},{"n":9,"title":"비교 · 최상급","status":"detailed","summary":"영어의 비교 표현은 세 층위다. 두 대상이 **대등**하면 ==as + 원급 + as==(as tall as), 한쪽이 **더**하면 ==비교급 + than==(taller than / more useful than), 셋 이상에서 **으뜸**이면 ==the + 최상급==(the tallest / the most useful)을 쓴다. 짧은 단어는 **-er/-est**, 긴 단어는 **more/most**를 붙이고, good-better-best 같은 **불규칙 변화**, much·far로 비교급을 강조하는 법, twice as ~ as 배수, the 비교급 ~ the 비교급 구문까지 함께 익힌다. ==more cheaper 같은 이중 비교, very + 비교급, than을 then으로 쓰는 실수==는 반드시 피한다.","subtopics":[{"key":"positive-as","title":"원급 비교 (as tall as)","points":["두 대상의 **정도가 같을** 때 ==as + 형용사/부사 원급 + as==로 감싼다. 가운데는 **비교급이 아니라 원급**이다.","\"as tall as\", \"as fast as\"처럼 as ~ as 사이에는 딱 **한 단어(원급)**만 넣는다.","뒤의 as는 **접속사**라 뒤에 「주어+동사」가 올 수도, 대명사(mine·yours)만 올 수도 있다.","수량은 ==as many as==(셀 수 있는 것)·==as much as==(셀 수 없는 것·금액)로 구분한다."],"examples":[{"en":"This laptop is as light as that one.","ko":"이 노트북은 저것만큼 가볍다.","parts":[{"t":"This laptop","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"as light as","role":"SC"},{"t":"that one.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Her phone is as expensive as mine.","ko":"그녀의 폰은 내 것만큼 비싸다.","parts":[{"t":"Her phone","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"as expensive as","role":"SC"},{"t":"mine.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The new model runs as fast as the old one.","ko":"새 모델은 구형만큼 빠르게 작동한다.","parts":[{"t":"The new model","role":"S"},{"t":"runs","role":"V"},{"t":"as fast as","role":"M"},{"t":"the old one.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This café is as busy as the one downtown.","ko":"이 카페는 시내에 있는 곳만큼 붐빈다.","parts":[{"t":"This café","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"as busy as","role":"SC"},{"t":"the one downtown.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He speaks English as fluently as a native.","ko":"그는 원어민만큼 유창하게 영어를 말한다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"speaks","role":"V"},{"t":"English","role":"O"},{"t":"as fluently as","role":"M"},{"t":"a native.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Our team worked as hard as the others.","ko":"우리 팀은 다른 팀들만큼 열심히 일했다.","parts":[{"t":"Our team","role":"S"},{"t":"worked","role":"V"},{"t":"as hard as","role":"M"},{"t":"the others.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This backpack costs as much as a textbook.","ko":"이 배낭은 교과서 한 권만큼 비싸다.","parts":[{"t":"This backpack","role":"S"},{"t":"costs","role":"V"},{"t":"as much as","role":"M"},{"t":"a textbook.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The exam was as difficult as we expected.","ko":"그 시험은 우리가 예상한 만큼 어려웠다.","parts":[{"t":"The exam","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"as difficult as","role":"SC"},{"t":"we expected.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["This is as taller as that.","This is as tall as that. (as ~ as 사이는 **비교급이 아니라 원급**이다)"],["She is so tall as her sister.","She is as tall as her sister. (긍정 동등 비교는 **as ~ as** — so ~ as는 부정문에서)"],["This bag costs as many as a book.","This bag costs as much as a book. (금액·불가산은 **as much as**)"]]},{"key":"not-as","title":"열등·부정 비교 (not as good as)","points":["한쪽이 **덜**할 때 ==not as[so] + 원급 + as==로 「A는 B만큼 ~하지 않다」를 나타낸다.","not as ... as = not so ... as. **부정문**에서는 so도 쓰지만 as가 더 흔하다.","\"A is not as tall as B\"는 곧 **B is taller than A**와 같은 뜻이다.","가운데는 반드시 **원급**이고, 뒤는 as(than 아님)로 받는다."],"examples":[{"en":"This phone is not as expensive as that one.","ko":"이 폰은 저것만큼 비싸지 않다.","parts":[{"t":"This phone","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"not as expensive as","role":"SC"},{"t":"that one.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The sequel was not as good as the original.","ko":"속편은 원작만큼 좋지 않았다.","parts":[{"t":"The sequel","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"not as good as","role":"SC"},{"t":"the original.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"My laptop is not so fast as yours.","ko":"내 노트북은 네 것만큼 빠르지 않다.","parts":[{"t":"My laptop","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"not so fast as","role":"SC"},{"t":"yours.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Today is not as cold as yesterday.","ko":"오늘은 어제만큼 춥지 않다.","parts":[{"t":"Today","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"not as cold as","role":"SC"},{"t":"yesterday.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The second lecture was not as clear as the first.","ko":"두 번째 강의는 첫 번째만큼 명확하지 않았다.","parts":[{"t":"The second lecture","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"not as clear as","role":"SC"},{"t":"the first.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This restaurant is not as crowded as it used to be.","ko":"이 식당은 예전만큼 붐비지 않는다.","parts":[{"t":"This restaurant","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"not as crowded as","role":"SC"},{"t":"it used to be.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He does not work as carefully as his partner.","ko":"그는 동료만큼 꼼꼼하게 일하지 않는다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"does not work","role":"V"},{"t":"as carefully as","role":"M"},{"t":"his partner.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The remake is not as memorable as the classic.","ko":"리메이크는 고전만큼 기억에 남지 않는다.","parts":[{"t":"The remake","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"not as memorable as","role":"SC"},{"t":"the classic.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["This phone is not as expensive than that.","This phone is not as expensive as that. (as ~ **as**로 받는다 — than 아님)"],["The sequel was not as better as the first.","The sequel was not as good as the first. (as ~ as 사이는 **원급 good**)"],["It is not so cheaper as the other.","It is not so cheap as the other. (가운데는 **원급 cheap**)"]]},{"key":"comparative","title":"비교급 + than (cheaper than)","points":["두 대상을 비교해 한쪽이 더하면 ==비교급 + than==을 쓴다. than은 **비교 상대**를 이끈다.","**1음절·일부 2음절**은 -er(cheaper), **긴 단어**는 more(more useful). ==둘을 겹치면 안 된다(more cheaper ✗)==.","than 뒤는 대명사 **주격이 원칙**이나 구어에서 목적격(than me)도 흔하다.","비교 대상은 **같은 종류**끼리(내 폰 vs 네 폰, 가격 vs 가격) 맞춘다."],"examples":[{"en":"This laptop is cheaper than the other one.","ko":"이 노트북은 다른 것보다 더 싸다.","parts":[{"t":"This laptop","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"cheaper","role":"SC"},{"t":"than the other one.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The new bridge is longer than the old one.","ko":"새 다리는 옛 다리보다 더 길다.","parts":[{"t":"The new bridge","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"longer","role":"SC"},{"t":"than the old one.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This textbook is more useful than that website.","ko":"이 교과서는 저 웹사이트보다 더 유용하다.","parts":[{"t":"This textbook","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"more useful","role":"SC"},{"t":"than that website.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She arrived earlier than her classmates.","ko":"그녀는 반 친구들보다 더 일찍 도착했다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"arrived","role":"V"},{"t":"earlier","role":"M"},{"t":"than her classmates.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The subway is faster than the bus at rush hour.","ko":"지하철은 출퇴근 시간에 버스보다 더 빠르다.","parts":[{"t":"The subway","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"faster","role":"SC"},{"t":"than the bus","role":"M"},{"t":"at rush hour.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This essay is more persuasive than the previous draft.","ko":"이 에세이는 이전 초고보다 더 설득력 있다.","parts":[{"t":"This essay","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"more persuasive","role":"SC"},{"t":"than the previous draft.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Online courses are more flexible than evening classes.","ko":"온라인 강좌는 야간 수업보다 더 유연하다.","parts":[{"t":"Online courses","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"more flexible","role":"SC"},{"t":"than evening classes.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The weather today is warmer than it was last week.","ko":"오늘 날씨는 지난주보다 더 따뜻하다.","parts":[{"t":"The weather today","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"warmer","role":"SC"},{"t":"than it was last week.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["This laptop is more cheaper than that.","This laptop is cheaper than that. (**이중 비교 금지** — -er와 more를 동시에 못 쓴다)"],["She is taller then me.","She is taller than me. (비교의 **than**을 then으로 쓰면 안 된다)"],["This is more useful as that.","This is more useful than that. (비교급 뒤는 **than**)"]]},{"key":"comp-emphasis","title":"비교급 강조 (much cheaper)","points":["비교급을 강조해 「훨씬」이라 할 때 ==much·far·even·a lot·still + 비교급==을 앞에 놓는다.","==very는 비교급을 못 꾸민다==(very better ✗). very는 원급 전용이다(very good).","much cheaper, far bigger, even faster처럼 **강조어 + 비교급** 순서다.","a bit·a little은 「조금 더」, much·far는 「훨씬 더」로 정도 차이를 준다."],"examples":[{"en":"This model is much cheaper than the old one.","ko":"이 모델은 구형보다 훨씬 더 싸다.","parts":[{"t":"This model","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"much","role":"M"},{"t":"cheaper","role":"SC"},{"t":"than the old one.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The new campus is far bigger than the old one.","ko":"새 캠퍼스는 옛 캠퍼스보다 훨씬 더 크다.","parts":[{"t":"The new campus","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"far","role":"M"},{"t":"bigger","role":"SC"},{"t":"than the old one.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This route is even faster during the day.","ko":"이 경로는 낮에는 한층 더 빠르다.","parts":[{"t":"This route","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"even","role":"M"},{"t":"faster","role":"SC"},{"t":"during the day.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Her second novel is a lot better than her first.","ko":"그녀의 두 번째 소설은 첫 작품보다 훨씬 더 낫다.","parts":[{"t":"Her second novel","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"a lot","role":"M"},{"t":"better","role":"SC"},{"t":"than her first.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The line moved much more slowly than expected.","ko":"줄은 예상보다 훨씬 더 느리게 움직였다.","parts":[{"t":"The line","role":"S"},{"t":"moved","role":"V"},{"t":"much","role":"M"},{"t":"more slowly","role":"M"},{"t":"than expected.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This edition is still more detailed than the last.","ko":"이 개정판은 지난 판보다 여전히 더 상세하다.","parts":[{"t":"This edition","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"still","role":"M"},{"t":"more detailed","role":"SC"},{"t":"than the last.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Tickets are far more expensive on weekends.","ko":"표는 주말에 훨씬 더 비싸다.","parts":[{"t":"Tickets","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"far","role":"M"},{"t":"more expensive","role":"SC"},{"t":"on weekends.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["This model is very cheaper than the old one.","This model is much cheaper than the old one. (**very는 비교급 불가** — much/far/even을 쓴다)"],["The campus is more bigger than before.","The campus is far bigger than before. (**이중 비교 ✗**, 강조는 far/much)"],["It is a lot more faster now.","It is a lot faster now. (fast는 **-er만** — more와 겹치면 안 된다)"]]},{"key":"superlative","title":"최상급 (the cheapest / the most)","points":["셋 이상에서 **으뜸**이면 ==the + 최상급==을 쓴다. 최상급 앞 the를 빠뜨리지 않는다.","짧은 단어는 -est(cheapest), 긴 단어는 most(most interesting). ==the most tall ✗ → the tallest==.","최상급 뒤에는 **명사**가 자주 따라온다(the cheapest option).","소유격·this 등이 the를 대신하면 the를 생략한다(my best friend)."],"examples":[{"en":"This is the cheapest option on the menu.","ko":"이것이 메뉴에서 가장 싼 선택지다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the cheapest option","role":"SC"},{"t":"on the menu.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She is the tallest player on the team.","ko":"그녀는 팀에서 가장 키가 큰 선수다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the tallest player","role":"SC"},{"t":"on the team.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"It was the most interesting lecture this term.","ko":"그것은 이번 학기 가장 흥미로운 강의였다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"the most interesting lecture","role":"SC"},{"t":"this term.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This laptop has the longest battery life.","ko":"이 노트북은 배터리 수명이 가장 길다.","parts":[{"t":"This laptop","role":"S"},{"t":"has","role":"V"},{"t":"the longest battery life.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"That was the most expensive meal of the trip.","ko":"그것은 여행에서 가장 비싼 식사였다.","parts":[{"t":"That","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"the most expensive meal","role":"SC"},{"t":"of the trip.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He gave the clearest explanation in class.","ko":"그는 수업에서 가장 명확한 설명을 했다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"gave","role":"V"},{"t":"the clearest explanation","role":"O"},{"t":"in class.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This is the busiest street in the city.","ko":"이곳은 도시에서 가장 붐비는 거리다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the busiest street","role":"SC"},{"t":"in the city.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Summer is the hottest season of the year.","ko":"여름은 일 년 중 가장 더운 계절이다.","parts":[{"t":"Summer","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the hottest season","role":"SC"},{"t":"of the year.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["It was the most tall building.","It was the tallest building. (짧은 단어는 **-est** — most를 안 붙인다)"],["This is cheapest option here.","This is the cheapest option here. (최상급 앞 **the**를 빠뜨리면 안 된다)"],["She is the most smart student.","She is the smartest student. (smart는 **-est**)"]]},{"key":"superlative-scope","title":"최상급 범위 (in the city / of the three)","points":["최상급의 **범위**는 ==in + 단수 장소·집단==(in the city, in the class), ==of + 복수·기간==(of the three, of the year)으로 나타낸다.","in 뒤에는 보통 **단수 명사**(장소/조직), of 뒤에는 **복수 명사나 기간**이 온다.","\"the tallest **in** the city\", \"the youngest **of** the three\"처럼 구별한다.","기간(the year, the week)에도 of를 쓴다: the coldest day **of** the year."],"examples":[{"en":"It is the tallest building in the city.","ko":"그것은 도시에서 가장 높은 건물이다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the tallest building","role":"SC"},{"t":"in the city.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She is the smartest student in her class.","ko":"그녀는 반에서 가장 똑똑한 학생이다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the smartest student","role":"SC"},{"t":"in her class.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This is the best café in the neighborhood.","ko":"이곳은 동네에서 가장 좋은 카페다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the best café","role":"SC"},{"t":"in the neighborhood.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He is the fastest runner of all the athletes.","ko":"그는 모든 선수 중 가장 빠른 주자다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the fastest runner","role":"SC"},{"t":"of all the athletes.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"That was the coldest day of the year.","ko":"그날은 일 년 중 가장 추운 날이었다.","parts":[{"t":"That","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"the coldest day","role":"SC"},{"t":"of the year.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This is the most popular course in the department.","ko":"이것은 학과에서 가장 인기 있는 강좌다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the most popular course","role":"SC"},{"t":"in the department.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She is the youngest of the three sisters.","ko":"그녀는 세 자매 중 막내다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the youngest","role":"SC"},{"t":"of the three sisters.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["He is the tallest of his class.","He is the tallest in his class. (단수 집단은 **in**)"],["She is the youngest in the three.","She is the youngest of the three. (복수·숫자 범위는 **of**)"],["It was the coldest day in the year.","It was the coldest day of the year. (기간은 **of**)"]]},{"key":"multiple","title":"배수 비교 (twice as big as)","points":["배수는 ==배수사 + as + 원급 + as==로 쓴다: twice as big as, three times as much as.","**twice**(2배)는 as ~ as만 쓰고, three times부터는 ==times as ~ as== 또는 비교급 than도 가능하다.","half(절반)도 같은 자리에 온다: half as large as.","수량 배수는 ==times as many as==(가산)·==times as much as==(불가산)로 구분한다."],"examples":[{"en":"This apartment is twice as big as ours.","ko":"이 아파트는 우리 것의 두 배 크기다.","parts":[{"t":"This apartment","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"twice as big as","role":"SC"},{"t":"ours.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The new plan costs three times as much as the old one.","ko":"새 요금제는 옛 것의 세 배 비용이 든다.","parts":[{"t":"The new plan","role":"S"},{"t":"costs","role":"V"},{"t":"three times as much as","role":"M"},{"t":"the old one.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Their house is half as large as mine.","ko":"그들의 집은 내 집의 절반 크기다.","parts":[{"t":"Their house","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"half as large as","role":"SC"},{"t":"mine.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This laptop is twice as fast as the previous model.","ko":"이 노트북은 이전 모델보다 두 배 빠르다.","parts":[{"t":"This laptop","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"twice as fast as","role":"SC"},{"t":"the previous model.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The city has four times as many people as our town.","ko":"그 도시는 우리 마을보다 네 배 많은 사람이 산다.","parts":[{"t":"The city","role":"S"},{"t":"has","role":"V"},{"t":"four times as many people as","role":"O"},{"t":"our town.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This bag holds twice as much as that one.","ko":"이 가방은 저것의 두 배를 담는다.","parts":[{"t":"This bag","role":"S"},{"t":"holds","role":"V"},{"t":"twice as much as","role":"O"},{"t":"that one.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The premium ticket is three times as expensive as standard.","ko":"프리미엄 표는 일반석의 세 배 비싸다.","parts":[{"t":"The premium ticket","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"three times as expensive as","role":"SC"},{"t":"standard.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["This room is twice bigger than ours.","This room is twice as big as ours. (배수는 **배수사 + as ~ as**)"],["It costs three time as much as that.","It costs three times as much as that. (**times** 복수로 쓴다)"],["The city has twice as much people as ours.","The city has twice as many people as ours. (가산명사는 **as many as**)"]]},{"key":"the-comp-the-comp","title":"the 비교급 ~, the 비교급 ~ (The more, the better)","points":["「~할수록 더 ~하다」는 ==The + 비교급 ~, the + 비교급 ~== 구문이다. 두 절 모두 the로 시작한다.","각 the 뒤에 **비교급**을 두고, 원래 자리에서 앞으로 끌어온다: You practice more → The more you practice.","짧게는 「The + 비교급, the + 비교급」만 남기고 ==be동사를 생략==하기도 한다(The higher the price, the better the quality).","뜻은 **비례**다: 앞이 커지면 뒤도 커진다."],"examples":[{"en":"The more you practice, the better you get.","ko":"연습을 많이 할수록 더 잘하게 된다.","parts":[{"t":"The more","role":"M"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"practice,","role":"V"},{"t":"the better","role":"M"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"get.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The sooner we leave, the earlier we arrive.","ko":"일찍 떠날수록 더 일찍 도착한다.","parts":[{"t":"The sooner","role":"M"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"leave,","role":"V"},{"t":"the earlier","role":"M"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"arrive.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The higher the price, the better the quality.","ko":"가격이 높을수록 품질이 더 좋다.","parts":[{"t":"The higher","role":"M"},{"t":"the price,","role":"S"},{"t":"the better","role":"M"},{"t":"the quality.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"The more expensive the phone, the longer it lasts.","ko":"폰이 비쌀수록 더 오래간다.","parts":[{"t":"The more expensive","role":"M"},{"t":"the phone,","role":"S"},{"t":"the longer","role":"M"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"lasts.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The harder the exam, the lower the average score.","ko":"시험이 어려울수록 평균 점수가 더 낮다.","parts":[{"t":"The harder","role":"M"},{"t":"the exam,","role":"S"},{"t":"the lower","role":"M"},{"t":"the average score.","role":"S"}]},{"en":"The colder it gets, the more energy we use.","ko":"추워질수록 우리는 더 많은 에너지를 쓴다.","parts":[{"t":"The colder","role":"M"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"gets,","role":"V"},{"t":"the more energy","role":"M"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"use.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"The longer you wait, the harder it becomes.","ko":"오래 기다릴수록 더 힘들어진다.","parts":[{"t":"The longer","role":"M"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"wait,","role":"V"},{"t":"the harder","role":"M"},{"t":"it","role":"S"},{"t":"becomes.","role":"V"}]}],"mistakes":[["More you practice, better you get.","The more you practice, the better you get. (두 절 모두 **the**로 시작한다)"],["The more you practice, you get the better.","The more you practice, the better you get. (뒤 절도 **the 비교급을 앞으로** 보낸다)"],["The more cheaper it is, the more people buy.","The cheaper it is, the more people buy. (**이중 비교 ✗** — the cheaper)"]]},{"key":"less-least","title":"열등 비교 (less / the least)","points":["열등 비교는 ==less + 원급 + than==(덜 ~한), 최하는 ==the least + 원급==(가장 덜 ~한)으로 쓴다.","less/least는 **긴 형용사**에 주로 쓴다(less expensive). 짧은 말은 not as ... as가 자연스럽다.","less는 more의 반대, least는 most의 반대다.","==less 뒤에는 원급==만 온다(less cheaper ✗)."],"examples":[{"en":"This phone is less expensive than that one.","ko":"이 폰은 저것보다 덜 비싸다.","parts":[{"t":"This phone","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"less expensive","role":"SC"},{"t":"than that one.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The bus is less crowded than the subway.","ko":"버스는 지하철보다 덜 붐빈다.","parts":[{"t":"The bus","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"less crowded","role":"SC"},{"t":"than the subway.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This is the least expensive item in the store.","ko":"이것은 가게에서 가장 싼 물건이다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the least expensive item","role":"SC"},{"t":"in the store.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Her essay was less convincing than his.","ko":"그녀의 에세이는 그의 것보다 덜 설득력 있었다.","parts":[{"t":"Her essay","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"less convincing","role":"SC"},{"t":"than his.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This route is less direct than the highway.","ko":"이 경로는 고속도로보다 덜 직선적이다.","parts":[{"t":"This route","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"less direct","role":"SC"},{"t":"than the highway.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"It was the least popular choice on the survey.","ko":"그것은 설문에서 가장 인기 없는 선택이었다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"the least popular choice","role":"SC"},{"t":"on the survey.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The second option is less risky than the first.","ko":"두 번째 선택지는 첫 번째보다 덜 위험하다.","parts":[{"t":"The second option","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"less risky","role":"SC"},{"t":"than the first.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["This is less expensive as that.","This is less expensive than that. (less 비교는 **than**으로 받는다)"],["It is the less popular choice.","It is the least popular choice. (최하는 **the least**)"],["This route is less shorter than that.","This route is less short than that. (less 뒤는 **원급**)"]]},{"key":"one-of","title":"one of the + 최상급 + 복수명사","points":["「가장 ~한 것 중 하나」는 ==one of the + 최상급 + 복수명사==다. 명사는 반드시 **복수**다.","one이 주어면 **동사는 단수**로 받는다: One of the best restaurants **is** ~.","==one of the best restaurant ✗ → restaurants==. 복수를 잊지 않는다.","하나만 콕 집지 않아 단정을 피하는 **완충 표현**이다."],"examples":[{"en":"This is one of the best restaurants in town.","ko":"이곳은 시내에서 가장 좋은 식당 중 하나다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"one of the best restaurants","role":"SC"},{"t":"in town.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She is one of the smartest students in the program.","ko":"그녀는 프로그램에서 가장 똑똑한 학생 중 한 명이다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"one of the smartest students","role":"SC"},{"t":"in the program.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"It is one of the most popular apps this year.","ko":"그것은 올해 가장 인기 있는 앱 중 하나다.","parts":[{"t":"It","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"one of the most popular apps","role":"SC"},{"t":"this year.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"That was one of the longest meetings of the week.","ko":"그것은 그 주 가장 긴 회의 중 하나였다.","parts":[{"t":"That","role":"S"},{"t":"was","role":"V"},{"t":"one of the longest meetings","role":"SC"},{"t":"of the week.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He is one of the fastest swimmers on the team.","ko":"그는 팀에서 가장 빠른 수영 선수 중 한 명이다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"one of the fastest swimmers","role":"SC"},{"t":"on the team.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This is one of the cheapest flights available.","ko":"이것은 이용 가능한 가장 싼 항공편 중 하나다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"one of the cheapest flights","role":"SC"},{"t":"available.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Tokyo is one of the largest cities in the world.","ko":"도쿄는 세계에서 가장 큰 도시 중 하나다.","parts":[{"t":"Tokyo","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"one of the largest cities","role":"SC"},{"t":"in the world.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["This is one of the best restaurant in town.","This is one of the best restaurants in town. (one of the 최상급 뒤 **복수명사**)"],["One of the students are absent.","One of the students is absent. (주어 **one**은 단수 동사로 받는다)"],["It is one of the most cheap flights.","It is one of the cheapest flights. (cheap은 **-est**, 명사는 복수 flights)"]]},{"key":"latin","title":"라틴계 비교 (superior to / prior to)","points":["라틴어에서 온 ==superior·inferior·prior·senior·junior·preferable==는 이미 비교 뜻을 품어 than 대신 ==to==를 쓴다.","superior to(~보다 우수), inferior to(~보다 열등), prior to(~이전), senior/junior to(연장/연하).","==superior than ✗ → superior to==. than을 쓰지 않는 것이 핵심이다.","prefer도 같은 계열이다: ==prefer A to B==(B보다 A를 선호)."],"examples":[{"en":"This model is superior to the previous version.","ko":"이 모델은 이전 버전보다 우수하다.","parts":[{"t":"This model","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"superior","role":"SC"},{"t":"to the previous version.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The cheaper fabric felt inferior to the original.","ko":"더 싼 원단은 원본보다 품질이 떨어지는 느낌이었다.","parts":[{"t":"The cheaper fabric","role":"S"},{"t":"felt","role":"V"},{"t":"inferior","role":"SC"},{"t":"to the original.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She is senior to me in the department.","ko":"그녀는 부서에서 나보다 상급자다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"senior","role":"SC"},{"t":"to me","role":"M"},{"t":"in the department.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Please finish the reading prior to the lecture.","ko":"강의 전에 읽기 자료를 끝내라.","parts":[{"t":"Please finish","role":"V"},{"t":"the reading","role":"O"},{"t":"prior to the lecture.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This engine is superior to anything on the market.","ko":"이 엔진은 시장의 어떤 것보다도 우수하다.","parts":[{"t":"This engine","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"superior","role":"SC"},{"t":"to anything on the market.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The knockoff is clearly inferior to the brand name.","ko":"그 짝퉁은 브랜드 제품보다 확실히 열등하다.","parts":[{"t":"The knockoff","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"clearly","role":"M"},{"t":"inferior","role":"SC"},{"t":"to the brand name.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"He is two years junior to his colleague.","ko":"그는 동료보다 두 살 아래다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"two years junior","role":"SC"},{"t":"to his colleague.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Their service is superior to their competitors'.","ko":"그들의 서비스는 경쟁사들보다 우수하다.","parts":[{"t":"Their service","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"superior","role":"SC"},{"t":"to their competitors'.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["This model is superior than the old one.","This model is superior to the old one. (라틴계 비교는 **to** — than 아님)"],["Finish the reading prior than the class.","Finish the reading prior to the class. (**prior to**)"],["I prefer tea than coffee.","I prefer tea to coffee. (**prefer A to B**)"]]},{"key":"irregular","title":"불규칙 비교 (better / worse / farther)","points":["불규칙: ==good/well-better-best, bad/badly-worse-worst, many/much-more-most, little-less-least, far-farther[further]-farthest[furthest]==.","farther는 **거리**, further는 **정도·추가**에 주로 쓴다.","==gooder ✗ → better, baddest ✗ → worst==. 규칙형을 억지로 만들지 않는다.","비교 대상은 격을 맞춘다: ==my score vs my brother's==(my brother 아님), mine vs yours."],"examples":[{"en":"This coffee tastes better than the others.","ko":"이 커피는 다른 것들보다 맛이 더 좋다.","parts":[{"t":"This coffee","role":"S"},{"t":"tastes","role":"V"},{"t":"better","role":"SC"},{"t":"than the others.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Traffic today is worse than usual.","ko":"오늘 교통은 평소보다 더 나쁘다.","parts":[{"t":"Traffic today","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"worse","role":"SC"},{"t":"than usual.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"My score is higher than my brother's.","ko":"내 점수는 우리 형 점수보다 더 높다.","parts":[{"t":"My score","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"higher","role":"SC"},{"t":"than my brother's.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This store has more options than that one.","ko":"이 가게는 저 가게보다 선택지가 더 많다.","parts":[{"t":"This store","role":"S"},{"t":"has","role":"V"},{"t":"more options","role":"O"},{"t":"than that one.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"She has less free time than her roommate.","ko":"그녀는 룸메이트보다 자유 시간이 더 적다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"has","role":"V"},{"t":"less free time","role":"O"},{"t":"than her roommate.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The library is farther from here than the gym.","ko":"도서관은 여기서 체육관보다 더 멀다.","parts":[{"t":"The library","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"farther","role":"SC"},{"t":"from here","role":"M"},{"t":"than the gym.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"This laptop is the best of the three.","ko":"이 노트북이 셋 중에 가장 좋다.","parts":[{"t":"This laptop","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the best","role":"SC"},{"t":"of the three.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Your handwriting is neater than mine.","ko":"네 글씨가 내 것보다 더 깔끔하다.","parts":[{"t":"Your handwriting","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"neater","role":"SC"},{"t":"than mine.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["This coffee tastes gooder than the others.","This coffee tastes better than the others. (good의 비교급은 **better**)"],["Traffic is more worse than usual.","Traffic is worse than usual. (worse에 **more 금지** — 이중 비교)"],["My score is higher than my brother.","My score is higher than my brother's. (점수끼리 비교 — **my brother's**)"]]}],"db":{"title":"비교·최상급 DB · 변화형 & 관용","intro":"비교·최상급의 뼈대는 세 가지다. ==짧은 단어 -er/-est, 긴 단어 more/most==, 그리고 good-better-best 같은 **불규칙 변화**다. 아래 4개 그룹으로 ①불규칙 변화표 ②규칙별 -er/more 선택 ③much·far·the 비교급 the 비교급 같은 관용·강조 ④라틴계 비교(superior to)와 배수(twice as ~ as)까지 한눈에 정리했다. ==more cheaper·very better·superior than==은 대표적 함정이다.","groups":[{"label":"불규칙 비교변화표","note":"규칙을 따르지 않고 **통째로 외워야** 하는 핵심 15개다. ==far와 old, late는 뜻에 따라 두 갈래==로 갈리니 특히 주의한다.","items":[{"w":"good / better / best","ko":"좋은","ex":"This is the best coffee here."},{"w":"well / better / best","ko":"건강한 · 잘","ex":"She feels better today."},{"w":"bad / worse / worst","ko":"나쁜","ex":"Traffic is worse than usual."},{"w":"badly / worse / worst","ko":"나쁘게 (부사)","ex":"He did worse on the retest."},{"w":"ill / worse / worst","ko":"아픈","ex":"He looked worse by evening."},{"w":"many / more / most","ko":"(수가) 많은","ex":"She has more books than me."},{"w":"much / more / most","ko":"(양이) 많은","ex":"This costs more than that."},{"w":"little / less / least","ko":"(양이) 적은","ex":"I have less time than you."},{"w":"far / farther / farthest","ko":"먼 (거리)","ex":"The gym is farther than the café."},{"w":"far / further / furthest","ko":"더한 (정도·추가)","ex":"We need further discussion."},{"w":"late / later / latest","ko":"늦은 (시간)","ex":"This is the latest update."},{"w":"late / latter / last","ko":"후자의 · 마지막 (순서)","ex":"I prefer the latter option."},{"w":"old / older / oldest","ko":"나이 든 (일반)","ex":"He is older than his cousin."},{"w":"old / elder / eldest","ko":"연장의 (형제)","ex":"My eldest sister lives abroad."},{"w":"near / nearer / nearest","ko":"가까운","ex":"Where is the nearest station?"}]},{"label":"-er/-est vs more/most 규칙","note":"**음절 수와 철자**로 갈린다. ==1음절은 -er/-est, 3음절 이상은 more/most==, 2음절은 어미(-y·-le·-ow·-er)에 따라 갈린다. -ful·-ing·-ed·-ly는 more/most다.","items":[{"w":"tall / taller / tallest","ko":"1음절: -er/-est","ex":"He is taller than me."},{"w":"cheap / cheaper / cheapest","ko":"1음절","ex":"This is the cheapest one."},{"w":"fast / faster / fastest","ko":"1음절","ex":"The subway is faster."},{"w":"small / smaller / smallest","ko":"1음절","ex":"Mine is smaller than yours."},{"w":"nice / nicer / nicest","ko":"-e로 끝: -r/-st","ex":"This café is nicer."},{"w":"large / larger / largest","ko":"-e로 끝","ex":"Their house is larger."},{"w":"late / later / latest","ko":"-e로 끝","ex":"He arrived later than usual."},{"w":"big / bigger / biggest","ko":"단모음+단자음: 자음 반복","ex":"This is the biggest room."},{"w":"hot / hotter / hottest","ko":"자음 반복","ex":"Today is hotter than yesterday."},{"w":"thin / thinner / thinnest","ko":"자음 반복","ex":"This laptop is thinner."},{"w":"sad / sadder / saddest","ko":"자음 반복","ex":"It was the saddest scene."},{"w":"happy / happier / happiest","ko":"자음+y: y→i","ex":"She looks happier now."},{"w":"easy / easier / easiest","ko":"y→i","ex":"This test is easier."},{"w":"busy / busier / busiest","ko":"y→i","ex":"Mondays are the busiest."},{"w":"early / earlier / earliest","ko":"y→i","ex":"He came earlier than me."},{"w":"dry / drier / driest","ko":"y→i","ex":"It is the driest month."},{"w":"simple / simpler / simplest","ko":"-le로 끝: -r/-st","ex":"This is the simplest way."},{"w":"narrow / narrower / narrowest","ko":"-ow로 끝: -er/-est","ex":"This road is narrower."},{"w":"clever / cleverer / cleverest","ko":"-er로 끝: -er/-est","ex":"She is cleverer than she seems."},{"w":"quiet / quieter / quietest","ko":"2음절: -er/-est 가능","ex":"This room is quieter."},{"w":"famous / more famous / most famous","ko":"2음절 대부분: more/most","ex":"He is more famous now."},{"w":"careful / more careful / most careful","ko":"-ful로 끝: more/most","ex":"Be more careful next time."},{"w":"modern / more modern / most modern","ko":"more/most","ex":"This design is more modern."},{"w":"expensive / more expensive / most expensive","ko":"3음절 이상: more/most","ex":"This phone is more expensive."},{"w":"beautiful / more beautiful / most beautiful","ko":"3음절 이상","ex":"It is the most beautiful view."},{"w":"difficult / more difficult / most difficult","ko":"3음절 이상","ex":"This is more difficult than that."},{"w":"interesting / more interesting / most interesting","ko":"-ing 형: more/most","ex":"It was the most interesting talk."}]},{"label":"관용 · 강조 표현","note":"비교 구조를 활용한 **굳어진 표현**들이다. ==much·far·even·a lot·still은 비교급 강조==(very는 불가), the 비교급 the 비교급은 비례, as ~ as 관용구는 통째로 외운다.","items":[{"w":"much + 비교급","ko":"훨씬 더","ex":"much cheaper than before"},{"w":"far + 비교급","ko":"훨씬 더","ex":"far bigger than ours"},{"w":"even + 비교급","ko":"한층 더","ex":"even faster at night"},{"w":"a lot + 비교급","ko":"훨씬 더","ex":"a lot better than his first"},{"w":"still + 비교급","ko":"그보다 더","ex":"still more detailed"},{"w":"a little / a bit + 비교급","ko":"조금 더","ex":"a bit warmer today"},{"w":"the 비교급 ~, the 비교급 ~","ko":"~할수록 더 …하다","ex":"The more, the better."},{"w":"비교급 and 비교급","ko":"점점 더 ~한","ex":"It gets colder and colder."},{"w":"more and more","ko":"점점 더 많은","ex":"more and more students"},{"w":"as soon as possible","ko":"가능한 한 빨리","ex":"Reply as soon as possible."},{"w":"as much as possible","ko":"가능한 한 많이","ex":"Save as much as possible."},{"w":"as far as I know","ko":"내가 아는 한","ex":"As far as I know, it's free."},{"w":"as long as","ko":"~하는 한 (조건)","ex":"as long as you try"},{"w":"as well as","ko":"~뿐만 아니라","ex":"He sings as well as dances."},{"w":"as good as","ko":"거의 ~인","ex":"The deal is as good as done."},{"w":"no longer","ko":"더 이상 ~아닌","ex":"It is no longer free."},{"w":"no more than","ko":"겨우, ~에 불과한","ex":"no more than five dollars"},{"w":"no less than","ko":"~만큼이나","ex":"no less than a hundred people"},{"w":"not so much A as B","ko":"A라기보다 B","ex":"not so much luck as effort"},{"w":"would rather A than B","ko":"차라리 A하겠다","ex":"I'd rather walk than wait."},{"w":"the same as","ko":"~와 똑같은","ex":"Mine is the same as yours."},{"w":"twice as ~ as","ko":"두 배로 ~한","ex":"twice as big as ours"},{"w":"sooner or later","ko":"조만간","ex":"It'll happen sooner or later."},{"w":"more or less","ko":"다소, 대략","ex":"It's more or less done."},{"w":"all the more","ko":"그만큼 더","ex":"all the more reason to try"}]},{"label":"라틴계 비교 & 배수","note":"-or로 끝나는 **라틴계 비교어**는 than 대신 ==to==를 쓰고, 배수는 ==배수사 + as ~ as== 또는 times + 비교급 than으로 쓴다. by far·the very는 최상급 강조다.","items":[{"w":"superior to","ko":"~보다 우수한","ex":"This model is superior to the old one."},{"w":"inferior to","ko":"~보다 열등한","ex":"The copy is inferior to the original."},{"w":"prior to","ko":"~이전에","ex":"Read it prior to the lecture."},{"w":"senior to","ko":"~보다 상급·연장인","ex":"She is senior to me at work."},{"w":"junior to","ko":"~보다 하급·연하인","ex":"He is junior to her by two years."},{"w":"preferable to","ko":"~보다 나은","ex":"Tea is preferable to soda."},{"w":"anterior to","ko":"~보다 앞쪽의","ex":"anterior to the spine"},{"w":"posterior to","ko":"~보다 뒤쪽의","ex":"posterior to the joint"},{"w":"superior + to (than ✗)","ko":"than 금지, to만 쓴다","ex":"superior to (not superior than)"},{"w":"prefer A to B","ko":"B보다 A를 선호하다","ex":"I prefer tea to coffee."},{"w":"twice as large as","ko":"두 배 큰","ex":"twice as large as mine"},{"w":"three times as much as","ko":"세 배 (양)","ex":"three times as much as before"},{"w":"half as long as","ko":"절반 길이의","ex":"half as long as the first"},{"w":"four times as many as","ko":"네 배 (수)","ex":"four times as many as ours"},{"w":"ten times bigger than","ko":"열 배 큰","ex":"ten times bigger than the old one"},{"w":"as ~ as any","ko":"누구·무엇 못지않게","ex":"as good as any player here"},{"w":"as ~ as ever","ko":"여전히 ~한","ex":"as busy as ever"},{"w":"second to none","ko":"어디에도 뒤지지 않는","ex":"Their service is second to none."},{"w":"by far the + 최상급","ko":"단연코 가장 ~한","ex":"by far the best option"},{"w":"the very + 최상급","ko":"바로 그 최고의","ex":"the very best seats"},{"w":"much the + 최상급","ko":"단연 가장 ~한","ex":"much the largest share"},{"w":"nothing like as ~ as","ko":"~만큼 전혀 …가 아닌","ex":"nothing like as hard as it looks"},{"w":"none the wiser","ko":"여전히 (하나도) 모르는","ex":"I was none the wiser after."}]}]}},{"n":10,"title":"명사구","status":"detailed","summary":"명사 하나를 중심으로 살을 붙여 완성하는 **명사구**의 구조를 익힌다. 앞에서는 ==한정사 → 수사 → 형용사 → 핵심명사== 순으로 쌓고, 뒤에서는 **전치사구·관계절·to부정사·분사구**로 길게 확장한다. 한정사는 관사·지시사·소유격·수량사로 나뉘고, ==중심 한정사끼리는 못 겹치지만 all·both 같은 전치한정사는 겹쳐 쓸 수 있다==. 이렇게 만든 명사구가 문장의 ==주어·목적어·보어·전치사의 목적어==가 되므로, Build-a-Sentence에서 답을 이루는 핵심 단위다.","subtopics":[{"key":"skeleton","title":"명사구 기본 골격 (the two big dogs)","points":["명사구의 기본 어순은 ==한정사(Determiner) → 수사(Numeral) → 형용사(Adjective) → 핵심명사(Head Noun)==다.","**핵심명사**가 뼈대이고, 그 앞에 한정사·수사·형용사가 이 순서대로 붙는다.","**수사(one/two/three)**는 ==한정사 뒤, 형용사 앞== 자리를 차지한다: \"the **two** big dogs\".","형용사는 언제나 **명사 앞**에 오며, 여러 개면 나란히 늘어놓는다.","명사만으로도 명사구가 되고, 여기에 살을 붙여 ==점점 길게 확장==해 나간다."],"examples":[{"en":"a big house","ko":"큰 집 한 채다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"big","role":"Adj"},{"t":"house","role":"N"}]},{"en":"my old car","ko":"내 오래된 차다.","parts":[{"t":"my","role":"Det"},{"t":"old","role":"Adj"},{"t":"car","role":"N"}]},{"en":"the two big dogs","ko":"그 큰 개 두 마리다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"two","role":"Num"},{"t":"big","role":"Adj"},{"t":"dogs","role":"N"}]},{"en":"my three close friends","ko":"내 친한 친구 세 명이다.","parts":[{"t":"my","role":"Det"},{"t":"three","role":"Num"},{"t":"close","role":"Adj"},{"t":"friends","role":"N"}]},{"en":"these five new books","ko":"이 새 책 다섯 권이다.","parts":[{"t":"these","role":"Det"},{"t":"five","role":"Num"},{"t":"new","role":"Adj"},{"t":"books","role":"N"}]},{"en":"three small dogs","ko":"작은 개 세 마리다.","parts":[{"t":"three","role":"Num"},{"t":"small","role":"Adj"},{"t":"dogs","role":"N"}]},{"en":"this cozy little room","ko":"이 아늑하고 작은 방이다.","parts":[{"t":"this","role":"Det"},{"t":"cozy","role":"Adj"},{"t":"little","role":"Adj"},{"t":"room","role":"N"}]},{"en":"I bought a new phone.","ko":"나는 새 휴대폰을 샀다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"bought","role":"V"},{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"new","role":"Adj"},{"t":"phone.","role":"N"}]}],"mistakes":[["big a house","a big house (**한정사(a)가 형용사(big)보다 먼저** 온다)"],["the big two dogs","the two big dogs (**수사(two)는 형용사(big) 앞, 한정사 뒤**에 온다)"],["a houses","a house / houses (**부정관사 a는 단수 명사**에만 붙는다)"]]},{"key":"determiner","title":"한정사 종류와 겹침 (all the students)","points":["한정사는 명사 앞에서 **무엇을 가리키는지**를 정하며 크게 ==관사·지시사·소유격·수량사== 네 종류다.","**관사**(a/an/the), **지시사**(this/that/these/those), **소유격**(my/your/his/her/its/our/their·명사's), **수량사**(some/any/no/many/much/few/all/both/each/every…)로 나뉜다.","==중심 한정사끼리는 겹쳐 쓸 수 없다==: \"a my book\" ✗ → **\"a book of mine\"**, \"this my friend\" ✗ → **\"this friend of mine\"**.","**BUT 전치한정사(predeterminer) all/both/half/double**은 중심 한정사 앞에 덧붙일 수 있다: ==all the / all my / all these / both the / half the==.","다르게는 「**수량사 + of + 한정사**」로 풀어 **all of the / some of my / none of these**처럼 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"a book of mine","ko":"내 책 한 권이다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"book","role":"N"},{"t":"of mine","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"this friend of mine","ko":"이 내 친구다.","parts":[{"t":"this","role":"Det"},{"t":"friend","role":"N"},{"t":"of mine","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"all the students","ko":"학생들 전부다.","parts":[{"t":"all","role":"Det"},{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"students","role":"N"}]},{"en":"all my friends","ko":"내 친구들 전부다.","parts":[{"t":"all","role":"Det"},{"t":"my","role":"Det"},{"t":"friends","role":"N"}]},{"en":"all these books","ko":"이 책들 전부다.","parts":[{"t":"all","role":"Det"},{"t":"these","role":"Det"},{"t":"books","role":"N"}]},{"en":"both the teams","ko":"그 두 팀 다다.","parts":[{"t":"both","role":"Det"},{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"teams","role":"N"}]},{"en":"half the class","ko":"반 학급의 절반이다.","parts":[{"t":"half","role":"Det"},{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"class","role":"N"}]},{"en":"I read all the books.","ko":"나는 그 책을 전부 읽었다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"read","role":"V"},{"t":"all","role":"Det"},{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"books.","role":"N"}]}],"mistakes":[["a my book","a book of mine / my book (**중심 한정사끼리(관사 a·소유격 my)는 겹쳐 쓸 수 없다**)"],["the all books","all the books (**전치한정사 all은 중심 한정사(the) 앞**에 온다)"],["all of students","all of the students (**of 뒤에는 한정사 the**가 있어야 한다)"]]},{"key":"post-prep","title":"후치수식 ① 전치사구 (the book on the table)","points":["명사를 뒤에서 꾸미는 첫 번째 방법은 ==전치사구(전치사 + 명사)==다.","\"the book **on the table**\"처럼 위치·소속·관계를 명사 **뒤에 통째로** 붙인다.","**of**는 소속·부분을 나타내 \"a cup of coffee\", \"the price of the ticket\"처럼 쓴다.","전치사구는 형용사와 달리 **핵심명사 뒤**에 오는 점을 반드시 지킨다.","전치사 뒤 명사에도 **관사(the/a)**가 필요하다: \"on the table\" (on table ✗)."],"examples":[{"en":"the book on the table","ko":"탁자 위의 그 책이다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"book","role":"N"},{"t":"on the table","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"a house with a garden","ko":"정원이 있는 집이다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"house","role":"N"},{"t":"with a garden","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the man in the blue jacket","ko":"파란 재킷을 입은 남자다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"man","role":"N"},{"t":"in the blue jacket","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"a cup of coffee","ko":"커피 한 잔이다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"cup","role":"N"},{"t":"of coffee","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the keys under the sofa","ko":"소파 밑의 열쇠들이다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"keys","role":"N"},{"t":"under the sofa","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"a girl with red hair","ko":"빨간 머리 소녀다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"girl","role":"N"},{"t":"with red hair","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"The store near my house is closed.","ko":"우리 집 근처 가게가 문을 닫았다.","parts":[{"t":"The","role":"Det"},{"t":"store","role":"N"},{"t":"near my house","role":"Pm"},{"t":"is","role":"Aux"},{"t":"closed.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"I like the painting on the wall.","ko":"나는 벽에 걸린 그림이 좋다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"like","role":"V"},{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"painting","role":"N"},{"t":"on the wall.","role":"Pm"}]}],"mistakes":[["the on the table book","the book on the table (**전치사구는 명사 뒤에서** 수식한다)"],["a coffee cup of","a cup of coffee (**of 전치사구**는 명사 뒤에 통째로 온다)"],["the book on table","the book on the table (**전치사 뒤 명사에도 관사 the**가 필요하다)"]]},{"key":"post-relative","title":"후치수식 ② 관계절 (the man who called)","points":["명사를 문장(절)으로 꾸미는 방법이 ==관계절==이며, 명사 뒤에 who/which/that로 잇는다.","**주격 관계대명사**(who/which/that)는 명사가 **하는 동작**을 설명한다: \"the man who called\".","**목적격 관계대명사**는 흔히 생략해 \"the book (that) I read\"처럼 바로 이어 붙인다.","관계대명사가 **주어 역할**을 하므로 뒤에 he·it 같은 **대명사를 또 쓰지 않는다**.","장소·시간은 **where/when**으로 이어 \"the house where I live\"처럼 쓴다."],"examples":[{"en":"the man who called","ko":"전화한 남자다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"man","role":"N"},{"t":"who called","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the book that I read","ko":"내가 읽은 책이다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"book","role":"N"},{"t":"that I read","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the woman who lives next door","ko":"옆집에 사는 여자다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"woman","role":"N"},{"t":"who lives next door","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the movie we watched","ko":"우리가 본 영화다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"movie","role":"N"},{"t":"we watched","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"a restaurant that serves sushi","ko":"초밥을 파는 식당이다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"restaurant","role":"N"},{"t":"that serves sushi","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the students who passed the exam","ko":"시험에 합격한 학생들이다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"students","role":"N"},{"t":"who passed the exam","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the house where I grew up","ko":"내가 자란 집이다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"house","role":"N"},{"t":"where I grew up","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"The teacher who helped me is very kind.","ko":"나를 도와준 선생님은 매우 친절하다.","parts":[{"t":"The","role":"Det"},{"t":"teacher","role":"N"},{"t":"who helped me","role":"Pm"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"very kind.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["the man who he called","the man who called (**관계대명사 who가 주어**라 he를 또 쓰지 않는다)"],["the book which I read it","the book which I read (**목적격 관계절**에서 it을 또 쓰지 않는다)"],["the woman lives next door","the woman who lives next door (**주격 관계대명사 who**를 빠뜨리면 안 된다)"]]},{"key":"post-infinitive","title":"후치수식 ③ to부정사 (the best way to learn)","points":["명사 뒤에 ==to부정사(to + 동사원형)==를 붙여 **미래·목적·해야 할 일**을 나타낸다.","\"the best **way to learn**\", \"a **chance to win**\"처럼 명사가 뜻하는 행동을 이어준다.","**something·anything·nothing** 뒤에도 to부정사를 붙인다: \"something to eat\".","way·time·chance·reason·place 같은 명사가 **to부정사와 자주 짝**을 이룬다.","\"something to eat\"처럼 -thing류는 **형용사도 뒤에** 붙는 점을 기억한다 (something cold to drink)."],"examples":[{"en":"the best way to learn","ko":"배우는 가장 좋은 방법이다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"best","role":"Adj"},{"t":"way","role":"N"},{"t":"to learn","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"something to eat","ko":"먹을 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"something","role":"N"},{"t":"to eat","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"a chance to win","ko":"이길 기회다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"chance","role":"N"},{"t":"to win","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the right time to leave","ko":"떠날 적절한 시간이다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"right","role":"Adj"},{"t":"time","role":"N"},{"t":"to leave","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"a place to stay","ko":"머물 곳이다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"place","role":"N"},{"t":"to stay","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"a reason to celebrate","ko":"축하할 이유다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"reason","role":"N"},{"t":"to celebrate","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"something cold to drink","ko":"마실 차가운 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"something","role":"N"},{"t":"cold","role":"Adj"},{"t":"to drink","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"I need a book to read.","ko":"나는 읽을 책이 필요하다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"need","role":"V"},{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"book","role":"N"},{"t":"to read.","role":"Pm"}]}],"mistakes":[["something eat","something to eat (**to부정사**로 명사를 수식한다)"],["the way learning","the way to learn (**way 뒤에는 to부정사**를 쓴다)"],["a chance winning","a chance to win (**chance 뒤에는 to부정사**를 쓴다)"]]},{"key":"post-participle","title":"후치수식 ④ 분사구 (the report written yesterday)","points":["분사구는 명사를 뒤에서 꾸미며 ==현재분사(-ing)는 능동, 과거분사(p.p.)는 수동==으로 나뉜다.","**현재분사**는 명사가 **하는 중**인 동작을 뜻한다: \"the man **standing** there\".","**과거분사**는 명사가 **당한** 동작을 뜻한다: \"the report **written** yesterday\".","분사 뒤에 목적어·부사가 붙어 \"a letter written in French\"처럼 **덩어리 전체**가 명사를 꾸민다.","분사 하나만 쓸 때는 명사 앞에 오기도 한다 (a barking dog) — 하지만 ==말이 붙으면 반드시 뒤==로 간다."],"examples":[{"en":"the man standing there","ko":"저기 서 있는 남자다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"man","role":"N"},{"t":"standing there","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the report written yesterday","ko":"어제 작성된 보고서다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"report","role":"N"},{"t":"written yesterday","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the girl wearing glasses","ko":"안경을 쓴 소녀다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"girl","role":"N"},{"t":"wearing glasses","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"a letter written in French","ko":"프랑스어로 쓰인 편지다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"letter","role":"N"},{"t":"written in French","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the people waiting outside","ko":"밖에서 기다리는 사람들이다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"people","role":"N"},{"t":"waiting outside","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"a house built in 1990","ko":"1990년에 지어진 집이다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"house","role":"N"},{"t":"built in 1990","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the dog barking loudly","ko":"시끄럽게 짖는 개다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"dog","role":"N"},{"t":"barking loudly","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"The car parked outside is mine.","ko":"밖에 주차된 차는 내 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"The","role":"Det"},{"t":"car","role":"N"},{"t":"parked outside","role":"Pm"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"mine.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["the report writing yesterday","the report written yesterday (**당한 동작(수동)은 과거분사 written**으로 쓴다)"],["the man stood there","the man standing there (**하는 중(능동·진행)은 현재분사 standing**으로 쓴다)"],["the barking dog loudly","the dog barking loudly (**부사가 붙은 분사구는 명사 뒤**에 온다)"]]},{"key":"stacking","title":"후치수식 겹침과 어순 (the tall man in the corner who is waving)","points":["후치수식은 여러 개를 겹칠 수 있고 순서는 대체로 ==전치사구 → 관계절== 순으로 이어진다.","전체 어순은 **한정사 → 형용사 → 핵심명사 → 전치사구 → 분사구/관계절**로 자란다.","\"the **tall** man **in the corner** **who is waving**\"이 앞수식·뒤수식을 모두 담은 예다.","짧고 가까운 수식(전치사구)을 **명사에 가깝게**, 긴 수식(관계절)을 **뒤쪽**에 둔다.","수식이 길어질수록 **핵심명사가 무엇인지** 놓치지 않는 것이 답을 맞히는 열쇠다."],"examples":[{"en":"the tall man in the corner who is waving","ko":"구석에서 손을 흔드는 키 큰 남자다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"tall","role":"Adj"},{"t":"man","role":"N"},{"t":"in the corner","role":"Pm"},{"t":"who is waving","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"a small book on the shelf about birds","ko":"새에 관한 선반 위의 작은 책이다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"small","role":"Adj"},{"t":"book","role":"N"},{"t":"on the shelf","role":"Pm"},{"t":"about birds","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the woman standing at the door who called you","ko":"문 앞에 서서 너를 부른 여자다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"woman","role":"N"},{"t":"standing at the door","role":"Pm"},{"t":"who called you","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the new restaurant near the park that serves pizza","ko":"피자를 파는 공원 근처의 새 식당이다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"new","role":"Adj"},{"t":"restaurant","role":"N"},{"t":"near the park","role":"Pm"},{"t":"that serves pizza","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"a young student with glasses reading a book","ko":"안경을 쓰고 책을 읽는 젊은 학생이다.","parts":[{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"young","role":"Adj"},{"t":"student","role":"N"},{"t":"with glasses","role":"Pm"},{"t":"reading a book","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"the old house on the hill built by my grandfather","ko":"할아버지가 지은 언덕 위의 오래된 집이다.","parts":[{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"old","role":"Adj"},{"t":"house","role":"N"},{"t":"on the hill","role":"Pm"},{"t":"built by my grandfather","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"The girl in the red dress who is singing is my sister.","ko":"빨간 드레스를 입고 노래하는 소녀가 내 여동생이다.","parts":[{"t":"The","role":"Det"},{"t":"girl","role":"N"},{"t":"in the red dress","role":"Pm"},{"t":"who is singing","role":"Pm"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"my sister.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["the man who is waving in the corner tall","the tall man in the corner who is waving (**형용사→명사→전치사구→관계절 순서**를 지킨다)"],["the in the corner tall man","the tall man in the corner (**전치사구는 핵심명사 뒤**로 보낸다)"],["a reading a book student young","a young student reading a book (**형용사는 명사 앞, 분사구는 명사 뒤**에 둔다)"]]},{"key":"np-role","title":"명사구의 문장 역할 (주어·목적어·보어)","points":["완성된 명사구는 문장에서 ==주어·목적어·보어·전치사의 목적어== 자리에 그대로 들어간다.","**주어**: \"The old bridge collapsed.\" — 명사구가 동사 앞에서 주인 노릇을 한다.","**목적어**: \"She bought a new laptop.\" — 동사 뒤에서 동작의 대상이 된다.","**보어**: \"He is a good teacher.\" — be동사 뒤에서 주어를 설명하며 **관사 a도 필요**하다.","긴 후치수식이 붙은 명사구도 통째로 한 덩어리라 ==Build-a-Sentence의 답 단위==가 된다."],"examples":[{"en":"The old bridge collapsed.","ko":"그 오래된 다리가 무너졌다.","parts":[{"t":"The","role":"Det"},{"t":"old","role":"Adj"},{"t":"bridge","role":"N"},{"t":"collapsed.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"She bought a new laptop.","ko":"그녀는 새 노트북을 샀다.","parts":[{"t":"She","role":"S"},{"t":"bought","role":"V"},{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"new","role":"Adj"},{"t":"laptop.","role":"N"}]},{"en":"He is a good teacher.","ko":"그는 좋은 선생님이다.","parts":[{"t":"He","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"good","role":"Adj"},{"t":"teacher.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I sat on the wooden bench.","ko":"나는 나무 벤치에 앉았다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"sat","role":"V"},{"t":"on","role":"M"},{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"wooden","role":"Adj"},{"t":"bench.","role":"N"}]},{"en":"The book on the table is mine.","ko":"탁자 위의 책은 내 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"The","role":"Det"},{"t":"book","role":"N"},{"t":"on the table","role":"Pm"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"mine.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I know the man who fixed your car.","ko":"나는 네 차를 고친 남자를 안다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"know","role":"V"},{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"man","role":"N"},{"t":"who fixed your car.","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"This is the best coffee in town.","ko":"이건 이 동네 최고의 커피다.","parts":[{"t":"This","role":"S"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"the","role":"Det"},{"t":"best","role":"Adj"},{"t":"coffee","role":"N"},{"t":"in town.","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"A cup of hot tea sounds nice.","ko":"따뜻한 차 한 잔이 좋겠다.","parts":[{"t":"A","role":"Det"},{"t":"cup","role":"N"},{"t":"of hot tea","role":"Pm"},{"t":"sounds","role":"V"},{"t":"nice.","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["Bought a new laptop.","She bought a new laptop. (**목적어 명사구**만으로는 문장이 안 되고 주어가 필요하다)"],["He is good teacher.","He is a good teacher. (**보어 명사구에도 관사 a**가 필요하다)"],["I sat wooden bench.","I sat on the wooden bench. (**전치사 on**이 있어야 명사구가 동사에 붙는다)"]]}],"db":{"title":"한정사 & 후치수식 레퍼런스","intro":"명사구를 만드는 **한정사 다섯 종류**와, 일부 수량사·분배사의 **조합 규칙**을 정리했다.","groups":[{"label":"한정사 5종 · Determiner Types","note":"명사 앞에 오는 한정사는 크게 **다섯 종류**다. 한 명사 앞에는 ==중심 한정사 하나만== 온다(a my book ✗).","items":[{"w":"관사","ko":"a · an · the","ex":"a book(하나) / an apple(모음 앞) / the book(특정한 그 책)"},{"w":"지시사","ko":"this · that · these · those","ex":"this pen(가까운) / those cars(먼 복수)"},{"w":"소유격","ko":"my · your · his · her · its · our · their · 명사~s","ex":"my bag / Toms car / the boys room"},{"w":"수량사","ko":"some · any · no · many · much · (a) few · (a) little · several · all · enough","ex":"some water / many books / enough time"},{"w":"분배사","ko":"each · every · either · neither · both","ex":"each student(각각) / every day(모든) / either side(둘 중 하나)"}]},{"label":"한정사 조합 · Combinations","note":"일부 **수량사·분배사**는 뒤에 두 가지가 가능하다: ① ==of + 한정사구== ② 바로 ==다른 한정사 앞==.","items":[{"w":"of + 명사구","ko":"수량사·분배사 + of + 한정사구(the/my/these…)","ex":"all of the students / some of my friends / each of the boys / neither of them / both of us / none of the books"},{"w":"바로 한정사 앞","ko":"전치한정사(all·both·half·double) + 중심 한정사","ex":"all the students / all my friends / all these books / both the teams / half the class"},{"w":"뜻 차이","ko":"the 유무로 범위가 달라진다","ex":"all students(학생 일반) ↔ all the students(그 학생들 전부)"}]},{"label":"후치수식 4종 Post-modifiers","note":"명사를 **뒤에서** 꾸미는 네 가지 도구다. 짧은 것(전치사구)을 명사 가까이, 긴 것(관계절)을 뒤쪽에 둔다. ==능동은 -ing, 수동은 p.p.==만 헷갈리지 않으면 된다.","items":[{"w":"전치사구 (위치·관계)","ko":"on/in/under/with 등 — 위치·소속","ex":"the book on the table"},{"w":"전치사구 (of)","ko":"소속·부분·수량","ex":"a cup of coffee"},{"w":"관계절 (주격 who)","ko":"사람 명사가 하는 동작","ex":"the man who called"},{"w":"관계절 (주격 which/that)","ko":"사물 명사가 하는 동작","ex":"a bus that goes downtown"},{"w":"관계절 (목적격, 생략 가능)","ko":"명사가 받는 동작","ex":"the book (that) I read"},{"w":"관계절 (where/when)","ko":"장소·시간","ex":"the house where I live"},{"w":"to부정사","ko":"미래·목적·해야 할 일","ex":"the best way to learn"},{"w":"to부정사 (-thing류)","ko":"something/anything 뒤","ex":"something to eat"},{"w":"현재분사 (-ing, 능동)","ko":"명사가 하는 중인 동작","ex":"the man standing there"},{"w":"과거분사 (p.p., 수동)","ko":"명사가 당한 동작","ex":"the report written yesterday"},{"w":"분사구 + 목적어/부사","ko":"덩어리 전체가 명사 뒤 수식","ex":"a letter written in French"},{"w":"후치수식 겹침","ko":"전치사구 → 관계절 순으로 나열","ex":"the man in the corner who is waving"}]},{"label":"명사구 확장 예 Building Up","note":"핵심명사 하나에서 시작해 ==한정사 → 형용사 → 후치수식== 순으로 살을 붙여가는 과정이다. 아무리 길어져도 **핵심명사가 뼈대**라는 점을 놓치지 않는다.","items":[{"w":"book","ko":"핵심명사만","ex":"book"},{"w":"a book","ko":"+ 한정사","ex":"a book"},{"w":"a good book","ko":"+ 형용사","ex":"a good book"},{"w":"a good book on history","ko":"+ 전치사구","ex":"a good book on history"},{"w":"a good history book that I bought","ko":"+ 관계절","ex":"a good history book that I bought"},{"w":"man","ko":"핵심명사만","ex":"man"},{"w":"the man","ko":"+ 한정사","ex":"the man"},{"w":"the tall man","ko":"+ 형용사","ex":"the tall man"},{"w":"the tall man in the suit","ko":"+ 전치사구","ex":"the tall man in the suit"},{"w":"the tall man in the suit who is speaking","ko":"+ 관계절","ex":"the tall man in the suit who is speaking"},{"w":"way","ko":"핵심명사만","ex":"way"},{"w":"the best way","ko":"+ 한정사·형용사","ex":"the best way"},{"w":"the best way to study","ko":"+ to부정사","ex":"the best way to study"},{"w":"car","ko":"핵심명사만","ex":"car"},{"w":"the red car parked outside","ko":"+ 형용사·분사구","ex":"the red car parked outside"},{"w":"a cup of hot tea","ko":"of 전치사구로 확장","ex":"a cup of hot tea"}]}]}},{"n":11,"title":"특수형태 답변","status":"detailed","summary":"대화의 답변은 **꼭 완전한 문장일 필요가 없다**. 앞에서 이미 나온 정보는 통째로 생략하고 ==핵심만 남기는 것==이 오히려 더 자연스럽다. 다만 실제 대화에서는 **명사구만으로 답하는 경우를 빼면**, 짧은 특수 답변도 거기서 그대로 끝나지 않고 ==and·but·so·or 같은 등위접속사로 절을 하나 더 이어==붙이는 것이 보통이다(\"Yes, but I still need more time.\" / \"So do I, and we should study together.\"). 이 개념은 다섯 가지 짧은 답 형태를 익힌다. ① **명사구만으로 답하기**(Which model? → \"The one with the best battery.\"), ② **Yes/No + 단서**, ③ **동사구 생략**, ④ **대용형** so·not·one, ⑤ **되받아 질문**과 **감탄·동의 응답**. ==반복되는 동사구를 또 쓰거나, so 대신 it을 넣거나, of course 뒤에 yes를 또 붙이는== 실수는 피한다.","subtopics":[{"key":"np-only","title":"명사구만으로 답하기 (The one with the best battery.)","points":["질문의 동사·주어가 뻔할 때는 ==명사구(NP) 하나==만 던져도 완전한 답이 된다. 굳이 \"It is ~\", \"I want ~\"를 붙이지 않는다.","\"Which model?\" 같은 물음에는 **The one with ~**, **The + 형용사 + one** 형태로 콕 집어 답한다.","명사구 뒤에는 **전치사구·관계절**을 이어 자세히 꾸민다(with the best battery / in the blue jacket).","==명사구 답은 특수 답변 중 유일하게== 등위접속사로 절을 잇지 않고 명사구 하나로 깔끔하게 끝내는 형태다.","주문·선택 상황에서는 ==명사구 + please==만으로 정중한 요청이 완성된다.","짧게 답할 때 **불필요한 be동사**(Is the ~)를 앞에 붙이지 않도록 주의한다."],"examples":[{"en":"The one with the best battery.","ko":"배터리가 가장 좋은 것으로 하겠다.","parts":[{"t":"The","role":"Det"},{"t":"one","role":"N"},{"t":"with the best battery.","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"A large iced latte, please.","ko":"라지 아이스 라떼로 부탁한다.","parts":[{"t":"A","role":"Det"},{"t":"large","role":"Adj"},{"t":"iced latte,","role":"N"},{"t":"please.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"The tall guy in the blue jacket.","ko":"파란 재킷 입은 키 큰 남자다.","parts":[{"t":"The","role":"Det"},{"t":"tall","role":"Adj"},{"t":"guy","role":"N"},{"t":"in the blue jacket.","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"Just a glass of water.","ko":"그냥 물 한 잔이면 된다.","parts":[{"t":"Just","role":"M"},{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"glass","role":"N"},{"t":"of water.","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"The second option, I think.","ko":"두 번째 것으로 생각한다.","parts":[{"t":"The","role":"Det"},{"t":"second","role":"Adj"},{"t":"option,","role":"N"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"think.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Two tickets for the evening show.","ko":"저녁 공연 표 두 장이다.","parts":[{"t":"Two","role":"Det"},{"t":"tickets","role":"N"},{"t":"for the evening show.","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"The blue one on the left.","ko":"왼쪽에 있는 파란 것이다.","parts":[{"t":"The","role":"Det"},{"t":"blue","role":"Adj"},{"t":"one","role":"N"},{"t":"on the left.","role":"Pm"}]},{"en":"My sister, actually.","ko":"사실은 내 여동생이다.","parts":[{"t":"My","role":"Det"},{"t":"sister,","role":"N"},{"t":"actually.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["The one it has the best battery.","The one with the best battery. (명사구 뒤 수식은 **전치사구·관계절**로 잇고 완전한 절을 또 넣지 않는다)"],["Is the second option.","The second option. (짧은 답에서는 **불필요한 be동사**를 빼고 명사구만 남긴다)"],["Give me a large iced latte please.","A large iced latte, please. (원하는 **명사구 + please**만으로 충분히 정중하다)"]]},{"key":"yesno-cue","title":"Yes/No + 단서 (Yes, but I still need more time.)","points":["Yes/No 뒤에 **담화표지·짧은 절**을 이어 붙여 ==부드러운 뉘앙스==를 더한다(Yes, but ~ / No, not really).","명사구 답이 아닌 이상, 실제 대화에서는 Yes/No + 단서로 끝내기보다 ==and·but·so 같은 등위접속사로 절을 하나 더== 이어 붙이는 경우가 많다(Yes, but I still need more time).","but·so·and 같은 **등위접속사**로 조건·반전·이유를 살짝 덧붙인다.","of course·definitely·not really는 그 자체로 **강한 긍정·부정**이라 그냥 짧게 끝내도 된다.","==거절도 \"No, thanks.\"처럼 짧게==, 수락도 \"Yes, please.\"처럼 짧게 끝내는 것도 자연스럽다.","확신이 덜할 때는 **Well,** 로 뜸을 들인 뒤 not exactly·sort of로 잇는다."],"examples":[{"en":"Yes, but I still need a little more time to finish.","ko":"그렇다, 다만 끝내려면 시간이 조금 더 필요하다.","parts":[{"t":"Yes,","role":"M"},{"t":"but","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"still","role":"M"},{"t":"need","role":"V"},{"t":"a little more time","role":"O"},{"t":"to finish.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"No, not really, but I might change my mind later.","ko":"아니, 딱히 그렇지 않다, 다만 나중에 생각이 바뀔 수도 있다.","parts":[{"t":"No,","role":"M"},{"t":"not really,","role":"M"},{"t":"but","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"might","role":"Aux"},{"t":"change","role":"V"},{"t":"my mind","role":"O"},{"t":"later.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Yes, of course, and I'll bring the drinks.","ko":"그렇다, 물론이다, 그리고 마실 것은 내가 가져오겠다.","parts":[{"t":"Yes,","role":"M"},{"t":"of course,","role":"M"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I'll","role":"S"},{"t":"bring","role":"V"},{"t":"the drinks.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"No, thanks.","ko":"아니, 괜찮다.","parts":[{"t":"No,","role":"M"},{"t":"thanks.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Yes, and that would really help me out.","ko":"그렇다, 그리고 그러면 정말 큰 도움이 되겠다.","parts":[{"t":"Yes,","role":"M"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"that","role":"S"},{"t":"would","role":"Aux"},{"t":"really","role":"M"},{"t":"help","role":"V"},{"t":"me out.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Well, not exactly.","ko":"음, 정확히는 아니다.","parts":[{"t":"Well,","role":"M"},{"t":"not exactly.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Yes, actually, and I've already started.","ko":"그렇다, 사실 이미 시작했다.","parts":[{"t":"Yes,","role":"M"},{"t":"actually,","role":"M"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I've","role":"S"},{"t":"already","role":"M"},{"t":"started.","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Yes, especially the second one, and it's cheaper too.","ko":"그렇다, 특히 두 번째 것인데 그게 더 싸기도 하다.","parts":[{"t":"Yes,","role":"M"},{"t":"especially","role":"M"},{"t":"the second one,","role":"O"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"it's","role":"S"},{"t":"cheaper","role":"SC"},{"t":"too.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["Yes, but I need more time please give me.","Yes, but I still need more time. (**Yes 뒤 단서**는 등위접속사 but으로 자연스럽게 잇고 명령절을 덧대지 않는다)"],["No, not really it.","No, not really. (**No + not really**는 그 자체로 완결된 답이다)"],["Yes, of course yes, and I'll bring the drinks.","Yes, of course, and I'll bring the drinks. (**of course**가 이미 강한 긍정이라 yes를 또 붙이지 않고, 이어지는 절만 and로 잇는다)"]]},{"key":"elided-vp","title":"동사구 생략·짧은 응답 (I'd love to, but I have a class then.)","points":["앞에서 나온 **동사구**는 통째로 생략하고 ==조동사(will·can·might)까지만== 남긴다(I will / I might).","to부정사 뒤 동사구도 생략해 **I'd love to.** / **I'd rather not.** 처럼 to에서 끊는다.","명사구 답이 아닌 이상, 짧게 끊고 나서 ==but·and·so로 이어지는 절==을 덧붙이는 것이 자연스럽다(I'd love to, but I have a class then).","==Not yet. / Of course not. / Maybe later.== 처럼 짧게만 끝낼 수도 있다. 그 자체로 완결된 답이다.","완료·조동사 답은 **주어 + (부정)조동사**로 짧게 맺고 필요하면 and로 절을 잇는다(No, I haven't, and I can't join).","핵심은 \"다시 말하지 않아도 아는 부분은 **말하지 않는다**\"는 경제성이다."],"examples":[{"en":"I will, and I'll text you afterward.","ko":"그렇게 하겠다, 그리고 끝나면 문자하겠다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"will,","role":"Aux"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I'll","role":"S"},{"t":"text","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"O"},{"t":"afterward.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I'd love to, but I have a class at that time.","ko":"정말 그러고 싶다, 다만 그 시간에 수업이 있다.","parts":[{"t":"I'd","role":"S"},{"t":"love","role":"V"},{"t":"to,","role":"M"},{"t":"but","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"V"},{"t":"a class","role":"O"},{"t":"at that time.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Not yet, but I'm planning to sign up soon.","ko":"아직 아니다, 다만 곧 신청할 계획이다.","parts":[{"t":"Not","role":"M"},{"t":"yet,","role":"M"},{"t":"but","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I'm","role":"S"},{"t":"planning","role":"V"},{"t":"to sign up","role":"O"},{"t":"soon.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Of course not.","ko":"당연히 아니다.","parts":[{"t":"Of course","role":"M"},{"t":"not.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I'd rather not, but thanks for asking.","ko":"안 하는 편이 낫겠다, 그래도 물어봐 줘서 고맙다.","parts":[{"t":"I'd","role":"S"},{"t":"rather","role":"M"},{"t":"not,","role":"M"},{"t":"but","role":"Conj"},{"t":"thanks","role":"M"},{"t":"for asking.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Sure, I can, so just let me know when.","ko":"그럼, 할 수 있다, 그러니 언제인지 알려만 달라.","parts":[{"t":"Sure,","role":"M"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"can,","role":"Aux"},{"t":"so","role":"Conj"},{"t":"just","role":"M"},{"t":"let","role":"V"},{"t":"me","role":"O"},{"t":"know when.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"No, I haven't, and I don't think I'll be able to join.","ko":"아니, 아직 안 했다, 그리고 참석하지 못할 것 같다.","parts":[{"t":"No,","role":"M"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"haven't,","role":"Aux"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"think","role":"V"},{"t":"I'll be able to join.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Maybe later.","ko":"아마 나중에.","parts":[{"t":"Maybe","role":"M"},{"t":"later.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I will finish it, and I'll text you afterward.","I will, and I'll text you afterward. (앞에서 나온 **동사구는 생략**하고 will만 남긴 뒤 절을 and로 잇는다)"],["I'd love to do it to, but I have a class.","I'd love to, but I have a class at that time. (**to 뒤 반복 동사구**는 생략하고 이어지는 절만 but으로 붙인다)"],["Not yet done, but I'm planning to sign up.","Not yet, but I'm planning to sign up soon. (**Not yet**만으로 '아직 안 했다'는 뜻이 완성된다)"]]},{"key":"pro-forms","title":"대용형 so·not·one (I think so, but I'm not sure.)","points":["think·hope·guess·believe 뒤에서 앞 내용 전체를 ==대용형 so==로 받는다(I think so). **it을 쓰지 않는다**.","부정으로 받을 때는 **동사 + not**(I hope not / I'm afraid not)으로 만든다.","명사구 답이 아닌 이상, so·not으로 받은 뒤에도 ==but·and로 절을 이어== 덧붙이는 경우가 많다(I think so, but I'm not completely sure).","반복되는 **가산명사**는 one(단수)·ones(복수)로 받는다(the red one / the blue ones).","one 앞에는 **관사·형용사**를 자유롭게 붙여 a bigger one, the small ones처럼 쓴다.","조건절에서도 **if so / if not**으로 앞 내용을 짧게 대신한다."],"examples":[{"en":"I think so, but I'm not completely sure.","ko":"그런 것 같다, 다만 완전히 확신하지는 못한다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"think","role":"V"},{"t":"so,","role":"O"},{"t":"but","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I'm","role":"S"},{"t":"not","role":"M"},{"t":"completely","role":"M"},{"t":"sure.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I hope not, but it's looking pretty likely.","ko":"아니길 바란다, 다만 꽤 그럴 것 같아 보인다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"hope","role":"V"},{"t":"not,","role":"O"},{"t":"but","role":"Conj"},{"t":"it's","role":"S"},{"t":"looking","role":"V"},{"t":"pretty likely.","role":"SC"}]},{"en":"I guess so, but I'd double-check first.","ko":"그런 것 같다, 다만 먼저 다시 확인해 보겠다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"guess","role":"V"},{"t":"so,","role":"O"},{"t":"but","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I'd","role":"S"},{"t":"double-check","role":"V"},{"t":"first.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I don't think so.","ko":"그렇지 않은 것 같다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"don't","role":"Aux"},{"t":"think","role":"V"},{"t":"so.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"I'd like a bigger one, so could you check the back?","ko":"더 큰 것으로 하고 싶다, 그러니 뒤쪽을 확인해 줄 수 있는가?","parts":[{"t":"I'd","role":"S"},{"t":"like","role":"V"},{"t":"a bigger one,","role":"O"},{"t":"so","role":"Conj"},{"t":"could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"check","role":"V"},{"t":"the back?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The blue ones are nicer, but they cost a bit more.","ko":"파란 것들이 더 낫다, 다만 값이 조금 더 나간다.","parts":[{"t":"The","role":"Det"},{"t":"blue","role":"Adj"},{"t":"ones","role":"S"},{"t":"are","role":"V"},{"t":"nicer,","role":"SC"},{"t":"but","role":"Conj"},{"t":"they","role":"S"},{"t":"cost","role":"V"},{"t":"a bit more.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"The red one, please.","ko":"빨간 것으로 부탁한다.","parts":[{"t":"The","role":"Det"},{"t":"red","role":"Adj"},{"t":"one,","role":"N"},{"t":"please.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"I believe so, and I'll confirm it later.","ko":"그런 것 같다, 그리고 나중에 확인해 주겠다.","parts":[{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"believe","role":"V"},{"t":"so,","role":"O"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I'll","role":"S"},{"t":"confirm","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"later.","role":"M"}]}],"mistakes":[["I think it, but I'm not sure.","I think so, but I'm not completely sure. (앞 내용을 받을 때는 it이 아니라 **대용형 so**를 쓴다)"],["I don't hope so, but it's likely.","I hope not, but it's looking pretty likely. (hope의 부정 응답은 don't가 아니라 **hope not**으로 만든다)"],["I want the red it.","The red one, please. (반복되는 가산명사 대신 **대명사 one**을 쓴다)"]]},{"key":"follow-up","title":"되받아 질문 (Have you tried it yet?)","points":["답 대신 **되묻는 질문**으로 대화를 이어갈 수 있다. 이때도 ==직접의문문의 도치 규칙==을 그대로 지킨다.","be동사·조동사·완료 have는 **주어 앞으로 도치**한다(Have you ~? / Are you ~?).","일반동사 되묻기에는 **do/does/did 도치**가 반드시 필요하다(Why do you ask?).","두 선택지를 함께 되물을 때는 ==\"…, or …?\"== 형태로 **or**를 넣어 던진다(Should we meet today, or is tomorrow better?).","Wh- 로 시작하는 되물음도 ==의문사 + 도치== 순서를 따른다(What did you have in mind?)."],"examples":[{"en":"Have you tried it yet?","ko":"벌써 그것을 해봤는가?","parts":[{"t":"Have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"tried","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"yet?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Why do you ask?","ko":"왜 물어보는가?","parts":[{"t":"Why","role":"Wh"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"ask?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Are you sure about that?","ko":"그것에 대해 확신하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Are","role":"V"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"sure","role":"SC"},{"t":"about that?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Do you really think so?","ko":"정말 그렇게 생각하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"really","role":"M"},{"t":"think","role":"V"},{"t":"so?","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Can I get back to you?","ko":"나중에 다시 연락해도 되는가?","parts":[{"t":"Can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"get back","role":"V"},{"t":"to you?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"What did you have in mind?","ko":"무엇을 염두에 두었는가?","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"O"},{"t":"did","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"have","role":"V"},{"t":"in mind?","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Which one do you mean?","ko":"어느 것을 말하는가?","parts":[{"t":"Which","role":"Det"},{"t":"one","role":"N"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"you","role":"S"},{"t":"mean?","role":"V"}]},{"en":"Should we meet today, or is tomorrow better?","ko":"오늘 만날까, 아니면 내일이 더 나은가?","parts":[{"t":"Should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"meet","role":"V"},{"t":"today,","role":"M"},{"t":"or","role":"Conj"},{"t":"is","role":"V"},{"t":"tomorrow","role":"S"},{"t":"better?","role":"SC"}]}],"mistakes":[["You tried it yet?","Have you tried it yet? (되묻는 질문도 **완료 have 도치**를 지킨다)"],["Why you ask?","Why do you ask? (일반동사 의문문은 **do 도치**가 필요하다)"],["What you had in mind?","What did you have in mind? (**did 도치**와 원형 동사 have를 지킨다)"]]},{"key":"exclaim-agree","title":"감탄·동의 응답 (So do I, and we should study together.)","points":["긍정 동의는 **So + 조동사 + 주어**(So do I / So am I) 어순을 지킨다. ==주어와 조동사 위치를 바꾸지 않는다==.","부정 동의는 **Neither + 조동사 + 주어**(Neither do I / Neither am I)로 만든다.","명사구 답이 아닌 이상, So/Neither 동의 뒤에는 ==and·so·but으로 이어지는 절==을 붙여 대화를 이어가는 것이 자연스럽다(So do I, and we should study together).","구어에서는 **Me too. / Me neither. / Same here.** 처럼 더 짧은 동의 표현을 자주 쓴다.","감탄은 ==What a + 명사구!== 또는 ==How + 형용사!== 로 짧게 끝낸다. 여기엔 절을 더 잇지 않는다.","앞 문장의 **동사 종류에 맞춰 조동사**를 고른다(be → am/is, 일반동사 → do, 완료 → have)."],"examples":[{"en":"So do I, and we should study together sometime.","ko":"나도 그렇다, 그리고 언제 같이 공부하면 좋겠다.","parts":[{"t":"So","role":"M"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I,","role":"S"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"we","role":"S"},{"t":"should","role":"Aux"},{"t":"study","role":"V"},{"t":"together","role":"M"},{"t":"sometime.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Neither do I, so let's just skip it this time.","ko":"나도 그렇지 않다, 그러니 이번엔 그냥 넘어가면 되겠다.","parts":[{"t":"Neither","role":"M"},{"t":"do","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I,","role":"S"},{"t":"so","role":"Conj"},{"t":"let's","role":"S"},{"t":"just","role":"M"},{"t":"skip","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"this time.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"So am I, but I can still make it work.","ko":"나도 그렇다, 다만 그래도 어떻게든 해낼 수 있다.","parts":[{"t":"So","role":"M"},{"t":"am","role":"V"},{"t":"I,","role":"S"},{"t":"but","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"can","role":"Aux"},{"t":"still","role":"M"},{"t":"make","role":"V"},{"t":"it","role":"O"},{"t":"work.","role":"OC"}]},{"en":"Me too, so let's grab lunch together.","ko":"나도 그렇다, 그러니 같이 점심 먹으면 좋겠다.","parts":[{"t":"Me","role":"S"},{"t":"too,","role":"M"},{"t":"so","role":"Conj"},{"t":"let's","role":"S"},{"t":"grab","role":"V"},{"t":"lunch","role":"O"},{"t":"together.","role":"M"}]},{"en":"Neither have I, but I've heard it's great.","ko":"나도 안 해봤다, 다만 좋다고 들었다.","parts":[{"t":"Neither","role":"M"},{"t":"have","role":"Aux"},{"t":"I,","role":"S"},{"t":"but","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I've","role":"S"},{"t":"heard","role":"V"},{"t":"it's great.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"Same here, and I could really use a break.","ko":"나도 마찬가지다, 그리고 정말 좀 쉬어야겠다.","parts":[{"t":"Same","role":"M"},{"t":"here,","role":"M"},{"t":"and","role":"Conj"},{"t":"I","role":"S"},{"t":"could","role":"Aux"},{"t":"really","role":"M"},{"t":"use","role":"V"},{"t":"a break.","role":"O"}]},{"en":"What a great idea!","ko":"정말 좋은 생각이다!","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"M"},{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"great","role":"Adj"},{"t":"idea!","role":"N"}]},{"en":"What a relief!","ko":"정말 다행이다!","parts":[{"t":"What","role":"M"},{"t":"a","role":"Det"},{"t":"relief!","role":"N"}]},{"en":"How exciting!","ko":"정말 신난다!","parts":[{"t":"How","role":"M"},{"t":"exciting!","role":"Adj"}]}],"mistakes":[["So I do, and we should study together.","So do I, and we should study together sometime. (동의의 So 응답은 **So + 조동사 + 주어** 어순이다)"],["What a great idea it is, and I love it!","What a great idea! (감탄문은 **명사구까지만** 말하고 뒤에 절을 잇지 않는 게 자연스럽다)"],["Me also, so let's grab lunch.","Me too, so let's grab lunch together. (구어 동의는 also가 아니라 **Me too**를 쓴다)"]]}],"db":{"title":"짧은 답변 DB · 관용구 & 대용형","intro":"짧은 답변의 핵심은 <b>아는 부분은 다시 말하지 않는다</b>는 경제성이다. ==앞에 나온 동사구는 생략하고, 반복되는 내용은 so·not·one 같은 대용형으로 받는다==. 다만 명사구 답을 빼면, 실제 대화에서는 이 짧은 조각 뒤에 <b>and·but·so·or 같은 등위접속사로 절을 하나 더 이어</b>붙이는 것이 보통이다. 아래 4개 그룹으로 축약 관용구, 대용형, Yes/No 뒤 담화표지, 동의·감탄 응답을 한눈에 정리했다.","groups":[{"label":"① 축약 · 짧은 응답 관용구","note":"앞 동사구를 생략하고 **정형화된 조각**만 남긴 표현이다. ==통째로 외워두면== 대화에서 바로 튀어나온다. 실제로는 뒤에 but·so로 절을 잇는 경우가 많다.","items":[{"w":"I'd love to.","ko":"정말 그러고 싶어요 (수락)","ex":"\"Want to join us?\" \"I'd love to, but I have a class then.\""},{"w":"I'd rather not.","ko":"안 하는 게 낫겠어요 (완곡한 거절)","ex":"\"Want to talk about it?\" \"I'd rather not.\""},{"w":"Not yet.","ko":"아직요","ex":"\"Have you finished?\" \"Not yet, but I'm almost done.\""},{"w":"Of course.","ko":"물론이죠","ex":"\"Can you help me?\" \"Of course.\""},{"w":"Of course not.","ko":"당연히 아니죠","ex":"\"Do you mind?\" \"Of course not.\""},{"w":"Sure.","ko":"그럼요","ex":"\"Could you wait a second?\" \"Sure.\""},{"w":"No problem.","ko":"문제없어요","ex":"\"Thanks for the ride.\" \"No problem.\""},{"w":"Not really.","ko":"딱히요","ex":"\"Are you busy right now?\" \"Not really.\""},{"w":"Maybe later.","ko":"나중에요","ex":"\"Coffee now?\" \"Maybe later.\""},{"w":"Not at all.","ko":"전혀요","ex":"\"Do you mind if I sit here?\" \"Not at all.\""},{"w":"If you like.","ko":"원한다면요","ex":"\"Should I call you?\" \"If you like.\""},{"w":"Why not?","ko":"안 될 거 없죠","ex":"\"Shall we try it?\" \"Why not?\""},{"w":"I think I will.","ko":"그럴 것 같아요","ex":"\"Are you coming tonight?\" \"I think I will.\""},{"w":"I hope so.","ko":"그러길 바라요","ex":"\"Will it be sunny?\" \"I hope so.\""}]},{"label":"② 대용형 so · not · one · do","note":"앞에 나온 **절이나 명사**를 짧은 형태로 되받는 장치다. ==so/not은 절을, one/ones는 가산명사를 대신==한다.","items":[{"w":"think so","ko":"(앞 내용 대신) 그렇다고 생각하다","ex":"\"Is it open?\" \"I think so, but call first.\""},{"w":"hope not","ko":"(앞 내용 대신) 아니길 바라다","ex":"\"Is it going to rain?\" \"I hope not.\""},{"w":"I'm afraid so.","ko":"유감이지만 그래요","ex":"\"Is the shop closed?\" \"I'm afraid so.\""},{"w":"I'm afraid not.","ko":"유감이지만 아니에요","ex":"\"Any tickets left?\" \"I'm afraid not.\""},{"w":"I don't think so.","ko":"그렇지 않은 것 같아요","ex":"\"Is he coming?\" \"I don't think so.\""},{"w":"one","ko":"(앞 가산명사 대신) 하나","ex":"\"Which shirt?\" \"The red one.\""},{"w":"a bigger one","ko":"더 큰 걸로","ex":"\"This size?\" \"I'd like a bigger one.\""},{"w":"ones","ko":"(앞 명사 복수 대신) 것들","ex":"\"Which shoes?\" \"The blue ones.\""},{"w":"do so","ko":"(동사구 대신) 그렇게 하다","ex":"\"Sign here.\" \"I'll do so.\""},{"w":"if so","ko":"그렇다면","ex":"\"If so, let me know.\""},{"w":"if not","ko":"아니라면","ex":"\"If not, we'll just wait.\""},{"w":"I believe so.","ko":"그런 것 같아요","ex":"\"Is she the manager?\" \"I believe so.\""},{"w":"I guess so.","ko":"뭐 그런 것 같아요","ex":"\"Are we done?\" \"I guess so.\""}]},{"label":"③ Yes/No + 담화표지 · 연결","note":"Yes/No 뒤에 **but·so·and** 같은 등위접속사를 붙여 절을 이어가며 뉘앙스를 조절한다. ==짧아도 태도가 분명하게== 전달된다.","items":[{"w":"Yes, but…","ko":"네, 그런데요","ex":"\"Yes, but I still need more time.\""},{"w":"No, but…","ko":"아니요, 그래도요","ex":"\"No, but I might change my mind.\""},{"w":"Yes, and…","ko":"네, 그리고요","ex":"\"Yes, and I'll bring the drinks.\""},{"w":"No, not really.","ko":"아니요, 딱히요","ex":"\"No, not really.\""},{"w":"Yes, of course.","ko":"네, 물론이죠","ex":"\"Yes, of course, and I'll help.\""},{"w":"Well, sort of.","ko":"음, 어느 정도는요","ex":"\"Did it work?\" \"Well, sort of.\""},{"w":"Yes, definitely.","ko":"네, 확실히요","ex":"\"Yes, definitely.\""},{"w":"No, thanks.","ko":"아니요, 괜찮아요","ex":"\"More coffee?\" \"No, thanks.\""},{"w":"Yes, please.","ko":"네, 부탁해요","ex":"\"Sugar?\" \"Yes, please.\""},{"w":"No, not yet.","ko":"아니요, 아직요","ex":"\"No, not yet, but soon.\""},{"w":"Yes, I think so.","ko":"네, 그런 것 같아요","ex":"\"Yes, I think so.\""},{"w":"Kind of.","ko":"뭐 그런 셈이죠","ex":"\"Do you like it?\" \"Kind of.\""},{"w":"Yes, especially…","ko":"네, 특히요","ex":"\"Yes, especially the second one, and it's cheaper.\""}]},{"label":"④ 동의 · 감탄 응답","note":"상대 말에 **맞장구**를 치거나 감정을 드러내는 조각이다. ==So/Neither 뒤에는 조동사+주어 도치==, 동의 뒤엔 and·so로 절을 잇고, 감탄은 What a…! / How…! 로 짧게 끝낸다.","items":[{"w":"So do I.","ko":"나도 그래요 (일반동사)","ex":"\"I love this song.\" \"So do I, and we should study together.\""},{"w":"So am I.","ko":"나도요 (be동사)","ex":"\"I'm so tired.\" \"So am I.\""},{"w":"So have I.","ko":"나도 그랬어요 (완료)","ex":"\"I've been there.\" \"So have I.\""},{"w":"Neither do I.","ko":"나도 안 그래요 (일반동사)","ex":"\"I don't smoke.\" \"Neither do I, so let's skip it.\""},{"w":"Neither am I.","ko":"나도 아니에요 (be동사)","ex":"\"I'm not ready.\" \"Neither am I.\""},{"w":"Me too.","ko":"나도요 (긍정)","ex":"\"I'm hungry.\" \"Me too, so let's grab lunch.\""},{"w":"Me neither.","ko":"나도 안 그래요 (부정)","ex":"\"I don't get it.\" \"Me neither.\""},{"w":"Same here.","ko":"나도 마찬가지예요","ex":"\"I'm exhausted.\" \"Same here.\""},{"w":"What a…!","ko":"정말 대단한 …! (감탄)","ex":"\"What a great idea!\""},{"w":"How …!","ko":"정말 …하네요! (감탄)","ex":"\"How exciting!\""},{"w":"Good point.","ko":"좋은 지적이에요","ex":"\"That's a fair concern.\" \"Good point.\""},{"w":"Absolutely.","ko":"전적으로요","ex":"\"Is it worth it?\" \"Absolutely.\""},{"w":"I agree.","ko":"동의해요","ex":"\"It needs work.\" \"I agree.\""},{"w":"Fair enough.","ko":"그럴 만하네요","ex":"\"I'd rather not.\" \"Fair enough.\""}]}]}}]};
